(3, '<p style="text-align:justify;">Information about our home<img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/MarkLetty/matthew_with_hat2.jpg" alt="" width="287" height="215" /></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 59, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1295642387, 0),
(4, 'DO you wish you could put your journal entries in your profile to create one place to see all the public information about you...\n\nI do so we am working to see if we can add that feature. if you want that feature then friend me so you can send me a message and let me know what else you want to see in parentfinder profiles.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'My Journal', 62, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1302803484, 0),
(6, 'Dear expecting parent(s),\n\nEven though we haven''t met, we have a special place in our heart for you and your baby.  We can''t even imagine the emotions that you are feeling right now but we want to thank you for taking the time to look over our profile.  We want you to know that even considering adoption for your baby is a loving, courageous, and selfless act.  We feel very blessed that you have decided to get to know us.  We want you to know that we will show unconditional love to our child if you choose us to be parents!  We will instill into our child morals and the importance of love, compassion, and forgiveness.  We will teach our child to treat others how they would want to be treated.  We promise to always be there for our child and to answer any questions that he or she has.  We promise to always be honest with our child that he or she is adopted and that adoption was a plan that their biological parent(s) made out of love.  Thank you again for taking the time to get to know us.  May God give you peace and comfort in whatever decision you make regarding your precious little baby.  \n\n\n\nSincerely,\nMark and Melissa\n\n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth parent(s) Letter', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296612629, 0),
(8, 'Several of my hobbies include: singing, cooking, writing, movie watching, spending time with our pets, and most importantly spending time with my husband and our family and friends!!! ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Melissa&#039;s Hobbies', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296016229, 0),
(30, 'Melissa has a genuine heart and a strong faith in God. She is a very nurturing, patient, and caring person and strives to put the needs of others before her own. Melissa loves to laugh and enjoys life to its fullest! Melissa is very responsible and can have a serious side when the time is appropriate. She is great with kids and they adore being around her! Melissa is an awesome wife and will be an excellent and loving mother!!!! We look forward to fulfilling our dreams of having a family!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Melissa from Mark', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296580733, 0),
(10, 'Mark is a kind, patient man with a loving heart.  He is a caring and nurturing gentleman.  Mark has a carefree spirit and enjoys every moment of life!  He loves to laugh and entertain others.  Mark adores children and they absolutely love being around him!!! Mark is also very responsible and has a serious side when the time is necessary.  Mark is hardworking and gives 100% in everything that he does.  Mark is a wonderful husband and will be a fantastic daddy!!!\nWe are so excited to take this journey together and make our dreams of having a family come true!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Mark from Melissa', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296185940, 0),
(11, 'Several hobbies of mine include:  spending time with my wife and our dog, and three birds,watching sports (mostly baseball and football), playing video games, watching movies,  hanging out with our family and friends, and singing!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Mark&#039;s Hobbies', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296010837, 0),
(12, 'Some of my interests include: God, my wife, growing our family, our dog and three birds, playing sports, taking day trips, family gatherings and vacations, laughing, going to Disney and water parks, and enjoying life!!!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Mark&#039;s Interests', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296010821, 0),
(13, 'We have a beautiful 3 bedroom, 2 1/2 bathroom town house in a gated community.  We have large kitchen ,cozy living room, front and back porch, one car garage, and a driveway. One of our three bedrooms is a future nursery! We already thought of cute themes for either gender baby!  We also decorated our upstairs bathroom in a rubber duck theme (for our future child)!!! Our neighborhood has a gated pool and cabana, as well as a playground. We have a lot of children in our community of all ages (from infant to teenager)!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our home!', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296010960, 0),
(14, 'We met on a blind date in October 2003.  We fell in love shortly thereafter and got married February 11, 2006.  Immediately after we were married we knew we wanted to start a family.  We had always talked about wanting to adopt even if we had biological children!!! Well God must have known our intent to adopt because we were unsuccessful in conceiving a child even after fertility treatments and a diagnosis of "unexplained infertility".  We knew that adoption was the right choice for us!!  We are so excited to grow our family through adoption!  We long to hear the pitter patter of little feet!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us!', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296011351, 0),
(15, 'Since this will be our first child, we are hoping to adopt a Caucasian, Caucasian/Asian, or Caucasian/Hispanic baby; age infant to one year.  We are open to a baby with mild alcohol exposure in the first trimester of pregnancy.  We are also open to a baby exposed to mild cigarette use during pregnancy.  For more information on other familial health risks that we are open to, please contact Heart of Adoptions. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Child Preferences', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296082519, 0),
(16, 'Melissa graduated from college/nursing school in 2003. She is a critical care Registered Nurse at a local hospital.  Mark graduated high school in 1996 and several years later attended a criminal justice academy.  He successfully graduated and obtained his certification in law enforcement.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our educational background and occupation', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296012173, 0),
(17, 'We are both of Christian faith and were baptized Catholic although we attend a non-denomination church at times.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Religion', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296012280, 0),
(18, 'We have a little dog named Spike (He acquired the name because of the spiked hair he had as a puppy)!  He is a Silky/Yorkshire Terrier.  Spike is 2 1/2 years old and loves children!  We also have 3 cockatiels Buddy, Brady, and David.  Buddy was our first pet and we added him to our little family a few months after we were married.  One year later we added Brady to our family. Last year we rescued David from the Humane Society and he has become a great addition to our family!!!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our pets', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296186385, 0),
(20, 'Mark is the youngest of 4 children.  He has very loving parents and a loving extended family. His family is excited and supportive of the couples decision to adopt! Mark grew up in a home full of love, acceptance, and laughter!  As a child, Mark''s parents raised foster kids for many years.  This was a memorable experience for the entire family! His parents look forward to gaining a new grandchild to love!  His sisters and brother look forward to a new niece or nephew!\n\nMelissa is the oldest of two children.  Her parents and extended family are very loving and supportive of their decision to adopt!  Melissa grew up in a loving home full of acceptance, and laughter.  Although her parents are divorced, the family still remains close and reunites for holidays and special occasions.  Her parents are excited to have their first grandchild.  Her brother is also thrilled to have his first niece or nephew.  Melissa also has two cousins who were adopted from Korea.  \n\nAdoption and foster care have been a positive experience for both families! ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our family', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296018570, 0),
(82, '1.  Left-Handed - Doug says she is almost always right\n2.  Olympics - enjoys the summer and winter games\n3.  Coke - favorite drink \n4.  Dancing - voted most likely to be on "Dancing with the Stars"  by her co-workers\n5.  Broken-nose - playing intramural football in college\n6.  Soccer, Track, and Cheerleading - in high school\n7.  Spain - country she wants to visit one day\n8.  Chips & Salsa - favorite snack\n9.  Warm Weather - anything below 80 degrees is chilly\n10. Cockroaches - hates them, but spiders and snakes okay \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Ten Things About Tricia', 127, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1307202759, 0),
(22, 'Hey parents want to add custom blocks to your profiles??? I am an administrator of PArentfinder and want to help you do more with this tools. email with any questions or suggestions you may have.\nLogin\ngo to your profile\nlook for the add my blocks near top left hand under Actions.\nClick Add my block.\nselect text block ( unless you know how to write HTML then you can select that)\nPut in a title, Like "Our church" Or I put in Look at this new feature\nThen hit save..\nRight now all you can do is add the block but soon you will be able to put more information in that block.\nGO try it!!! Now. Go ahead...you will not hurt anything.\n\nAlso check out that you can drag and drop these blocks around your profile. Try to move one of your blocks. Then let me know how it works.\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Look at this new feature', 62, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1302803197, 0),
