(25, 'Just in case you are curious....we decided to share some fun facts about ourselves (besides hobbies and interests)!\n\nFAVORITE FOOD:  hot buffalo wings\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE DESSERT:  anything chocolate!\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE COLOR:  baby blue\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE SEASON:  Fall  ( I love to bake homemade apple pie)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE THEME PARK:  Walt Disney World - Magic Kingdom\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE ROLLER COASTER: rockin'' roller coaster\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE TV SHOW:  Adoption Stories\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE MOVIE(S):  Meet the Parents, Meet the Fockers, and Little Fockers!\n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Fun Facts About Melissa', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296187937, 0),
(26, 'Just in case you are curious......we have decided to add some fun facts about ourselves!\n\n\n\nFAVORITE FOOD:  escargot\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE COLOR: blue\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE SEASON: winter\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE THEME PARK:  universal studios\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE ROLLER COASTER: the hulk\n \n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE DESSERT:  devils food cake\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE TV SHOW:  American Pickers\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFAVORITE MOVIE(S):  Harry Potter\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Fun Facts About Mark', 129, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296188476, 0),
(27, 'We live in a single family rancher with 4 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms. The kitchen is a cook''s dream and it is large enough to eat in. We have a half an acre of property that is fenced in. There is a basketball court in our backyard that has lights for night time play. We have a playroom in the basement that is full of toys, instruments and art equipment. It is a great place to play and learn at the same time.\n\nOur neighborhood is a family''s dream! There are lots of children on our street and everyone is friendly. When it snowed last year, the entire neighboorhood was outside helping each other shovel out their cars. For the neighbors that could not dig themselves out, they didn''t have to worry. Everyone else took care of that.\n\nOur street is a double wide street, perfect for biking. As well, it can only be entered from one side, which cuts down on traffic.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 444, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296228417, 0),
(29, 'Caucasian, Caucasian/Hispanic, Caucasian/Native American, Hispanic or South/Central American, Mediterranean, Muti-Racial', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Child Preferences', 444, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296353054, 0),
(35, 'Patrick and I met in 1999. At the time, I worked for a department store and the store hires police officers for security. On Patrick’s first day, while he was being introduced to all the store associates, I was immediately enamored. One day, I gathered enough courage to ask him out. Needless to say, we’ve been together ever since. \n\n\nAfter 11 years of being together, married for 9 of those years, I am now a Payroll Analyst and Patrick’s a Police Sergeant. We both have our college degrees and own a great and spacious home together. We have two pets, a golden retriever named Lady and a cat named Snickers. \n\n\nWe love to travel; whether it’d be going on a cruise (our favorite form of vacationing) or going on road trips to nearby vacation destinations. \n\n\nPatrick and I have always wanted to have a family. We have tried numerous attempts of fertility treatments but all were unsuccessful. We were devastated each time. After much thought and consideration about adoption, we realized that though we are unable to conceive, what matters the most is that we can create a happy and loving home for a child. \n\n\nYou must still have more questions about us, but the one question we can definitely answer is, yes. Yes, we will love him or her with every fiber of our being. We promise that we will take care, protect, and give him or her a loving and supportive home. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 133, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1296782839, 0),
(155, 'It has been one of our dreams to visit Spain for more than a decade and we decided that this was the summer to make this dream come true.  We love the culture, architecture, history and natural beauty.  It also helps that we both speak Spanish after having lived in two Latin American countries.  We could never just pick a favorite memory or place in Spain because ALL of it was just incredible.  The importance of people and the relationships they share with friends and families (or even just tourists like us) is so evident.   We are so lucky to have experienced this wonderful vacation and we now look towards our next dream of becoming parents.  \n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Dream Trip - Spain', 127, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1312223718, 0),
(37, 'Dear Birth Parent- Justin and I are glad you are taking the time to read our profile! We know you are making an important decision, and want you to know we are praying for you! We have been married over 10 years and have wanted children for a long time.\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'birth letter', 219, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1297360982, 0),
(39, 'Dear Birth Parent- Justin and I are glad you are taking the time to read our profile! We know you are making an important decision, and want you to know we are praying for you! We have been married over 10 years and have wanted children for a long time. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth Parent Letter', 219, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1297362135, 0),
(46, '<p>stuff<img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/MarkLetty/matthew_with_hat2.jpg" alt="" width="287" height="215" /></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Neighborhood', 59, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1298431675, 0),
(47, 'Here is some information about our family pets.\nhers is some more text about our pets\n\n\nMike and Mary are hopeful and excited adoptive parents waiting to adopt a baby.\nIf you are pregnant and considering placing your child for adoption, we are so excited that you are looking at our parentfinder info. Yes we have a Dear Birthmother Letter but to really get to know us please keep up with our journal, view our videos, and join parentfinder to chat with us directly. We can even have a video chat to help you know you are making the right decision. We want to hear from you and see if we are a match for your baby. We love that you are taking care of your baby and so will we.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'family pets', 62, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1302624298, 0),
(154, 'We also enjoy spending time with the other two members of our family: our cat (Wilma), and our dog (Macy). Both are rescues: Bo adopted Wilma in 2003, and together we adopted Macy from a local shelter in 2009. They bring us so much joy.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Pets', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1312056880, 0),
(153, 'Bo is the best friend a person could ask for. He is sensitive and smart, and he is engaged in the world around him. He is always interested in learning something new, but he also loves traditions. He loves to laugh, and he is a wonderful storyteller. He will make a loving father, invested in every aspect of his child''s life.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'In Adrienne&#039;s Words', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1312056744, 0),
(50, '<p>Come view our profile book with our adoption agency, Heart of Adoptions, Inc.</p>\n<p> <a href="http://www.myadoptionplan.com/Families/Patrick+Mylene.pdf">http://www.myadoptionplan.com/Families/Patrick+Mylene.pdf</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Or if you are unable to go directly to our profile, click on link below and on page, look for Mylene and Patrick.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><a href="http://www.myadoptionplan.com/AdoptFam.html">http://www.myadoptionplan.com/AdoptFam.html</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Thank you for checking our profile!</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Profile Book', 133, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1298739595, 0),
(51, 'This is our house', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our House', 59, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1299263941, 0),
(54, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;"><span style="color:#800000;font-family:Georgia;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:10pt;text-align:justify;"><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Siena/Torre_Stretched.JPG" alt="" width="146" height="347" /><span style="color:#888888;"><span style="font-family:Georgia;">Sien</span><span style="font-family:Georgia;">a is the perfectly preserved medieval city that is tucked away in a tradition-filled country. The Sienese people cling to the greatness that it achieved hundreds of years ago and possess a strong sense of community that protects their traditions. It boasts an uncommonly safe community that gracefully juxtaposes older generations with younger ones. We believe this is an ideal place to raise a child.</span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'SIENA', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1301920836, 0),
(53, 'This block would contain information about Mark as described by Letty his wife', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Mark by Letty', 59, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1320674314, 0),
(55, '<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;color:#000000;"><span style="color:#993300;font-size:small;">I</span>t would be nearly impossible to find two more spoiled dogs than our puppies, Barney Doodle and Baxley Blue. Half brothers who are 6 months apart in age, these pups add so much joy to our lives. They are the most playful, loving dogs who just want the simple things in life: a nice walk, a little food, and a lot of cuddles! Oh, and a treat or two along the way never hurts either!  We''</span><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;">ve posted some videos starring Barney and Baxley.  See for yourselves just how silly we are!</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Georgia;color:#800000;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Scheming_Bugs.JPG" alt="" width="600" height="450" /><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Barney and Baxley', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1333388857, 0),
(56, '<p>       <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Lisa_1996.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="134" />     </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:Georgia;color:#888888;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">We could say that there is nothing particularly extraordinary about us apart from, perhaps, our beginning. Our meeting was a dream come true. Really, everyone tells us so: an American woman, an Italian man, and an extended summer vacation in the Tuscan hills of Italy where we met. It was a whirlwind romance that grew into a committed relationship which led to our marriage. That was nearly 14 years ago! We married in a local church in Siena, Italy, Francesco’s home town, and our friends and family from all over met and celebrated with us. We chose to live in Siena, first in the city’s center, but for the past few years we have been enjoying living in an old farmhouse just outside of the city with our two dogs, Barney and Baxley. And it''s been good. </span></p>\n<p>       <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Francesco_1996.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="134" /></p>\n<p><span style="color:#003366;font-family:Georgia;font-size:medium;"><span style="font-size:16px;"><br /></span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Americana in Italy', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1302001787, 0),
(57, '<p><span style="color:#000000;font-size:x-small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;"><span style="color:#993300;"><span style="font-size:small;">F</span>rancesco</span> owns and manages an historic hotel that has been a family business for nearly 100 years. Francesco enjoys walking in the halls and rooms of the hotel knowing that all of his relatives, near and distant, were frequently present. Each little niche was a favorite spot of somebody and Francesco takes care to preserve it properly and respectfully.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:Georgia;color:#888888;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:left;"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><span style="color:#993300;"><span style="font-size:small;">L</span>isa</span> owns and operates an English-language book store which is located inside the hotel. In addition to providing literary pleasures in the English language, Lisa’s shop has become a regular meeting place for the international community, who reside within and surrounding Siena. </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:left;"><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/HotelBookshop/Shop.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" />  <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Lisa_at_Work.JPG" alt="" width="135" height="200" />  <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/HotelBookshop/ShopDetail.JPG" alt="" width="133" height="200" /></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Georgia;color:#888888;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">Video Guide of the Hotel has been posted! Take a tour through the Gardens, Reception, and Common rooms to see where we spend our days. I was even able to get a small glimpse of a room...!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Whistle while we work...', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1320771798, 0),
(64, '<p>Mark is a great guy.... yes</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Mark', 59, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1320673186, 0),
(148, 'When Bo proposed in 2007 (after we had been dating for more than a year), he said nothing more than "I want to build a family with you." After accepting his proposal, we began planning not just our wedding, but our life together. As time has passed, some plans have changed, but our goal is the same: we want to build a family together.\n\n\nWe were married in the Fall of 2008 in the Roman Catholic Church that Bo has attended since childhood and that we continue to attend together. We''d like to say that we got married on a day with perfect weather, but it was more like a torrential downpour. In the end, our selection of "Baby It''s Cold Outside" for our first dance was perfect.\n\n\nWe took it all in stride, laughed like crazy, and took our pictures outside at the local football stadium as planned. We''re incredibly grateful for that day, because it showed us -- together -- that even when things don''t go precisely as planned, they still turn out exactly as they are supposed to. Our wedding day was a memorable beginning to our life together.\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'A Brief History of Us', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1312055331, 0),
(150, 'Thank you for taking the time to look at our profile. We want you to know that we admire your courage and willingness to choose a home for your baby. Above all, please know that your baby would be loved, safe and unconditionally accepted within our family.\n\n\n\n\nWe hope that this profile shows you a little about who we are, and how much we are looking forward to building our family.  If you would like any additional information not contained here, or if you would like to speak with us, please contact us!  We would be honored to speak with you, and we look forward to learning about you, too.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Thanks', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1312055528, 0),
(59, '<p> </p>\n<div style="color:#000000;font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:10px;background-color:#ffffff;margin:8px;">\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Georgia;color:#800000;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">We are blessed with wonderful friends and family and though they may not always be in our immediate vicinity, they are ever present in our lives.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Georgia;color:#800000;"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Shane_and_Corinne.jpg" alt="" width="52" height="50" />  <img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Nipoti.jpg" alt="" width="61" height="50" />  </span></span><img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Lisa_and_Carla.JPG" alt="" width="60" height="50" />  <img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Catharina_and_Carla.JPG" alt="" width="67" height="50" />  <img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Giovanni.JPG" alt="" width="48" height="50" />  <img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Miriam.JPG" alt="" width="52" height="50" />  <img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Cora.JPG" alt="" width="54" height="50" />  <img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Birthday_Boy_Francesco.JPG" alt="" width="67" height="50" />  <img style="border:0px;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Corinne_at_Palio.JPG" alt="" width="67" height="50" /></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Georgia;color:#800000;"><strong>G', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Families', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1301481685, 0),
(60, 'The Maternity and Adoption program at Catholic Charities of Dallas has been a licensed Child Placing Agency since 1985 and meets all State of Texas Licensing Minimum Standards and is also accredited by the Council on Accreditation (COA).', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT US', 559, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1301429890, 0),
(61, '<p>More details</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'More details', 559, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1301433366, 0),
(62, '<p><span style="color:#800000;font-family:Georgia;"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"> </span></span></p>\n<p class="MsoBodyText"> </p>\n<p class="MsoBodyText"><span style="color:#888888;">We are blessed with a wonderful family and though they may not always be in our immediate vicinity, they are ever present in our lives. Check out our Family photo album and the Family video to take a look at Granny and Nonno, Oma and Papa, Zia Miriam, Tante Claudia, Uncle Tom and Cousins Catharina, Shane, Carla, Corinne and Cora! Most of these snapshots have been taken in the past year or so at some gathering in either Germany, Italy, Florida or New York. We hope you enjoy them!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'We are Family...', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1301935364, 0),
(65, 'We''ve set up our Profile page to give you small sampling of who we are, but it''s our Journal that is becoming the active page where you can get to know us better. As the title implies, it''s just a bunch of random stuff--Lists, Notes, Thoughts, Plans--for you to get to know us better. Feel free to share your thoughts, too!\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Thoughts Notes Lists Plans...', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1303326808, 0),
(70, '<p>Please check out our <a href="http://app.picaboo.com/WebView/Project.aspx?clientID=af04bd94db4aebb6f9cdcc4a995e61be&amp;version=112581&amp;siteID=ViaPreview">photo book</a>!</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Photo Book', 633, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1305502576, 0),
(78, '<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/IMG_2429.JPG" alt="" width="300" height="105" /></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><span style="color:#993300;">A</span> growing collection of memories, thoughts and ideas specifically related to sharing our lives with a child.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><span style="color:#993300;">A Special Note:</span> The illustrations in these entries are particularly dear as the artist was Lisa''s Godmother, Tante Helga, who wrote and illustrated many German childrens books during her life. One book in particular, an autobiography of sorts, reflected a happy summer visit from her cousins (Lisa''s mother and aunt, Tante Christa) where the three cousins set out for a picnic with "Tante Lina and Onkel Rolf." Poor Tante Christa got an ear-ache on that very day! From her early childhood, Lisa has always envisioned these "family portraits" as a perfect decoration for a nursery. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Brief_History_and_a_Thought.pdf">Brief_History_and_a_Thought.pdf</a></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Expectations_and_Hopes.pdf">Expectations_and_Hopes.pdf</a></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Education.pdf">Education.pdf</a></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Glimmer_of_Anticipation.pdf">Glimmer_of_Anticipation.pdf</a></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Hopeful Path to Parenthood', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1333543357, 0),
(83, '1. Soccer - still plays, played on three teams at the same time, captain\n2.  College football and World Cup - two of his favorite sporting events\n3.  Night Owl - prefers to stay up late\n4.  Snickers - favorite candy (likes most candy)\n5.  EDSBS - believes "every day should be Saturday"\n6.  Movies - likes comedy, action, and suspense\n7.  Listener - his friends say he is great at listening and hanging out ( I agree)\n8.  Music - rock, especially classic rock\n9.  Jeep - has owned the same on for 16 years\n10. Running - enjoys running with friends, Tricia or just alone', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Ten Things About Doug', 127, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1307203575, 0),
(84, '<p>Let me know if you need help, I am trying to create a few short videos to help answer any questions you may have. You can friend me,rest your cursor over my picture at the top of the page and a menu will come up and befriend should be an option.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Mike is also an admin of the site', 62, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1310773905, 0),
(90, 'We went on our first date three days before Christmas. We had an instant connection and it felt as if we had known each other for years. Nick went back to visit his parents for the holiday, but we talked on the phone for three hours at a time (Nick''s mom says that she knew it was something big when her son spent more than ten minutes on the phone).  After dating for just over 4 months, we were engaged.  Nick had to go on his first deployment for eight months and it was an extremely difficult time for both us, but we made it and became a stronger couple because of it.  About four months after his deployment, we got married.  It was a beautiful wedding, but the best part was that we were married!  Since then we have been through some difficult and challenging times together, but thankfully we always had each other.  Knowing that someone is always in your corner and supporting you is the most amazing feeling and we are both so lucky!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 732, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318196515, 0),
(91, '\n10. I was born in Germany and have lived and visited over 30 countries across the world.\n\n9. I am an avid South Carolina fan, and while I won’t insist on our child attending that\nUniversity, I will certainly encourage it ;-)\n\n8. Huge animal lover\n\n7. I love watching and playing sports (golf, soccer, basketball, baseball, tennis and football)\n\n6. Traveling is a passion of mine...and part of the job\n\n5. I love my parents and am very grateful for all they have done for me\n\n4. I fully believe that everything happens for a reason, no matter how vague it may be\n\n3. French hens\n\n2. My family is the most important thing to me\n\n1. I “heart” my wife...which means that I not only love her, but I like her too :-)', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Top Ten Facts about Nick', 732, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1309214728, 0),
(92, '10. I love to wear flip flops year round\n9. My favorite hobby is taking pictures\n8. I love traveling around the world and meeting new people\n7. I adore my niece and have loved watching her grow\n6. My favorite teams are the Jacksonville Jaguars, FSU, Tampa Bay Rays and the\nOrlando Magic\n5. I’m a huge animal lover\n4. I’m an extremely silly person\n3. I love being a teacher\n2. Family is the most important thing to me.\n1. My husband is my best friend.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Top Ten Facts about Tiff', 732, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1308793573, 0),
(98, '<p><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Brief_History_and_a_Thought.pdf">Brief_History_and_a_Thought.pdf</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Brief_History_and_a_Thought.pdf"></a><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Expectations_and_Hopes.pdf">Expectations_and_Hopes.pdf</a></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Hopeful Path to Parenthood', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1309455883, 0),
(99, '<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Siena/Torre_Stretched.JPG" alt="" width="146" height="347" /><span style="font-family:Arial;">Siena is the perfectly preserved medieval city that is tucked away in a tradition-filled country. The Sienese people cling to the greatness that it achieved hundreds of years ago and possess a strong sense of community that protects their traditions. It boasts an uncommonly safe community that gracefully juxtaposes older generations with younger ones. We believe this is an ideal place to raise a child.</span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:10pt;text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:Arial;"></span></p>\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Siena', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1309456237, 0),
(94, 'All of our animals are part of our family. Spencer is a silly rabbit that we all love and adore.  He loves his hop around time and playing with the dogs.  Zoey and Aila have both been around children since they were puppies. Aila prefers small children that love to snuggle up and Zoey is always up for a game of fetch, if you are willing to throw the ball a MILLION times. ;-)', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Pets', 732, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1326974486, 0),
(223, 'www.patrickrebeccaadoption.com', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Website', 1070, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318201120, 0),
(97, '<p><span> </span><img style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Lisa_1996.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="134" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us">As an introduction We could say that there is nothing particularly extraordinary about us apart from, perhaps, our beginning. Our meeting was a dream come true. Really, everyone tells us so: an American woman, an Italian man, and an extended summer vacation in the Tuscan hills of Italy where we met. It was a whirlwind romance that grew into a committed relationship which led to our marriage. That was nearly 14 years ago! We married in a local church in Siena, Italy, Francesco’s home town, and our friends and family from all over met and celebrated with us. We chose to live in Siena, first in the city’s center, but for the past few years we have been enjoying living in an old farmhouse just outside of the city with our two dogs, Barney and Baxley. And it''s been good.</span></p>\n<p><span> </span><img style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Francesco_1996.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="134" /></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'L&#039;Americana in Italia', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1309534022, 0),
(101, 'Our extended family is beyond excited and supportive about our decision to adopt.  If you decide to place your child into our home, your child will be showered by love by four grandparents, aunts, uncles and so many cousins!  Our families are both different and very similar.  While both of our fathers were in the military, Nick traveled the world and Tiff lived in the same house since 2nd grade.  Both our families give us unconditional love and support in our life decisions.  We were also brought up with many of the same values and morals. When our families first met, we hoped that they would get along, but we never expected the instant closeness that would develop.  Over the years we have spent holidays as one big family and even gone on vacations together. We have our disagreements and our struggles, but we love and support each other warts and all.\nIn addition to our traditional family we have our chosen family.  These are our friends.  While they may not be related to us by blood, they are family just the same.\nEveryone is so excited about making new additions to our family.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 732, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318196906, 0),
(224, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/1068-GregandBecky/1068-GregandBecky.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Greg and Becky''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 1068, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1318204259, 1),
(242, 'test', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Blog', 1103, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318552325, 0),
(102, 'We have set up our Profile page to give you a general introduction to us , but it is our Journal where we''ll try to share a more active part of our lives. Just as it''s title indicates, our Journal is a random collection of thoughts, lists, notes, and plans, which will hopefully allow you to get to know us, the things we do, and the people we cherish better. We hope you''ll check it out! \nLisa and Francesco', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Thoughts...Notes...Lists...Plans', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1309530362, 0),
(103, 'Dakota, our Alaskan Malamute dog, is a gentle giant. He loves belly rubs and walks. Dakota is very playful and loves to interact with people, especially children! \n\n\nMikey, our Cockatiel, loves to sing in the morning. He is very verbal and will say "good morning", peek-a-boo", what''s mommy doing" as well as ask you to sing Jingle Bells with him...his favorite tune!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Pets...', 769, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1310234466, 0),
(105, '<p>Family and friends are so important to us. We enjoy spending lots of time with our family and friends. Everyone is looking forward to a new addition. We are so thankful for all their support and love throughout this journey. We couldn''t do this without all of them. And we can''t wait to share their love and kindness with a new baby.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our family and friends', 800, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1309985646, 0),
(145, '<p style="text-align:center;"><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Anne.JPG" alt="" width="58" height="50" />   <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/BBQ_in_Germany.jpg" alt="" width="67" height="50" />   <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Birthday_Boy_Francesco.JPG" alt="" width="67" height="50" />   <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Catharina_and_Carla.JPG" alt="" width="67" height="50" />   <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Corinne_Lisa_Claudia.JPG" alt="" width="81" height="50" />   <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Giovanni.JPG" alt="" width="48" height="50" />   <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Miriam.JPG" alt="" width="52" height="50" />   <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Jim_MarieLuise.JPG" alt="" width="56" height="50" /></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><span style="color:#993300;font-size:small;">W</span>e are blessed with a wonderful family and though they may not always be in our immediate vicinity, they are ever present in our lives. Check out our Family Photo album and Family video to take a look at Granny and Nonno, Oma and Papa, Zia Miriam, Tante Claudia, Uncle Tom and Cousins Catharina, Shane, Carla, Corinne and Cora! Most of these snapshots have been taken in the past year or so at some gathering in either Germany, Italy, Florida or New York. We hope you enjoy them!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Together Family', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1320771505, 0),
(107, 'We love spending time together with each other and our families.   We enjoy traveling to new places.  We like to go on new adventures.  We have been on cruises, taken a hot air balloon ride, tubing in Jamaica, and have driven a moped through the Florida keys.  We hope to travel with our baby and enjoy seeing new places through a child''s eyes.   \n\nHeather enjoys reading and relaxing on the beach.  Shopping and hanging out with friends and family bring her joy.   \n\nGreg has a passion for cooking.  He likes to think of new recipes and try them out.  Greg likes all sports but soccer is his favorite sport to play.   Playing paintball is something he doesn''t get to do all that often but it one of his favorite things to do on a Saturday.  \n\nWe are an active, fun loving couple!  We feel like we have a strong sense of adventure and love to try new and exciting things. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Hobbies and Interests', 744, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1309985749, 0),
(108, '<p>Buddy and Polly are our two lovable furry friends. They are both so cuddly and loving. Walks around our neighborhood and to the parks close by are some of their favorite times. Both of them would love to have a baby in the house. We also have a little bird, Simon, who is a super, sweet part of our family. He''s learning to talk and keeps us entertained.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our animal friends', 800, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1319816594, 0),
(109, 'Our current family consists of Greg, Heather and our two adorable dogs, Bosley and Chelsea. Bosley is a Yorkshire terrier and he has tons of energy and loves people.  His passion in life is to play and chase lizards in the yard.       \nChelsea is a Pomeranian, whom we adopted from the SPCA.  She is a sweet, gentle girl who enjoys playing with her toys.  She is very independent and likes to relax on the back of the couch and look out the window. Bosley & Chelsea get along nicely and keep each other company when we are unable to be at home.   They enjoy being around kids and they are anxiously awaiting the new addition to our family.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Pets', 744, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1309987731, 0),
(110, 'We are lucky that we have loving, caring parents who support us in our daily lives.  Our parents are excited to be grandparent’s.  Our parents have raised us to be generous caring people and have provided us with the tools to be wonderful, loving parents.   Greg’s parents are already grandparents to three grandchildren (Alan-Michael, Dante & Jayden) and are excited to add another grandchild to their family.  Greg’s mom lives a short distance from us and cannot wait to spend time with her new grandchild, taking them to the playground or just loving on them.  Greg’s dad lives in New York, but makes yearly trips to Florida, where he rents a beach house and invites the family over to spend time together.  Heather’s parents live very close by and will be an important part of our child’s life.  Heather’s parents also have two grandchildren, (Travis and Amber) the family birthdays, holidays and sporting events are something they enjoy participating in.   Heather’s mother will spend a lot of time at our house helping out with watching and taking good care of the baby.   They have a best friend type of relationship and the baby will be a blessing for the entire family. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Parents', 744, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1309987782, 0),
(111, 'We have been truly blessed with a wonderful family.  Our siblings are very important to us and we enjoy spending a lot of time with them and their families.  Greg has two sisters (Heather & Amanda), one brother (Chris) and a step-sister (Amanda).  Both of Greg’s sisters live nearby and spend a lot of time visiting us.  Heather has two sons who always visit and like to spend time playing catch or riding bikes.  Greg’s brother lives in Texas, and has a son.  They visit when they can and like to spend time at the beach in Florida and visiting with family.  Greg’s step-sister lives in New York with her two children.  Whenever we go back to New York, we enjoy spending quality time with them.  Heather has one brother who lives in Tampa.  He is the wonderful father to Travis and Amber, our niece and nephew.  We travel to Tampa on occasion to watch them play baseball and softball.   Our siblings are very excited that we are adopting and cannot wait to be an active part of the baby’s childhood.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our siblings, nieces and nephews', 744, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1309987865, 0);
INSERT INTO `aqb_pc_members_blocks` (`id`, `content`, `share`, `approved`, `unmovable`, `irremovable`, `uncollapsable`, `collapsed_def`, `title`, `owner_id`, `visible_group`, `visible`, `column`, `order`, `type`, `date`, `val`) VALUES
(112, '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color:#000090;font-family:Tahoma;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color:#000090;font-family:Tahoma;"><span style="font-size:19px;"> </span></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Tahoma;color:#000090;font-size:small;">We are both blessed to have professional careers that not only provide financial stability, but give us the freedom to pursue all of our many interests and hobbies.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Tahoma;color:#000090;">We are active and love doing anything outdoors, whether it''s walking our dogs, hiking, biking, golfing, swimming, relaxing at the pool, or grilling out with friends and family. Lisa stays in shape by running and playing competitive tennis. She also enjoys playing her french horn in a concert band throughout the year, reading biographies and US Weekly, planning vacations, cuddling the dogs, and watching anything on OWN (Oprah''s network). Kristi likes swimming, road/trail biking, schooling the boys on the basketball court, lifting weights, cooking big dinners for the family, playing clarinet and guitar, and doing house projects. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma;color:#000090;"> </span></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color:#000090;font-family:Tahoma;font-size:small;">We also love to travel. Seeing the world and learning about other cultures is something we can''t wait to share with our children. We typically vacation with our families and sometimes other friends, as we have fun playing with the kids and having family time together. Our favorite place is Hawaii, and we usually make a trip there every year. We also enjoy skiing in Colorado and visiting New York City for Broadway shows.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Hobbies and Interests', 796, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1319377987, 0),
(141, '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><span style="color:#993300;font-size:small;">A</span> narrow dirt path leads to an old, rustic farmhouse we call home. Situated on a large piece of property in the middle of farmlands, we are basically undisturbed with the exception of an occasional tractor passing by. Moving to the country was the best decision we ever made. </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><span style="color:#993300;font-size:small;">A</span>s weekend farmers, we enjoy the benefits of our garden but not always the gardening work! We also have a series of barns behind the house, and we’re thinking about getting some free-range chickens and hens, a goat or two and maybe even a pig. OK, the pig and the goat probably won’t happen, but it’s fun to think about.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Life_on_the_Farm.pdf">Life_on_the_Farm.pdf</a></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial;"><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Farmhouse/Home.001.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" /></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Arial;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1333388576, 0),
(142, '<p> </p>\n<p class="MsoBodyText"><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><span style="color:#993300;font-size:small;">W</span>hile we hope that our Profile page will give you a general idea of who we are, our Journal is where we will be posting a more active part of our lives. Just like the title implies it will host a random collection of our thoughts and plans and lists and notes. Welcome to our humble world!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Thoughts…Notes…Lists…Plans', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1320771349, 0),
(143, '<p><img style="float:left;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;margin-top:1px;margin-bottom:1px;" dir="ltr" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Siena/Torre_Stretched.JPG" alt="" width="126" height="300" /><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><span style="color:#993300;font-size:small;">S</span>iena is the perfectly preserved medieval city that is tucked away in a tradition-filled country. The Sienese people cling to the greatness that it achieved hundreds of years ago and possess a strong sense of community that protects their traditions. It boasts an uncommonly safe community that gracefully juxtaposes older generations with younger ones. We believe this is an ideal place to raise a child.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/LivinginSiena.pdf">LivinginSiena.pdf</a><br /></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:10pt;text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;"> </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Siena', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1321460001, 0),
(144, '<p><img style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Lisa_1996.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="134" /></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:x-small;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><span style="color:#993300;font-size:small;">A</span>s an introduction We could say that there is nothing particularly extraordinary about us apart from, perhaps, our beginning. Our meeting was a dream come true. Really, everyone tells us so: an American woman, an Italian man, and an extended summer vacation in the Tuscan hills of Italy where we met. It was a whirlwind romance that grew into a committed relationship which led to our marriage. That was over 14 years ago! We married in a local church in Siena, Italy, Francesco’s home town, and our friends and family from all over met and celebrated with us. We chose to live in Siena, first in the city’s center, but for the past few years we have been enjoying living in an old farmhouse just outside of the city with our two dogs, Barney and Baxley. And it''s been good.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;" lang="en-us" xml:lang="en-us"><img style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LisaFrancesco/Family/Francesco_1996.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="134" /><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'An Americana in Italy', 494, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1333631789, 0),
(117, 'Jill is a remarkable woman - generous, smart & kind. She has a smile that can light up a room and warm my heart. She is the love of my llife and my best friend. Jill loves like no other and is a better friend and person than anyone I''ve ever met. You know that person that just gets you? Who knows what you need and when you need it? Yep, that''s her!                                                         \nKid''s always gravitat to Jill- she''s just a natural ''kid'' person. I have no doubt Jill will be a fantastic mother... she''s already proven it in the way she loves and cares for Sierra & Lance. Jill is right there with me for the fun stuff and the tough stuff - to encourage, guide & enjoy the children. Her patience and postitive attitude turn even the simplest moments into the best memories!                 \nJill has always dreamed of being a mother and I long to see that dream come true. Jill will give so much love, attention, devotion and encouragement... any child is lucky to be loved by her.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Jill through Jeromy&#039;s eyes...', 197, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1310676050, 0),
(118, '<p> <span style="font-family:ComicSansMS;color:#ffffff;font-size:x-large;"><span style="color:#000000;font-size:small;">Written by : Nick</span><span style="font-family:ComicSansMS;color:#ffffff;font-size:x-large;"> </span></span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;font-size:small;">Tiff is an amazing woman who was put on this earth to have a family.  Whether it be teaching the youth of America, playing with out neice, or babysitting for our friends and neighbors, I can see the sparkle in her eye that is only put there by a child.  Tiff has an unmeasurable capacity to love and she always puts the needs of other, people and animals, before her own.  This is what instantly drew me to her and what keeps me falling in love with her all over again each day.  She was born and raised in Florida, so being one of probably five native Floridians, in the state it gives her the sunny disposition to always see the bright side of life.  Her wonderful parents did a phenomenal job of making her the incredible person she is today.  Tiff spoils all of our animals rotten, but keeps them, and me grounded at all times.  She keeps this family running and organized.  Every day I learn something new about her, but the one thing I will never forget is that, without her, I will always be incomplete.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;font-size:small;"><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/NickandTiffanie/Tiff_Cinderellas_Castle.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="282" /></span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;font-size:small;"><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/NickandTiffanie/london1_186x200.jpg" alt="" width="142" height="155" /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Tiff', 732, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1310770914, 0),
(149, 'After trying to conceive biological children for some time (including dozens of doctor visits and negative pregnancy tests), we have jointly come to the realization that we are being called to adopt. That said, we are grateful for the time spent together trying to build our family. Unexpected years of infertility have allowed us to become even more comfortable and confident in our relationship and our path.\n\n\nThough we have not yet been blessed with the gift of children, we have been blessed with a great deal of happiness, good fortune, and lots of adventure. As you are searching for a home for your baby, we are searching for a child to fill our home and our hearts.\n\n\nWe would be eternally grateful for the opportunity to parent the baby that you are selflessly bringing into this world. Formal education is very important to us, but we also recognize that many wonderful things can be learned outside of classrooms. We want to show our children the places we have seen from Hawaii to Rome -- and provide them with all that this wide world has to offer. More than those tangible things, though, we want to show them that they are loved beyond measure and that they will always have a place to belong: both in our hearts, and in yours.\n\n\nWe cannot imagine how difficult this decision must be for you, and we hope and pray that you find comfort in it. Thank you for taking the time to learn a little about us. We would be honored to speak with you further so that we can answer any questions you have -- and so that we can learn a little about you! We also want you to know that we would welcome the opportunity to continue our relationship through letters and pictures.\n\n\nThank you (more than words can say) for considering us. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Dear Birth Parent', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1312055039, 0),
(124, '<div class="boxContent" style="text-align:left;">\n<div class="bx_sys_default_padding">\n<p>Bo (whose real name is Ryan) has two older sisters.  All three siblings were raised together in a loving and comfortable home. The family remains quite close; both of Bo''s sisters, their five children, and Bo''s parents all live within fifteen minutes of our home in Ohio. That proximity allows us to spend a great deal of time together, including regular Sunday dinners and summer camping weekends. Bo''s father is a successful small business owner; his mother provides administrative support to those working to rehabilitate inmates at a local prison.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Bo, who is 32 years old, is a classically trained chef, having completed culinary school after graduating from high school. After a number of years in the food industry, Bo joined the family business as its sales distribution manager. While he no longer cooks professionally, he does the majority of the cooking at home. (Adrienne is incredibly grateful for that arrangement!) They are both grateful, too, for his flexible hours and the many benefits of working in the family business.</p>\n<p> </p>\n</div>\n</div>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Bo', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1312058155, 0),
(121, '<p>Please click on our on this profile <a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/MikeandMary/alanamy.pdf">alanamy.pdf</a></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Profile', 62, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1310986291, 0),
(125, '<p style="text-align:left;"><span lang="en" xml:lang="en"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:left;" dir="ltr">Adrienne is an only child, but she was raised alongside her many cousins. (In fact, she served as maid of honor in two of their weddings, and she is Godmother to one of their children.) She has a very large extended family (her mother was the middle child of seven children), and she has always enjoyed spending holidays and vacations (from Columbus to Toronto to the Grand Canyon) with them. Adrienne''s grandfather is also a big part of our life; we see him at least once a week and include him in traditions from carving pumpkins at Halloween to coloring eggs at Easter.</p>\n<p style="text-align:left;" dir="ltr"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:left;" dir="ltr">After high school, Adrienne attended a small liberal arts college. While working her way through college (through a number of jobs, lots of saving, and hard work), she kept busy with activities from student government to residential life. After college, Adrienne went to law school. She spent the summer of 2001 studying at Oxford University in England and traveling around much of Europe. Adrienne''s mother, a remarkable woman and wonderful example of motherhood, passed away just before Adrienne began her third year of law school. Adrienne''s father and step-mother currently live in Florida. Her father works to help people suffering from an addiction to alcohol; her step-mother is an emergency room nurse. Both are caring, wonderful people who could not be more excited about becoming grandparents. We see them several times a year, including every Thanksgiving in Florida, and we talk to them on the phone and online several times a week. For the past seven years, Adrienne has worked at a large law firm, helping clients to address complex legal issues. At 33 years old, Adrienne enjoys her work, but she also enjoys her free time.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Adrienne', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1312056661, 0),
(152, 'Adrienne is a devoted and faithful friend. She is organized and intelligent, but she is also silly. She can laugh at herself, and she doesn''t take life too seriously. She is quick to forgive. She will make a patient and involved mother. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'In Bo&#039;s Words', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1312056688, 0),
(126, '<p style="text-align:left;">We are both blessed to have wonderful friends, who have always seemed more like family. In fact, the eight individuals who stood up with us at our wedding were all high school friends, with whom we remain close.</p>\n<div style="text-align:left;">\n<div style="text-align:left;">Together, we make a great team. We enjoy planning and hosting get- togethers with friends and family. We have regular game nights with good friends (Cranium, Taboo and Pit are favorites) as well as an annual gingerbread house- building contest at Christmastime. We enjoy going to see movies and plays, trying new restaurants, and we especially enjoy traveling together.</div>\n</div>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'In Our Free Time', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1312058352, 0),
(151, 'Bo is a second degree black belt in Tae Kwon Do. Through TKD, Bo enjoys testing his own skills, spending time with good friends, and teaching the school''s children self-confidence and respect. Bo is also an avid sports fan, and we enjoy being season ticket holders of the local professional football team. \n\nAdrienne shares regular breakfasts with her high school friends, likes to shop, and possesses an uncanny knowledge of celebrity news. She is also an avid reader and movie-watcher!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Interests', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1312056245, 0),
(127, 'Bo is a second degree black belt in Tae Kwon Do. Through TKD, Bo enjoys testing his own skills, spending time with good friends, and teaching the school''s children self-confidence and respect. Bo is also an avid sports fan, and we enjoy being season ticket holders of the local professional football team.  \n\nAdrienne shares regular breakfasts with her high school friends, likes to shop, and possesses an uncanny knowledge of celebrity news.  She is also an avid reader and movie-watcher!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'In Our Free Time', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1312055945, 0),
(128, '<p>At the moment, we own two suburban homes: one townhouse, and one condo. We are renting out the townhouse and living in the condo, which is located in a wonderful, family-friendly neighborhood less than 1/2 mile from where Bo works. Now that we have finished remodeling the condo, we plan to sell it in 2011 to buy our dream home!</p>', '0', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 560, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 1000, 'text', 1311096023, 0),
(129, 'Adam comes from a large and blended extended family. He has a younger brother as well as 5 step sisters and 6 neices and nephews. With stepparents, 13 Aunts and Uncles and more than 20 cousins the holidays are a time for bustling familt reunions full of home cooking, card games and laughter.\n\nKristie comes from a much smaller family. As an only child, Kristie developed close friendships and best friends Staci and Jennifer can''t wait to become "Aunties". Kristie''s parents, Frank and Laurie, live nearby and are thrilled at the thought of becoming first time grandparents! \n\nOn both sides of our extended families children have been adopted. Children have joined the family through both private, and foster care adoptions, both domestic and international. This strong support network will help us navigate some of the special challenges adoptive children encounter.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Friends and Family...', 769, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1311211630, 0),
(130, 'From Niagara Falls to the Grand Canyon, whether on a cruise ship or camping, our sense of adventure drives us to explore the world around us. We are an active couple who never fails to have a good time no matter where we find ourselves. Whether trying a new ethnic food, negotiating for a trinket, or snuggling around a campfire we enjoy life and time together.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Adventures...', 769, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1311211922, 0),
(131, 'We have worked hard to create a stable, secure and loving home, but nothing is more important to us than family. We cherish the time we have with our extended families and dream of the day when we will have our own family to create memories with.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Dreams for the Future...', 769, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1311212144, 0),
(140, 'Our names are Scott and Marlene.  We met 6 years ago online.  Our courtship was a blast.  Scott would cook for me, took me to a museum, a haunted house, concerts and we would go on family outings too with his wonderful son Blane.  After 6 months, we got married and I had an instant family.  We both grew up in the Midwest and have those great midwestern values.  My husband grew up in Missouri and has one brother.  I grew up in Kansas and have two sister and have the unique pleasure of being an identical twin.  I am a pharmacist and my husband is a construction worker.  We put a lot into our jobs.  But now we want to put a lot into a family and are trying to build ours.\nWe enjoy vacationing in exotic locations, camping, fishing, hot tubbing and going to concerts.  We also like everyday things like shopping, watching our son play sports or running errands.  We enjoy playing with our 2 dogs who are also part of our family.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About us, by Marlene', 867, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1311515453, 0),
(710, '<p><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:medium;">Laura draws cartoons and here are a few for the kids playroom.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:x-small;"><img style="float:left;" title="Octopus and fish" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LauraRyan/img177.jpg" alt="Octopus and fish" width="210" height="241" /><img style="vertical-align:middle;" title="Space Out" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LauraRyan/img178.jpg" alt="Space Out" width="210" height="225" /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:x-small;"><img style="vertical-align:middle;" title="Skater" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LauraRyan/img179.jpg" alt="Skater" width="210" height="243" /><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Cartoons', 2552, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1334865115, 0),
