(186, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;line-height:12pt;margin:0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-family:georgia, palatino;color:#000000;font-size:medium;">Like many families today, we both work.  It allows us to live a comfortable life as well as provide for the future of our family.  Dennis works as a Produce Manager for a local supermarket while Jenn is a Staff Accountant for a nonprofit company.  Since Dennis sets his own hours and works just fifteen minutes from home, he is able to adjust his schedule to fit our family’s needs.  Jenn looks forward to taking some time off after our second child is placed before returning to work in a reduced capacity.  For the days we both work, Jenn’s dad takes care of Ryan and looks forward to twice as much fun with two grandchildren.  Though we both work hard during the day, family is our priority and we believe evenings and days off should be dedicated to family time and family activities. </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Work', 740, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1315251046, 0),
(187, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;line-height:12pt;margin:0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="background-color:#ffffff;font-family:georgia, palatino;color:#000000;font-size:medium;">We both grew up in loving and supportive families.  <span style="background-image:none;background-attachment:scroll;background-repeat:repeat;background-position:0% 0%;">Dennis is the youngest of his parents’ three boys, while Jenn is the oldest of three girls.</span>  Our parents always emphasized the importance of family, and spending time together was a priority.  As kids, Dennis and his brothers loved playing golf with their grandfather, family cookouts in the backyard, and Sunday morning breakfasts after church.   Jenn’s favorite childhood memories include the annual vacation in Maine and Christmas day celebrations with her large extended family.  </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;line-height:12pt;margin:0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="background-color:#ffffff;font-family:georgia, palatino;color:#000000;font-size:medium;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="background-color:#ffffff;font-family:georgia, palatino;font-size:medium;"><span style="background-image:none;background-attachment:scroll;background-repeat:repeat;background-position:0% 0%;color:#000000;">Today our family has grown to include three nephews and a niece, as well as many cousins and friends with young children.  Together we enjoy celebrating birthdays, gathering for week night dinners and creating the largest cheering section for the kids’ various sports teams.  We enjoy watching as the children in our family grow, and feel fortunate we can play an active role in their lives</span><span style="color:#000000;">.  We value the closeness that comes from growing up with siblings and are eager for Ryan to share the same experience with a little brother or sister.</span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family', 740, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1340653306, 0),
(191, '<p><img style="vertical-align:top;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/GregandDenise/Untitled.png" alt="" width="200" height="152" /></p>\n<p><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">We are very blessed with a beautiful home about twenty minutes from Denise’s</span><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">mother and thirty minutes from her sister. Greg’s job allows him to work from home</span><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">most of the time and commuting is usually a “walk downstairs”. It’s on a cul-de-sac</span><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">where a child can ride a bike in safety and has a long driveway that is perfect for</span><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">pulling little red wagons or riding Big Wheels. There is also a large back yard (good</span><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">for soccer balls) and an above ground pool. Last year Greg started a garden, and the</span><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">boys love to help (especially eating the strawberries!). Our home is about 45 minutes</span><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">from Boston so we can easily enjoy a taste of the city whenever we want. The</span><br /><span style="font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:small;">neighborhood is full of young children, and we cannot wait to add one more!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 974, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1315413852, 0),
