(208, 'David: ADOPTED at birth from Milwaukee, WI.  American.  Caucasian.   Ancestry: Irish, Swedish and Native American.\n\nKimberly:  American.  Caucasian.  Ancestry: Irish, French, German, English and French-Canadian.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Nationality/Ethnic background:', 1006, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1316545739, 0),
(209, 'David:  University of Wisconsin.  Bachelors of Arts-Political Science, Finance.\nPlayed soccer for the University.\nVP of his Fraternity\nUniversity of Tampa.  Master of Business Administration-MBA in Finance.\n\nKimberly:  University of Florida.  Bachelor of Science in Nursing.  \nSorority member active on many committees both within the sorority and on campus.  Played on the sorority''s flag-football team.\nUniversity of Florida.  Master of Science in Nursing-Pediatric Nurse Practitioner.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Education', 1006, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1316545897, 0),
(210, 'No.  David and one of his sisters were each adopted at birth.  They had the best experience so both have undertaken the role of adoptive and/or foster parents as adults.  His older sister has 4 biological children and just adopted 2 of her 4 foster children.  His two best friends which were the "Co-Best Men" in our wedding were adopted.  Kimberly''s grandmother was adopted at birth.  \nWe have two adult neighbors/good friends and three of our daughter''s friends that were adopted.  Several of our neighbors and some of our church friends are “foster parents” to some really amazing kids.  \n\nBoth of our children were adopted.  Even our cats were adopted!!!  Kimberly is the ONLY ONE NOT adopted.  Your baby will have plenty of close relatives and family friends that understand firsthand the blessings that come from being adopted into happy loving homes.\n\nBirthparents frequently express concern about whether their child will feel "different" if adopted into a family where no one else is adopted.  Will they ever build a connection with someone that personally understands the gifts of love they were given?  THAT is clearly not an issue in our family!!!!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Are you able to have children biologically? ', 1006, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1316546461, 0),
(211, 'HAVE FUN!  LAUGH A LOT!  ENJOY BEING A KID!  In order to be able to really learn about the world kids have to feel free to roll in the grass, bury themselves in sand at the park, engage in cooking and messy art projects, dribble their yummy popsicles at festivals and jump into big rain puddle without fear of soiling their clothing or angering their parents.  Kids and their clothes can be washed and bath time is so much fun!  Naturally, need to learn when it is not the right time to get “good and dirty” such as before a “Daddy Daughter Dance” or a concert.  \n\nWe role-model selflessness, empathy and charity.  We use good southern manners, share, respect others and their property.  It is far better to give with your heart than with possessions.  Together we emphasize the use of verbal communication to resolve problems and promote asking for help as a way of learning new skills.  \n\nDinner time is sacred family time.  We share stories, accomplishments, dreams and attempts.  Our kids are only little for such a short period so we choose to focus solely on them from the time David gets home from work until they are asleep.  We do not turn on the TV (except for a holiday movie or a TV special designed for families) until after they are in bed and we have had some “us” time.   Every night after playing together, some “serious tickle torture” or “climbing on Daddy the human monkey-bars” the kids pick out books designed for each of their levels and we read together snuggling on the couch.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'What are your attitudes and values on child rearing?', 1006, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1316546578, 0),
(213, 'Our first adoption three years ago was a dream come true! It happened so fast, but there''s not a moment of it that doesn''t still replay in our minds. Soon after we finished our paperwork, we got a call from ACC that a mother gave birth and was looking at our profile.<br><br>It was a Wednesday, and we anxiously waited for any word. Friday we decided to start preparing. That night we removed furniture from a room, Saturday we painted, Sunday we set up the nursery, and Monday we went to work as normal. But it was no ordinary day! At about 10:00am, ACC called us to say Carmen, Addysn’s birthmother, had chosen us and to come and pick up our baby!<br><br>We were overwhelmed with joy! Tina remembers running through her school crying tears of joy, while Andrew was barely able to say, “I’ve got to go! We got our baby!” We met up, bought out Babies R Us, and went to meet our new baby girl.<br><br>Addysn is an amazing child! She may not be our flesh and blood, but she is a reflection of us. She has our mannerisms, sense of humor, and nurturing skills. We, along with our extended family, love Addysn wholeheartedly, and can''t imagine life without her. We''ll feel the same way about your child, too.<br><br>Every day we''re in awe of what a special girl God has blessed us with.  She is fearless, loving, funny, beautiful, and intelligent. We love when she asks about Carmen and we are able to share her adoption story and the gift we were given. For months now, she has prayed for a baby. We also pray that God again blesses us with a child to love and care for.<br><br>We’ve been told how lucky Addysn is to have had us adopt her. However, there were many families who wanted her and would''ve loved her. We''re the lucky ones because Carmen allowed us the honor of raising her child. We hope our words speak to your heart and you give us the honor of doing the same for your child. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Daughter Addysn', 616, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318465514, 0),
