(215, 'We have strong relationships with our siblings and our parents.  We are blessed to have 6 nieces and nephews with whom we spend a lot of time.  We live close to many members of our family.  Kristin has one sister and Michael has two sisters and a brother. Kristin''s mom is a retired teacher who lives a mile from us and is going to be part of our childcare plan during the school year for our son our daughter.  We both have a big extended family with many aunts, uncles, and cousins with whom we spend holidays.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Our Family', 917, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1316893437, 0),
(421, '<p><a href="http://youtu.be/4i0_HS5frwk">You can see our video by clicking here.</a></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'See our video here', 1477, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1325513807, 0),
(280, 'Hello,\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to consider our family as a loving and caring home for the child you are blessed to bring into this world.   Making the decision to bring your baby to full term and seek out a family that will embrace and cherish the opportunity to welcome him or her into their lives is very courageous.  This unselfish act shows an amazing amount of love and caring on your part.\n\nIf we were fortunate to be selected as your adoptive family, you have a promise from every member of our family that we will love, cherish, and adore this baby and provide him or her with an abundance of support in every endeavor they seek in life.\n\nWe hope our pictures and stories will give you a great indication of our loving family environment. \n\nUpon moving back home to the Tampa, FL area about six years ago, we specifically chose to buy our home in a community we had researched for years.  We were not as concerned with the color of the house, but rather with living in a house surrounded by wonderful families, top-rated schools, and an environment rich in activities for growing children.  Our community has 25 miles of nature trails, and several nearby sport complexes that deliver the means for all kinds of youth sports. Our schools are some of the best in the district.\n\nOur family is one to be involved in the community and schools by giving back through volunteering. Greg coaches youth baseball and basketball teams.  Becky volunteers to be the team mom on the sporting teams, and chaperones on school field trips, and in-class activities. \n\nOur family also has a wonderful big brother, currently six years old, who is very excited about the idea of having a little sister or brother that he can help teach to play and learn.  Lastly, we have a wonderful Golden Retriever named Cassie and Radgoll Cat named Milo that are both very gentle and have been great pets for our family.\n\nThank you for considering us as an adoptive family for the beautiful life y', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth Mother Letter', 1068, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1319407193, 0),
