(243, 'Our Little Man, Tyler  \n\nTyler has touched our lives in ways we could never have imagined. Watching him grow has been like a daily gift.  From the moment he started crawling he has been on the move. He climbs everything (or at least, he tries to). He makes himself at home no matter where he is. Tyler is friendly and outgoing and charms every old lady he meets at the grocery store. He loves to dance, clap, hang upside down, and push his car. He rarely turns down food and always seems to know when we sneak him a vegetable. The curiosity in his eyes and his insatiable energy is keeping us young!  \n\nThe love we feel for Tyler has strengthened our marriage and made us a more complete family.  At times we can''t wait to see how his little personality develops and what interests he will have.  We look forward to watching him grow and see who he becomes in the future.\n\nTyler''s Adoption \n\nIn the spring of 2010 we got the phone call that would change our lives forever; a birthmother from Florida named Brandi had created an adoption plan for her son and chose us to parent him. It was one of the happiest days of our lives! At her request we planned on being at the hospital for his birth. We were so honored she wanted us there to help support her. About a month, and several phone calls later, we headed to sunny Florida to meet Brandi face to face and see our new little man. Early the next morning, before the sun was up, Tyler was born.  We are so happy that we can tell him we were all there together to welcome him into the world with love.\n\nMay of 2010 was the first time we spoke to Tyler''s birth mother, Brandi. We were so grateful to have the chance to learn more about her and her family. Every piece of information we were given has been written down and is waiting for Tyler when he is ready. It is important for our son to know that she chose adoption out of the love she had for him. Since the day he was born, we have talked to him about his birth family. If it were', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Tyler', 1107, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318557952, 0),
