(253, 'We try to take advantage of as much fun time as possible. We love to get out of the house and do things in our community. We go walking through museums, and visiting local festivals. Each year we spend a day at the Renaissance Festival, something we have attended nearly every year since we were married. We take afternoon walks as a family and have dance breaks in the living room (Tyler loves to dance). When we can, we try to travel as a family. Tyler has been flying cross country since he was two months old and has even had the privilege of flying first class. We like to visit our extended family as much as possible so we take a couple of trips each year. When it''s nice outside we take Tyler to the zoo; he isn''t afraid of anything and even got to pet a baby alligator once (don''t worry, it was only on the tail). \n\nDavid loves to be outdoors! He is an avid biker and can''t wait to start throwing a ball around with his little man. Whenever he can, he will spend a day golfing and watches football every Sunday during the season. David travels a lot for work and takes full advantage of it. He has been to Paris, Russia, India, and China, just to name a few. \n\n Most of Michelle''s hobbies center on crafts and sewing. She is looking forward to the years of making Halloween costumes for the family and creating things for the home. She cooks nearly every night and loves it. Michelle comes from a family that enjoys eating, so she feels like she''s sharing her love when she cooks for others. Her specialties are Stuffed Bread and Mexican Casserole. Michelle tries to garden, but doesn''t exactly have a green thumb. She loves to dance and sing whenever she can. \n\nTyler''s favorite activities are climbing, reading and chasing the dog.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Activities and Hobbies', 1107, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318807998, 0),
(249, 'Thank you so much for reading about our family. Taking the time to learn about us means more than we will ever be able to tell you. Although we have not met you, we feel grateful for your strength and courage. We can only imagine the challenge you now face and want you to know you are in our hearts. This humble album is only a glimpse into our lives but we hope it serves you well. We have a lifetime of love to give and hope you will consider our home for your child. It is truly an honor to have the opportunity to be a part of your life. \n\n\nWith Warm Thoughts and Wishes,\n\n\nDavid, Michelle and Tyler\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Dear Friend', 1107, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318807412, 0),
(250, 'The best way to describe Michelle would be curious.  She is always inquisitive about new things and wants to learn about everything.  It is that insatiable quest for knowledge that has kept our lives interesting for the past 13 years.  Michelle is a proud college graduate having completed her college degree in 2008.  Michelle is now staying home with our son while completing her second degree for teaching. She plans on teaching elementary school once our children have started school themselves. She loves the theater and is always looking for opportunities to contribute or add to them in the local community.\n\nMichelle has always possessed the qualities of a great wife and mother. Her patience is only eclipsed by her thoughtfulness.  At times I feel sorry for Tyler because his mommy knows all the tricks before he does!  I have leaned on her for guidance with him because she interacts with him in a way that I can only hope to achieve.  Nothing comes before her family in her eyes and she exhibits that every day.  From cooking meals to planning activities, she always places our needs first.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Michelle, Why I Dig Her - By David ', 1107, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318807651, 0),
(251, 'There is so much to know about David. His adventurous personality is what drew me to him when I first met him at the bank. He loves all sports, from tennis to football. He has been known to spend weekends camping or hiking and patiently tries to teach me to appreciate the outdoors as much as he does. David joined the United States Air Force right after graduating from high school and has proudly served for the last 15 years. Currently working for the Secretary of Defense, David has the rare opportunity to travel all over the world, something he has never taken for granted. While serving his country and being a good husband, David found the time to earn his college degree. He is silly and likes to joke around with his friends and family. He genuinely appreciates the people in his life and always puts the needs of his family before anything else. David is loving and loyal, offering a helping hand or laugh to everyone in his life. His charm and wit is what makes people trust him and is the reason I love him with all my heart. \n\n\nBefore we brought Tyler home I had a feeling he would be a great dad, and I was right. When Dave gets home from work at the end of the day, he gets right on the floor to play with our little man. David hugs and kisses Tyler every day and even started the family tradition of a family hug before bedtime. Whenever Dave is on a trip in some far away country, he asks for daily pictures to make sure he doesn''t miss a thing. Seeing David as a father makes me so proud to call him hubby.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'My Hubby, David - By Michelle ', 1107, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318807742, 0),
(252, 'Tyler has touched our lives in ways we could never have imagined. Watching him grow has been like a daily gift.  From the moment he started crawling he has been on the move. He climbs everything (or at least, he tries to). He makes himself at home no matter where he is. Tyler is friendly and outgoing and charms every old lady he meets at the grocery store. He loves to dance, clap, hang upside down, and push his car. He rarely turns down food and always seems to know when we sneak him a vegetable. The curiosity in his eyes and his insatiable energy is keeping us young!  \n\nThe love we feel for Tyler has strengthened our marriage and made us a more complete family.  At times we can''t wait to see how his little personality develops and what interests he will have.  We look forward to watching him grow and see who he becomes in the future.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Little Man, Tyler  ', 1107, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318807884, 0),
(254, 'In the spring of 2010 we got the phone call that would change our lives forever; a birthmother from Florida named Brandi had created an adoption plan for her son and chose us to parent him. It was one of the happiest days of our lives! At her request we planned on being at the hospital for his birth. We were so honored she wanted us there to help support her. About a month, and several phone calls later, we headed to sunny Florida to meet Brandi face to face and see our new little man. Early the next morning, before the sun was up, Tyler was born.  We are so happy that we can tell him we were all there together to welcome him into the world with love.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Tyler&#039;s Adoption ', 1107, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318808065, 0),
(255, 'Living on an Air Force base provides a network of recourses for service members and their families. Our neighborhood is filled with children of all ages. Our home is brand new with a small fenced back yard, front porch and lots of neighbors. We have parks, playgrounds and recreation centers perfect for young children to safely play. One important aspect of our life here is the support of our friends and neighbors. Raising children here is a community effort, with all families working together in order to keep our homes happy and safe. \n\nThe military community presents unique opportunities for children. Most military kids have met others from all over who share their experiences and introduce Tyler to opportunities that aren''t always available to others.  Perhaps one day we will be able to travel overseas and give him the gift of seeing new countries and new cultures.\n\nWe also consider ourselves a part of the Washington DC community. We love that there is always something to do or a new place to go as a family. We try to take advantage of the many things to do here. We have lived in Maryland for a total of 10 years and are still surprised that we are still able to find new activities to enjoy.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home and Community ', 1107, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1318808115, 0),
