(263, 'Jack - My name is Jack, I am four years old and I LOVE baseball.  Well, really I love all sports but baseball is my favorite.  I want to be in the big leagues when I grow up.\n\nI go to preschool now and am really enjoying learning all my letters and hope to be reading soon.  I am looking forward to when I am bigger and I get to ride the bus to school.  \n\nWhen I am at home I like to help Mommy cook and play games with Daddy.  My little brother, Elliott, is my best friend and I like helping Mommy and Daddy take care of him and I try to teach him new things; like how to play baseball!\n\nI would really like to have more kids in our family so we can have a whole baseball team.\n\n\nElliott - My name is Elliott.  I am only one and a half so I am still learning how to talk.  Even without many words, I am getting better at letting people know what I want.  \n\nOne of my first words was "hungry."  It must be because I really like to eat.  My favorite food is pizza, we have pizza night every Monday with Mommy''s family.  \n\nI also like to sing and dance.  I get really excited when Mommy and Daddy let me watch my favorite show, \n"The Wiggles."\n\nI really love to play with my brother, he and Daddy are teaching me how to play sports.  I hope I am as good as they are when I get bigger. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Teachers', 746, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1320414739, 0),
