(299, 'Thank you for taking time to look at our profile. We know you''re in the middle of a series of intense, difficult and\nheroic decisions about your baby''s future. We are confident that we can provide your child with a loving home that is safe, supportive, stimulating, fun and understanding.\nOur names are John and Rema, but we are actually a family of four, including our two dogs; Goldie and Walter. Walter is a tough, but sweet Jack Russell Terrier, and Goldie is a gentle Sheltie mix. They''re the nicest dogs either of us have ever had and we''ve had them both about four years.\nWe are lucky that our jobs (we''re both teachers) will allow both of us to take a lot of time-off, including a year-long sabbatical, for child-care. We have both been teaching for more than ten years, so we know the hard parts and the great parts that come with taking care of children. We haven''t had a child as a part of our own family, but we know it will add an immeasurable depth and joy to our lives.\nWe have also both been lucky to have been able to travel around a lot. We''ve been to India, where we go to visit\nRema''s family. We''ve also been to Europe and we''ve travel around many different states in the US. We both enjoy new places, cultures, ways of living, foods, music and traditions and we know that being able to share our appreciation of the world with a child will be as good for us as for the child. Both of us also love music, reading, movies (not always the same music, books or movies), cooking, swimming, camping, walking and bike riding.\nWe''ve been married ten years. We met each other eleven years ago at work. We live in a three-bedroom house in a\nsafe, friendly neighborhood with good schools. Our house is across the street from bike trails and hiking trails and near playgrounds and the recreation center.\nRema''s mother visits us every two or three years, from India, and we see John''s parents, his sisters, niece and nephew regularly. OUR parents are very excited about welcoming a grandchild into the family and our friends and neighbors are excited about our decision to adopt.\nWe have the desire, patience and the love needed to give a child a great start in life and a sense of the wonder of the world. We will provide a stable, safe and stimulating home and a place your baby can imagine, choose and build for his or her future.\nWe would love to meet you, so you can get to know us and feel absolutely comfortable about choosing us.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth Parent Letter', 1160, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1349578899, 0),
