(312, '<p>We’re Katie and Joey, and we’re excited that you are taking the time to read our profile. We can’t imagine what you are going through at this moment, but we’re humbled and honored that you would consider us to raise your child.\n\n<p>We’ve known each other since 2001. It was love at first sight for Katie, but it took over two years before Joey built up the courage to ask her out in late 2003. The rest was history. Joey proposed on June 25, 2007, in front of Cinderella''s Castle, and surrounded by our family and friends, we were married almost one year later on May 24, 2008. \n\n<p>In 2010, we bought our first house together just outside of Orlando, which we share with our rescue dachshund, Danica. We love living in Central Florida! It gives us the chance to be outside most of the year and enjoy the sunshine.\n\n<p>We share many of the same interests: traveling, cooking, photography, and watching sports—just to name a few. We''re also active in our community, volunteering for several nonprofit organizations. But there''s nothing that both of us enjoy more than curling up on the couch and watching a movie or taking Danica for a walk around the neighborhood. Family time is most important to us. \n\n<p>We chose adoption to build our family after struggling for three years with infertility. While it was certainly difficult, we are thankful for this obstacle. It not only strengthened our relationship, but it made us appreciate the chance to become parents that much more.\n\n<p>Thank you so much for taking the time to read a little bit about us. We look forward to meeting you soon.\n\n<p>(To view our profile book, visit: http://www.mixbook.com/photo-books/interests/adoption-profile-6012161)', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Welcome', 1247, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1334624984, 0),
(316, 'Princess Kailey is our beautiful, brilliant and absolutely one of kind eight-year old daughter. She is a “social butterfly” that is very artistic and verbal, enjoys singing and listening to music. Kailey enjoys riding her bicycle, loves school and enjoys reading, mathematics and computer activities. Some of her interests include playing chess, board games such as Monopoly and Scrabble, and of course she loves playing games with her dad on the Wii. Kailey’s favorite vacation spot is Disney World in Orlando, Florida. She is naturally compassionate and protective and is excited and overjoyed about her new role as a big sister!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Kailey', 1183, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1320879431, 0),
(317, 'Princess Kailey is our beautiful, brilliant and absolutely one of kind eight-year old daughter. She is a “social butterfly” that is very artistic and verbal, enjoys singing and listening to music. Kailey enjoys riding her bicycle, loves school and enjoys reading, mathematics and computer activities. Some of her interests include playing chess, board games such as Monopoly and Scrabble, and of course she loves playing games with her dad on the Wii. Kailey’s favorite vacation spot is Disney World in Orlando, Florida. She is naturally compassionate and protective and is excited and overjoyed about the possibilities of becoming a big sister!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT KAILEY (BY: MOM &amp; DAD)', 1183, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1322432211, 0),
(318, 'We appreciate the time you have spent getting to know us. Our thoughts and prayers are with you as you make this important decision and hope you find comfort and peace through this process.  As parents we promise to provide your child with all the love, laughter and joy his heart and hands can hold. If you choose us to parent your child, our promise to you is to protect, nurture, encourage and support his dreams and interests through education and a variety of experiences. \nWe will be happy to keep in touch through email, photos, and occasional phone calls. We also look forward to speaking with you about the amount of contact desired. We understand the act of love that is involved through adoption and will always share your childs’s special story with them.  If you are interested in talking to us, please contact Adoption & Beyond at 913.381.6919 or via email caroline@adoption-beyond.org  to learn more about us!\nWith our best wishes and love,\nCurtis, Tori & Kailey\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR PROMISE', 1183, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324688132, 0),
(319, 'Tori is the oldest of three children. She was raised by her parents that have been married for over 40 years.  Tori is a strong individual. She is proud but not prideful, principled and praying. Tori is also humble, humorous and hardworking. She puts family first and balances all that life throws her way an effortless sense, with style, class and grace. Tori is intelligent and confident; yet firm, fair, settled but open-minded. She is instinctively maternal, giving and truly caring for and about others. Tori has made me a more balanced and happier man. I’m not perfect and neither is she but I know with the utmost confidence that she is perfect for me. She is my best friend and I not only love her, but I’m in love with her.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT TORI (BY: CURTIS)', 1183, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1320898675, 0),
(320, 'Curtis is the oldest of two. He was raised by his parents that have been married for over 41 years. Curtis is a loving, patient, kind and fun-loving person. He is smart, warm and slow to anger. Actually, Curtis is the epitome of my dad! Every waking moment, his goal is to be the best father in the world; his shows an enormous amount of patience and understanding as he teaches our daughter a new skill. Curtis is always willing to think outside the box and works well with others. He is very protective of his family and works hard to provide for his family. I have been given favor by God…I love the person Curtis was, is and will be! ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT CURTIS (BY: TORI)', 1183, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1320898623, 0),
(325, 'We are fortunate to have amazing family members and friends who are incredibly supportive of our decision to adopt. Much of our immediate family lives in the Orlando area or within a short driving distance. We see our parents at least once a month, whether it''s to spend a day at Disney World or grab dinner at the local food truck bazaar. Even though our siblings live out of town, they visit often for family dinners, birthdays, holidays, and other special gatherings. This will be the first grandchild for Katie’s parents and the second for Joey’s parents. Everyone could not be more excited to welcome a new baby into our family!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family and Friends', 1247, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1327670956, 0),
(321, 'We live in a suburban city in Northwest Missouri. Our spacious 4 bedroom, 3 and half bath home is nestled in a quiet cul-de-sac. Our home is warm, inviting and full of laughter and love. We often enjoy family dinner in a large kitchen adjacent to a screened deck where our daughter, Kailey enjoys creating and designing outdoor-friendly projects. \nOur neighborhood has a clubhouse, pool, playground and tennis courts.  Our community has excellent schools, great shopping, restaurants, and family-friendly activities and events. Nearby you will find a library, hospital, and fire station. We travel a short distance to the zoo, several museums and our church, where we worship as a family.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR HOME', 1183, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1320880060, 0),
(322, 'Hello! We are a family of three who love to become a family of four!  Our names are Curtis, Tori & Kailey.  We appreciate you taking the time to view our profile; and are very excited to share our story with you. As we begin to write this letter, we are overwhelmed with feelings of thankfulness that you are considering us to parent your child. We cannot imagine your thought process and multitude of emotions you are experiencing as you prepare to make this important decision. We know how precious your child is to you and that we are entering this relationship with open hearts and minds. We find this act of love to be the most selfless and loving decision for your child’s future.\nWe have no idea of the strength it takes to choose parents for your child, but can attempt to empathize with the emotional pain of unsuccessful attempts to grow our family after the birth of our daughter. Through prayer and meditation, our decision to adopt has been made with joy, peace and commitment to expand our family. As your choice, please believe that we will provide your child with a home filled with love, laughter and acceptance. As you learn more about us through our profile, we hope you will feel the love and commitment we share as a family and that your child will be welcomed with open arms and hearts! Please believe that when we share your child’s birth story with them, we will include the depths of your love, sacrifice and bravery.\n\nSincerely,\n\nCurtis, Tori & Kailey\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'BIRTHPARENT LETTER', 1183, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1321335458, 0),
(323, 'Curtis was raised in the Midwest and Tori in the South. We met while working together and spoke over the phone several months before we had our first date. A few months after our first date, Curtis moved over 700 miles away. We communicated via phone, letters and occasional emails. Curtis and Tori took turns traveling to visit one another. The long-distance courtship lasted 3 years and solidified our friendship. We had a beautiful church wedding with over 250 family and friends. We have been married for over 11 years and have known one another for 15 years. We are best friends and soulmates. We have a strong marriage and loving relationship. We are both educators and have similar interests and goals. We know what each other is thinking without a spoken word.  We spend most weekends watching movies, playing games with our daughter and relaxing by laughing and talking with one another. We feel blessed to be in each other’s lives and feel that either of us would not be complete without the other.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR STORY', 1183, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1320880190, 0),
(326, 'When we were ready to buy a house in early 2010, we wanted a place that had a small-town feel, despite living in a big city. We found that in our community. Many of the families in our neighborhood have young children, and they all gather outside in the evenings to play and ride their bikes. We''re also minutes away from the beaches and we recently bought passes to a few of the theme parks, so there is no shortage of kid-friendly activities. And when it''s time to start school, our neighborhood is located in an excellent school district. The elementary and middle schools are both A-rated.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home and Community', 1247, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1328192968, 0),
(327, '<p>We love spending time together and are rarely apart from one another.  In the winter, we<br />enjoy playing board games, building snowmen, and   sledding.  In the warmer seasons, we<br />like to go to the park near our home, go fishing in our boat, go to the local rodeo, go swimming<br />and have bonfires in our backyard. We usually eat a home-cooked supper together every night<br />of the week, which we feel is very important.</p>\n<p>We are part of a very close-knit and supportive church family.   We have many friends with<br />young children, and we get together with them often for fun and fellowship.</p>\n<p>Our son Mason is two and a half. He is a sweet, energetic little boy, and he gives the best<br />hugs!  He adores babies and loves being with other children.  He will be a great big brother!<br />He often asks if he can have a baby brother or sister to play with. Neither of us can<br />imagine our lives without our own siblings, and we hope that someday Mason has one to play<br />with and to lean on as they grow up together.</p>', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Life Together', 1262, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1321041125, 0),
(328, '<p>We live in a small town (population approximately 1800) in a rural area. We have a comfortable three-bedroom historic home and a fenced-in back yard with plenty of room to run and play. It is a very friendly, safe town with a wonderful school system. We live three blocks from the park, where we spend a lot of time in the summer. We also live very near to the library and pool. Every August there is a town celebration with a parade, music in the park and games for the kids.  We live approximately 20 miles from a larger town with more shopping and entertainment options, as well as a 300-bed hospital and clinic. We also live about an hour from a larger city with one of the nation''s leading medical centers. We feel blessed to be able to enjoy the benefits of life in a rural area while enjoying the amenities of the larger cities in our area as well.</p>', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home and Community', 1262, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1321041713, 0),
(340, '<b>From Katie:</b> I could be having the most stressful day ever, but when I come home, all of that fades away. This is because I know I’m coming home to a man who can make me smile and laugh in a second. Joey has this incredible gift of making everything better, and not just with laughter. It’s the way he’ll surprise me after work for no reason with a bouquet of flowers or show up at my office with lunch. I can’t wait to see him share the same compassion that he shares with me with our future child. I already see this in the way he dotes on our nephew. Joey is more than just my husband. He is my best friend and my other half. I can''t imagine my life without him, and more than anything, I am so excited to see him become a father.\n<p><b>Things I love (from Joey):</b> sports, photography, cooking, sarcasm, movies, art, food trucks, traveling, our dog Danica, and reading.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Joey', 1247, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1334621040, 0),
