(1199, 'People think Alaska and they think cold and snow. Don''t believe the hype. We live in a temperate region in Alaska, just above Seattle. \n\nThe town we live in is in the most SOUTHERN region of Alaska.  Our town is liberal. It''s culturally diverse and it''s amazingly beautiful, with no snow.  Colette''s restaurant is in Alaska, so we live there seasonally. \n\nWe also have a second residence in San Francisco where we split time, so when the restaurant is closed we''re in California.\n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'What? Alaska? ', 834, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358820306, 0),
