(342, 'From Erica: <br />\nBryan is the most caring, creative and generous person. His unique personality goes hand-in-hand with his creativity. The way his creative mind works never ceases to amaze me. He’s a poet and a collage artist. If there is a word in the English language capable of being used with an innovative new twist, Bryan will find it. With his collage art, he''s able to take pieces that don''t look like they could fit together and make a wonderful piece of art. His spontaneous concerts on either piano or guitar are always a treat. He is great at putting things into perspective for me when I’m having a bad day or an irrational moment. He’s taught me that things always happen for a reason, and at the right time. I feel I’m a better person for having Bryan in my life.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Bryan ', 1272, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1321971484, 0),
(343, '<p>Our house is in a quiet suburban neighborhood.  Josh loves the large kitchen to cook everyday meals and try new recipes; he also bakes cheesecakes and strawberry-rhubarb pies. Upstairs, we have a bedroom for guests and another room for our baby. Both bedrooms have a great view of the fenced-in backyard and the woods beyond. Our favorite place is the bonus room where we have our computers, books, and easy chair.</p>\n\n<p>Our neighborhood schools are among the best in the state, and we are surrounded by them. At one end of our street is a cul-de-sac, and at the other is the elementary school. Both the middle school and high school are within walking distance from our home.</p>\n\n<p>Nearby are several parks where we go on walks. One park offers a petting zoo and Fourth of July festivities.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 1302, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1321926719, 0),
