(350, '<p>We were both raised with a strong value of family. We have been blessed to be brought up with loving and supportive parents, as well as siblings to play with, learn from and rely on.<br /><br />Near and far, we''ll go wherever we''re invited to share in family milestones. For one of our anniversaries, we traveled with Monica''s parents to Las Vegas, and this past October, we went with Josh''s parents to San Francisco for a family wedding. We were delighted to celebrate with Josh''s family as both of his grandmothers turned 85 this year.<br /><br />Josh''s parents celebrated their 37th anniversary this year. Dad retired from military service as a lieutenant colonel in the United States Air Force and still works as a plant manager. Mom is a homemaker. Josh''s brother, Zach, recently married. He is a podiatrist and his wife Lauren is a speech pathologist living in North Carolina.<br /><br />After 41 years of marriage, Monica''s parents went on a safari in Kenya and Tanzania. Dad is a neurologist, and Mom is a homemaker. She has two older sisters who live in Virginia. Michelle is a harpist, is married to Seth, and has two wonderful boys and a sheltie. Lauren is a marketing director, is married to Andy, and has a baby daughter and a black Labrador.<br /><br />Friends are family members you get to choose. We have so many cherished friends old and new. They, along with our families, are excited about our decision to adopt. Like us, they look forward to sharing in our joy of welcoming and raising a child.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 1302, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1322102010, 0),
(351, 'Erica''s parents live in the Kansas City area and are only 20 minutes away. Her sister lives in Chicago. We have a large extended family on both sides. On Erica''s dad''s side alone there are 21 first cousins. Many of the relatives on both sides of Erica''s family live within an hour''s drive.\n<p></p>\nBryan''s parents, older brother and one of our nephews \nlive in the suburbs of Chicago. His sister, her husband, a niece and nephew live on a farm in western Illinois. \nHis younger brother and his wife live in Colorado.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About our families', 1272, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1322159645, 0),
