(359, 'We enjoy spending time together as a family, so our free time is mostly spent together- whether we are playing in the yard, building sandcastles on the beach, having a tickle fight on our bed (we are both addicted to the giggles!), or dancing to Backyardigans in the living room. We often go for family walks or bike rides and Eli usually convinces us that we must stop at one of the many parks in our neighborhood. He would swing until dark each night if we let him! We have a large, beautiful backyard that includes a wooden playset (with swings!) and a big sandbox. Our yard is often the location for gatherings with family and friends and Dan is usually found behind the grill cooking ribs, brats, burgers or some other grilled wonder. In the summertime we like to camp and enjoy exploring our state parks. We have a big, comfortably furnished tent (Dan even bought battery powered fans during a heat wave a few summers ago!). Every summer we talk about saving up for a camper, but a part of us just really enjoys the tent experience. This summer Laura went on a salamander hunt with Eli and helped him earn his young explorer patch. We choose to spend a lot of our free time together as a family because we genuinely enjoy being together.  \n\nFamily is very important to us. We live close to much of our family and enjoy Sunday dinners, cook-outs, hay rides, holidays, and the joy of being able to spend time together. Eli loves spending time with his cousins (there are 11 right now). We are grateful that we are able to share the love of an extended family with our children.  \n', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'A Little About Our Family', 1338, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1322943343, 0),
