(364, 'Dear Birthmother,\n\nWe understand how difficult it must be to make a decision about the future of your newborn.  We can provide a home that is safe an secure, and a family that is loving and closely bonded.  We are adopting to extend our family as we had infertility problems after Krista was born and it is our dream to have more children.\n\nWe live in East Tennessee in a great family neighborhood in a basement rancher.  Our immediate family includes Andy, Krista, and I.  Krista is 8 years old and has been waiting for a brother or sister for a long time now.  She is thrilled about the adoption process and is ready to meet her new sibling.  Krista loves gymnastics, cheerleading, basketball and music.  We have two dogs that are adorable and love children.  Their names are Squirt and Autumn.  Squirt is 10 years old terrier mix and Autumn is a 4 year old Greyhound Mix.  There are many children in our neighborhood of all ages.  We have many get-togethers with friends and family at our home which is one of our favorite things to do.  Our family loves to travel to visit family in Buffalo, NY and a family tradition to visit Mickey Mouse in Orlando, FL every year which we enjoy with our nieces and nephews.  Our extended family is just as important to us as our own immediate family.  \n\nAndy and I both work full time with flexible schedules to accommodate and raise our family.  As a family we enjoy game nights, movie nights, school and church activities, friends birthdays, roller skating, skiing, kayaking, volunteer activities for the American Heart Association, and camping together as a family.    \n \nAndy and I both have strong sense of family values that include respect, dignity, integrity, honesty, forgiveness, faith, and love.  We are so excited about the adoption process, and wish to thank you for taking the time to read our letters.\n\nSincerely,\nKathy \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth Parent Letter', 1488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1323319436, 0),
