(370, 'We live in a 4 bedroom basement rancher. Our house has 3 den''s, 2 1/2 baths, kitchen, dining room, and a two car garage. We have a nice size back yard and a great pool. Our second upsairs den is poolside, and we spend time there in the Spring, Summer and Fall. We really enjoy having friends over to grill out and play in the pool. A favorite pool game is water volleyball. Our downstairs den is used mainly in the winter, when we can enjoy the fireplace and large screen TV. \n\nOur neighborhood has a neighborhood watch program and is conveniently located near great schools, shopping, and area parks. We are located close to the lake which makes it convenient when taking the boat out.  \n\nOur house is a home filled with love and fond memories, awaiting many more to come. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 1419, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1323440905, 0),
(371, 'Bradley and Deidre met in a lounge on their college campus. Deidre was first attracted to Bradley’s personality because he was always upbeat and had a great outlook on life. She liked how Bradley knew what he wanted out of life and his clear vision of his goals and dreams for the future. Bradley was attracted to Deidre’s spirit. He says she was very easy to be around and loved to have a great time. The couple dated for three years before becoming engaged and then they were married almost two years after their engagement. Both Bradley and Deidre’s parents were supportive of their marriage', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'How we Met!', 1145, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1323829315, 0),
(372, 'Sabrina writes:\n	OK, well I am married to Dee Dee''s cousin Bill. I first met her at her grandmother’s funeral. I was the one that didn''t know anyone because I just started dating my now husband and it was very awkward to be there. She made me feel at ease and kept checking on me to make sure that I was ok. She went out of her way for me, it just goes to show what a caring person she is. That was about 6 years ago. More recently I met Brad at another cousins wedding. We sat at the same table as them, and we got along so well and had such a great time with them. I think, if I remember correctly, this is when they were just starting their adoption journey. They are incredibly loving and caring people, they have a great relationship with each other, which is amazing with all they have been through trying to have a baby; they want nothing more than to be parents and share their love of life with a son/daughter. I hope that you are truly considering them to raise your baby, I don''t think you could possibly choose better parents for her. On top of that, they have a great family, her parents are moving to be closer to her since they are retired, which I think is amazing!!!! Thank you for asking this and letting me share my thoughts!!! Good luck with your decision, I know it cannot be easy, but rest assured you are on the right track with this couple!!!\nAmanda writes:\n"I''ve known and been friends with Deidre since grade school through high school. Deidre is energetic, fun, and caring and always has a smile on her face. Recently we had Deidre and Brad over for dinner and this was our first time meeting Brad. He is a great guy and those two make a perfect couple! Our daughter is almost 2 and she was drawn to Brad right away and didn''t leave his side all night as he played with her. Deidre brought her stickers and coloring books which she loved. She remembers that day and every once in a while will want to talk about it and say "Dee Dee! (whom she called both Brad and Deidre that night). That night we also talked about their long road to wanting to become parents and I can tell how much they want to parent. They would give your little baby so much love and she would be lucky to have them as parents."\nChristine writes:\n	My family lives just a door down from Brad and Deidre. I feel very fortunate to have the best neighbors in the world. We met them not long after they moved in, many years ago. They are both honest, sweet, fun loving people who truly love each other. My family and theirs has something in common. We tried for years to conceive and were unable. We now have 11 year old twins that we adopted at birth. I have spoken over the course of Brad and Deidre’s journey through adoption as a neighbor and friend. It has been a long road for them and I know that adopting is the one thing they want more than anything in their lives. When you have to wait and be patient for God to bring you the child you know is meant to be your family it is very hard. Believe me I know firsthand. It would be a true blessing for the them and I know they would do anything in their power to give your precious baby all the love, nurturing and support she will need to grow up and be a great person, just like they are. When you wait and pray for something so hard when you finally get it you never take it for granted.\nSarah writes:\n	I''ve known Deidre since we were in Junior High. She and Brad are a wonderful couple. They''re loving and stable with a close knit family. They''re honest, reliable and stable people with hearts of gold. They''ve wanted a child for so long. A child would be so lucky to grow up in their loving home surrounded by aunts, uncles, grandparents, cousins and friends. Brad and Deidre are warm, welcoming, honest, stable, hardworking people who will give their child an amazing upbringing. They want a child so much and have had a difficult road but never lost faith and hope. Please know they will be the best parents for baby. Help them complete their family.\nDonna writes:\n	I am a neighbor of Brad and Deidre, they are some of the nicest people we know. Always smiling when we see them. They always wave when we drive by no matter how busy they are with yard work. Your baby would be one very lucky to be loved by Brad and Deidre. Best of Luck\n\nMore references in the photo section, please check the rest out.  \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'References ', 1145, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1323903221, 0),
(373, 'An Openly Adopted Child''s Legacy\n\nOnce there were two expectant mothers. \nOne carried and cared for you beneath her beating heart \nShe became your Birthmother. \nThe other carried the hope of you within her.\nShe became your Mom. \n\nAs the days passed, and you grew bigger and stronger, \nYour Birthmother knew that she could not give you all you needed after your birth. \nMeanwhile, your Mom was ready and waiting for you. \n\nOne day your Birthmom and your Mom found each other. \n\nThey looked into each other’s eyes and saw a friend. \nYour Birthmom saw the life your Mom could give you. \nYour Mom saw how much your Birthmom loved and cared for you. \n\nThey decided that what you needed was both kinds of love in your life. \n\nSo now you have two families, \nOne by birth, the other by adoption. \n\nAnd you have a home where you can get: \nyour questions answered, \nyour boo boos bandaged, \nyour heartaches soothed, \nAnd much needed hugs. \n\nAnd a place where you can find: \nanswers to your questions, \nyour image in the mirror, \na part of yourself, \nAnd much needed hugs. \n\nTwo different kinds of families \nTwo different kinds of love\nBoth a part of you.\n\n© Brenda Romanchi\n\nThis is my favorite adoption poem. There are some more adoption poems in our photo section.  Please check them out.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'An Openly Adopted Child&#039;s Legacy', 1145, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1323904395, 0),
(374, '  Shelby Jane was born in 2006. She wants to be a real princess or a doctor when she grows up. She is in kindergarten this year. She goes to our parish school. Our whole family loves it there. She has a lot of friends at school and in our neighborhood. She is always telling me things that we need to save for our baby. She is very excited for the day she gets her baby brother or sister. \n   Shelby is very loving and she is always happy to be with other children, especially her cousins. She is very close with her Grandparents and looks forward to spending as much time with them as she can. We are so looking forward to seeing her develop a bond with her new sister or brother. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Shelby', 1591, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332856311, 0),
(375, 'Shelby likes taking ballet. She enjoys soccer and t-ball. She likes to swim and takes lessons at the YMCA. She loves to play dress up. Her favorite movies are anything Disney Princess, Hocus Pocus, Megamind, and Despicable Me. Her favorite toys are Barbies, Little people, Disney Princess, her American girl doll. At home her blanket is still rather close, he is pretty beat up after all these years, but she has told me she is never selling him. She loves to play with the neighbor girls. She likes to read books and is doing well in her reading. She enjoys school and her friends there. She loves her family and always likes to see them. Her favorite TV shows are cartoons of course, Billy the Exterminator, and Once Upon a Time.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Interests of Shelby', 1591, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1323977295, 0),
(376, '   Bob’s mother passed away 2 years ago. We miss her dearly. His father and step-mother live in California, we love to see them when we can, and have many phone calls between us to keep up to date on eachothers lives. Bob has 2 brothers  and 2 sister-in-laws in our area, and 2 step-brothers in California. We have one niece in California and one here.  Bob’s grandma is also very involved in our lives. \n   Tasha’s parents live just down the road. We get together with everyone often . Her sister and brother-in-law live down the road. They are expecting a daughter in March.  Her adoptive family is very important to us . We also have a big extended family that we spend a lot of time with. We get together with her birth family on her father’s side. Both our families are very supportive and are  looking forward to a new addition.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 1591, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1352066477, 0),
(377, '      We met at the end of summer 1997, we were married  in Nov. 1998. Our hope had been to start our family right away. God had other plans for us. After eight years we were blessed with  Shelby Jane. When she was two we tried for another child and were unsuccessful. At that time we began to talk about adoption. We prayed on it, discussed it, and met with our social worker. \n        After that first meeting we knew this was the path for us.  We had a conversation in the parking lot after that first meeting and we both just knew.\nWe have lived in our new home since 2008. We love our neighborhood. We live on a corner lot. We have several parks within walking distance. We belong to a Catholic Church and send Shelby to a private school. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 1591, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324066748, 0),
(378, '<p><span style="font-family:''trebuchet ms'', geneva;font-size:small;">Click <a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/1414-DavidElizabeth/1414-DavidElizabeth.html" target="_blank">here</a> to see our official profile book! You can find out LOTS more about us here! </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''trebuchet ms'', geneva;font-size:small;">Contact our agency if you would consider placing your child with us.</span></p>', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 1414, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1371000658, 1),
(379, 'To our child: I don''t know where you are, or when you will arrive in our life. What I do know, is that we already love you so much! You are in my thoughts and prayers every moment, and I can not wait until the day I get to hold you, kiss you, and tell you how much I love you and how much I prayed and hoped for you for so long. Until that day, know that I will be thinking of you often, and loving you more with every breath. Love, Daddy and Mommy\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Letter to our future child', 1145, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324088008, 0),
(380, 'We met in the fall of 2006.  Recognizing that ours was a special relationship, we were introduced to each other’s parents within weeks of our first date.  We believe that God brought us together when he did for a reason.  Sadly Jerry’s father passed away a month after we started dating.  We are grateful that Kiley was able to meet him. \n\nWe each feel that we are blessed to have the other in our lives and we thank God for that.  We are each other’s best friend and we cherish the time we spend together.  We often enjoy walks around the lake near our house, running, biking, playing with our pets, and sitting together for morning coffee before we start our day.   We always manage to have a good time and to make each other laugh no matter where we are or what we are doing.\n\n\n\n\nWe have done some traveling as a couple and we enjoy exploring new places and destinations together.  We are excited to experience these adventures as a family!  We also love to spend time with our friends, whom we consider part of our extended family.  We meet quite often for: children’s birthday parties, barbeques, Halloween and Christmas parties, sporting events, or to just get together.   We treasure these times and look forward to introducing our child into the group of children that are becoming fast friends due to their parents being such longtime friends.', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 1679, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324238445, 0);
