(381, 'We are blessed to have such an amazing and supportive family. It is wonderful for us that our families get along so well.  Our parents and siblings are thrilled that we have chosen adoption and are looking forward to spoiling their next grandchild, niece or nephew.\n\nOur parents get along very well and like to spend time together. Our mothers like to chat over a cup of tea when they visit.\n		\nWe are very close with Kiley’s brother and his wife.  We are able to visit with them a few times each year at holidays and during our annual family vacation.\n\nJerry’s twin brother recently got married! His wife brought two girls to the family. We are looking forward to getting to know our two new nieces as well as spending time with his brother’s daughter who we have a close relationship with.\n\nJerry’s older brother lives close by and we are able to spend time with him and his longtime girlfriend at all the major holidays.\n\n', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 1679, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324238653, 0),
(382, 'We live in a small New England town north of Boston.  We are in close proximity to many playgrounds, parks, and state forests. There’s even a river right out back for us to fish or canoe in. Coop loves to jump in there every chance he gets!\n\nAlthough our house is not much to look at from the outside it is very comfy and cozy on the inside. There’s plenty of space to move around in.  The house has a huge backyard with a cool permanent screen house and a custom fire-pit (that Jerry built).  \n\nWe love to spend time out back.  It’s perfect for having coffee and watching the birds, squirrels, chipmunks, groundhogs, deer & other wild animals.\n\nWe build plenty of fires in our fire-pit, and like to make Smores.  It’s especially neat when all the fireflies come out.\n', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our House', 1679, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324239460, 0),
(383, 'Nicholas is 6 ½ years old and is our miracle from God. He is social, funny, makes friends easily and good natured. He is always willing to help someone out, whether it’s a family member, a teacher, a friend, a bug or a dog. He is very musical, enjoys “playing” piano and writing songs. Nicholas is active and likes playing sports, especially baseball, basketball and karate. He loves being outside either at the park or just going for a walk with Grandma/Grandpa. He is sweet, empathetic and always trying to solve a situation just like a super hero! Nicholas is quick thinking and intelligent. Nicholas loves science and experimenting with various equipment like test-tubes and magnifying glass/microscope. “Dr. Nicholas” is always trying to figure out some new science potion to help people with their muscles.  He likes to investigate, is clever, confident and “on the ball”. He enjoys a good joke and has fun with riddles. He knows who he is and is happy with himself. He is very verbal and will engage in long conversations about life and things around him. He is very curious and inquisitive and willing to learn new things all of the time.  \nNicholas is an amazing boy and will be an equally amazing big brother. He is very excited to become one and wants to dress up in his “tuxedo suit and dapper shoes” when he meets her or him. He talks about his new sister/new brother and how he will take care of her or him. He can’t wait to feed her the bottle, help put on his clothes, take her out for a walk, and have him sleep in his room. We give thanks to God every day for Nicholas. He is a true and bright light in our family that is meant to be here. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Nicholas', 1585, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324247023, 0),
(384, 'We have two dogs and a cat.  Their names are Jake, Dexter, and Tooter.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Pets', 1451, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324262034, 0),
(385, '<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/kmcnutt/TheMcNutts-29.jpg" alt="" width="218" height="327" /><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/kmcnutt/Kristies_Favorite_Things_001_crop.jpg" alt="" width="264" height="365" /></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT KRISTIE', 1451, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1324262435, 0),
(386, 'Our home is in a quiet neighborhood that is filled with young families. We just built our dream home in 2009. It is a two-story brick home with lots of room and we can not wait until it is filled with the happy sounds of a child. The back yard is a nice size and has plenty of room for a swing set. We also live close to an elementary school and a couple of parks. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Our Home', 1434, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324265924, 0),
(387, 'Dear Birth family,  \n        Love brought us together and love is the reason we want to adopt again. We know it is also the reason you are considering adoption for your baby. Life is a precious gift and we honor you for choosing it. We have been blessed with children both biologically and by way of adoption, and we eagerly anticipate adopting again. Our full welcome letter is on our photo page.\n         Thank you again for looking at our profile. We pray that you will have comfort as you plan for your baby''s future. You can rest assured that should you choose us, your little one will be surrounded by LOTS of LOVE and FAMILY. And your baby will always know how very special you are!\n         Sincerely,\n        Debbie and Mark\n\n  We have adopted via Friends In Adoption Agency, Catholic Guardian Society and Home Bureau, and Adoption Star. We are open to using our attorney or an adoption agency for an adoption- whichever you feel more comfortable with.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth family letter', 1300, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1354804051, 0),
(388, 'Bill was born in August of 1973. He was raised in a loving home with his younger sister, Carrie. As a child, he attended Catholic grade school and went on to public high school. Bill earned a degree in communications from Cleveland State.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Bill', 1321, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324563851, 0),
(389, 'My name is Ron and I am 40 years old. I am a middle school reading teacher and soccer coach. I was born and raised in Tennessee and have lived here my whole life. I have one sister and one brother. I am the middle child. I am very family oriented and love to spend time with my beautiful wife of 17 years. I love to watch and play football and soccer. My wife and I are TSU season ticket holders and attend Tennessee Titans games as often as we can.\n\n \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT RON', 1644, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324567665, 0),
(392, 'Jessica and I currently live in a 4 bedroom/2 bathroom single family home with a two car garage in a privately gated village within one of Pasco County’s master developments.  The master development is made up over various villages of middle to upper class families.  It has 4 clubhouses that offer gyms, basketball courts, tennis courts, volleyball courts, indoor racquet ball, pools, and play grounds.  Each of the clubhouses also provides social clubs and activities for their residents of all ages.  \n\n\nThe master development also has 2 public elementary schools, 1 middle school, and 1 high school.  A new Community College campus is underway to open in 2014 adjacent to the high school.  At the entrance of the master development, there is a Pasco County fire station within 3 miles from the house.  Additionally, a new hospital will be opening in late 2012 5 miles from the house.  \n\n\nWe also live within 8 miles of Jessica''s mom and father. Jessica''s mother is currently retired and hopes to one day be able to care for our child as opposed to daycare. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 1699, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1324940479, 0),
