(410, 'Adoption has been to us an act of love, faith and perseverance. My husband and I began our journey 10 years ago when we decided to adopt. Our decision came from our love and desire for children. We have always wanted children and talked about it often when we were dating.\n\nPeople say ‘God’s time is the best’. This is so true, when on a blessed day in December 2002; we received a call about a baby boy. We were going to be parents and our life changed for the better. Having the opportunity to parent our son has been an incredible, sensational experience. While this was a joyous time for us, we thought about our son’s birth parents and continue to think about them everyday, everyday. What an honor they placed upon us…allowing us to parent their baby.  We are so thankful for their decision. When discussing his adoption story with him, we always convey to our son how much his birth parents loved and sacrificed for him. They have shown an incredibly selfless act of love to our son and us. \n \nGrowing as a family through adoption has been an incredible and joyous experience for us. We have met many wonderful people through Logan’s adoption process, from the hardworking social workers to his foster parents.  We had so much trouble choosing his god parents that he ended up with three sets.  Everyone is excited and supportive of welcoming another child into our family through adoption. \n\nWe know that your journey has just begun and moving forward will also not be easy. With your decision you are giving your baby a chance at a better life and at the same time blessing a couple with the gift of parenthood. In our eyes, you are doing an honorable, loving thing and you will always have a special place in our hearts. We are proud of your strength and courage in making plans to assure your child has the best possible life. We wish you every good thing as you make that decision and continue on your journey. \n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Experience with Adoption', 1737, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1325783723, 0),
(412, 'Education is a value that we share and pass along to Logan. We value education not just in the classroom but through life’s experiences as well.  We love teaching Logan about different cultures and languages through travel. We try to visit different countries at least twice a year. With Logan, we have traveled to Africa, Europe, South American and many Caribbean Islands. \n\nWe love reading, science, and exploring the natural world. We have strong spiritual values based on faith, love and personal responsibility.  This is incorporated in everything we do.  Most importantly, we want Logan and any other child we may have to learn self-love and have a high self-esteem.  We believe these are the greatest gifts we can pass to them.  It will help them overcome challenges they may face during their lives.  We teach Logan our values, guide him through school and model respect for others.  However, we want him to discover who he is and what he \nwants to do with his life. Our family motto is \n“We do what we have to so we can do what we want to do.”  He can accomplish anything he wants as long as he works for it. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Parenting and Values ', 1737, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1325347476, 0),
(413, 'We thank you for your time and consideration. We wish you well as you make your plans.\n\n\nYou may call us toll free at 1-888-678-1433 or email us at jeffandnana.adopting@gmail.com\n\n\nYou can also contact our agency birthmother social worker-- Ellen at Catholic Charities at 410-659-4032 or toll free at 1-877-677-9524. she can also be reached via email at decision@cc-md.org. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact information', 1737, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1325224136, 0),
