(432, '<p><strong>Honesty</strong>: We are truthful with each other at all  times. Your child will know his or her story, and that story will be a  treasured part of our family’s history.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Integrity</strong>: We will honor our agreement with you  regarding openness and ongoing contact. With your permission, we would  like to stay in touch with you throughout your child’s life.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Respect</strong>: We communicate respectfully, even when we  disagree. We do not yell, and we don’t criticize and belittle each  other. Your child will be part of a respectful, loving family.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Learning</strong>: We value education and learning in all its  forms. We both have advanced degrees in our fields, and we believe that  learning opportunities exist all around us. Your child will have access  to excellent educational opportunities and will be encouraged to reach  his or her potential.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Community</strong>: We are active participants in our diverse  community, singing in choirs, participating in our church and  neighborhood, and doing volunteer work. Your child will be an integral  part of our community and will have an opportunity to make friends and  connect with others through community activities.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Acceptance</strong>: We live in a diverse neighborhood and  city, and we believe that differences should be valued and celebrated.  Your child will have mentors and friends from a broad range of racial,  ethnic, and cultural backgrounds, and will be fully accepted as a member  of our family by our extended family, friends and community.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Stability</strong>: We both have secure, flexible jobs, and  we live well within our means. Our marriage is stable and secure, and we  own our home. Your child will be part of a stable family and will have  many opportunities to learn and grow.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Values', 1704, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1325953394, 0),
(433, 'Bill is an avid traveler. He enjoys visiting different places to discover their secret treasures. Bill has been to many places in Europe and South America. An outdoor enthusiast describes him well. He enjoys biking, hiking, sailing, skiing, and running. Each year Bill and his dad participate in the MS Peddle to the Point. He and his dad take their bicycles on a 150 mile ride to raise money for individuals with multiple sclerosis. Bill dreams of owning his own sailboat, but for now he and Holly are able to enjoy sailing on Lake Erie with close friends. Whether it''s cold or warm, Bill just loves to be outdoors enjoying the fresh air and the world around him.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Interests of Bill', 1765, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1329094729, 0),
(434, 'Holly is a "social butterfly". She enjoys spending time with family and friends. Holly has a passion for children and this comes through in her teaching. When away from school, she enjoys creating homemade meals and baking yummy desserts and breads. In warm weather, she loves taking on the outdoors, whether it be running, hiking, or relaxing at the pool. In colder weather, she enjoys watching old movies and playing board games. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Interests of Holly', 1765, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1329094815, 0),
(482, '<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_7620.JPG" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></p>\n<p>Alex is a natural athlete. He is 12 years old and in the 7th grade. He''s played travel hockey in Canada and plans to continue to play where ever we live. Aside from sports he is the kindest most gentle boy you will ever know. When we brought Faith home family and friends had to fight Alex for a chance to hold her. To this day he totes her around and cuddles with her while watching movies. When we told him we wanted to adopt again he said "That''s awesomely  wonderful!"</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_7647.JPG" alt="" width="215" height="323" /></p>\n<p>Our high spirited Nicholas is 10 years old and in the 5th grade. He has an incredibly energetic and intense personality. He''s so smart and driven that he''s doing 7th grade work right along with his older brother. As you can see in the picture, when he sees something he finds interesting he can focus with such effort the whole world seems to stop. When he plays a sport he gives everything he has. He doesn''t know how to do anything half hearted, including loving his family. He never lets any of us part from him without a hug and an "I love you". He even gets up with his dad at 5 am just to say goodbye.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_7743.JPG" alt="" width="318" height="212" /></p>\n<p>Jackson is our free spirit. He never follows the crowd. We can''t go anywhere without checking to make sure he is still with us. He has a true artistic personality with such a gentle heart. The other day he was playing near a group of kids that kept running through his creation of blocks. He never got mad or lashed out. He just kept rebuilding. When he plays baseball he likes to etch out drawings in the sand with his bat before his turn. He recently surprised us all with his new found talent and passion for playing catcher on his baseball team. Jackson''s vibrancy and passion ensures everyone always loves to be around him!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_7678.JPG" alt="" width="206" height="309" /></p>\n<p>Our darling Cooper is irresistible. Everyone falls in love with him instantly. His smile melts your heat and his big blue eyes can get him anything he wants. Cooper is 6 years old and in the first grade. He enjoys doing anything his brothers and sister are doing. It doesn''t matter if it''s football, baseball, basketball, hockey, soccer, Lego''s, artwork or riding his bike. He will enjoy it all just as long as he has one of his brothers or his sister by his side. His hugs and kisses are given away freely and he says "I love you" every fifteen minutes. He is the most lovable kid!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_7434.JPG" alt="" width="201" height="303" /></p>\n<p>Faith is a bit of a spit fire. She knows what she wants and she knows how to get it. I am so excited to watch all that energy and strong will as we direct it into the right direction so she will someday be a strong Christian woman. She is the sparkle in her brothers eyes. I never thought that four boys could love a little girl so much. They carry her around, watch movies with her and even enjoy a good tea party with her from time to time.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_7766.JPG" alt="" width="251" height="376" /></p>', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Our Kids', 1004, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1329097839, 0),
(438, 'I guess we''ll start at the beginning!  Justin was born in Washington DC in 1978.  His older sister Jessica had just turned 5 yrs old when he was born.  Justin grew up in northern VA and lived in the same house until he was 19 yrs old.  His family moved to central Florida at that time and they all still live there today.\n\nKim was born in Philadelphia, PA in 1980 as the youngest of 3 girls.  She lived in Delaware until she was 12 yrs old, when her family moved to south Florida where they all still live today.\n\nWe met in March of 1998 in Deerfield Beach, Florida.  Both of us were guests at a wedding.  Justin was a sophomore in college and Kim was a senior in high school.  Justin can still remember seeing Kim for the first time.  She was wearing a pretty flowered dress and holding a basket of wedding programs.  Kim remembers thinking Justin was so cute!  We began dating from that day and dated for almost 2 years.  We then both finished college and Justin was commissioned into the Air Force.  He traveled extensively throughout the country and to the middle east.\n\nIn 2005, we crossed paths again and knew we were meant to be together.  We got married in July of 2006 and God richly blessed our wedding day with the outpouring of love from our family and friends.  \n\nSince then we have lived in several states due to Air Force assignments and moving for graduate schools.  Justin also separated from the Air Force in 2009 to become a full-time law student.  He recently graduated law school and will soon begin work in legal council at the federal government level.  \n\nWe are best friends, partners, and teammates.  We are so grateful to the Lord for blessing us with each other and placing us in beautiful families.  We are so excited to become parents as we have wanted to add children to our family since we married.  We aren''t perfect, but we serve a God who is, and we''ll do everything in our power to ensure that our children grow up with the assurance that God loves them, we love them, and that you love them.\n\nThanks for taking the time to get to know us a little bit more and reading our story. :)\n\nKim and Justin\n', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our story', 724, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1338581833, 0),
(439, '<p><span style="color:#ffffff;">Waiting Family Ready to Adopt</span></p>\n<h2><span style="color:#ffffff;">We want to adopt a child</span></h2>\n<h3><span style="color:#ffffff;">Hopeful Adoptive Parents</span></h3>\n<h2><span style="color:#ffffff;">Unplanned Pregnacy </span></h2>\n<h3><span style="color:#ffffff;">Place my baby</span></h3>\n<p> </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Hopeful Adoptive Parent', 59, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1326223706, 0),
(440, '<h1>Are you a birth mother with an adoption plan or looking for some great parents for you new born?</h1>\n<p>We hope that you are doing what is right for you. We hope you are considering parenting. But if you know that is not for you we have. We hve prepred to be parents for many years now. </p>\n<h2>We hope you look at our parent profile here on parentfinder and that we will be a great match for your baby.</h2>\n<p>We want to make sure you know there are options other than abortion. Wether you choose to parent or choose adoption we support your decsion. </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth Mother seeking family - We are ready to adopt', 62, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1327010116, 0),
(441, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/1789-rmpc78/1789-rmpc78.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Rachael and Kevin''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 1789, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1326432276, 1),
(442, 'Dear Birthparents,\n\n \nAs I begin this letter, I am thinking of you and the decision you have made about the future of your baby. It takes very special people to choose the path of adoption.  You are unselfish and considerate because you have thought about what is best for your baby, and how much people like me would love a baby.  If you feel I am the person you’d like to raise your baby, please be assured that your baby will be very much loved and cared for.  I will always be grateful to you, and you will always hold a special place in my heart.  Whatever led you to choose adoption, it is important that you know deep in your heart that your baby will be loved very much and all his/her needs will be met.  Your baby will be our baby in every way.  I will always think of you and let our child know that you are very special people.\n \n\nWhen the time comes, I will tell our baby about you and the adoption process.  If there are specific thoughts and feelings that you’d like me to share about you with our child, or if you’d like to know specific things about me, please let me know by sharing those thoughts through letters or telephone calls to the case worker.\nBecause I have to work, I have already arranged for a very reliable friend to provide day care.  She has her own in-home daycare and is wonderful with children.  She is also a very special person in many ways.  She was adopted and because of her experience is able to relate to adopted children in a unique way. \n \nIf the things I’ve shared about myself make you feel that I would be the best person to become your child’s mother, please know that I will work every day to prove worthy of your trust. \n \n\nPatiently waiting parent,\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birthmother Letter', 1581, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1326484363, 0),
(443, '<h1><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:large;">our new nursery</span></strong></h1>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'our house', 1796, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1326574115, 0),
(444, 'Gracias por su interés en nosotros como familia. Adoptar un/una bebé es algo que hemos querido hacer por muchos años, y estamos muy emocionados a empezar. \n\n\nSomos una pareja joven que quiere ser padres por medio de adopción. Ya somos casados por 8 años y no podemos creer que ha pasado tan rápido. No tenemos hijos todavía, pero queremos dar a un bebé una vida llena de amor y seguridad. Tenemos una familia quien nos apoya con la decisión de adoptar, y también están muy emocionados con la posibilidad.\n\n\nVivíamos en Bolivia por dos años, trabajando como voluntarios con Cuerpo de Paz. Ahí aprendimos español, y nos enteremos sobre la cultura Hispana/Latina. Desde ese tiempo, ha sido un gran parte de nuestra vida, y español y la cultura Latina sigue siendo importante para nosotros. También quisiéramos que la cultura y el idioma sea importante en la vida de nuestro bebé.\n\n\nSomos una pareja flexible, paciente, y que sabe reír. Queremos criar un/una bebé con amor, confianza y con oportunidades educaciónales, y que conozca lugares diferentes. Esperamos que Usted nos considera si está pensando en adopción para su bebé. Sería un gran honor. \n\n\nEn este sitio tenemos fotos que pueda mirar para conocernos un poco mejor. También que sienta cómoda a llamar si quiere más información. Nuestro número de teléfono es 410-714-3723.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'EN ESPANOL', 1395, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1328061799, 0),
