(459, 'Fardin and I both put ourselves through college and although we value the experience, we want our children to be able to focus on school. That is why we have created a college fund for Roya and plan to do so for all our children.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'EDUCATION IS A PRIORITY FOR US', 1846, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1327971806, 0),
(458, 'We had always hoped for a large family but shortly after we were married we found out that conceiving would be difficult for us.  After numerous fertility treatments we were blessed with our daughter, Roya, in 2006.  We have enjoyed every minute with her, and nothing would make us happier than to have another child, but we know it is not possible for us to add to our family biologically.  There are wonderful adoption stories on both sides of our families so it seemed like a natural choice.\n\nRoya was our first miracle and if we are lucky enough to adopt a child, he or she will be our second miracle.\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR HOPE FOR ANOTHER MIRACLE', 1846, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1327947488, 0),
