(466, 'Barry’s family has always been close knit. We either talk to or see both of his parents on a weekly basis, if not more than that. Luckily we live in an area that keeps us fairly close. We realize this might not always be the case so we make the most of it now. We do a lot together like golfing, fishing or family dinners. It seems there is always some family get-together happening whether its Sunday dinner, a birthday, a holiday, or just because. We love hearing the giggles and squeals of Owen and his 9 cousins playing together (who are all very close in age). Barry’s family is also always there to help in whatever way they can.', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family Time', 1883, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1328509006, 0),
(467, 'Christmas is our favorite holiday. We added several new traditions with Owen''s arrival to our family. Each Christmas Eve we let Owen open one present and this present is always pajamas. Owen also gets a new ornament each year for our tree. These ornaments are a wonderful reminder of each Christmas Owen has been part of our family. Each year we also carve pumpkins for Halloween to put out on our porch. This year we changed things up. We made Angry Bird pumpkins by completely painting them black, red, or yellow and then gluing on eyes, eyebrows, and beaks we’d cut out of cardstock. We even made a Naughty Pig pumpkin.\n\n \nWe have a tradition on Sunday evening where either Barry or I will make a family treat. We''ve made such things as banana bread, cookies, cakes, brownies just to name a few. Owen loves to help by pouring in the ingredients. Sometimes we will invite one of Barry''s siblings or his parents over to come enjoy it with us. We also try to make birthdays extra special. The night before his party Rebecca decorates the dining area with a theme Owen helps choose. His reaction the next morning is always priceless. Rebecca also makes a mini cake just for him. It’s a tradition we want to carry on with all our future children.', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Traditions', 1883, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1328509043, 0),
(468, 'As a family we always try to spend a lot of time together. Sometimes this is just snuggling up to watch a movie, and sometimes it is going on a drive. We enjoy traveling and seeing new things. Lots of times we will take a day trip to see one of the many scenic or historical areas nearby. We live only an hour or so from Jackson Hole and West Yellowstone. We also travel to Utah quite often since we have family there and we like to visit historical and scenic places there too. Before Owen joined our family, we took a couple trips to California including Disneyland and San Diego. For the longest time, we looked forward to when we would have children to share in these experiences. Last year we took Owen to Disneyland and to the beach for the first time and it was all we had hoped for. We continue to look forward to the new experiences and adventures our family will have. Really it doesn''t matter what we are doing as long as we are together.', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Traveling', 1883, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1328509067, 0),
(469, 'Owen’s birthmother had us come to the hospital to see her and Owen that same day he was born. We instantly fell in love with him the moment we saw him. We have sent email updates with pictures once a month since Owen''s birth. Slowly our adoption has become more open to include annual visits, occasional phone calls, and some chatting using texting or Facebook. \n\nOwen is full of energy. He loves playing outside where he can run and explore. He loves taking baths and playing in the dirt (good thing they go hand-in-hand). Owen is big into trains, space, superheros, and Legos. It''s not unusual to find either one of us on his bedroom floor building a train track or counting down a rocket launch with him.\n\nOwen loves to learn and learns quickly. By age two he could count up to nine and tell us the name of a letter he saw. Currently he is learning to read, and he loves to point out words that he knows as we drive around. \n\nWe have been talking to Owen about being a big brother. We always chuckle at his response when asked if he wants a baby brother or sister; he says wants a baby sister because they have long hair. We know he would equally love to have a baby brother. We have also read to him a book about being a new big brother. He loves the part where it talks about holding and singing to the baby. Owen has always been an affectionate boy, loving to give and receive hugs and kisses. He will be a great big brother when the time comes.', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Owen', 1883, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1328509132, 0),
(470, 'We were both raised in small farming communities. Our mothers are both educators and fathers have both worked in farming. AJ has two older siblings, one brother and one sister. Kim has two older siblings.  We were both raised in close and caring catholic families, AJ raised on a farm and Kim in a small town.  We both remember spending holidays with our extended family and enjoy getting together with family as much as possible. \n	There are special occasions that we share with our families other than the usual holidays.  Both of us have hometown fairs that we like to attend and every February we join many friends and family at the state Knights of Columbus Bowling tournament.  We enjoy taking small trips with our families as much as possible even if it is just a day trip.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Families', 1894, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1328550942, 0),
