(474, '            My name is Victoria and I am twenty-two years old. I was in the same difficult position that you are in right now...As I opened [their profile], I took the deepest breath I could possibly take and began to read about the family. As I was reading I remember having such a comforting and happy feeling. Heather and Jason and their four boys looked so happy and I could tell that they were a family that had complete trust in God. This was it! This was the family that God had chosen for my baby girl...[Before giving birth] Heather came all the way from Washington to spend the week with me. We walked and talked for hours. We were instant friends. Heather and I became very close in that week and we shared many stories. We made new memories as well...Signing my rights over as [Faith''s] mother was the most difficult thing I''ve ever done...Heather made sure to let me know that I would always be a part of [her] life and that Faith will always know that I chose adoption for her because I loved her so much and wanted her to have everything she could ever dream of...  Heather and Jason have kept every promise to me they have ever made... They have given me so much love and I know without a doubt that they truly care for my well being and they consider me apart of the family...The first time I was able to see Faith...since I left the hospital, I was reassured that I had made the right choice...Everything had fallen into place. Heather and Jason were Mom and Dad and I was Aunt Victoria. Faith was so comfortable with her family and such a bright happy little girl. She has a wonderful life. This family is so amazing and there aren''t enough words or paper in this world to describe the love and adoration I have for them. In my eyes they are the perfect family. Heather and Jason are always there when I need them with love, advice, and support. They have had a huge part in my healing process and they remind me often that Faith will know who I am and why I chose adoption for her. They are both loving, caring, Christian people. They truly care about my feelings and they help me to make it through each day.\n            Birth Mom, I am writing to tell you that this process is not easy, but each day that passes gets a little easier. I feel a sense of strength that I have never known before.\n                                       Victoria', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Letter from Birthmom', 1004, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1328740428, 0),
