(483, '<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_5366.jpg" alt="" width="382" height="255" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Victoria is Faith''s birth mom. Words can''t express the love that we have for her. She is a very special part of our family. Our relationship started out very slow and cautious on both parts but after a while we have figured out the kind of relationship that we want for each other. Sometimes we go for long periods of time without talking, other times we spend time texting and every once in a while we enjoy taking on the phone. We have enjoyed several visits since Faith was born. Those visits are filled with both laughter and tears which always brings us closer together. We have a great appreciation for the gift she has given us and for the strength she has. We continue to encourage her to set goals for herself and one at a time achieve those goals. We are so excited for the life that she is living and the love that we share for each other.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_5171.jpg" alt="" width="356" height="238" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>            My name is Victoria and I am twenty-two years old. I was in the same difficult position that you are in right now...As I opened [their profile], I took the deepest breath I could possibly take and began to read about the family. As I was reading I remember having such a comforting and happy feeling. Heather and Jason and their four boys looked so happy and I could tell that they were a family that had complete trust in God. This was it! This was the family that God had chosen for my baby girl...[Before giving birth] Heather came all the way from Washington to spend the week with me. We walked and talked for hours. We were instant friends. Heather and I became very close in that week and we shared many stories. We made new memories as well...Signing my rights over as [Faith''s] mother was the most difficult thing I''ve ever done...Heather made sure to let me know that I would always be a part of [her] life and that Faith will always know that I chose adoption for her because I loved her so much and wanted her to have everything she could ever dream of...  Heather and Jason have kept every promise to me they have ever made... They have given me so much love and I know without a doubt that they truly care for my well being and they consider me apart of the family...The first time I was able to see Faith...since I left the hospital, I was reassured that I had made the right choice...Everything had fallen into place. Heather and Jason were Mom and Dad and I was Aunt Victoria. Faith was so comfortable with her family and such a bright happy little girl. She has a wonderful life. This family is so amazing and there aren''t enough words or paper in this world to describe the love and adoration I have for them. In my eyes they are the perfect family. Heather and Jason are always there when I need them with love, advice, and support. They have had a huge part in my healing process and they remind me often that Faith will know who I am and why I chose adoption for her. They are both loving, caring, Christian people. They truly care about my feelings and they help me to make it through each day.<br />            Birth Mom, I am writing to tell you that this process is not easy, but each day that passes gets a little easier. I feel a sense of strength that I have never known before.</p>\n<p>                                                                                  Victoria</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_5526.jpg" alt="" width="383" height="256" /></p>\n<p> </p>', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Faith&#039;s Birthmom', 1004, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1329098333, 0),
(484, '<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/IMG_6315.jpg" alt="" width="333" height="222" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Our home is a retreat from the rest of the world. A place that we can relax and just be together. We enjoy having family movie nights where we all snuggle together on our huge couch. We have fire pits in our secluded backyard where we roast marshmallows and sing praise songs. We have a little sitting area in our master bedroom where Heather has her morning coffee and enjoys a good book. This is also where as a couple we hash out the days events after the kids are all tucked into bed. This quiet place is where Alex had his first cup of (decaf) coffee as he and his dad talked man to man about life and it''s ups and downs. This is a special place where it is quiet and anyone can come to have some alone time or one on one time with someone special.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/outnumbered/living_room_1.JPG" alt="" width="370" height="208" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Often all four boys will be sprawled across the living room floor with Faith bounding over their bodies while they set up a mini figurine city from one side of the room to the other. Other times they are setting up a family football game in the yard while Jason builds a fire for an evening of marshmallows and singing. Many afternoons they ride their bikes and scooters together with Faith tagging along in her little motorized 4-wheeler and Alex running his remote car between everyone trying not to get hit. We love to be together and want so much to share this with another little one.</p>', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 1004, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1329099393, 0),
