(502, '<p><strong>Tim and i are hoping to adopt a child via Private or Independent Adoption which means you, the expectant parent, select *us* to become the adoptive mother and father of your little one versus going through an agency (where you give the agency your little one and then the agency places the little one with the adoptive mother and father).  In Private adoption YOU directly select us and choose us.</strong><br /><br /><strong>Tim and I are telling everyone we know about our desire to adopt an infant – because 50% of adoptions happen through word of mouth!  That’s why we’re calling the expectant mother who picks us our guardian angel ♥ – we know you’re connected to us through friends or relatives or acquaintances.</strong><br /><br /><strong>In Private adoption, we’d ensure that our expectant mother would have an attorney (whose fees we would pay for).   We will have an attorney too, who will work with your attorney to ensure that we follow all the the state laws and everyone’s rights are protected.  For more information about Private Adoption, the<a href="http://ffpa.org/staticpages/index.php?page=FAQ" target="_blank"> FAQ page of the Families for Private Adoption group</a> has great information.  Here''s a link for the Families for Private Adoption <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Families-for-Private-Adoption/160143610688351" target="_blank">Facebook page.</a> </strong></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Private or Independent Adoption', 1865, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1347116069, 0),
