(515, 'We met in the fall of 2006.  Recognizing that ours was a special relationship, we were introduced to each other’s parents within weeks of our first date.  We believe that God brought us together when he did for a reason.  Sadly Jerry’s father passed away a month after we started dating.  We are grateful that Kiley was able to meet him. \n\nWe each feel that we are blessed to have the other in our lives and we thank God for that.  We are each other’s best friend and we cherish the time we spend together.  We often enjoy walks around the lake near our house, running, biking, playing with our pets, and sitting together for morning coffee before we start our day.   We always manage to have a good time and to make each other laugh no matter where we are or what we are doing.\n\nWe belong to a terrific Christian church which has an extraordinary children''s program and we look forward to introducing our little one to everyone there. We firmly believe that God intended for us to grow our family through adoption and we feel so fortunate to have this opportunity to begin our family.  ', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About us', 1679, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1330019545, 0),
(516, 'Our parents get along very well and like to spend time together. Our mothers like to chat over a cup of tea when they visit.\n        We are very close with Kiley’s brother and his wife.  We are able to visit with them a few times each year at holidays and during our annual family vacation.\n    \nWe are blessed to have such an amazing and supportive family. It is wonderful for us that our families get along so well.  Our parents and siblings are thrilled that we have chosen adoption and are looking forward to spoiling their next grandchild, niece or nephew.\n    \nJerry’s twin brother recently got married! His wife brought two girls to the family. We are looking forward to getting to know our two new nieces as well as spending time with his brother’s daughter who we have a close relationship with.        \n\nJerry’s older brother lives close by and we are able to spend time with him and his longtime girlfriend at all the major holidays.\n\nYour child will be able to play with cousins close to his or her own age.  Kiley’s brother has three young children, and even though her family lives in Florida, we speak to them almost daily and visit them numerous times throughout the year.  \nJerry’s family is local, which makes visits easy.  His niece Kayla loves to sleep over our house.   \n\nWe also enjoy attending our annual family reunions.  Everyone in our extended family is loving and supportive and they are all excited to welcome the newest member.', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family', 1679, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1330019691, 0),
