(527, 'A Baby Step Adoption, Adoption Associates, LLC\nBarbara Casey, Esquire\n527 Elm Street\nReading, PA 19601\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'A Baby Step Adoptions', 2121, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1330393524, 0),
(528, '<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">We’re best friends. Whether we’re trekking around Disney World or running an errand to the grocery store or Lowes, we love spending time together. Laughter is an important part of our life, and it’s our sense of humor, along with strong family roots, and faith that has seen us through good times and bad. We’ve been friends for 19 years and during this time, we’ve built a strong foundation of trust, appreciation, mutual respect, and love. Together we make a great team!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">Our fondest memories are of the times we spend together. We like to travel but we also enjoy just being outdoors, especially in our backyard— grilling, gardening, or relaxing in the hammock or on our deck. Whenever we get the chance we like to take local “adventures”— just by jumping in the car to explore. We are continually amazed at the interesting things to see and do in the area. We were married on a beautiful autumn day in 2005. Our wedding was a celebration of love, family, and friends. We honeymooned in Disney World since Elizabeth is a big fan, and BJ had never been. We thought it would be a great place to celebrate the start of our life together.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 2160, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1341277420, 0),
(529, '<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">Our family is our foundation. We both grew up in families that taught us to love unconditionally and cherish life. Elizabeth was born and raised in a small town in Pennsylvania and her mom still lives in the same house that she and her older sister grew up in. Elizabeth was very fortunate to have her grandmother live with them until she was 13 years old and she cherishes those memories. BJ was born and raised in a small town Pennsylvania too. He has nine brothers and sisters so the house was always “active”. BJ’s mom still lives in the house where all the children grew up and where they all return for special events and holidays. BJ remains close to his mother, nine siblings, seven in-laws, and 17 nieces and nephews. Family traditions are very special to us and we look forward to passing them onto our child. Our families are very important to us and we spend a lot of time with them. All our family and friends are very excited that we’re adopting and can’t wait to know and love this very special child.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family', 2160, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1341277592, 0),
(836, '<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">I first met Elizabeth in a grad school class and was instantly attracted to her sweet smile, her easygoing personality, and sense of adventure. She loves to plan fun trips and vacations for us ranging from historic treks through New England, cruises to the Caribbean, adventures through the Southwest and of course, return trips to Disney World. Elizabeth is my confident, best friend, and the love of my life. She has a passion for family. She is caring and nurturing and has dreamt of being a Mom as long as I have known her. Her love for our nieces and nephews is overwhelming and I have no doubt she will be a wonderful mother. I consider Elizabeth the cornerstone of the family. She is the energy that fuels our marriage and I can’t image being without her.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Elizabeth by BJ', 2160, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1341281293, 0),
(531, 'We married in 2010, but we met over 25 years ago.  We are truly living an amazing love story.  We met after a football game in junior high.  It''s funny how some moments are permanently etched in your memory.  The chill in the fall air, the excitement and energy from a winning game, the butterflies in your stomach from meeting someone new when you least expect it.  This was one of those moments and from then on we were each other''s best friend. It''s like there was a bigger plan.  After much heartache, we split when the decision was made for Lisa to go off to college and Don joined the Marine Corps.  Before Don left for the Marine Corp he left a letter on Lisa''s windshield.  The letter expressed Don''s desire to be a Marine and his support of Lisa''s success at school.  He promised that one day we would be back together even if it was many years in the future.  The funny thing about the letter is that he wrote on it "you better have this letter 20 years from now at our reunion!"\nTwenty years later, Lisa is a school administrator.  Don''s daughter enrolls in her school.  Lisa helps her get accepted into a specialized program and never tells the daughter that she was her father''s first love.  A mutual friend finds out that Lisa helped Don''s daughter get into the program and Don contacts Lisa to thank her.  Next thing you know Don and Lisa go to their high school reunion together and its 20 years later!  Imagine Don''s surprise when Lisa showed him the letter that was written to her 20 years earlier!  It''s now one of their most cherished possessions.  \nWithout sounding too sappy, there wasn''t a day that went by where we didn''t think of each other.  We have a strong faith in that some things are just meant to be.  We are so thankful that we have been blessed to be together.  It just had to be the right time and the right place.  God really does work in mysterious ways!  We have so much love to offer and such an appreciation for life and family to share.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 2043, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1330404110, 0),
(530, '<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">We live in a warm and friendly home that is bright and welcoming. We searched to find just the right house to start our family and the moment we walked in, we knew we were home. We have three bedrooms, two bathrooms along with a living room, dining room, kitchen, and finished attic. </span><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">The rooms are spacious with lots of room to play and grow.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">One of our very favorite parts of our home is our yard. It''s fenced in and lush with plants, bushes, and a huge vegetable garden. We have a lovely deck that is fantastic for summer gatherings and barbeques with our family and friends.   </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">Our neighborhood is very kid friendly with quiet streets and lots to do within walking distance. We have two schools, a playground, the public library, and a quaint downtown just a few blocks away. We are close enough to Pittsburgh to enjoy all the city has to offer, but far enough away to enjoy true small town living.  We really love where we live!<br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 2160, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1341278687, 0),
(835, '<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;">The first thing that attracted me to BJ was his sense of humor. He has a quick wit and a knack for always making me laugh. He smiles and laughs easily and he''s easy to be around. I''m in awe of his gentle spirit and patience. He is honest and hard-working and never misses an opportunity to make me feel special. With him, I feel safe and loved.  BJ will be an amazing father some day and has so much to offer a child. He''s devoted to our nieces and nephews. They love to be around their "Uncle BJ." He is my lifelong companion and very best friend. Through it all, he is the person I love going through life with.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About BJ by Elizabeth', 2160, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1341280131, 0),
(532, 'Bubbles for Babies: a virtual event that educates and spreads the good news of adoption\n\n\n\n\n\nAdoption Education Workshops: \n4 part interactive series of workshops that provide education and a chance to dispel myths of open adoption and adoption in general.\n\n ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Events of Catholic Social Service', 74, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1330444879, 0),
(533, '<p><span style="font-size:small;color:#ff0000;"><strong>How we met each other</strong>……</span>  Our dads served on the mission field together as single men, but neither of them guessed that years later, their son and daughter would get married.  But one time when I (Judi) and my parents were going through Wisconsin, my dad decided he’d like to stop in and visit Gary and his family.  It was on that visit that Reuben and I met for the first time.  Our dads weren’t trying to play match-maker, but apparently God was! <img title="Laughing" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/plugins/tiny_mce/plugins/emotions/img/smiley-laughing.gif" border="0" alt="Laughing" />  Six months later, we began courting. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="color:#ff0000;font-size:small;"><strong>Courtship</strong>…… </span>Because of living eight hours apart, we only saw each other about once a month.  The rest of our courtship happened by phone and email.  And we had LONG talks and LOTS of emails! <img title="Smile" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/plugins/tiny_mce/plugins/emotions/img/smiley-smile.gif" border="0" alt="Smile" />  But it worked and ten months later we were happily married—for life!  We do not enter marriage lightly.  We believe that when we said our vows to each other before God, they stand until one of us dies.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size:small;color:#ff0000;">Our married life... </span> We know how to laugh and enter into life’s joys together</strong>… the simple joys of a peaceful walk in the field when the sun is setting, a child’s tiny hand in ours… the “bigger” joys of growing closer to each other, finding new friends, experiencing God’s provision in unexpected ways, and so much more!  <strong>We also have learned by experience how to journey through life’s hard times</strong>—sorrows, losses, and difficulties—and come out richer on the other side.  God has blessed with a deep sense of oneness and we are truly each others’ best friend!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;color:#ff0000;"><strong>Reuben’s description of Judi</strong>: </span> the first thing I noticed about Judi when we met was her <strong>sweet personality</strong>.  She really cares about people, and it shows.  She is a <strong>deep thinker</strong>, and at first I thought she was too serious.  But I learned pretty quickly that she is also <strong>quick to tell a joke or laugh</strong> along with someone else.  She longs to be a mother, to be able to give her love to a child, and I have held her more than once while she cried, wondering when she’ll have that privilege.  <strong>I know she’ll be a great mom!</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;color:#ff0000;"><strong>Judi’s description of Reuben</strong>: </span>Every married woman longs to have her husband be her <strong>best friend</strong>.  I can say without a single doubt that I have found that in Reuben.  He is the most <strong>tender, patient, devoted</strong> husband that I could wish for.  I truly can’t imagine life without him!  He is also <strong>very good with his hands</strong> and can fix about anything.  He is a <strong>good provider</strong>, and is careful to spend money wisely.  He is a tease, and <strong>I love his humor</strong>. <img title="Smile" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/plugins/tiny_mce/plugins/emotions/img/smiley-smile.gif" border="0" alt="Smile" />  Children just naturally gravitate to him, and he, too, longs to have a son or daughter of his own. <strong>I can’t wait to watch him be a dad!</strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size:small;color:#ff0000;">Things that are important to us:</span> 1</strong>) that our home be one where Christ is put first, and that he be glorified in everything we say and do.  <strong>2)</strong> That our children would learn to discern right from wrong, based on God’s Word and character. <strong>3)</strong> That we would protect our children from influences that would lead them away from the Lord.  Among these things are negative friendships, degrading music and reading material, and the television.  <strong>4)</strong> That the lines of communication between us as a couple and us with our children ALWAYS be kept open.  We want to always be close and in touch with our children’s hearts and make ourselves available to them whenever they need us.  <strong>5)</strong> That we as a family would pursue a deep and personal relationship with God, as well as love for the people around us.  We recognize that people are more important than any material possession.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>For months now we have prayed often as a couple for the special lady that is to be the birthmother of our child.  If you choose to give us the priceless gift of your child, then those prayers have been for you. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>May God grant you wisdom &amp; peace in your decision!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Respectfully,                                                                          </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>  Reuben &amp; Judi</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>**To learn more about us by visiting our website: <a href="http://www.bigheartsemptyarms.webs.com/">www.bigheartsemptyarms.webs.com</a></strong></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About us...', 2121, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1331829959, 0),
