(565, 'One of our favorite aspects of our marriage is that we are always laughing. We are easily amused, and we like to be silly together.\n\nWe truly love to spend time together. A typical evening or weekend would start with taking a walk together with our 2 dogs, Rocky and Tucker. Sometimes, Tom will mow the lawn while Jenn plants flowers. We also love to relax at home and watch Sunday afternoon football (Go Chiefs!). We also love to go to baseball games (Go Red Sox!).\n\nAt the same time, we do many things separately. Tom does small photography jobs on the side, while Jenn goes to craft nights with girlfriends.\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 2308, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331651415, 0),
(566, '1. It’s possible to make any house feel like a home.\n2. Books!\n3. Pray for my family.\n4. In order to cook, I just throw a whole bunch of ingredients together and hope it comes out ok.\n5. You can do anything you put your mind to.\n6. Christmas is the best time of the year.\n7. Stay positive, even when things aren’t so good.\n8. Elvis is the king.\n9. Be yourself, no matter how unique or different you are.\n10. Sing from your gut!!\n11. Laugh a lot. Don’t take life so seriously.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Jennifer-isms', 2308, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331220815, 0),
(567, '<p>Tom has a lot of energy, so he likes to take the two dogs for long walks or a hike. He loves photography and catching life moments for families, engaged couples, and weddings. Tacos, hamburgers, pizza, and pancakes are his four main food groups. Music has always played a central role. He plays guitar and drums, and there is always some type of music playing in the house.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1. Flip-flops are always better than socks.</p>\n<p>2. Burgers, pizza and tacos are food groups.</p>\n<p>3. Elvis is not the king. <img title="Tongue out" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/plugins/tiny_mce/plugins/emotions/img/smiley-tongue-out.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" /></p>\n<p>4. Photographs are amazing moments captured.</p>\n<p>5. You’ll never understand what God allows to happen – just trust that there’s a reason.</p>\n<p>6. People and connections can get you a lot of places.</p>\n<p>7. The ocean is incredible. </p>\n<p>8. Bigger is often better.</p>\n<p>9. There is always something to do with your time.  Don’t sit around.</p>\n<p>10. Work hard, play hard.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Tom-isms', 2308, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1338312401, 0),
(568, '<p>One of Jenn''s favorite things to do is curl up with a good book. She loves how her imagination can take her anywhere. Jenn is a complete nerd. Her favorite school subjects were math and science. A few other hobbies she enjoys are singing, gardening, arts &amp; crafts, and Christmas time! Jenn has a big extended family (her mom is 1 of 6 children, and her grandma is 1 of 9 children), and every year we go to the Annual Family Reunion and we overflow a pavilion.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1. It’s possible to make any house feel like a home.</p>\n<p>2. Books!</p>\n<p>3. Elvis is the king.<img title="Tongue out" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/plugins/tiny_mce/plugins/emotions/img/smiley-tongue-out.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" /></p>\n<p>4. Pray for your family.</p>\n<p>5. Cooking is just throwing a whole bunch of ingredients together, hoping it comes out ok.</p>\n<p>6. You can do anything you put your mind to.</p>\n<p>7. Christmas is the best time of the year.</p>\n<p>8. Be yourself, no matter how unique or different you are.</p>\n<p>9. Sing from your gut!!</p>\n<p>10. Laugh a lot. Don’t take life so seriously.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Jennifer-isms', 2308, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1331668347, 0),
