(582, '<p><span style="color: #cc0066;">Education:</span><span> Bachelors in Business and Industrial Engineering</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Occupation:</span><span> Runs Family Business </span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Interests: </span><span>Running, wallyball, rollerblading, tennis, dancing and golf</span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Height:</span><span> 6&rsquo; <br /></span><span style="color: #cc0066;">Eye Color:</span><span> Hazel <br /> </span><span style="color: #cc0066;">Hair Color:</span><span> Sandy Brown</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span>I am sincere and honest, and have a very personable and outgoing personality with a great sense of humor. Our friends and family say that I’m very dependable and a very good listener. I find satisfaction in working hard (at work, at home, or for friends and relatives) and always willing to volunteer my time to help with projects. Halloween is my favorite time of year, with the cool crisp air and the leaves turning colors, but mostly I love dressing up in creative costumes with my family. I love to go all out and decorate the outside of our house for Halloween and Christmas for everyone to enjoy. I love playing with our daughter, Sabrina, and acting like a kid again and making everyone laugh. My favorite vacation spot is Disney World.\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\nRalph comes from a loving family with three siblings, one brother and two sisters who all live in the Cincinnati area. He is the second youngest sibling. Both of Ralph’s parents were loving and caring and happily married for 36 years. He has two nephews and one niece who adore him. Ralph has a Bachelor’s of Science and a Bachelor of Business degrees and uses both of these skills as an entrepreneur of a rental company that has been in the family for two generations. He has a great sense of humor and always puts a smile on everybody’s face. He is a caring and loving person, and always willing to give a helping hand to family and friends for different projects. He is a wonderful father and husband, and enjoys spending quality time with each of them.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Meet Ralph', 2401, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331594824, 0),
(583, 'http://www.ben-and-sue-adopt-wi.com/', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Website', 2405, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331592483, 0),
(584, 'If you are facing an unplanned pregnancy and considering adoption, please consider us to adopt your baby or young child.\n\nWe are truly in awe of your strength and courage to consider adoption. It takes a special person to make such a decision and offer the gift of parenthood to others. We have never been in your shoes, and you not in ours. However, perhaps together, we may be able to turn two very different yet difficult situations into a blessing. It is our promise to you that, should you decide we are the couple you have been searching for, your baby will be loved and nurtured and raised as our own. Yet he or she will always know their very special adoption story and of your love and sacrifice as they grow. We have a completed homestudy and foster-to-adopt license, so you can be assured that we can bring your baby home from the hospital to raise him/her without foster care.\n\nWe can only begin to imagine what a difficult decision you must be facing. It is clear that you love your child enough to do what you feel is best for their future. We have both dreamed of growing our family and feel thankful that we are in a position to pursue our dream together through adoption. We would be honored if you would consider us as adoptive parents for your baby. Thank you for taking the time to learn about us and considering us a part of your adoption journey. \n\nAre you pregnant, please feel free to browse and read about the journey of our lives.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Welcome', 2401, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331594548, 0),
(585, '<p><span style="color: #cc0066;">Education:</span><span> Bachelors in Art</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Occupation:</span><span> Stay at Home Mom and Consultant Graphic and Web Designer </span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Interests: </span><span>Reading,  gardening, decorating, creating flower arrangements, drawing, painting,  running, golfing, cooking, dancing and rollerblading</span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Height:</span><span> 5&rsquo; 5&rdquo;<br /></span><span style="color: #cc0066;">Eye Color:</span><span> Blue <br /> </span><span style="color: #cc0066;">Hair Color:</span><span> Dark Brown (Naturally Curly)</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span>I am a friendly and nice person who loves to laugh and make others laugh. I love to have people around me and enjoy spending many hours playing with our daughter. I am the youngest of eight siblings and enjoy hosting large family gatherings. I enjoy traveling to explore new places and can&rsquo;t wait to share this with our children. I love the beach, playing by the pool and going to Kings Island with our family and friends. One of my favorite pastimes is making crafts and giving them to family and friends. I also love to take photos, draw and paint as you can see throughout this profile of the images I&rsquo;ve creative. I am always trying to come up with creative ideas of crafts for us to create as a family. I am the Daisy Girl Scout Leader for Sabrina''s troup and loving this.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="paragraph-style-1"><span>Patty comes from a family of eight children and is the youngest sibling who all but one live in the Cincinnati area. We get together on a weekly basis and enjoy doing many things as a family. Her parents had a loving marriage for over 25 years and for many years her mother worked in a daycare running the infants room. She is now retired enjoying life with her grandchildren. Patty has four nieces and one great-nephew. She has a Bachelor&rsquo;s of Arts in Graphic and Web Design and loves the freedom to work or stay home with my family. Patty always has a smile for everyone and has a great caring personality that makes people want to be around her. She has a deep passion for family, friends and togetherness. She has taken on the role of motherhood to Sabrina with great pleasure and joy. Patty loves to take many photos and maintains a secure website of our family together for others to enjoy.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Meet Patty', 2401, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331594809, 0),
(586, '<p><span style="color: #cc0066;">Age:</span><span> 5</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Eye Color:</span><span> Brown <br /> </span><span style="color: #cc0066;">Hair Color:</span><span> Brown</span></p><p><span style="color: #cc0066;">Activities:</span><span> Swimming, Dance, Gymnastics, Soccer, T-ball and being a Daisy Girl Scout</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\nSabrina joined our family in 2006 as an infant through adoption and brings us so much joy and happiness. Her adoption is open and we keep in contact with her birthparents and provide a secure website of family photos they can look at anytime. \n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\nSabrina is always smiling and has a very cheerful personality. She adores all of her extended family and is always showing them her love and affection. Sabrina is very outgoing and loves to play with other children. She loves to sing and dance, make friends, play soccer and t-ball at the YMCA, and especially loves to have books read to her. She absolutely loves Kindergarten and can''t wait until next year when she gets to go all day to 1st grade. She is so excited about having a baby brother or sister to play with and become a big sister!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Sabrinas Story', 2401, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331596001, 0),
(587, '<p><span style="color: #cc0066;">Married:</span><span> 10 years</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Family Interests:</span><span> Traveling, Playing Games, Swing and Ballroom Dancing, Playing in Park, Taking Walks, Running 5K''s, Camping, Rollerblading, Visiting with Friends and Family, & Having Fun </span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br />Family Values: </span><span>Family comes first, Faith, Fun, Education, Love and Respect for Others</span><span style="color: #cc0066;"><br /></span><span style="color: #cc0066;">Religion:</span><span> Catholic <br />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span>Our names are Ralph and Patty. We met in 2000 and have been happily married for ten years. We adopted Sabrina, our daughter, in 2006 and she fills our days with wonder and amazement. Our home is located in a suburban neighborhood with a beautiful wooded backyard with a brand new swingset just awaiting more children.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class="paragraph-style-1"><span>We anticipate the joy of adopting a second child in the very near future. We want to share our love, and encourage each of our children to unfold into the person they are each meant to be. We are an active, two-parent family, treasuring the small moments of everyday life, like lullabies and kisses, first steps, and first words. As you will soon see, family and friends are so very important to us and we are a fun loving couple eager to expand our family. We are very family oriented, cooking meals every night together and make a big breakfast every Sunday morning. We love to spend our days together as a family.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\nWe have a loving, committed and supportive relationship of each other. From the beginning we have known that we both want to be parents. We have an \nabundance of love to share and our decision to adopt stems from our history of each being raised with many siblings. While we already have much to be thankful for in life, the addition of your child to our family will be a most welcomed blessing for us. We believe in strong values, quality education and compassion for people. Family is the most precious “possession” a person can have and your child will be wrapped in the unconditional love shared with those already a part of ours. \n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<b>\nOur Family and Friends... </b>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\nWe both have very loving family and friends who are just as excited as we are about a new child joining the family, and we look forward to welcoming this baby with open hearts and arms! We are very fortunate to have most of our family very close by and both of us come from decent sized families. We are very close to our families and keep in constant contact with them. Our friends are very important to us, we consider them our extended family and we get together with them and their families frequently.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 2401, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331600221, 0),
(588, '<p><font size="-1">We are a very loving family who above all enjoy having fun and spending time together. We both grew up in Cincinnati and have our families close by and visit often. We bought our home in 2003 in a nice suburban area with lots of kids in the neighborhood that are always outside playing with Sabrina. They enjoy riding bikes and hiking through the wooded trails with us.</font></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n										<p>Our family and friends are very supportive of our decision to adopt again and see it as a wonderful way for us to grow our family. We will create a loving, supportive and fun atmosphere in which your child will thrive and know they are loved.</font></p>\nWe have many similar interests. Ralph loves to run in 5k Marathons, play tennis, golf and rollerblade in the park. Ralph enjoys the outdoors and loves to work around the house.</font></p>\n										<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Patty enjoys drawing like the pictures in this letter, painting, reading, making flower arrangements and doing other crafty things. Patty also loves to garden, play golf, run 5k&rsquo;s with Ralph and go rollerblading together. Sabrina loves to run with us in her stroller and always yells for daddy to go faster.</font></p>\n									 <p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We also love to swing dance and ballroom dance, mostly because it makes us laugh at how silly we probably look trying to get the steps right, but also because it&rsquo;s just fun. We both believe that exercising is very important to staying healthy. We enjoy taking walks or running throughout the neighborhood. We love taking Sabrina to the nearby park, watching her swing, slide and play in the sandbox with other children. We recently bought an RV and have had many wonderful experiences camping with friends over the summers.</font></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n										<p>We enjoy taking vacations and wish to see many more places in our lives. We would like to revisit places we went to on trips as children like Disney World, Bermuda and Nantucket. We went to Italy on our honeymoon and had a wonderful experience with many stories to share. We have gone on cruises, seen the beach many times, enjoyed skiing trips and plan to see many more places. We have taken Sabrina to the beach a few times in Florida and she loves playing in the sand and watching the dolphins. </font></p>\n										\n									 <p>&nbsp;</p>\n										<p>We attend a large local Catholic Church and were both baptized and raised as Catholics. We find that going to church is a way to bring the family together and look forward to our weekends together sharing with God. We grew up miles away from each other, but were actually baptized in the same church and feel this was destiny. We both grew up with solid morals and values, and we look forward to sharing our faith with our children.</font></p>\n									 <p>&nbsp;</p>										\n		<p>We believe we would be great parents for your baby for many reasons. We love kids and can offer a secure family life filled with love and laughter. This child will have the warm embrace of a large extended family, and our support as parents to develop their interests, passions and talents. We are financially secure, strongly value education, and appreciate the unique role a parent can play in terms of developing their child&rsquo;s judgment, values and view of the world. Thank you for taking the time to read our letter and may God bless you and grant you peace in your decision and happiness in your life.</font></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Lives Together', 2401, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331597955, 0),
(589, 'We have many similar interests. Ralph loves to run in 5k Marathons, play tennis, golf and rollerblade in the park. Ralph enjoys the outdoors and loves to work around the house.\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\nPatty enjoys drawing like the pictures in this letter, painting, reading, making flower arrangements and doing other crafty things. Patty also loves to garden, play golf, run 5k’s with Ralph. We love to go rollerblading and riding our bikes together as a family.\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\nWe also love to swing dance and ballroom dance, mostly because it makes us laugh at how silly we probably look trying to get the steps right, but also because it’s just fun. We both believe that exercising is very important to staying healthy. We enjoy taking walks or running throughout the neighborhood. We love taking Sabrina to the nearby park, watching her swing, slide and play in the sandbox with other children and also in our own backyard. We own an RV and have had many wonderful experiences camping with friends over the summers.\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\nWe enjoy taking vacations and wish to see many more places in our lives. We would like to revisit places we went to on trips as children like Disney World, Bermuda and Nantucket. We went to Italy on our honeymoon and had a wonderful experience with many stories to share. We have gone on cruises, seen the beach many times, enjoyed skiing trips and plan to see many more places. We have taken Sabrina to the beach a few times in Florida and she loves playing in the sand and watching the dolphins. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Hobbies', 2401, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331599050, 0),
(590, 'We attend a large local Catholic Church and were both baptized and raised as Catholics. We find that going to church is a way to bring the family together and look forward to our weekends together sharing with God. We grew up miles away from each other, but were actually baptized in the same church and feel this was destiny. We both grew up with solid morals and values, and we look forward to sharing our faith with our children.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Faith', 2401, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1331599164, 0),
