(604, 'At A Caring Connection of Catholic Charities, we will help you decide whether you feel parenting or adoption is the best choice for your pregnancy. Our adoption specialists have over thirty years combined experience in the area of pregnancy counseling and adoption and are available to help you in planning for your child''s future.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Thinking about adoption?', 1948, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332345646, 0),
(605, '   People say that we are a fun couple to be around…and we like to agree! We are always joking, laughing, and having a good time; whether it is at the grocery store, at home, or out with friends or family. Even though we have important careers which we do take seriously; we try not to take life too seriously in general. Our home is full of laughter! We have several pets that are all rescued and that we love with all of our hearts. Our time at home often includes playing with our dogs, cats, or bunnies; who all get along and have taken to our humorous, upbeat environment at home.  We are so excited to be able to include our future children in all of our activities and become the fun family instead of the fun couple.\n\n                                  \n\n   Both of us are educators that value hard work, honesty, and helping to improve others through learning. Shanna is an Elementary School Special Education teacher who advocates daily for her students to receive the best education possible and works hard to help these exceptional children become the best children they can be.\n \n                                \n\n\n   John is a Professor at a Public University and takes pride in helping both undergraduate and graduate college students become better public speakers, conflict managers, researchers, and of course, the best young adults they can be. We both take great pride in being the first in our families to not only earn a college degree but also earn graduate degrees.\n\n \n\n\n\n\n   We have been married for almost 6 years, but we have been together for 8. Ask either of us and we will both say that we knew the other was the one almost right away. We are best friends who just enjoy each other. We have a daughter in heaven, Stella Mae. She was born premature a year ago and lived for five amazing days. We know that we will see her in heaven one day.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Shanna &amp; John', 2421, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332651338, 0),
(606, 'The home we own is in the countryside, and we truly have the best of both worlds; great neighbors who are close by, but also over an acre of land to enjoy!  With this great open space we have, we love working outdoors, working in our vegetable and flower gardens, grilling outside, and watching our dogs run free and play.  When the weather is nice, we love to spend time on the back patio with our pets and watch the sunset while our hummingbird feeder is visited.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 2421, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332650225, 0),
(607, 'Mrs. Runner\nCandy enjoys staying fit through aerobic exercise and working out in our neighborhood gym. In the past year she decided to become a runner. She enjoys running 5K races (3.1 miles) when possible and is training for her first half marathon (13.1 miles). Running and exercise give her a sense of freedom and accomplishment.\nMrs. Performer (church pics)\nCandy has always loved music and singing! As a child she would pretend to be a disc jockey and would record her “sessions” on tape and sing in her microphone. As she got older, Candy continued her love of music and performing through involvement in choir, band, and drama during high school and college. Currently, she enjoys singing and leading worship at her church. She is also a member of a local chorale society where she sings and performs with other music-loving adults.\nMrs. Creative (silly faces)\nCandy’s creativity is evident in her personality. She is outgoing and witty and loves to make others laugh. Her creativity is also seen in her career as a music educator. She often writes songs for her students to use in her classroom and creates choreography for her concert programs.  Candy teaches in a small, K-4 school with about 310 students total that she sees 3-4 times a week. Her programs have included Christmas musicals, which she loves to create and direct, as well as recorder concerts and family folk dance events that occur in the spring.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Who Candy Is', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332361785, 0),
(608, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/1123-Steve_and_Monica/1123-Steve_and_Monica.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Monica and Steve''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 1123, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1332369765, 1),
(609, 'test test', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Who We Are', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332518069, 0),
(610, '<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">How We Met</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">We met at a rodeo dance in Candy’s home town during the summer of 1998 while Candy was home from college.<span> </span>We danced all night and felt an instant connection!<span> </span>We dated for a little over a year before getting engaged, and we were married less than a year after that. We are dedicated to our marriage and see marriage as being a lifelong commitment.<span> </span>We continually seek to improve our marriage by attending conferences and workshops that give us the skills to love, serve, and cherish each other.<span> </span>A strong marriage is crucial to raising a healthy child and we plan to model for our child what it means for a husband and wife to love and cherish one another.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;"><span style="font-size:small;"><strong>What We Believe</strong> </span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Candy and I are both committed Christians.<span> </span>Our relationship with Jesus Christ is the foundation of who we are as individuals and as a couple.<span> </span>Whether it is in personal times of study and prayer or in our involvement with our church through leading Sunday School and serving on the worship team, we plan to model for our child what it means to follow Christ.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;"><span style="font-size:small;"><strong>What We Do</strong> </span></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Candy has been a music teacher for more than 11 years.<span> </span>In college she earned a Bachelor’s degree in Music Education.<span> </span>Over the years she has taught Jr/Sr High band and choir as well as elementary music.<span> </span>She now teaches K-4 general music to over 300 students!<span> </span>She is well equipped with many fun songs and games to expose our child to music from a very early age. In the future Candy looks forward to being a dedicated stay-at-home mom to our children.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Chad has worked in the agriculture industry for almost 15 years.<span> </span>In college he earned both a Bachelor’s and Master’s degree in Agriculture.<span> </span>He currently is employed in a technical sales role for an agricultural company.<span> </span>His office is in our basement so he is at home when he does not have to travel on business.<span> </span>Chad is looking forward to the times when he will be working at home and will have the opportunity to be close to his wife and child.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;"><span style="font-size:small;"><strong>What We Like </strong></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">We are each other’s best friend so many of the things that we do we enjoy doing together.<span> </span>One of our favorite pastimes is making music together.<span> </span>Whether it is in our basement, at a small coffee shop, or at our church, we love singing and playing music as a team.<span> </span>We also enjoy travelling together. The mountains are our favorite destination. We try to make it to the mountains of Colorado or New Mexico at least once a year.<span> </span>The crisp mountain air filled with the scent of pine is very relaxing. We also enjoy day hikes to immerse ourselves in the surrounding beauty.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Our Uniqueness</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">We are unique in many aspects and one of those is that we both grew up as only children. Being an only child taught us many things. We learned to be self-reliant and responsible. We also realized the importance of pitching in and helping whenever necessary. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Something else unique about us is that we are truly each other’s best friends. We always make an effort to do things together. Whether it’s washing dishes, folding laundry, or even paying the bills, we work together as a team to accomplish what needs to be done.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Who We Are', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1332903509, 0),
(611, '<p>Our Summer House is located in Michigan.</p>\n<p>The house is located in Dowagiac.</p>\n<p>It''s 1 of 13 houses on an island.</p>\n<p>We floated all the timbers on the water to island with no problems.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Summer House', 62, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1332528114, 0),
(612, 'We''ve created a photo book to share more about ourselves.  There are a couple ways to view the book.  You can use the "Print Profile" button at the top right of the page to download a 54 MB PDF and save it to your desktop for offline viewing or printing.  You can also click on the following link to immediately view a lower resolution version without having to download the whole file first:\n\nProfile Photo Book\n\nYou can also view online versions of Jacob''s update books.  These versions have had the name of Jacob''s birthmother and siblings removed, as well as the messages of a more personal nature.  They serve as an extension of our profile, giving you more insight into our family and our journey as parents.\n\nUpdate 1\n\nUpdate 2\n\nUpdate 3\n\nUpdate 4\n\nUpdate 5\n\nUpdate 6\n\nUpdate 7\n\nUpdate 8', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Profile Book', 2525, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1373721929, 0),
(613, 'Monica was born in Mexico City, growing up there until she was nine and her family moved to Elkhart Indiana where her Dad who is a doctor took a new job there. Monica quickly adjusted to new surroundings, lifestyle (moving from the big city to a small town) and of course a new language and greatly enjoyed her childhood in Indiana.  Upon graduating from Indiana University Monica moved to the Washington DC area to be closer to her family who had moved there while she was at IU and began a successful career in Information Technology Sales.\n\nMonica speaks fluent Spanish and French.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Monica', 1123, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1370808836, 0),
(614, 'Steve was born in Connecticut but since his Dad was in the Navy, Steve had lived on the East Coast, West Coast, South, Midwest and in Europe by the time he was in the fifth grade! Steve as family eventually settled down in the Washington, DC area. Upon graduation from Villanova University Steve spent 10 years flying jets in the Navy and since then has worked as a manager in the aerospace industry.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Steve', 1123, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332637903, 0);
