(616, 'We''ve created a photo book to share more about ourselves.  There are several ways to view the book.  You can use the E-Book Profile link directly below to view it here at ParentFinder.  You can use the "Print Profile" button at the top right of the page to download a 46 MB PDF and save it to your desktop for offline viewing.  You can also point your browser to the following link:\n\n<p>\nhttp://app.picaboo.com/WebView/Project.aspx?clientID=dba52e74a3c3537501c447e6334574ad&version=216901&siteID=ViaPreview \n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Profile Photo Book', 2525, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332650736, 0),
(617, '<p style="text-align:justify;">We''d love to hear about you and your family, or answer any questions you may have about ours.  You can reach us through the ParentFinder messaging system, or, if you''d like to contact us directly, you may email us at:</p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p><a href="mailto:steven.and.annemarie@gmail.com?Subject=ParentFinder%20Profile">steven.and.annemarie@gmail.com</a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;">Or you may call 434-515-0826 and leave a voice message and we''ll return your call.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact Info', 2525, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1373729186, 0),
(1422, '<p style="text-align:justify;">I’m a mechanical engineer in the construction consulting industry and have been with my current firm for over nine years.  I’ve been an avid reader since I was very young and hope to foster that interest in our children.  I collect novels, comic books, and action figures of my favorite franchises – Star Wars, Transformers, and Batman.  I play drums and enjoy making cover recordings.  I play racquetball a couple times a week to keep in shape and enjoy doing things outdoors like hiking, camping, bicycling, and cooking out.  I like doing some of my own automotive work when time permits.   I’ve recently gotten interested in photography and am having a good time trying to get better at it.  I look forward to spending time with my family - going out to eat, watching movies, going to church, and taking vacations. I’ve loved every minute of being a father the past couple years and am ready to see our family grow.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Steve', 2525, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1401848391, 0),
(631, 'We discovered the joy and miracle of Adoption in 2009 when we adopted our son Jake. He is nothing short of a miracle indeed! Jake is growing and learning and discovering who he is. As of now he is leaning toward being right-handed, seems to love choo-choo trains, Disney, Sesame Street, baseball and loves hanging out with his dog, Zoe! Jake knows his ABCs and can count to 40! He loves to jump, play and swim in the pool or the ocean. This kid has touched so many people''s lives and a child can''t have too much love!!!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Jake', 2552, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1333030446, 0),
(618, '<p>We are very close with both of our families, and we see them often. Your child will have 11 cousins, ranging in age from 4 to 22, as well as four grandparents, five aunts, and five uncles. Brian’s sister is also expecting a baby, so your child will have a cousin of the same age! Everyone is impatiently waiting for the new babies to join the family, and they are very supportive of our adoption plans. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Brian''s family has a long history of adoption. His aunt and uncle built their family through adoption many years ago. One of Brian''s cousins and his wife adopted their two children, teenagers now, from Russia, and another cousin and her husband adopted their little girl from Russia two years ago. She''s 3, and has everyone wrapped around her little finger.  With this history, your child will never feel out of place in our family.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 2382, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1342710048, 0),
(619, '<p>The first time we saw our house, we both knew "this is it." It’s a simple ranch house, very much like the homes both of us grew up in. Our home is comfortable and cozy, with a huge backyard that is all fenced in so your child can play safely. We plan to put a swingset in the middle of the yard when your child is older.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img style="float:left;margin:5px;" title="Our backyard" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/brianronni/backyard.JPG" alt="Our backyard" width="300" height="225" />We live in a very safe neighborhood, where there’s not a lot of traffic and people love to walk their dogs. There is a small park just down the street from our house. It has lots of green grass and the latest play equipment. In the summer, there are usually several children playing there when we drive or walk by. When your child gets tired of playing in our backyard, we’ll be able to walk down to the park as a family to play.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Wisconsin is a great place to grow up. Your child can go sledding in the winter, swimming in the summer, play in mud puddles in the spring, and jump in huge piles of leaves in the fall. We live in a small city, and it has many of the benefits of the small towns we grew up in, such as good schools, a wonderful public library, and lots of family-oriented events like a Fourth of July parade and fireworks. But we’re also lucky because we live within easy driving distance of larger cities and several universities, which means your child will be exposed to multicultural activities and diverse viewpoints.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 2382, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1332894124, 0),
(620, '<p>We met five years ago when we were set up by a mutual friend. We got engaged less than a year after our first date, and we were married nine months later.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration:underline;">To us, family is number one.</span> We are lucky to come from loving families, with parents who always let us know that children come first. They came to every ball game, school play, and concert any of their kids were ever in. We are following their example. We often travel to watch our older nieces and nephews play different sports, and we are planning to be front and center at every event and activity your child takes part in.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration:underline;">Our faith is central to our lives and who we are.</span> Our shared Catholic faith is one of the first things that drew us together. We attend church services regularly, and we try to be as involved in our church as we can. Brian is a member of a men’s organization there, and we volunteer for different church activities, such as working at a food stand at the county fair in the summer, serving dinner during the annual fall festival, and purchasing gifts for the Giving Tree at Christmas. We are looking forward to sharing our faith with your child.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration:underline;">Traditions, big and small, are important to us.</span> Some of these are family traditions, like roasting hot dogs in the fireplace at Ronni’s parents’ house during the holidays. Others we have created ourselves, like calling each niece and nephew on their birthday to sing "Happy Birthday" (very badly, we might add!). If you have family or other traditions that you would like your child to be aware of, we would love to know what those are, and talk to you about how we can make those traditions part of our family, too.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 2382, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1337892281, 0),
(621, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/2534-RamonandAnne/2534-RamonandAnne.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Ramon and Anne''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 2534, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1332710399, 1),
(622, 'Hola,\n\nNos llamamos Ramón y Anne.  Nos gustaría comenzar por darles las gracias por su valiente decisión a considerar adopción.  Sabemos que al hacer esta decisión solamente quieren lo mejor para su hijo y respetamos su deseo de encontrar la mejor familia para amar y cuidar a su bebé.  (En esta carta cuando usamos hijo/niño, queremos decir hija/niña también).  Escogimos fotos que capturaron el amor que compartimos como una pareja y como una familia, y apreciamos que tomen el tiempo para leer nuestra carta.  Esperamos la oportunidad de conocerles para decirles más de quienes somos nosotros y cuánto su hijo será amado por nosotros y nuestra familia entera.\n\n\nAnne: Nací en 1965 en Long Island, Nueva York, donde mis padres todavía viven en la casa de mi niñez.  Tengo una hermana que es tres años menor que yo y que tiene tres hijos.  Todos ellos viven en Texas.  Gradué del Colegio de Marymount en 1989 e inmediatamente comencé a enseñar.  En 1990 me mudé a San Francisco, California donde enseñé educación especial y serví como administradora en la misma escuela por 12 años.  Durante este tiempo recibí la maestría en educación especial de la Universidad Estatal de San Francisco.  En 2002 me mudé a Texas y seguí enseñando educación especial para la misma escuela hasta que me mudé a Arizona en 2009.  Hoy en día trabajo como especialista en comportamiento para un distrito escolar local.  Me gusta decorar, cocinar, ver películas graciosas, estar con Ramón, leer y ayudar a otros.  Como especialista en comportamiento puedo ayudar a maestras y a padres a trabajar con niños que tienen dificultades de comportamiento.  Soy miembra de Beta Sigma Phi, una organización de servicio para mujeres y en 2011 me eligieron Reina del baile del Día de San Valentín.\n\n\n\nRamón: Nací en 1973 en Texas.  Soy hijo único y tengo una relación muy íntima con mis padres quienes viven en Texas.  Crecí en un hogar bilingue y hablo español e inglés.  Pasé varios años como gerente de ventas antes de recibir el bachiller en sociología con un énfasis global de la Universidad de Texas A y M en 2001.  Después de la graduación comencé a enseñar educación especial en una escuela para niños con incapacidades emocionales y de comportamiento.  En 2009 dejé la enseñanza y comencé a trabajar como un oficial federal de cumplimiento de la ley y fui asignado a un puesto en el sur de Arizona.  Hoy en día estoy completando una maestría en administración pública en la Universidad de Wayland Baptist.  Pienso graduarme en el otoño de 2012.  Me gusta escuchar y tocar música, levantar pesas, pasar tiempo en el agua (piscina, playa o lago), hacer comida asada, estar con Anne, aprender y trabajar duro para avanzar mi carrera para sustentar a mi familia.\n\n\nNos conocimos en 2003 mientras estábamos enseñando en la misma escuela en Texas y en septiembre de 2006 nos casamos.  Nos gusta pasar  tiempo juntos y hacemos casi todo juntos.  Hacemos un viaje grande cada verano, generalmente a Nueva York o a algún lugar con playa.  Nos gustan los deportes, especialmente el béisbol y el fútbol americano.  Anne es aficionada de los Yankes de Nuevo York y Ramón fue criado para aclamar a de los Cowboys de Dallas.  Aunque apoyamos a equipos diferentes, nos gusta asistir a eventos deportivos en vivo, especialmente NHRA Drag Racing (carreras de autos).  Compartimos los quehaceres de la casa y cocinamos la cena juntos cada noche.  Nos gusta experimentar con recetas nuevas y vivir una vida saludable haciendo ejercicio y comiendo bien.  Somos católicos, apoyamos a nuestra iglesia y asistimos a la misa cada semana.\n\nEstamos muy emocionados y listos para ser padres.  Hemos orado sobre esto y creemos que es el plan de Diós para nosotros que acojamos a un niño a nuestra familia por medio de adopción.  Queremos compartir con nuestro niño todas las experiencias maravillosas y tradiciones con que hemos sido benditos y sobre todo, amar a nuestro niño en la manera en que nuestros padres nos aman; porque ese es el mejor regalo que podemos dar a él o a ella.  Es nuestro deseo de criar a nuestro niño para que sea educado y que se convierta en una persona responsable y respetuosa.  Cuando nuestro niño llegue, Anne se quedará en casa por  tres meses y después tal vez regresará al trabajo por dos días a la semana cuando Ramón no esté trabajando.\n\nGracias otra vez por tomar el tiempo para saber más sobre nosotros.  Si nos escoje, seremos benditos, y su hijo será amado completamente y sin condición, no solamente por nosotros, sino por cada persona en nuestra familia.\n\nSinceramente,\nRamón y Anne\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Nuestra Informacion en espanol', 2534, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332729926, 0),
(623, '<p><a href="http://hopefuladoptivefamily.shutterfly.com/pictures/10">http://hopefuladoptivefamily.shutterfly.com/pictures/10</a></p>', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 2388, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1369969517, 1),
(624, '<p>You may contact us directly at <a href="mailto:tomandjenniferadopt@yahoo.com">tomandjenniferadopt@yahoo.com</a>. If you prefer, you can contact our agency at <a href="mailto:agency@cccofva.org">agency@cccofva.org</a> or 800-296-2376.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Conact Us', 2308, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1332856473, 0),
(625, '<p style="text-align:justify;">Jacob isn’t our first adoption experience.  Anne’s brother, Joey, was adopted.  We believe that a child’s adoption should not be kept hidden from him or her.  Our approach is to make our children aware from the very beginning that they’re adopted, and we believe there’s value in having birthparent involvement provided the situation is not harmful to the child.  Jacob’s birthmother initially decided she didn’t want to meet us or receive updates; however, she changed her mind at the hospital.  It was an emotional experience but very satisfying, and we’re glad that we''re able to maintain regular contact.  We hope that as our children grow to understand their adoption, it will be helpful that we can share our personal experience with the birthparents and speak of them as family.  We hope that in time our children will have a desire to participate in preparing updates and letters, and we’ll support them should they desire to meet their birthparents and siblings.</p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;">Since we''re pursuing a private adoption, there won''t be an agency between us to accommodate a closed or semi-open arrangement where contact information is not directly exchanged.  However, we recognize that we can’t understand how it feels to consider placing your child for adoption, and are willing to respect your decision regarding the level of openness you desire after placement.  Ultimately, we would defer to YOU to determine what level of post-placement interaction, if any, is right for you and your family.  We’re prepared to discuss, consider, and honor any arrangement you propose, be it ongoing contact and visitation, to periodic updates, to an effectively closed adoption.  We’d be willing to consider an open grandparenting arrangement as well.  We also recognize that your feelings regarding this may change over time.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ADOPTION OPENNESS', 2525, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1373722849, 0),
