(1218, 'Please be patient with us as we are still trying to work on figuring out how to set up our profile. It may not be the prettiest but it comes from the heart...', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our profile', 5151, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1359407548, 0),
(1219, 'We promise to support you.\nWe promise to honor your wishes.\nWe promise to never pressure you.\nWe promise to be fair.\nWe promise to love your baby like she is our own. \nWe promise to raise her with morals and values.\nWe promise to talk about you to her constantly, and tell her how much you love her.\nWe promise to send cards and letters and pictures.\nWe promise to share cards and letters and pictures with her.\nWe promise phone calls.\nWe promise to be surrounded with family and friends.\nWe promise to encourage her to always be herself.\nWe promise to love her for exactly who she is.\nWe promise to give her everything within our power.\nWe promise to expose her to many different cultures and ideas.\nWe promise to be the best parents we can be\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'What We Promise You', 5151, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1359653378, 0),
(626, '<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Hello.<span> </span>Thank you for taking the time to find out more about us.<span> </span>We can only imagine all of the emotions you’re feeling right now.<span> </span>Whether you are an expectant parent or the relative of one, our prayer for you is that you will have peace and comfort during this time.<span> </span>If you decide to make an adoption plan for your child, and after reading through our profile you decide that you might want us to be a part of your adoption plan, we would love to visit with you.<span><span> </span>Regardless of whether we ever meet or not, our hope and prayer is for God’s best for you and your child. </span></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;"><span>God Bless,</span></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;"><span>Chad and Candy</span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Dear Expectant Parent', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1334712638, 0),
(708, '<p><span style="font-size: medium;">I enjoy swimming, cooking, sking, sweing, bird watching and most outdoors activities. I have had a great time reading children books to our kids. We go to the library every week. </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About us', 1342, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1334725976, 0),
(627, '<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;" class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Our Home</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">We live in a newer subdivision of our town and our home was built in 2005. Our home is mid-sized and is just right for us and our future children. We have 2 bedrooms upstairs, the master and the nursery, and 2 bedrooms, our office, and a spare room downstairs. Since we moved into our home more than two years ago we’ve added beautiful hardwood floors throughout the upstairs, an iron privacy fence, an outdoor shed, and a spacious deck in the backyard. One of our favorite places to hang out in is our music “studio” which is located in the basement. Here we have Chad’s many guitars, an amplifier, and pedals along with our keyboard and Candy’s bass guitar. This is the place we love to jam, sing, and play together. We also have a neat play house built underneath our staircase that will make an excellent fort or doll house someday!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;" class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Our Neighborhood</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Our neighborhood is very family-oriented and kid-friendly. An adjacent subdivision has a small pond, a walking/bike trail, a water park, and a playground that everyone enjoys going to throughout the different seasons of the year. There are many young couples and young children in our neighborhood so our children will have plenty of playmates nearby.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;" class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Our Community</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Our town is a mid-sized town with a small town feel to it. There always seems to be something happening downtown such as sidewalk sales, live music with local talent, as well as car shows and parades. The recreation commission also has a variety of activities that are family and children related. We look forward to seeking out and allowing our child the opportunity to try new things such as swimming lessons, dance, karate, and softball and/or baseball.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">We also enjoy living within 20 minutes of a large metro-city. Because of the size and diversity within this city we know there will be several opportunities to get involved in a variety of multi-cultural events and activities. Knowing the importance of exposing our child to their own cultural heritage, if our child is of another race we will actively seek out and participate in as many cultural activities as possible.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Where We Live', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1332903925, 0),
(628, '<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Our Parents </span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Chad grew up in a two-parent, two-income family and his parents have been married for 40+ years. Candy’s parents divorced when she was very young and she was raised primarily in a single-parent home. However, Candy’s mother remarried about 10 years ago.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">We enjoy spending time with both sets of parents for birthdays, holidays, and throughout the year. Our annual Thanksgiving tradition is spent with Chad’s parents eating a delicious meal and then spending time seeing the Christmas lights. Both sets of parents look forward to the day they can call themselves grandparents and when they can share their love with a grandchild.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Our Extended Family </span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Even though we are both only children, we have tons of cousins on both sides of the family. We do not often see Chad’s side of the family because everyone is so spread out. Much of Candy’s family live in the same town or very close together. Every Christmas Eve is spent at her aunt and uncle’s home where we all eat too much food, open Christmas gifts, and play tons of games.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Our Adoption Connection</span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Adoption is already a part of our extended family. Candy’s cousin made an adoption plan for her child and her husband was adopted. Both of their adoptions were and continue to be open adoptions in that they visit in person and e-mail throughout the year. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Our families are supportive of our adopting a child of any race. Our parents have lived in multicultural neighborhoods in various times of their lives. We also spent portions of our early childhood in multicultural neighborhoods and schools. Some of our best friends growing up were Jewish, Asian, Hispanic, and African American.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">Our “Little Brother” </span></span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;font-size:small;">Another very important relationship and member of our family is Chad’s “little brother” Trent. Chad and Trent were matched together through the Big Brother/Big Sister Organization about 10 years ago. Chad is an excellent “big brother” as he has mentored Trent in a variety of ways (e.g., tutoring Trent with his school work, helping him to receive his hunter’s safety license, spending time with Trent in studying and discussing the Bible, playing board games, and hunting). Even though we don’t live in the same town anymore, Chad still makes every effort to talk with Trent and take him out for an evening of good food and “guy time” whenever possible.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Who Our Family Is', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1332904423, 0),
(629, 'Our home is a warm, loving and safe environment. We have the house already baby-proofed from our 2009 adoption of our son Jake. Our home is constantly filled with music, love, laughter ... and a few dog hairs from our adopted dog Zoe. She and Jake are huge pals and want to play "yellow ball" with a new brother or sister!\n\n\nWe chose to stay near our hometowns so that we could be around both sets of grandparents. (Both sets of in-laws are still married to each other and these grandparents live nearby) and Nan-Nan & Paw-Paw and Mimi & Oppy are so excited about us adopting. Our friends are too! We''ve been trying to explain to Jake was a terrific Big Brother he will be and what a big responsibility that comes with that title. \n\n\nFamily is so important to us ... both our "Given Family" of relatives and our "Chosen Family" of our friends. We are Aunt La La and Uncle Ry Ry to our friends'' children. It is one big happy family. We don''t think a child can have too much love and too much caring.\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our House', 2552, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1332944879, 0),
(630, '<p style="text-align:justify;">We have an approved home study through Family Life Services in Lynchburg, Virginia, who will also be providing our post-placement services.  We have retained a local attorney who is passionate about adoption and has two adopted children of her own. </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;">We strongly encourage you to speak with your family and/or a counselor and carefully consider ALL options available to you, including those which keep your baby with you or someone in your family.  We have retained a family counselor with extensive experience in adoption. She will be available upon request for confidential sessions at no cost to you and with no commitment for pursuing an adoption plan.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'AGENCY INFORMATION', 2525, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1374721960, 0),
