(661, '<p><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;color:#000000;font-size:small;">We were ecstatic when we got the news that we were chosen to adopt our son Tommy through Adoptions Together in May 2010. We only had one week to get ready for his arrival and quickly put together a nursery. Our friends and family were thrilled about our good news and showered us with everything we needed. We were in the hospital when he was born and brought him home the next day.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;font-size:small;"><span style="color:#000000;">Tommy has filled our lives with so much joy and we absolutely love being parents. His giggles, and hugs make us smile every day. He is a sweet little boy who enjoys playing with cars and trains, going on walks, and reading books. We still long for more children and know that Tommy will be a great big brother.</span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Adopting Tommy', 2158, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1342014112, 0),
(662, 'Julie and Kirk were both involved in the Big Brothers/Big Sisters program before we met.   We always wanted to help children and even talked about adoption when we were dating.   \n\n\nAfter our two biological sons were born, we experienced infertility problems.  We knew that the time had come to find our children through adoption.  But honestly, we had wanted to adopt for so very long.....it was just God''s way or telling us DO IT!  \n\n<a href="http://s1191.photobucket.com/albums/z475/juliea388/Facebook/Instagram%20Photos/?action=view&amp;current=431999_10150710363978343_632428342_11567257_1872325631_n.jpg" target="_blank"><img src="http://i1191.photobucket.com/albums/z475/juliea388/Facebook/Instagram%20Photos/431999_10150710363978343_632428342_11567257_1872325631_n.jpg" border="0" alt="Happy Birthday, Dr. Seuss! http://instagr.am/p/HrsKvvkiWZ/"></a>\nOur son <b>Rory</b> came home to us from China in 2005.  He is full of energy and giggles.  He fit into our family right from the beginning and called Julie "Mama" from the moment they first met!   Rory has some special needs but none of us let them stand in his way.  We love him with all of our hearts and our boys are so happy to have Rory as their younger brother.\n\n<a href="http://s1191.photobucket.com/albums/z475/juliea388/?action=view&amp;current=141409L.jpg" target="_blank"><img src="http://i1191.photobucket.com/albums/z475/juliea388/141409L.jpg" border="0" alt="Photobucket"></a>\n<b>Sam''s</b> birth parents contacted us from our Parent Profile in January 2010.   In June, Julie was there when Sam was born and was the first person to ever hold him and feed him.  It was truly a blessing beyond words to be there for his birth.  His birth parents are AMAZING people who we keep in touch with via Facebook and texts. <b> There are no words to express our gratitude to them for giving us our beautiful son. </b>  He is funny, smart, sweet and just filled with so much love.\n\n<a href="http://s1191.photobucket.com/albums/z475/juliea388/Facebook/Instagram%20Photos/?action=view&amp;current=537852_10150790690268343_632428342_11874335_9150614_n.jpg" target="_blank"><img src="http://i1191.photobucket.com/albums/z475/juliea388/Facebook/Instagram%20Photos/537852_10150790690268343_632428342_11874335_9150614_n.jpg" border="0" alt="Tybee Island http://instagr.am/p/JKxOYykida/"></a>\n<b>Thomas</b> is our oldest biological son.  He is now 13 and is one of the sweetest tweens you will ever meet.  He''s kind, worries about everyone, loves to help watch his brothers, but also loves your typical teen stuff....iPads, iCarly, iEverything!  :)  When he was a toddler, he was diagnosed with Autism.  Now?  He is in regular middle school classes and a typical kid.  I consider the fight with Autism won!! (brushing off hands) ;)\n\n<a href="http://s1191.photobucket.com/albums/z475/juliea388/Facebook/Sams%201st%20Birthday%20Family%20Pics/?action=view&amp;current=247845_10150271875263343_632428342_9272436_5831676_n.jpg" target="_blank"><img src="http://i1191.photobucket.com/albums/z475/juliea388/Facebook/Sams%201st%20Birthday%20Family%20Pics/247845_10150271875263343_632428342_9272436_5831676_n.jpg" border="0" alt="Photobucket"></a>\n<b>Henry</b> is our 10 year old son who is in the Gifted and Talented program at his school.  He is, no question, a genius.  One day you will read about him on TV or hear about something awesome he invents, trust me.  He''s off to Space Camp again this summer along with a pal he met there last year and couldn''t be more excited!   \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Amazing Boys', 2683, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1334089769, 0),
(663, '<b>888-501-6281  TOLL FREE </b>\n\nThis is our toll-free number you can use to call us directly.  If I don''t pick up (it''s actually my cell), please leave me a message and I will call you right back.\n\nOR....\n\nYou can email us at:  <b> adoptionhopes@aol.com </b>\n\nOR....\n\nI try to sign on Yahoo Messenger quite often...\n\n<b>adoptionhopes2 </b> \n\nTHANKS :)', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact Us', 2683, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1334182188, 0),
