(683, 'Our 4 BDRM home is filled with light and color and love- and the smell of good cooking!  We have a big front yard and a stone porch that Jeremiah made last summer.  Our backyard is fenced and we have preserved space behind us.  Our yard is home to lilacs, honeysuckle, blueberry, raspberry, rose, and butterfly bushes and lots of gorgeous trees- we''ve even camped in tents in our backyard!  Our bird feeders attract bright cardinals, finches, and woodpeckers.\nOur community is family-friendly.  Within walking distance of our house is the highly-rated elementary school, several playgrounds, two libraries, the YMCA, parks and trails, places to get pizza and ice cream, and even a children''s sculpture garden!  \nOur neighbors all look out for each other, there are lots of children in the area, and several of our neighbors (including the guidance counselor of the local elementary school) have adopted children.  \nNearby in our community is an organic farm where each week we get vegetables, fruits, and flowers. We loved picking berries, apples, and pumpkins with Bodhi and he loved the mini-petting zoo there!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home and Community', 2631, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1334114428, 0),
