(705, 'We adopted Blazer from a breeder.  She was the last puppy and we knew she was meant to be ours.  We named her after the blaze orange color.  Blazer is a very calm, loving, 7 year old tomgirl.  Great with children.\n\nShe has her own paw bed and toys.  She loves getting treats and presents on holidays.  On her birthday she gets a Paw cookie treat with a few dog biscuits.\n\nHer hobbies are:\n*playing steal the bone (whoever can get the bone first)\n*Eating beefsticks and pupcorn with her dad (DJ)\n*fetching her glow ball outside\n*Going for rides in the jeep with her mom (Tanya)\n*Sleeping\n2:00 afternoon naps\n*Going to the farm to run around (likes to go through grandmas garden even though not suppose to)\n*Great pheasant hunter (Flushes them up and carries them back)\n*Loves running along with grandpa when he drives the fourwheeler\n* Laying out on the deck in the sun', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Blazer', 1363, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1334773968, 0),
(706, '<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span><span style="line-height:115%;font-size:10pt;"><span style="font-family:Calibri;">We have long desired to build a family and have always felt that adoption would play an important role in that process.<span> </span>We have also believed for a long time that, in some way, our family would be multiracial.<span> </span>Therefore, we realize that our adopted child may be of a different race and trust in God’s plan to see what that race might be.<span> </span>As we continually trust in God’s timing and plan for our family, we now believe that the time has come for us to seek out the one special expectant family who is creating an adoption plan for their child -- an adoption plan that includes a loving Christian home and opportunities for education and the arts. </span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Hopes and Dreams', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1334710965, 0),
(707, 'As parents to your child, we promise that:\n\n\n 1.Your child will be given all of our love. They will know they are loved through our words, actions, and sacrifices on their behalf.\n 2.Your child will know who Jesus Christ is and will be given ample opportunity to grow in their love and understanding of Him. They will be raised in a Christian home where our faith will be modeled in the context of a loving and committed marriage.\n3.Candy will be a devoted stay at home mom to your child. She will be able to take maternity leave as soon as the adoption is placed. Candy thoroughly enjoys teaching music, but it has always been in her heart to be a mother and to raise a family. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Promise to You and Your Child', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1334712363, 0),
