(715, '<p style="text-align:center;"><em><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;arial black&quot;, &quot;avant garde&quot;;"> <span style="font-family:&quot;Book Antiqua&quot;;font-size:small;">"As long as love is in your heart, the string will ALWAYS be there."</span></span></strong></em></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:medium;text-decoration:underline;">The Invisible String</span><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:medium;">, by Patrice Karst, is a children''s book that reminds children and adults they are <em>never</em> truly alone.  This will be true of the birthparent(s) of our child. Our child will always know of the unselfish gift of life his/her birthparent(s) gave.   As explained in the story, "People who love each other are always connected by a very special string made of love.  Even though you can''t see it with your eyes, you can feel it deep in your heart and know that you are always connected to the ones you love." </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;book antiqua&quot;, palatino;font-size:medium;"> This couldn''t be more true with the adoption process.  We ALREADY hold an invisible string for the birthparent (s) of the child we hold in our hearts and wish for in our prayers.  That invisible string will be shared with our child.  He/she will always hold that invisible string for his/her birthparent(s).  We will make sure of that. </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'THE INVISIBLE STRING', 2395, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1336095668, 0),
