(722, 'We live in a yellow rancher in a neighborhood with several families with children.   Abbie loves the light yellow color and the bridge in the front yard.  Sam loves planting flowers and taking care of the vegetable garden in the backyard.  On evenings where there is a gentle breeze you will find us dining outside on our picnic table often with friends.  Sam loves to grill, and Abbie loves to entertain.\nWe love to watch the children riding their bikes and playing together in the neighborhood.  We look forward to raising our child in this wonderful community. \nFor pictures of our home please view our home sweet home photo album.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 2302, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1338342069, 0),
(723, '<p><span style="color:#000000;"><span style="font-family:Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:small;">Anna says:<br /><br />Thad has always been a great husband, but I really love seeing him as a Dad. Music is a big part of his life. He is really looking forward to teaching Serafina''s brother or sister the same little songs he taught her. While Thad is laid back, warm, and funny, he is also a courageous provider for our family. He works mostly from home for a computer software company. Thad''s flexible schedule means he will always be ready to play games or teach our children the recipe for his famous strawberry ice cream.</span></span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Thad', 2768, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1335536504, 0),
