(730, 'ALL I CAN BE\n\nI have dreamed a dream, it MUST come true. \nI have dreamed a dream, a world with you.\nThe story began as “Once upon a time”…\nAnd soon it became a search for a line.\nPink or Green? Yellow or Blue?\nTears on my pillow, I cried because we did not have you.\nThrough the clouds, a rainbow appeared.\nGod had a plan.\nHe said, “Do not fear.”\nThrough Faith we waited… and waited… and waited some more.\nUntil one day, we had a knock at the door.\nShe smiled shyly, you see? \nWe did not know her and she did not know me.\nFrom our hearts and under hers,\nWe share a love, not for our sake, for yours.\nThis love would never end, \nFor the rest of our lives, a hope to remain friends.\nA gift, impossible to repay, \nI must, I must thank her some way.\nI had a dream, it was all about you.\nHow could I imagine, it included her too.\nFrom Mother to Mother and to one another,\nI promise to be… all I can be.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', '&quot;All I Can Be&quot; Written by Rebecca', 1070, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1335885110, 0),
