(741, 'Colleen grew up in Massachusetts. She has two brothers and one sister. Both of her parents are living.\n\nColleen graduated from Tufts University with a masters degree in Occupational Therapy. She works in the medical field with the elderly as the Director of Rehabilitation.\n\nColleen loves the outdoors and can often be found in the back yard swinging on the hammock, pulling weeds, swimming in the pool, or playing with the dogs.\n\nColleen is extremely creative and enjoys arts and crafts. Her specialty is creating beautiful stained glass windows. She has even taken first place in a regional art contest!\n\nColleen can''t wait to have a child to love and raise. She has baby proofed the house, read every book she could find, took baby care classes, and dreams of the day she can hold a child in her arms.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Colleen', 2436, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1336256666, 0),
(742, 'John grew up in New York, close to the city. He has one sister who lives in Michigan. Both of his parents are living.\n\nJohn graduated from Rensellear Polytechnic Institute with a degree in Civil Engineering. He works for a private firm designing bridges, roads, and utilities.\n\nJohn enjoys sports and frequently bicycles. He loves watching football and baseball games. John also enjoys working on anything mechanical. He works on cars and has renovated three properties.\n\nJohn is an amazingly smart man. He is methodical and able to figure out solutions to any problem. He is a great listener, caring, compassionate, gentle, and kind. He will make a patient and wonderful father!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About John', 2436, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1336257042, 0),
(743, 'Hi! thanks so much for taking a closer look at us! We are a young couple who can''t wait to love and nurture a beautiful child.\n\nWe live on the beautiful seacoast of New Hampshire, and a short walk to the beach.\n\nWe own two homes, our personal home and a rental property.  Our personal home has a huge back yard with a pool and deck as well as great neighbors with young children.  Our rental property is a grand victorian the next town over. We have great tenants and like to work hard and take pride in our homes.\n\nWe have several interests in common and like to spend our free time working on our home and yard, going for walks on the beach, swimming in our pool, taking weekend getaways, and travelling the world!\n\nWe have travelled to many places including Australia, New Zealand, Europe, Central America, Alaska, Hawaii, and Southeast Asia. We love planning trips and can''t wait to show a child the different cultures and environments in the world.\n\nIn our free time, we often take a drive to a surrounding New England state and go hiking, biking, kayaking, or just for a scenic drve.\n\nWe both hold our family in very high regards. We are thankful to our parents, have great relationships with our siblings, and love family get togethers, bar-b-cues, and holidays!\n\nTo learn more about us, please contact our adoption attorney .....  adoption@biancopa.com\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About The Both Of Us!', 2436, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1336497151, 0),
(744, 'Education and Enrichment are a priority for us.  We want our children to have every opportunity available to help them learn, grow and become the best version of themselves.  Our children attend private schools who share our goals for our children, teaching them in a warm and nurturing environment, exposing them to literature, art, science, music and helping them grow and learn.  We love that our school has families that will mirror our own, with families comprised of adopted and biological children and parents that share our values.  We are also fortunate enough that we can supplement their schooling with activities that they love including dance, music, soccer, baseball and art.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Education and Enrichment', 2532, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1336271611, 0),
(745, '<p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span>As parents to your child, we promise that:</p>\n<ol><li>Your child will be given all of our love.  They will know they are loved through our words, actions, and sacrifices on their behalf.</li>\n<li>Your child will know who      Jesus Christ is and will be given ample opportunity to grow in their love      and understanding of Him. They will      be raised in a Christian home where our faith will be modeled in the      context of a loving and committed marriage. </li>\n<li>Candy will be a devoted      stay at home mom to your child. She      will be able to take maternity leave as soon as the adoption is placed. Candy thoroughly enjoys teaching music,      but it has always been in her heart to be a mother and to raise a family.  <span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></li>\n</ol><p><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-size:small;"> </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Promise To You and Your Child', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1336338272, 0),
(747, 'Hello,\n\nWe are Belinda and Ryan and we would like to start out by saying that we THANK YOU for taking the time to learn about our family and considering us as an adoptive family. We truly admire and respect you for making this loving adoption plan for your child. We can not imagine how difficult this decision has been for you.  We truly admire your courage for making such a loving plan of adoption. If we are fortunate enough for you to entrust your child to us, we will make sure that your child understands the amazing love you had for him or her and the plan that you chose for him or her was one full of love. We would like to thank you for the great love you have for your child and the strength that has brought you to your adoption plan.\n\nOur story starts 13 years ago when a mutual friend decided we needed to meet. We began dating and fell deeply in love and married in 2004. We both wanted to have a family from the start as family is one of the most important things to us. We are both very close to our families. We have chosen adoption to grow our family as Belinda is unable to carry a child. We have had several pregnancy losses over the last few years. Adoption is close to our hearts as Belinda’s oldest brother is adopted. We are very blessed to have our families and close friends support our decision in adoption and welcoming a new child to our family. \n\n\nWe both grew up in small towns in southwestern Pennsylvania. We have a very strong, close and loving relationship with our parents, grandparents, and siblings. Belinda has 3 brothers and Ryan has 1 brother. Ryan’s mother is an elementary school teacher and Ryan’s father was an art teacher. Belinda’s father is a retired carpenter and Belinda’s mother was a homemaker and is now a store manager.  We have a niece, nephew and a god son that we love to spend as much time as possible with. They are the joy in our day.  We added a furry four legged child named Sassy to our family. She is a Westie. She joined our family almost 6 years ago. She is spoiled rotten and we cannot wait to have a child in the house for her to love. We both grew up with very close, loving and caring families. We are very blessed as both of our families get along together very well.  \n\n\nWe love to garden, go to the park, read, fish, play games, picnic, decorate for the holidays, go to movies, watch sports and play sports. We love any activities we can do as a family with extended family members to continue our close relationships.\n\nWe have a large three bedroom home in a small town with a big yard for children to play in. We live in a very close nit neighborhood with quite a few young children. We live in a very good school district. It is less than a mile from home. We both have very stable jobs. Our work places are no more than 10 miles from home and school. Belinda’s job allows her to have a very flexible schedule and work from home if need be. We are both financially ready to provide for a child. \n\nWe both would love nothing more than to grow our family by adding a child. Your child would be very loved and cared for. They would be provided every opportunity we could possibly give them in life. He or she will be given all the love and care in the world. There will also be a college education provided. We feel education is very important for a child. We would also like to bring a child up in the church. We would love to be able to teach a child about love, caring, respect, morals and values. We look forward to doing activities as a family and would love nothing more than to be able to raise a child with the same love and care we both were given and are still given from our families. Our families and close friends along with us are very excited about adding a new member to our family. \n\n\nWe thank you for taking the time to learn about our family. If you choose to place your child with us, he or she will be in a very nurturing and loving environment. They will be treasured! \n\nThank you again for considering our family in the loving adoption plan that you are making for your child.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth Family Letter ', 2820, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1352672626, 0),
(746, '<p><em>Our openness to other races.</em> We believe that God has a plan for building our family and that a fundamental part of His plan includes being a multiracial family. If your child is of another race we promise to bring their cultural heritage into all of our lives.  We will educate your child through books, media, and cultural events so that he or she can feel comfortable with his or her racial identity.  We will also expose your child to role models of the same race and gender, both in history and in the present, so he or she can learn what it means to be a man or woman of that race in today’s society.</p>\n<p><em>A comfortable relationship among us all. </em>We realize the importance of your child knowing his or her own adoption story from an early age. Furthermore, we understand that you may desire updates regarding his or her life. Through a mutually agreed upon communication plan you will be able to watch your son or daughter flourish as they grow. We are committed to your son or daughter knowing their history and knowing of your great love and sacrifice on their behalf.  We understand that communication between you, us, and (if you desire) your son or daughter can be an important piece that makes all of us whole and complete individuals who are equipped to live our lives as people touched by the miracle of adoption.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Being Open', 2488, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1336338076, 0),
