(749, '<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div><span style="font-size:20px;"><strong><br /></strong></span></div>\n<ul><li><a title="Uplanned Preganancy" href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=section&amp;id=7&amp;Itemid=53">Uplanned Preganancy</a> \n<ul><li><a title="FAQs" href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;layout=blog&amp;id=34&amp;Itemid=71">FAQs</a></li>\n<li><a title="Contact us &amp; Let us help you" href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=53&amp;Itemid=72">Contact us &amp; Let us help you</a></li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div><img src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/header/default/pregnancy.gif" alt="Birth Mother Contact Form" /><p><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=41&amp;Itemid=45">How do I start?</a><br /><br /><span>Birth Parent Hotline 24 hr/7 days 800-681-4673 (Hope)</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h1>Unplanned Pregnancy</h1>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" align="center"><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" width="60%" valign="top">\n<p>If you are experiencing an unplanned pregnancy and do not feel you are ready to parent, you may wish to consider adoption. We will be happy to discuss all options related to the pregnancy with you.</p>\n<p>If you do choose adoption, our agency provides each birth mother with her own personal birth parent counselor who guides you through the process in person. She can help you get to and from doctor appointments, set up housing, insurance appointments, such as Medicaid, WIC and food stamps if you qualify. Most importantly, she can talk to you and listen to your feelings while going through the process of adoption. The birth parent counselor helps you find the plan that is right for you!</p>\n<p>Services available to you are tailored to your specific needs. They may include, but are not limited to:</p>\n<ul><li>Appropriate Living Expenses </li>\n<li>Medical Care</li>\n<li>Counseling</li>\n<li>Your own attorney and legal fees paid</li>\n<li>Choose and meet your adoptive family</li>\n</ul><p>We would love to answer any of your questions about our program, and to assist you in making an adoption plan that will work for you. You may contact us at 1-800-681-4673, or (775) 825-HOPE, or you may e-mail us at <a href="mailto:info@parentfinder.com">info@adoptionchoicesofnevada.org</a> and we will help you with any questions you may have.</p>\n<p>If you would like to download our Birth parent Intake Packet, please <a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/birthmother.pdf">click here.</a></p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><td colspan="2"> </td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h3>Preganant? Need Help?</h3>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=category&amp;layout=blog&amp;id=34&amp;Itemid=82">FAQs</a></td>\n</tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=53&amp;Itemid=83">Contact Us &amp; Let Us Help You</a></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div><br /><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/birthmother.pdf"><span>DOWNLOAD THE BIRTH PARENT INTAKE PACKET</span></a> <br /><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=53&amp;Itemid=53">Contact Us</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<ul><li><a title="Go to top" href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=section&amp;id=7&amp;Itemid=53#Top"><img title="Goto top" src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/top.gif" alt="Goto top" /></a></li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n<small>Copyright © 2010 Adoption Choices of Nevada, All Right Reserved.</small></div>\n</div>\n</div>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Unplanned Pregnancy', 2830, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1338553946, 0),
(750, '<div>\n<h1>  Adoptive Parents</h1>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" align="center"><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" width="60%" valign="top">\n<p>Your family profile is often a birth parent''s first introduction to your family, so it should provide a picture of what the child''s life will be like with you.</p>\n<p>Begin with any informal greeting that is comfortable. Describe to the birth parents how you feel about being considered. You could also use this first paragraph to acknowledge their courage in deciding to make an adoption plan.</p>\n<h4>Do not...</h4>\n<ol><li>try to present yourselves as what you think a birth parent might want, but as you really are.</li>\n<li>include identifying information (last names, address, telephone number, name of workplace, or church), unless your intermediary has requested it.</li>\n<li>hand write information unless specifically requested by your intermediary.</li>\n<li>orget to ask your intermediary for specific guidelines of information to be included, such as number of photographs, length, etc.</li>\n</ol></td>\n</tr><tr><td colspan="2"> </td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h3> </h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Adoptive Parents', 2830, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1338554088, 0),
