(777, '     Our home is located outside of the city in a quiet subdivision in TN.  The mountains can be seen in the background around the area and is close to water.  The house is around 5 years old.  It has 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, a large bonus room, living room, kitchen, dinning room, and a small laundry room.  We have around 2300 sq ft.  We have a large back yard.  Our lot is almost an acre.  It is close to the elementary school and to Ragan''s work.  One of the reasons we moved into our house was because of the excellent school district that our kids would go to school if we had them.\n\n     \n     The city that we live outside of has many things to offer.  We have local playgrounds, historical parks, swimming pools with large fancy slides, and a learning center.  We have concerts, plays, festivals, and parades.  During the summer months, you can see movies underneath the stars.  Also, we are at the perfect location to do other activities such as going to theme parks, zoos, aquariums, NFL football games, pro hockey games, Broadway plays, touring caves, and visiting state parks', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR HOME AND COMMUNITY', 2901, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1337389652, 0),
(778, '     Eric''s aunt Dawn was in the nursing program with Ragan. Ragan and Dawn would ride together for clinicals.  Eric had seen a glimpse of Ragan. On March 3, 1998, Dawn invited Ragan to go to the movies with her, Brian, and Eric.  We went to the movies and saw the second Blues Brothers.  After the movie, we went to Wendy''s to eat.  Both of us were so shy and quiet.  The following weekend was spring break for college, and we went out again with Brian and Dawn. We hit it off and started dating. By Oct of 1998, we were engaged, and got married the following Oct of 1999.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'HOW WE MET', 2901, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1337568293, 0),
(779, '<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="901" align="center"><tbody><tr><td colspan="3" width="899" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">\n<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="200"><tbody><tr><td height="100" align="left" valign="top">\n<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="899"><tbody><tr><td width="222"><img src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofoklahoma.org/images/oklogo.jpg" alt="" width="260" height="94" /></td>\n<td width="652" align="right" valign="top">\n<h5><strong><br />Available 24 hrs per day, 7 days a week<br />Toll Free: 800.898.6028</strong></h5>\n<h5><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofoklahoma.org/grants/grantsandloans.html">Grants &amp; Loans</a> |<a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofoklahoma.org/adoptionlinks/adoptionlinks.html"> Adoption Links</a></h5>\n</td>\n<td width="23" align="right" valign="top"> </td>\n</tr></tbody></table></td>\n</tr></tbody></table><img src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofoklahoma.org/images/oknavbar.jpg" border="0" alt="" width="900" height="32" /><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="877"><tbody><tr><td height="32" align="left" valign="top"><img src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofoklahoma.org/images/okmain.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="490" /><br /></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></td>\n</tr><tr><td colspan="3" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><img src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofoklahoma.org/images/okbottombar.jpg" alt="" width="900" height="32" /></td>\n</tr></tbody></table>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Adoption Choices of Oklahoma', 2933, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1337621897, 0),
(780, '<div>\n<h1><a href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/"><br /><img src="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/images/logo.png" alt="San Antonio Adoption Agencies for Pregnant Teens" /></a></h1>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<ul><li><a title="Home" href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/"><span>Home</span></a></li>\n<li><a title="Services" href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/services.html"><span>Services</span></a></li>\n<li><a title="Our Clients" href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/our-clients.html"><span>Our Clients</span></a></li>\n<li><a title="About Us" href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/about-us.html"><span>About Us</span></a></li>\n<li><a title="Contact Us" href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/contact.html"><span>Contact Us</span></a></li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div><img src="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/modules/mod_image_show_gk4/cache/slide-3gk-is-95.jpg" alt="" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><img src="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/images/ac-arrow.png" alt="ac-arrow" width="71" height="62" /></p>\n<h1>The San Antonio Adoption Agency for Pregnant Women</h1>\n<p><strong><strong>We are a Local Adoption Agency here to meet your needs!</strong></strong></p>\n<p>Our mission at Adoption Choices of Texas is to serve you, the birth mother, during the adoption process. To meet your needs, here are just some of the services that we provide:</p>\n<ul><li>A Personal Counselor to talk to - someone who has seen situations similar to yours and can provide helpful, friendly, non-judgmental advice</li>\n<li>Medical Expenses</li>\n<li>Choice of Adoptive Family</li>\n<li>Legal Expenses</li>\n<li>Attorney</li>\n</ul><p>All of our adoption services are locally based right here in Texas.</p>\n<p>Learn More about all of the wonderful <a href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/services.html">adoption agency services</a> we offer to birth moms</p>\n<h2>Clients We Serve</h2>\n<p>We specialize in helping pregnant young women who want to learn more about adoption.</p>\n<p>We have worked with many Texas clients in the past - but we realize that each and every pregnancy situation is unique.</p>\n<p><a href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/our-clients.html">Learn more</a> about our approach towards clients, and read testimonials from some of our past clients.</p>\n<h2>Contact Us Any Time</h2>\n<p>We make it easy for you to contact us throughout the website. Feel free to find the information you need on the site. Then when you''re ready, feel free to contact us for a confidential no pressure - no obligation conversation with one of our birth mother counselors.</p>\n<p>We understand that this is a challenging time in your life, and we would like to provide you with all of the facts so that you can make an informed decision. Feel free to <a href="http://adoptionsanantonio.org/contact.html">contact us</a> when you''re ready. 855-304-4673</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Contact Us for Help</p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<h2>Learn How We Can Help You.</h2>\n<p><strong>210-787-3900</strong></p>\n<p>Call or complete the form and an adoption counselor will contact you.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h1>Adoption Choices of Texas adoption agency for pregnant women and birth mom</h1>\n<h1><span>El</span><span> </span><span>San Antonio</span><span> </span><span>agencia de adopción</span><span> </span><span>para las mujeres embarazadas</span><br /><br /><span>Somos una</span><span> </span><span>agencia de adopción local</span><span> </span><span>aquí para satisfacer sus</span><span> </span><span>necesidades!</span><br /><br /><span>Nuestra misión en</span><span> </span><span>Opciones</span><span> </span><span>de Adopción de</span><span> </span><span>Texas es</span><span> </span><span>para servirle a usted</span><span>, la madre biológica</span><span>,</span><span> </span><span>durante el</span><span> </span><span>proceso de adopción.</span><span> </span><span>Para satisfacer sus necesidades</span><span>, aquí son sólo</span><span> </span><span>algunos de los servicios</span><span> </span><span>que ofrecemos</span><span>:</span><br /><br /><span>Un asesor personal</span><span> </span><span>para hablar con</span><span> </span><span>-</span><span> </span><span>alguien que ha visto</span><span> </span><span>situaciones</span><span> </span><span>similares a la suya</span><span> </span><span>y puede proporcionar</span><span> </span><span>muy servicial, amable</span><span>, sin prejuicios</span><span> </span><span>consejos</span><br /><span>Gastos Médicos</span><br /><span>Elección de</span><span> </span><span>la Familia Adoptiva</span><br /><span>Gastos Legales</span><br /><span>abogado</span><br /><span>Todos nuestros servicios de</span><span> </span><span>adopción</span><span> </span><span>son de base local</span><span> </span><span>aquí en Texas</span><span>.</span><br /><br /><span>Más información</span><span> </span><span>acerca de todos los</span><span> </span><span>servicios de las agencias</span><span> </span><span>de adopción</span><span>maravillosas</span><span> </span><span>que ofrecemos a</span><span> </span><span>las madres</span><span> </span><span>de nacimiento</span><br /><br /><span>Clientes a quienes servimos</span><br /><br /><span>Nos especializamos</span><span> </span><span>en ayudar a</span><span> </span><span>las jóvenes embarazadas</span><span> </span><span>que deseen aprender</span><span> </span><span>más sobre la adopción</span><span>.</span><br /><br /><span>Hemos trabajado con</span><span> </span><span>muchos clientes</span><span> </span><span>de Texas</span><span> </span><span>en el pasado</span><span> </span><span>-</span><span>, pero</span><span> </span><span>nos damos cuenta de</span><span> </span><span>que la situación de</span><span> </span><span>todos y cada</span><span> </span><span>embarazo es único</span><span>.</span><br /><br /><span>Aprenda más sobre</span><span> </span><span>nuestro enfoque</span><span> </span><span>hacia los clientes</span><span>, y</span><span> </span><span>leer los testimonios</span><span> </span><span>de algunos de nuestros</span><span> </span><span>últimos clientes</span><span>.</span><br /><br /><span>Póngase en contacto con</span><span> </span><span>nosotros en cualquier momento</span><br /><br /><span>Te lo ponemos fácil</span><span> </span><span>para que usted pueda</span><span> </span><span>comunicarse con nosotros</span><span> </span><span>a través del</span><span> </span><span>sitio web.</span><span> </span><span>Siéntase libre</span><span> </span><span>para encontrar</span><span> </span><span>la información que necesita</span><span> </span><span>en el sitio.</span><span> </span><span>Luego, cuando</span><span> </span><span>esté listo,</span><span> </span><span>no dude en</span><span> </span><span>contactar con nosotros para</span><span> </span><span>una evaluación confidencial</span><span> </span><span>sin presión</span><span> </span><span>-</span><span> </span><span>ninguna conversación</span><span> </span><span>obligación con</span><span> </span><span>uno de nuestros consejeros</span><span> </span><span>de nacimiento</span><span> </span><span>la madre</span><span>.</span><br /><br /><span>Entendemos que este</span><span> </span><span>es</span><span> </span><span>un momento difícil</span><span> </span><span>en su vida</span><span>, y</span><span> </span><span>nos gustaría</span><span> </span><span>ofrecerle</span><span> </span><span>todos los hechos</span><span> </span><span>para que usted pueda</span><span> </span><span>tomar una decisión informada</span><span>.</span><span> </span><span>No dude</span><span> </span><span>en contactar con nosotros</span><span> </span><span>cuando esté listo</span><span>.</span><span> </span><span>855-304-4673</span><br /><br /><span>Póngase en contacto con</span><span> </span><span>nosotros para obtener ayuda</span><br /><br /><span>Aprenda cómo</span><span> </span><span>podemos ayudarle</span><span>.</span><br /><br /><span>210-787-3900</span><br /><br /></h1>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Adoption Choices or Texas', 2934, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1337623677, 0),
(781, '<div>\n<div>Adoptive Parents</div>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" align="center"><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" width="60%" valign="top">\n<p>Your family profile is often a birth parent''s first introduction to your family, so it should provide a picture of what the child''s life will be like with you.</p>\n<p>Begin with any informal greeting that is comfortable. Describe to the birth parents how you feel about being considered. You could also use this first paragraph to acknowledge their courage in deciding to make an adoption plan.</p>\n<h4>DO NOT...</h4>\n<ol><li>try to present yourselves as what you think a birth parent might want, but as you really are.</li>\n<li>include identifying information (last names, address, telephone number, name of workplace, or church), unless your intermediary has requested it.</li>\n<li>hand write information unless specifically requested by your intermediary.</li>\n<li>orget to ask your intermediary for specific guidelines of information to be included, such as number of photographs, length, etc.</li>\n</ol></td>\n</tr><tr><td colspan="2"> </td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h3>Background Check Instructions</h3>\n<ul><li><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/Washoe%20County%20Sheriff%20and%20Carson%20City%20Fingerprints%20info.doc">Washoe County Sheriff</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/Fingerprint%20Instruction.LasVegas.Initial.doc">Las Vegas Fingerprint Instruction</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/Fingerprint%20Instruction.Henderson.Initial.doc">Henderson Fingerprint Instruction</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/Fingerprint%20Release%20Consent.doc">Fingerprint Release Consent</a></li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h3>Home Study Instructions</h3>\n<ul><li><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/docs%20needed%20home%20study.doc">Documents Needed to Complete Home Study</a></li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/Nevada-application.doc"><span>Download Application</span></a><br /><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=58"><span>Need a Home Study</span></a><br /><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/PostPlacementAdvise-AdoptiveParentsfromBirthParents.pdf"><span>Post Placement Advise</span></a><br /><a href="http://www.surveymonkey.com/s/CDZXS9T" target="_blank"><span>Survey for parents</span></a><br /><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/Nevada-application.designated.doc">Designated Adoption Application</a><br /><span>Adoptive Parents are only to use this application if they have located their own birth mother and are asking our agency to process all the paperwork.</span></div>\n<div>\n<h3>Preparing a Family Profile</h3>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tbody><tr><td><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=54&amp;Itemid=77">Biographies</a></td>\n</tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=55&amp;Itemid=78">Your Family &amp; Community</a></td>\n</tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=56&amp;Itemid=79">Life as Parents &amp; Child Desired</a></td>\n</tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=57&amp;Itemid=80">Relationship with Birthmothers &amp; Photographs</a></td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</div>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Adoptive Parents', 2935, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1337625391, 0),
(782, '<div>\n<div>\n<div><br /><br /><img src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/header/default/pregnancy.gif" alt="Birth Mother Contact Form" /><p><a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=view&amp;id=41&amp;Itemid=45">How do I start?</a><br /><br /><span>Birth Parent Hotline 24 hr/7 days 800-681-4673 (Hope)</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<ul><li><img title="Narrow screen" src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/user-screen1.png" alt="Narrow screen resolution" /></li><li><img title="Wide screen" src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/user-screen2-hilite.png" alt="Wide screen resolution" /></li>\n</ul><ul><li><img title="Decrease font size" src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/user-decrease.png" alt="Decrease font size" /></li><li><img title="Default size" src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/user-reset.png" alt="Default font size" /></li><li><img title="Increase font size" src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/user-increase.png" alt="Increase font size" /></li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n<span><a href="http://adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/">Home</a> <img src="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/templates/acnevada/images/arrow.png" alt="" /> Uplanned Preganancy</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>Unplanned Preganancy</div>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" align="center"><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" width="60%" valign="top">\n<p>If you are experiencing an unplanned pregnancy and do not feel you are ready to parent, you may wish to consider adoption. We will be happy to discuss all options related to the pregnancy with you.</p>\n<p>If you do choose adoption, our agency provides each birth mother with her own personal birth parent counselor who guides you through the process in person. She can help you get to and from doctor appointments, set up housing, insurance appointments, such as Medicaid, WIC and food stamps if you qualify. Most importantly, she can talk to you and listen to your feelings while going through the process of adoption. The birth parent counselor helps you find the plan that is right for you!</p>\n<p>Services available to you are tailored to your specific needs. They may include, but are not limited to:</p>\n<ul><li>Appropriate Living Expenses </li>\n<li>Medical Care</li>\n<li>Counseling</li>\n<li>Your own attorney and legal fees paid</li>\n<li>Choose and meet your adoptive family</li>\n</ul><p>We would love to answer any of your questions about our program, and to assist you in making an adoption plan that will work for you. You may contact us at 1-800-681-4673, or (775) 825-HOPE, or you may e-mail us at <a href="mailto:adoptioninfo@adoptionchoicesofnevada.org">adoptioninfo@adoptionchoicesofnevada.org</a> and we will help you with any questions you may have.</p>\n<p>If you would like to download our Birth parent Intake Packet, please <a href="http://www.adoptionchoicesofnevada.org/app/birthmother.pdf">click here.</a></p>\n</td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Unplanned Pregnancy', 2935, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1337625509, 0),
(783, 'Ragan was born and raised in KY with her parents and younger sister. Majority of her family lived in the area. After high school, she went to college in KY, and she received a bachelor''s degree in nursing.  A few months after graduating, Eric and her married in Ragan''s childhood church.  She worked about 3 years at a local hospital before joining the Navy. Since she had her degree in nursing, she was an officer in the Navy. She was station at Naval Air Station Jacksonville.  During her time in the Navy, she was deployed to the Middle East as a Navy Nurse.  She had a honorable discharged from the Navy. After she discharged, Eric and her moved to KY until she got a job in TN and moved. We left FL to be closer to our family.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT RAGAN', 2901, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1337647154, 0),
(784, 'Eric''s dad was in the Air Force  and was station in NY when Eric was born. After his dad discharged from the military, his mom, dad, and older brother moved back to KY where he grew up. His parents divorced while he was young; but, his dad remarried and had another son.  When Eric graduated from high school, he joined the Air Force. He was deployed to Turkey during Desert Storm. He was stationed at Lakenheath Air Force Base in England. He had a honorable discharged from the military. After discharge, he went back to KY and went to college for a few years. After he quit college, he met Ragan, and a year and half later they were married. Eric was working at a factory before Ragan joined the Navy, and we moved to FL. Eric worked at a movie theater while we were in FL. It was nice because we could see new movies for free. When Ragan was discharged from the Navy, we moved back to KY where Eric worked at a temp agnency. When we moved to TN, it was decided that Eric would be a stay at home spouse, and that he would take care of our child while Ragan worked. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT ERIC', 2901, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1337651902, 0),
(785, '  We are both from large extended families that we love to spend time with.  Most of our families lives in KY and TN.  We talk to our family on a regular basis on the phone, and visit them frequently. Over the years, we have taken family members on vacation with us to places such as Branson, MO; Daytona Beach; Orlando, FL; and Williamsburg, VA.  Also, we have taken small day and over night trips with family members to the zoo, theme parks, and shopping.  We like to take our family members to restaurants, sight seeing, and to the movies.\n\n     Through out the year, we have many family meals.  We have meals during the holidays such as Mother''s Day, Thanksgiving, and Christmas.  We have so many places to go and family members to see for Christmas Day and Eve since we are from a large family.  Also, we have other special meals for anniversaries and birthdays.  At times, we have cookouts, and will roast marshmallows and hot dogs.  Also, we have small home cook meals with our grandparents, parents, siblings, nieces, and nephews.\n\n     Our family is very excited and supportive about us adopting.  They cannot wait to have a new member of the family to spoil and love.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR FAMILY', 2901, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1337651005, 0),
(787, 'Kian is four years old.  He is a loving, social child who loves kids, bigger and younger. He loves to give babies kisses and hugs and will often ask to help feed or hold the babies in his life.  Kian’s current fascination is all things dinosaurs!  We just celebrated his birthday with a dinosaur theme that consisted of finding dinosaur fossils and breaking open dinosaur eggs as party bags.  He loves books and we make weekly trips to the library.  We will often have book marathons where we read 10-12 books at one time!  Kian also loves running around outside exploring rocks, flowers, dirt...you name it, he''ll find something fascinating about it!  He swims almost daily and can swim independently. He loves to do cannonballs or dive in with a cry of "To infinity and beyond!"  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Kian', 1923, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1352941533, 0),
(788, '<div>\n<div>HOPEFUL WAITING FAMILY INTERESTED IN INFNT OR CHILD DOPTION</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h1>Hopeful waiting family interested in infant or child adoption</h1>\n<h2>Hopeful waiting parents interested in infant or child adoption</h2>\n<h3>Hopeful waiting couple interested in infant or child adoption</h3>\n</div>\n</div>', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Tags', 1772, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1338150487, 0),
(789, '<span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;">We have a lot of love to share!\n<br>\n<br>\nWe knew that we wanted to add to children to our family. We were able to get pregnant, but sadly unable to bring the babies to full term. After our miscarriages, we felt that God must have a different plan for us. \n<br>\n<br>\nThanks to positive adoption examples within our families and among our friends, we know there are courageous birth parents out there searching for a forever family to love their children. We are anxious to find our match.\n<br>\n<br>\nPlease feel free to contact us at <b>kimkev1101@gmail.com</b></span>\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Why We Want to Adopt', 2952, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1345209177, 0),
