(800, 'I grew up in Maryland, very close to the University of Maryland.  I am the youngest of three - I have an older brother and an older sister.  My parents live nearby and we see them often.  \n\nMy sister and brother-in-law live about an hour away.  We see them often as well, and my sister and I will often get together to go shopping.  My sister has two grown children which would be my niece and nephew.  We are looking forward to a family wedding next spring when my nephew will be getting married.  My niece is getting ready to move out on her own to live and work in Florida - I am very close to her and will miss her very much.\n\n\nMy brother and sister-in-law live in New Jersey.  We see them a few times a year.  They have three boys.  Their youngest is Colby''s age.  Colby and his cousin have a great time together.  The oldest is about to go off to college while the middle one is starting high school.\n\n\nFamily events and holidays are lots of fun because I have a lot of aunts, uncles, and cousins who live nearby.  It is not unusual to have 15-20 people for Thanksgiving and Christmas dinner.  There is nothing more important to me than family.  I consider myself very lucky that I have always had such large family gatherings on holidays all of my life.  With so many people and kids, there is always a lot of chaos and laughter.  I always look forward to getting the whole family together, especially since I''ve been cooking Christmas dinner the last few years.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Tracy&amp;#039;s Extended Family', 1078, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1339450017, 0),
(801, 'Erik also grew up in Maryland, not far from the University of Maryland.  We both went to the University of Maryland, but we actually met each other while working together at Sears.\n\nErik is the middle child of three.  He has an older sister who was adopted before Erik came along.  Erik also has a younger brother.  Erik''s mother and stepfather still live in Maryland as do his father and stepmother.  We see all of Erik''s family often, sometimes even meeting in the middle of Maryland and Virginia for a lunch or dinner.  \n\nErik''s sister and brother-in-law live in Maryland.  Their daughter/our niece just began high school.  Erik''s brother and sister-in-law live in Seattle.  We usually see them every other summer and always look forward to spending time with them.  When they visit, we usually all go on vacation together at the beach.  We have many happy memories of family vacations with them as well as Erik''s mom at Rehoboth Beach, Delaware especially.  We enjoy spending time with our niece and nephew who are high school and middle school age.  Colby loves hanging out with his boy cousin and they will spend all day boogie boarding.  Last summer, we met our newest niece for the first time who is about to turn three this fall.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Erik&#039;s Extended Family', 1078, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1339448021, 0),
