(812, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/3c335efcb487630e6f0f2db4233136e9.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="220" /></span>Thank you so much for considering us as parents for your child. We admire you for making what may be the hardest decision of your life. We think that your courage shows how much you love your child and want the best for him/her. If you choose us, we promise that your child will always know your adoption decision was a selfless act of love, and you will always be deeply respected in our home. </span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">It’s hard to express the love, consideration and respect we have for you and how much it means that you have considered us as parents for your child. We want you to know that we will always discuss adoption openly and honestly with your child. He or she will always know how special and courageous you are and that your adoption decision was made out of love by choosing the best for him/her. We look forward to providing you letters and pictures as your child grows, if you</span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> desire. </span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Please know that we will do our very best to provide every opportunity for your child to reach their fullest potential. We will never be able to thank you enough for the chance you are giving us, for your trust in us. We want to be the best parents to your child. Never forget that you are also part of our hearts. We hope to hear from you soon.<span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/ST_Engag_035.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="240" /></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Love,</span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><em><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Tim and Sabrina</span></em></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'THANK YOU FOR THINKING OF US!', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339959154, 0),
(813, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_1066.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="188" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong>We live our life to its fullest</strong>.</span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;">We hope you can see how much we love having a good time. We believe that life is all about making memories, being grateful for each moment and appreciating the most simple things. For instance, being from Brazil Sabrina had never experienced snow. On vacation, while visiting Tim’s family, Sabrina saw snow for the first time, she jumped into it trying to make a snow angel and could not believe how cold it was especially wearing just jeans! We had so much fun freezing our bottoms, we could not stop laughing. We want to bring many opportunities for your child’s first experiences.</span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"> </span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_1628.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="200" /></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong>Polish-American &amp; Brazilian: a perfect match! </strong>Sabrina was born and raised in Brazil and Tim is Polish- American so we come from two extremely different backgrounds and we blend each of our cultures and traditions. Sabrina speaks Portuguese. Preparing to visit Sabrina’s family in Brazil, Tim signed up for Portuguese class in order to communicate with her family. Once we arrived in Brazil, despite all his efforts, he only felt comfortable saying a few words. Sabrina’s family decided they love Tim “speaking Portuguese or not” and your child will be raised to learn both languages and <img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture1.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="246" />cultures.  We want to learn about your family traditions and culture, so we can also incorporate them into our family.</span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">                      </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">                      </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"> </span></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"> </span></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"> </span></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"> </span></strong></span></span></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/center2.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="150" /></span></strong></span></span></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;">Our Christian faith has always been important to us.</span></strong><span style="font-size:small;">We don’t see  religion as a denomination, but as a link with God. Our Christian Center brings people from all religions together where we study the teachings of Jesus Christ. His teachings tell us “to love one another and do unto others…” When we were dating, a friend of Sabrina’s, whom Tim barely knew, was down on her luck with two young daughters to support. Afforded the opportunity, Tim helped Sabrina’s friend by providing her housing for a month when she lost her job. To this day, her friend reminds Sabrina how grateful she is toward this charity. We look forward to teaching your child about God’s love.</span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'GET TO KNOW US', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339821100, 0),
(818, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture_013.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="200" /><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Since high school, Sabrina has enjoyed working with <strong>computers.</strong> A few years ago, she decided to build her own desktop. She bought all the parts and in less than 3 days,  “Baby Blue”, as she calls it was up and running. In her free time at home, she is always setting up and  fixing electronic devices for us and for others. She looks forward to introducing your child to this skill, so if interested he/she will also be taught how to build and repair computers.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_2636.JPG" alt="" width="150" height="279" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Sabrina <strong>loves visiting NASA</strong>. Growing up, she had a fascination with how life would be like in outer space. She always dreamed of becoming an astronaut. She constantly told her parents, that one day she would visit NASA, see a shuttle launch and take a picture with an astronaut. These dreams became reality when we were able to go to NASA and see the final launch of the Discovery shuttle. On that same day, she was able to meet and talk to an ex-astronaut. She wants to provide these opportunities for your child to chase his/her dreams as well.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/alaska.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="236" />Photography </strong>is another passion of Sabrina’s. She can’t wait to take pictures of your child. On a recent trip to Alaska over a 7 day period she took over 1800 pictures! Do you know how that translates to your child? We would gladly share your child’s pictures with you, if you desire. It’s also our plan one day to take your child to see the majestic Alaska landscapes. <span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong></strong></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Sabrina&#039;s Interests', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339820203, 0),
(814, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_1832.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="200" /><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;">Tim went to dinner with his friends at a restaurant where Sabrina worked. We noticed each other right away. Tim took a seat where he could catch Sabrina’s eye. She walked past Tim’s table on more than one occasion but didn’t say a word always taking a glance at him as she passed by. Tim decided that rather than ask for her number, he would come back another day soon. Sabrina had also been thinking about what to do. For the first time on her life, she decided to give out her number! So as Tim was leaving she nervously gave him a business card with her name and number on it. He was shocked and relieved! We went out on a date within a couple of days and have been together ever since.</span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;">When we learned about our infertility, we knew adoption was for us. We made our decision through prayer, love and the strong desire to become parents. We attribute our strong marriage to the <strong>principles  of our faith, respect, trust and open communication with one another</strong>. We are ready to share our life with your child within these same principles. We are thrilled for the opportunity to build our family through adoption.</span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'BECOMING A COUPLE', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339825673, 0),
(815, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/christmas_2011_2271.JPG" alt="" width="200" height="150" /><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Tim never ceases to amaze me with his <strong>ability to make everyone comfortable</strong>.  He has a <strong>positive personality</strong>.  He always tells me that any challenge can be overcome with hard work and determination.  He learned these traits watching how his parents treated themselves and others.  He looks forward to <strong>inspiring your child to be the finest person that they can be.</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_7042.JPG" alt="" width="150" height="200" />Tim <strong>cares deeply for his family</strong>. We spend a lot of our vacations going to visit Tim’s family. They always talk of their childhood when playing baseball in the back yard, football in the front yard, riding bikes and building a snowman. For instance, they talk about making their own baseball diamond every summer. It took many hours to mow the grass in the field behind the house. There was one catch though, in the middle of the field, there were two trees! This didn’t stop them from playing the game they loved from sunrise till sunset. <strong>Tim looks forward to becoming a dad so he can teach your child about things he enjoys.</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_1055.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="150" /></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:small;">Tim will be a very involved father and looks forward to having a lot of fun with your child. </span></strong><span style="font-size:small;">He has a <strong>warm</strong> heart that makes it hard for him to say no.  Children in the neighborhood are always at our door asking if he has time to play. On a recent vacation, Tim’s niece and nephew asked him to go outside and play in the snow with them.  There was a foot of snow on the ground and the temperature was about 22 degrees.  He borrowed a hat and some gloves and braved the temperature to have some fun in the snow!!!!</span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Meet Tim (By Sabrina)', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339819800, 0),
(816, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/DSC04337.JPG" alt="" width="200" height="244" /><span style="font-size:small;">Tim <strong>loves chocolate</strong>.   Sabrina has given Tim a giant Easter egg is the tradition in Brazil. Tim looks forward every year to see what kind and “size” of egg she will bring him. His favorite one was the first time Sabrina gave him an egg, because it was a surprise. Tim can’t wait to see your child receive their egg.</span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"> </span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"> </span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"> </span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"> </span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_0727.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="150" />Tim has always been <strong>involved in sports</strong>.  His current <strong>passion is golf.</strong> He enjoys the opportunity to spend time with his friends in a casual but competitive environment. He has been playing golf for the last 12 years but he is still trying to make his first hole in one! No matter how he plays he can’t wait to get back and try again for a hole in one. Tim is already shopping for golf clothes and clubs for your child.</span> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:right;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;">T</span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;">im <strong>enjoys being the “official” Santa Claus at the Christian community center.</strong> It brings so much joy to see the children’s excitement when Santa arrives. Most of the children are speechless and have an amazed look in their eyes when asked “What do you want for Christmas?” <img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_0728.JPG" alt="" width="300" height="206" /><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture11.png" alt="" width="300" height="248" /></span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Tim&#039;s Interests', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339824631, 0),
(817, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_0203.JPG" alt="" width="250" height="188" /><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Sabrina is a very <strong>spiritual, and courageous person who stands up for what she believes in</strong>. She believes that everything happens for a reason and any situation in life leads to growth as a person. Her favorite (and frequent) saying is: <strong>“Yes, it can be done! God is in our side”.</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;"><img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_1949.JPG" alt="" width="250" height="188" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">                                                  </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Sabrina has a very beautiful smile and laugh which makes everyone feel welcome when they meet her. She has a <strong>kind nature</strong> which allows her to be a great and trusted friend and wonderful wife. When someone needs her help she is always ready and has the right words of encouragement. She also has a <strong>great sense of humor </strong>and it allows her to laugh at herself and the things she does. For instance, we always joke about her pronunciation of some English words in a Portuguese accent. Sabrina <strong>looks forward to helping your child become self-confident in all aspects of his/her personality.</strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/IMG_2901.JPG" alt="" width="150" height="200" /></span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Sabrina is <strong>adventurous and has a passion for sun and snow</strong>. In the summer, she enjoys spending time at the beach searching for shells and body surfing in the waves no matter how big they are. In the winter, when we travelled to visit my family, she enjoys building snow men and snow angels in the bitter cold! We will make sure that your child enjoys all the seasons of the year.</span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;"><img style="vertical-align:text-top;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/c53.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="150" /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/butter2.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="162" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Since childhood, Sabrina has had a special place in her heart for <strong>butterflies</strong> because of their beauty. Today, they have a totally different meaning connected to her faith. A butterfly is born through the life of a caterpillar. They <strong>symbolize the opportunity of second chances</strong>. On a recent trip, I surprised her by taking a detour to a butterfly garden. She was in awe! They danced through the air and landed on her; we spent hours watching and taking pictures of these beautiful creatures. We want to give your child every opportunity to fulfill his/her destiny.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Meet Sabrina (By Tim)', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339820863, 0),
(819, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">If you choose us your baby will have <strong>2 grandmothers and 1 grandfather, 6 uncles, 2 aunts with 8 cousins so far.</strong> We both have been blessed to grow up in homes with loving and supportive parents who always wanted the very best for us. Our parents have taught us the value of a positive work ethic and responsibility.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture4.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="258" />Even though Tim’s family doesn’t live in the same state, we do communicate regularly and visit one another spending vacations, special occasions and holidays together. One year when we visited, we took his mother on a day trip to a memorable vacation cabin on a lake, that the family had rented when Tim was a child. We look forward to making our own memorable vacations with your child. <img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture3.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="240" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture2.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" />Sabrina’s family lives in Brazil.  They visit often, spending a minimum of two months with us. While they are here we spend much of our time together going to theme parks, cooking brazilian dishes, and shopping. They look forward to helping Sabrina teach your child Portuguese and many other brazilian traditions.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture5.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="360" />Every year on our trip to visit Tim’s family in Michigan, we plan a day at a Detroit Tigers game. This year, it just happened to be his mother and niece’s birthday.  The family had t-shirts made to wear in celebration, surprising both of them.  We look forward to bringing you child with us as we continue our annual tradition of a day at the ballpark.<img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/DSC_4155.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="134" /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339824705, 0),
(820, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong>Christmas and Easter are our favorite holidays</strong> because of our Christian faith. Tim always encourages Sabrina to bring as many traditions from Brazil to incorporate in our home and Sabrina also loves his Polish –American culture.</span><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture10.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="263" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">It has always been a <strong>Christmas tradition </strong>within Tim’s family to make sugar cookies for Santa on Christmas Eve. Every year we join our niece and nephew making cookies then writing a letter to Santa before going to bed.</span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Before exchanging gifts Christmas morning, Tim’s family enjoys cooking their traditional breakfast. Here is Tim and his brother making polish pancakes, hash browns, and scrambled eggs.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> <img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture9.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="249" /></span><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Growing up, Sabrina only saw Christmas trees in movies. It is not tradition to have one in Brazil.  Upon moving to the USA, she was so excited to have her first Christmas tree. The first tree was a small 3’ with just a few decorations.  Now she has a large 6’ tree. Each year she finds ornaments that have a special meaning.  One of her favorites is Santa riding the space shuttle.  This is a reminder of all the dreams she has realized in her life.  Dreams that she and Tim want to share with your child!</span> <span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">We began our <strong>Easter tradition </strong>by exchanging <strong>giant chocolate eggs</strong>, as Sabrina’s father gave to her as a child.  When Sabrina was very young, she searched her home trying to find the egg that her father had for her.  Once she found it she would caress the egg every day, waiting for Easter. Her father calls every year to ask if she still gives her egg this special attention.  Tim enjoys coloring eggs because as a child it was tradition to color eggs along with his siblings. <strong>We look forward to sharing these traditions with your child.</strong>  <strong>We would also like to <img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture7.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="284" />know some of your traditions to bring to our family.<span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/DSC_3426.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="134" /></span></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong> </strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Celebrating Holidays', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339824436, 0),
(821, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture12.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="164" />Our home is in a suburban neighborhood full of <strong>young families</strong>. It’s <strong>cozy</strong>, yet has <strong>plenty of room</strong>. When we were looking to buy a home our first thought was about <strong>location and schools</strong>. There are great elementary and high schools nearby. We have a <strong>huge backyard</strong>, which we plan to turn into a playground so we can invite your child’s friends for fun play days. <img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture13.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="169" /></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong>Kids from our neighborhood love playing ball outside, riding their bikes, and swimming in our community pool.</strong> One day when Sabrina came home from work, she could not find Tim. She decided to check outside and to her surprise, there he was playing basketball with our neighbors’ kids! Now, they quite often knock on our door to invite Tim to play. They have a lot of fun and get very excited when Tim is able to play.  Tim is always ready to play and is prepared to come home daily and join your child in whatever activities he/she is involved in.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339825039, 0),
(822, '<p style="text-align:justify;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture14.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="235" /><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">We love going to all the <strong>theme parks </strong>because we feel like children again. Sabrina’s <strong>favorite attractions </strong>are the rollercoasters and Tim loves the 3D simulators.  When Sabrina was a child her family in Brazil could not afford to bring her to Disney. Once she moved to the  USA, she made her dream come true. Recently, during one of her family’s visits, she surprised her parents by bringing them to Disney. We got very emotional when we saw her mom and dad crying after seeing Mickey and Cinderella’s castle. Sabrina was able to make not only hers but her parents’ dream come true as well. We look forward to taking your child with us and making some wonderful memories.</span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture15.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="290" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/49c6e01591d6313cdcc400273cfebff5.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="135" /></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"> </p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="text-align:justify;"><span style="font-family:&quot;comic sans ms&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:small;">Here we are welcoming our youngest niece. She is the newest addition to a wonderful best friend’s family, along with three adorable boys. Every time we visit them, they ask about when your child will join them to play! <strong>This baby girl will be one of your child’s closest friends.</strong> We always have a wonderful time with these kids. One time we were all together in their kitchen trying to make fondue. All eyes were fixed on the  chocolate fountain waiting for it to be ready, so we could eat the delicious strawberries dipped in chocolate.<img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture16.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="211" /> <img style="float:left;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/TimandSabrina/Picture17.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="303" /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'WE LOVE CHILDREN: Being around them and acting like them!', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339959257, 0),
(823, '<p>Email: <a href="mailto:timsab@hotmail.com">timsab@hotmail.com</a></p>\n<p> </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'CONTACT INFO', 895, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1339825853, 0),
(858, '<p>Paul and Carey have been married for 14 years.  They have a wonderful, Christ-centered marriage and are excited to adopt another child into their family and share their faith in Jesus Christ.  They are each other''s best friend and their life is full of close extended family, friends and good food that Paul loves to prepare for everyone.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Paul and Carey both graduated from the University of North Texas.  Carey has a degree in broadcast journalism and has had a successful career in public relations.  She works from home, which gives her the flexibility to take care of their home and family and spend quality time with her daughter.   Paul has a business degree and a Masters in International Finance and currently works for the FDIC.  They are financially secure and own their own home. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We have traveled all over the world on mission trips.  Our first mission was to an orphanage in Romania.  That is where the Lord called us to adopt and Romania will always hold a special place in our hearts.  We have also been to Turkey, Kenya, Ecuador and Bolivia on mission trips working with children.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Isabella is now four and she is so excited to be a big sister.  She prays every night for her “Baby Brother or Sister” and tells us that Jesus is bringing him/her.  We adopted Isabella privately and were blessed to hold her in our arms on the day she was born.  That was the best day of our life!  Her birth mother wanted a closed adoption, and although we hope she one day changes her mind, we do respect her wishes.  However, we are very excited about open adoption and the extended family we hope to develop with the birth mother.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>A typical day in the our family usually begins with lots of snuggles.  Our daughter Isabella loves to dance, play princess dress-up and tea party.  She attends an all Spanish-speaking school and plays the cello. She also loves to help her Papa cook.  During the cooler months we take nightly walks to the park with the whole family. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We have a large, close-knit family who are very supportive of adoption and most all of them live within an hour of us.  Grandparents on both sides have been very supportive of adoption and have been caregivers for Isabella when we have a business meeting, are out of town or on date night.</p>\n<p> </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR FAMILY', 3257, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342068469, 0),
(824, 'E-mail: <a href="mailto:adoption@makingourfamilycomplete.com">adoption@makingourfamilycomplete.com</a><BR> \nTollfree: 1-866-580-2424<BR>\nWebsite: <a href="http://www.makingourfamilycomplete.com">http://www.makingourfamilycomplete.com</A>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact Us', 929, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1340553420, 0),
(825, 'About the Girls- Ashley and Tiffany have always been very adventurous and imaginative. They both get excellent grades in school and are involved in many activities such as student council, media, track, art, and reading club. Tiffany is a great artist and can usually be found drawing. She also loves to play the guitar. Tiffany is our social butterfly so her friends can usually be seen coming and going. Ashley is our dancer. She is always dancing or singing around the house. She also loves to  play outside and loves to help mom.\n\n\nThe girls have been begging for a brother for years. Like mom and dad they feel that we are missing a sweet baby boy in our family. They can’t wait to play with him, feed him, and teach him wonderful things.\n\nFrom Ashley- We are a really close family. If anyone is ever struggling the rest of the family always helps out. I’ve wanted a brother my whole life. When mom and dad told me we were going to adopt I cried I was so happy! I can’t wait to meet him!\n\nFrom Tiffany- Mom and dad are the best! I think we have the best family and I cant wait to share it with our brother. We might have to make a schedule to spend time with him to be fair because we all want to! He will never be alone and he will always be loved!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About the Girls', 3117, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1340570274, 0),
(826, '<p style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;color:#ff3366;font-size:12px;">About the Girls- <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/RandyCrystal/big_sisters.jpg" alt="" width="72" height="96" /></p>\n<p><span style="color:#ff0000;font-size:small;">Since the girls could talk they''ve been asking for a brother. They love each other deeply and are best friends, but have always felt like they were missing a piece to their sibling puzzle. The day we told them we were going to adopt they started crying and cheering with excitement. </span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#ff0000;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#ff0000;font-size:small;">Ashley is 14. She is always super helpful. Dance is her favorite pasttime and she is such a joy to watch. She is in highschool and loves it. Ashley is an encourager and is always thinking about others. She has loved her little sister from the moment she met her. They have always been best friends.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#ff0000;font-size:small;">Tiffany is 12 and in 6th grade. She plays the guitar, and loves to bless God with her music. Tiffany is very artistic and uses her talents to bring joy to others. She looks up to her big sister and can always be found with her.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#ff0000;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#ff0000;font-size:small;">Neither one of them can wait for their brother to arrive. I think we may actually have to make a schedule to spend time with him in order to combat fights over him : )</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About the Girls', 3117, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1353334458, 0),
(980, 'I don''t know your specific story.  I can''t imagine all that you are going through.  I do know that you are amazing and strong and a beautiful soul.  I know that you love the life growing inside of you.  I know it is complicated.  I know that we were meant to meet and to help each other.\n\nEver since I was a little girl, no more than 10, I have dreamed of a child that was a child of my heart and not my body.  I knew that another woman would carry my kindred child inside of her and that I would raise this child.  I have known this child, in my heart, and love this child unconditionally already.\n\nYour child will always know that you love them.  Your child will grow up knowing their story.  I will always speak with gratitude and love and respect of you.  I make this promise to you.\n\nI also promised to now and forever love your baby.  I will guide, teach, parent, play, laugh, heal, protect and give this life everything I have to offer.  I will do this when they are happy and when they are sad.  I will do this when they are angry or naughty or frustrated.  Through it all, I will guard, love and cherish this special being.\n\nI promise.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Rosebelle&#039;s Promise', 3735, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1346871493, 0),
(827, 'We believe it is important for families to spend time together, have fun together, and laugh together.  We have an annual tradition of visiting our state fair and riding the giant slide.  We love all the food at the fair, and we always try to find something new.  One year, Joel even tried alligator on a stick!  Whether we’re playing at home or out-and-about, your child’s life will be filled with plenty of fun family activities.\n\n\nWe believe that reading with children from birth, which we have done with our daughter, helps foster a lifelong love of learning.  We look forward to doing the same with your baby.  Shanyn’s favorite book to read is Barnyard Dance because there are fun rhymes that babies and toddlers love.  For older kids, she likes Curious George and Clifford books since Shanyn remembers enjoying those as a child!  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'On Parenting', 3096, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1347219693, 0),
(828, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/3164-DonaldandAndrea/3164-DonaldandAndrea.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Donald and Andrea''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 3164, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1340825836, 1),
(829, 'Anna (11) is seasoned big sister. She and her brother are best friends (although they would never admit it). She loves to watch out for him by making breakfast, helping on the computer, and playing for hours in the back yard. She can always be found at church playing with the babies and helping the mothers any way she can. Anna loves to dance, do cart wheels, and play volleyball. She loves the Chronicles of Narnia and creating her own fashion designs. She is so excited about becoming a big sister again. \n\nAndrew (9) is a a little boy who loves to be alive. His loves are super heroes, football, reading, and playing with his friends. He can answer any question about super heroes and writing his own comic books. He is a funny little boy with a sensitive spirit and a tender heart. He is very ready to be a big brother. \n\nKayla (17) is a niece who is a big part of our family. She is silly and loves to playing with the kids. She is smart, independent, and is our free baby sitter. She is preparing for college and looking forward to another cousin. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About the Children ', 3168, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342321505, 0),
