(1161, 'Jim and I were both invited along with a bigger group by a mutual friend to a Holy Thursday Mass dinner at Old St. Pat''s Cathedral in downtown Chicago. The event was held in the basement of the church and a passover meal was served right after Mass. Patty and Jim sat at different tables for the event. Then after mass and the dinner, the whole group went to a small Greek establishment in Greek town, a short walk from the church. \n\nJim sat right next to Patty and soon they began talking. It was a very easy conversation between them since they had a lot in common-- siblings who live on a farm, Chicago Cubs fans and nieces and a nephew about the same age. And they had some good laughs. \n\nThen it was time to go home. Sue was giving Patty a ride home and then they said good-by to Jim. Then when they got in the car, Patty said to Sue: "You have to have a BBQ and invite Jim!"\n\nAnd so she did. And here we are happily married... ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'How we met', 3313, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358218696, 0),
