(856, 'Hopeful adoptive couple\nHopeful adoptive family\nHopeful adoptive parents\nAdoptive couple\n\nadoptive couples\n\nadoptive family\n\nadoptive famlies\n\nadoptive parent\n\nadoptive parents\n\nHoping to adopt\nReady to adopt\nWant to adopt\nadopt my baby\nwaiting families\nwaiting family\n\nBirth mother looking for adoptive family? You found us.\nExpecting mother expecting family\nunwanted pregnancy\nunexpected pregnancy\n\nparent profiles parent adoption profile potential parents profile america adopts parent match adoption book\nadoption share forever family\n\nmy adoption profiles adoptionprofiles\nadopting profiles adoptingprofiles\nadoptive parents profiles\nAdoption profile\n\nAdoption profile Fl florida ca califorina tx texas ks ak alaska al ga il illinois in mt oh ohio ny new york nj new jersey vt nh ma mn mt wa va wv md or nd sd az nm new mexico nv nevada ok wi wisconson ms nc north carolina sc south carolina tn ky\n\nadoption parent profile parent profile  adoptive birthmother pregnancy unplanned pregnancy waiting parents happy home baby open adoption newborn birthmom adoption agency licensed adoption agency adoptive parent adopting a baby pregnant domestic adoption adopt baby adopt birthparent adopting adoptive parent profile birth parent birth mother adoptive parent profiles', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'SEO Profile', 3257, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1341956227, 0),
(861, 'We met in college shortly before classes began in 1996. From our very first conversation, we felt a special connection. We dated for 3 years before getting engaged. Even though we were young, we were in love and were ready to spend the rest of our lives together. \n\nWe were married for 5 years before having our first child. Having those years together gave us the opportunity to really understand each other and build a strong foundation for our future family.\n\nThis month will be thirteen years of marriage. We are even more in love than when we started out. Each year gets better and better as we work together to build a Godly home for our family. \n\nThe commitment we have is rooted much deeper than just a love for one another; it''s our love for God and our commitment to Christ to be faithful servants and a testimony to others.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 3174, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342491786, 0),
(862, 'We are very proud of the community in which we live. Our town has one of the best school districts in the state of Florida. It has a small town feel despite its proximity to Orlando. \n\nOur neighborhood is family friendly and our elementary school is less than a mile away. We like to bike, play tennis and enjoy all that our community has to offer. \n\nWe have lived in our home for 7 years. Our favorite part is our backyard where we enjoy swimming, playing games and fishing in the pond behind our house. The sunsets are beautiful in our backyard. \n\nWe feel so blessed that God has provided a wonderful home and community for us to raise our family. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 3174, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342492878, 0);
