(877, 'Sunday dinners with family \n\n\nExercise  \nNutrition \nMuseums of all types\nTheater shows \nReading\nIce skating \nDoing crafts with my younger nieces \nGoing shopping with my older nieces \nDiscovering new restaurants \nice skating \nCooking/baking new recipes & creating my own \nExperiencing different cultures through cuisine,  language, music & dance. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Interests &amp; Hobbies of Christine', 3297, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342656024, 0),
(873, 'www.facebook.com/waitingparents.brandonandberta', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'We are on FACEBOOK', 3324, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342614583, 0),
(874, 'Hi! My name is Stacy and I am a Pre-school teacher.  I also coach middle school track.  People say that I am a very caring, sincere, and patient person.  I love working with children and knew from a very early age that is what I wanted to do.  The opportunity to interact with children daily and make an impact in their lives is so inspiring to me and I can''t wait to have that opportunity with a child of our own.  \nI grew up in a small town just like Craig.  My family is not as big as Craig''s but we are very close and supportive and that has been very important in shaping the person I am today.  We love getting together and they are all very excited about Craig and I adding a cousin for my niece and nephew.   \nMany of my interests are similar to Craig''s, which is probably why we get along so well!  Just like Craig I also played basketball and ran track and cross country in college.  I still run daily and love to exercise.  I also enjoy going to the lake, reading (I am so excited about being able to read to our child), baking, going to sporting events, and spending time with our dog, Molly.  Spending time with family and friends, though, always tops my list.  We are both so blessed to have wonderful families and such great friends and can''t wait to add a child to all our cherished times with them.\nI am very excited that we have the opportunity to be able to adopt a child of our own.  Being able to share the same love, support, and faith that was given to me growing up is what I have always dreamed about.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Stacy', 3027, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342628346, 0),
(875, 'Molly is our chocolate lab.  We rescued her from a farm when she was about sixth months old.  Not sure what we were in for, Molly has turned out to be a wonderful dog.  She is very mild mannered and great with kids.  We have enjoyed having her as a pet and don''t know what we would do without her.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Molly', 3027, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342629142, 0),
