(1528, '     Hi!  We are Steve and Tracy. We have been married for eleven years and the Lord has blessed us with three children through adoption.  Our family is very close and enjoys being together.  We spend a lot of time playing, going to playgrounds and parks, reading stories, and learning new things together. We are active members of our church and strive to follow Jesus. Our whole family is very excited about adopting again.  \n\n\n     We always knew we wanted to adopt again.  We love parenting and being with our family.  We decided to wait until all the children were also eager and ready for another sibling and our youngest was older.  Each child came to us at different times asking about a new sibling.  Then we knew we were ready to start the process. They talk about a new baby brother or sister and pray for one all the time.  They want to know where the carseat will go, where they will sit at the table, if they can help feed them, and have figured out how they will take turns helping. We always remind them that Mommy and Daddy will do much of the work, but they will be great helps!\n\n\n    We are all very excited to welcome our next child into our family.  We love to laugh, have fun, support, and love one another.  We can hardly wait to share our love with another child.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'We are glad to meet you.', 6539, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1394315542, 0),
