(910, 'Going to sporting events (My favorites are baseball & Basketball games) \n\nGolfing \n\nExercise \n\nFinding new restaurants to enjoy with Chris & our family.  Japanese restaurants are my favorite.  I''m teaching my nephews how to hold chopsticks and they almost have it mastered.  I guess we''ll have to go back to the restaurant so they can keep trying. \n\nReading (sports, spiritual, motivational, business)\n\nMartial Arts (Kenpo Karate) \n\nPlaying with my dogs Macie & Bella \n\nGoing bowling with my nephews\n\nHiking with Christine''s father & brother', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Steven&amp;#039;s Interests &amp;amp; Hobbies', 3297, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1342981256, 0),
(911, 'Here is a portion of a reference letter that was written by the director of the school in which Christine works at.\n(Submitted to the adoption agency)\n\nIn order to ensure the success of her classroom, Christine is required to collaborate and communicate each day with her co-workers as well as the parents of children enrolled in her classroom.  She is flexible and patient with colleagues and parents and maintains a positive outlook.  \nChristine takes her role of educator very seriously.  She is calm, nurturing and caring while able to set clear expectations for the children in her care.  Christine understands each child''s abilities and needs and is skilled in planning for children in a manner that challenges them while allowing for regular successes.  Christine is unusually successful with children who are experiencing emotional difficulties.  She is able to assist children in communicating their needs while working through emotional situations. \n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Christine', 3297, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1349563239, 0),
