(917, '<p><img title="Bridget" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/JoeKelly/AboutBridget.gif" alt="Bridget" width="564" height="225" /></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;font-size:small;">Daughter. Sports enthusiast. Ultimate caregiver to her stuffed pal, Bert. Lover of ice cream, accordions, story-time, art projects, and anything that involves getting dirty or wet. Bridget’s an active and patient little girl. Having her as a big sister, your child will be surrounded by <span style="font-size:large;"><strong>kid activities</strong></span>, will have a sibling who is always game to play, and will grow up with someone who shares the common bond of adoption.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Bridget', 3329, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1343011659, 0),
(918, '<p><span style="color:#339966;font-size:small;">We met in high school at a local skating rink. Our first date was on Valentine’s Day a week later. It was one of the greatest moments of our lives. As corny as it sounds that night we both knew we would one day be husband and wife. </span><br /><br /><span style="color:#339966;font-size:small;">A year and a half later we married in a quiet wedding ceremony with just family and friends. We knew we wanted to start a family right away so we did. God blessed us with two beautiful daughters. Each one of our children’s births were magical moments that we will treasure forever. </span><br /><br /><span style="color:#339966;font-size:small;">When we could no longer have children it broke our hearts, but God showed us that He adopted us and we too can adopt to continue to grow our family. We are all so excited to welcome another child into our home. Being a parent has been our greatest accomplishment as individuals and as a couple and we can’t wait to do it again!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 3117, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1343059407, 0),
(919, '<p><span style="color:#b14e87;font-size:small;">Almost all of our family live within 30 minutes of our home. Grandma and Papa just 15 minutes away : ) They truly are the best grandparents we could ever ask God for. They bake cookies with our children, take them shopping for their birthdays, take them on vacation every summer, fish, make crafts, and much much more!</span><br /><br /><span style="color:#b14e87;font-size:small;">There are cousins, an aunt, and uncles to play with as well. We get together for birthdays (there is almost one every other month), holidays, and many celebrations in between.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 3117, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1343059479, 0),
(923, 'Decorating the Christmas Tree the Day after Thanksgiving ~\n\n\n\n\nGoing to see Holiday lights and displays during the Christmas season ~\n\n\n\n\nChristmas Eve dinner at Grandma Claire''s House ~\n\n\n\n\nAttending Midnight Mass on Christmas Eve ~\n\n\n\n\nEvery year we have a big pizza party where everyone makes a different type of pizza and we celebrate together by trying as many of them as we can. ~\n\n\n\n\nFamily trips to the farm during the autumn season ~\n\n\n\n\nDecorating pumpkins with our nieces & nephews ~\n\n\nCelebrating birthdays on the actual day with our entire family ~\n\n\n\n\nWhale watching, sailing & kayaking every summer ~\n\n\n\n\nGoing to New York City every spring ~\n\n\n\n\nSupporting our local animal shelter throughout the year.  At Christmas time we buy food, bedding, toys & treats for the animals that are waiting for a home. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family Traditions ', 3297, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1345076384, 0),
