(926, '<p> </p>\n<p>Steve and I met in my home town in Central Florida.  Steve was in his second year of college and I had just finished high school.  We met at my home church, began dating, fell in love and have never been apart since.  It has been almost twelve years and we still would rather be with each other than anyone else.  Steve and I were married the same day that he graduated from college.  He walked across the stage in the morning and we walked down the aisle that evening.  We lived in my home town for about a year and then Steve got a job that required us to move to another part of Florida.  We lived there for three years and Steve received a promotion to Georgia.  About seven years later, Steve received another promotion back to Florida. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Our marriage is based upon trust and a daily dependence on God.  We believe that God has brought us together and we could not be any happier.  We also believe that God delights in His children serving Him and wants to be the center of our marriage.  We attend a local Baptist church where we have become very involved.  Steve has taught Sunday School classes, been the Church Pianist, sang special music and sings in the Choir.  Jessica has taught Sunday School and Junior Church for children 2 and 3 years of age as well as start women’s Bible studies.  We both enjoy teaching Junior Church with an age range of 3 yrs – 6<sup>th</sup> grade.  We enjoy serving God together and count it a great honor to be able to influence the lives of children for Christ each week.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>For the first seven years of our marriage we tried to have children and were unsuccessful.  We prayed that the Lord would bless us with a pregnancy, went to the best doctors and tried all of the latest procedures with no success.  We always wanted to adopt, even before we knew we couldn’t get pregnant and felt the Lord had led us to this point to begin the adoption process.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>In October of 2009 we received the biggest answer to prayer we had ever experienced in our lives.  A birth-mother had chosen us to have her child.  Words can still not express love and gratitude we have for the birth-mother, who the Lord used to extend His grace upon our lives.  Just three short months later, on Christmas Eve morning, we welcomed Khloe into our world.  We were the first ones to hold this precious gift from God and she has continued to be the biggest blessing of our lives. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We are the proud owners of two basset hounds, Roxy and Quiksilver who are sister and brother.  They have been one of the most unexpected blessings in our lives and they have become a part of our family.  They have taught us a lot about responsibility and the need of being cared for.  We enjoy spending time with Roxy and Quiksilver.  They love to be walked around our neighborhood, playing in the back yard, discovering things that have been buried in the ground for years, sleeping anywhere they can and protecting Khloe.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We spend as much time together as a family as possible.  We enjoy going to sporting events like baseball, hockey and football games.  We enjoy bowling, miniature golf, roller skating, fishing, riding the Barbie jeep, and going out to dinner just to name a few things.  We attempt to do some sort of outside activity once a day together, whether it is swimming, walking, yard work, or going to the park and playing on the swings, we love doing things together.  We also enjoy spending time inside the house with Khloe.  It doesn’t matter if we are playing on the floor with her toys, using daddy as a jumping bag or watching a Disney movie, we always have fun and enjoy spending time together.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Although it feels like we have the “perfect” family, we know there is still something missing, our desire to have more children.  We have had so much fun raising Khloe that we can hardly wait until God blesses us with another birth-mother choosing us.  Just like with Khloe, we want to be able to share the love of God with them and raise them up for His glory.  We are so excited about being able to welcome another child into our family.  We long to share with our next child the same relationship filled with love, laughter and happiness.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 3186, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1343505365, 0),
(927, 'Wyatt and Jami met while working summer retail jobs in college.  Wyatt was the ‘hot’ guy in the department and initially Jami wanted nothing to do with him!  Wyatt pursued and Jami finally gave in - and to this day she is happy that she did!  They dated long distance for 2 years before finally landing in the same city.  Wyatt took his time proposing and seven (yes, SEVEN) years later they were married.  \n\n\nIn 2004 Wyatt and Jami moved to the Minneapolis area and they now live in a spacious 5 bedroom home located on Lake Minnetonka.  Their door is always open to friends and family and summers are most often spent boating and barbequing in the backyard.  They have a dog named Mya (Samoyed) and a cat named Boots.  Mya can be seen in two TV commercials!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 3384, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1344191400, 0),
(928, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/3384-Wyatt-and-Jami/3384-Wyatt-and-Jami.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Wyatt and Jami''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 3384, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1343591431, 1),
(962, 'Currently, we are a family of four.  Our daughter, Addie, is 8 years old and our son, Willie is 6 years old.  During the school year, Chad goes to work and Joy stays at home while the kids go to a nearby public school.  It is the best school in the county, and we love it there.  Joy is involved volunteering at the school and knows many teachers well.  After school, the kids work on “jobs”, homework, and playing outside.  Joy likes to cook and we usually eat dinner family style around the dinner table.  Dinner is followed by singing, playing a game, reading, or going on a walk with the dog.  Addie has found that she enjoys singing and performing and is currently in a children’s choir suited to that.  She also enjoyed playing soccer last fall.  Willie hasn’t quite yet figured out what extracurricular activities he enjoys, but that’s ok.  He and Addie enjoy playing the Wii together.  However, video games are limited to weekends during the school year.  He is a bright, happy boy that wants to make everyone smile.  It’s his “superpower”.  He is an instant friend to anyone he meets.\nOn the weekends we like to watch movies and play games as a family.  Sometimes we go yard sale-ing on the weekend or we go on dates.  Sometimes Chad and Joy go on a date and we get a baby-sitter.  Almost as frequently, Chad or Joy gets to take one kid out on their own special date.  We love doing that.  We also go to church on the weekend and meet with our small group.  We have a loving and supportive church with several adoptive/adopting families.  \nChad and Joy’s parents, grandparents and siblings all live within a 6 hour drive.  We are close to all of them.  Many of our holidays and school breaks are spent traveling to see them or they come to see us.  Our family is very supportive about us adopting and are ready to love on some more kids.  \nBoth the kids are excited about getting younger siblings.  We have asked them all kinds of questions about what type of kids we should get.  We were thrilled that race was not an issue for them, but of course Addie wants sister and Willie wants a brother.  :)\nWe live in a very diverse city.  Our school and neighborhood are filled with all different types of families.  And we have friends of all different races.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About our Family', 3152, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1360807131, 0),
