(934, '> Our parents are the best of friends!  Every-other-year we organize a family cruise and our combined families (12 of us) spend a week under the sun.  It is something that we all look forward to and talk about for months before and after.\n\n> Jami cannot wait to be a stay-at-home Mom!\n\n> Our nephew, Dominic, is adopted and we''re fortunate to be able to spend lots of time with him.  His Dad is Wyatt''s twin brother and they live just 20 minutes away.\n\n> Jami is an avid supporter and volunteer for the Animal Humane Society.  \n \n> We lived in Australia for 6 months!  While there we visited Malaysia, Taiwan, Tasmania and the Whitsunday Islands.\n\n> During college Jami backpacked through Europe studying art and architecture.  She visited 14 countries over a 2 month time frame and she documented it all in a sketch book.\n\n> Our dog, Mya, is in 2 commercials!  The commercials can be seen here:  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WBR0yu3VQIw -and- http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LCCimNvu7Os\n\n> We dated for SEVEN years before getting married in 2007.  Wyatt jokes that he was, "just making sure".  :)\n\n> Our house is always full of friends and family.  We live on Lake Minnetonka and have 2 boats, 2 jet skis and plenty of extra space.   Family BBQ''s and bonfires are a weekly event.\n\n> Our hobbies include boating, golfing, Twins games, hiking, and games with the family.\n\n> Favorite vacation spot:  Hawaii\n> Favorite day of the week:  Sunday\n> Favorite movie:  Elf\n> Favorite food:  Ice cream\n\n> Our house is just minutes from the local Dairy Queen...  Mmmmm...\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Fun Facts', 3384, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1344191185, 0),
(935, '<p>&gt; Our parents are the best of friends!  Every-other-year we organize a family cruise and our combined families (12 of us) spend a week under the sun.  It is something that we all look forward to and talk about for months before and after.<br /><br />&gt; Jami cannot wait to be a stay-at-home Mom!<br /><br />&gt; Our nephew, Dominic, is adopted and we''re fortunate to be able to spend lots of time with him.  His Dad is Wyatt''s twin brother and they live just 20 minutes away.<br /><br />&gt; Jami is an avid supporter and volunteer for the Animal Humane Society.  <br /> <br />&gt; We lived in Australia for 6 months!  While there we visited Malaysia, Taiwan, Tasmania and the Whitsunday Islands.<br /><br />&gt; During college Jami backpacked through Europe studying art and architecture.  She visited 14 countries over a 2 month time frame and she documented it all in a sketch book.<br /><br />&gt; Our dog, Mya, is in 2 commercials!  The commercials can be seen here:  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WBR0yu3VQIw -and- http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LCCimNvu7Os<br /><br />&gt; We dated for SEVEN years before getting married in 2007.  Wyatt jokes that he was, "just making sure".  :)<br /><br />&gt; Our house is always full of friends and family.  We live on Lake Minnetonka and have 2 boats, 2 jet skis and plenty of extra space.   Family BBQ''s and bonfires are a weekly event.<br /><br />&gt; Our hobbies include boating, golfing, Twins games, hiking, and games with the family.<br /><br />&gt; Favorite vacation spot:  Hawaii<br />&gt; Favorite day of the week:  Sunday<br />&gt; Favorite movie:  Elf<br />&gt; Favorite food:  Ice cream<br /><br />&gt; Our house is just minutes from the local Dairy Queen...  Mmmmm...</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Fun Facts', 3384, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1344191225, 0),
(936, '<p>Wyatt and Jami met while working summer retail jobs in college.  Wyatt was the ‘hot’ guy in the department and initially Jami wanted nothing to do with him!  Wyatt pursued and Jami finally gave in - and to this day she is happy that she did!  They dated long distance for 2 years before finally landing in the same city.  Wyatt took his time proposing and seven (yes, SEVEN) years later they were married.  <br /><br />In 2004 Wyatt and Jami moved to the Minneapolis area and they now live in a spacious 5 bedroom home located on Lake Minnetonka.  Their door is always open to friends and family and summers are most often spent boating and barbequing in the backyard.  They have a dog named Mya (Samoyed) and a cat named Boots.  Mya can be seen in two TV commercials!</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 3384, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1344191492, 0),
