(948, '    Brad and Maria were high school sweet hearts.  We enjoy doing things together and find strength in one another.  Together we each work full-time to provide for our family.  Our home is on the shores of Lake Erie.  In the summer time we are just minutes from the beach and an amusement park.  \n     Brad works for a family construction business and Maria is an Intervention Specialist for students with disabilities.  We value hard work and understand the importance of responsibility.  We balance our lives by enjoying the good life on evenings and weekends.  The “good life” consists of vacations, laughter and love, and making memories with family and friends.   We enjoy spending time with those that mean the most to us.   \n     It is our wish and desire to begin a family and welcome children into our lives.  Unfortunately, we were unable to conceive a baby.  We believe that God had other plans for us.  His plan was adoption and we look forward to watching his plan unfold and welcoming children into our loving home. \n\n\n   \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 3564, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1344870646, 0),
