(951, 'We live in a small, diverse community in a quiet neighborhood.\n\nWe live about a block from one of many local parks.  \nWe live very close to the heart of the twin cities, where there are lots of activities for families to partake in. \n\nOur home was built a year ago in an already established area. The town we live in is actually where Regina grew up and where her family still lives. \n\nIt is a close kit community with lots of fun community events for families. We live three blocks from one of the local elementary schools and five blocks from the local high school. Our home is a split level, open floor plan, with a family room and lots of space for a family to live and play together. We have a great fenced in backyard where we like to spend a lot of time, playing with our dog Patch or having family over to BBQ or make smores on the bonfire. \n\nPatch is 18 pounds of cuddly fun. He loves kids and is the most happy when he is playing fetch in the yard or catching a Frisbee.  He is a terrier, so he is very energetic and would love to have kids here all the time to play with him.  \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 3585, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1348519458, 0),
(952, 'Both of our extended families are very large and spread out all over the states. We have between us, 21 aunts and uncles and even more than we can count for great aunts and great uncles.  We won’t even begin to tell you of the cousins!   Even though we are spread out all over the place we see our extended families as often as we can.  There are reunions, holidays and family celebrations that always bring people home.  If there is one big similarity in our growing up years it would be this. We have large families but we know and love them all.  \n\n\n\n\nThere are many things we like to do.  We spend as much time as we can with family and friends and try to include them in on our favorite pastimes.  We share a love of baseball. Regina’s Dad instilled that in her when she was very little. He is a baseball coach in the community.  One of our very first dates was to a Twins game at the Dome.  We continue to cheer them on even when they are losing. We try to get to a few games each season and really love the new stadium. \n\n\n\n We also love to cheer on the Nebraska Huskers, especially the football team.  Weston’s family, being mostly from Nebraska, is HUGE Husker fans, so really what choice did she have but to become a fan?  We have even traveled down to Lincoln to take in a game and every year we get together with friends and family to watch games and wear our Red, White and Black.\n\n\n\n We share a love for movies and enjoy going to them or having movie and popcorn nights at home.  We love spending summer nights at one of the two drive- ins that are near where we live. We both remember going with our families growing up in our pajamas and would love to share that experience with our own child someday. \n\n\n\nWe also like to travel. We like going on short road trips to visit family or friends as well as flying to places we haven’t yet seen.  We also usually go camping a couple times each summer or early fall.  Our favorite all time trip was to Disneyworld on our Honeymoon.  Regina had been there a few times before, but it was Weston’s first trip and we loved every minute of it. If there is one place we are the most excited to take our child it would be there. We are looking forward to sharing the magic of Disney with them and watching their face light up with joy. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', ' Life as we know it', 3585, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1348519027, 0),
(953, '<p><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;font-size:large;">Please take a few minutes to view our online photo album via the link at the bottom of our Birth Parent Letter.  Just click where it says <span style="text-decoration:underline;">photo album</span> in the letter and it will open a new tab where you can learn more about both of us, our family and see a lot more photos.  Each page can be enlarge by clicking on the page. Thanks! </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'MORE ABOUT US!', 3578, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1345135033, 0),
