(961, 'Dear Birthparent: \n\nWe are extremely happy at the thought of being parents and look forward to the joys of raising a child. We are happy and content with our lives except for one thing. We really want to be a mom and a dad. Unfortunately, God has a different plan for us. Words cannot express the respect and admiration that we have for you and the decision you are making. \n\nOur greatest hope is to raise a child in a happy, loving home where they have every opportunity to enjoy the good things in life. It is our desire to allow your child to explore their interests, growing into the individual they have the will to become. We will guide your child to become a caring, compassionate and respectful person. Most of all, your child will be loved. We are excited to share our values and lessons we learned from our parents and extended family. The values of a good education, working hard for what you have, learning to appreciate the simple things in life, and most of all, treating others with kindness and respect. \n\nThe story of our life together began some 20 years ago. We met our freshman year of college, when a mutual friend introduced us. We became friends, and it wasn''t until our junior year in college that we began dating. We dated four years before we married. We married in August 1997, and will have been married 15 years this August. We believe that being friends prior to dating has been a strength in our relationship. \n\nAfter we were married, we made our home on the family farm. This is the same place that Brandon lived for most of his life. We live 11 miles from town, and we feel raising children on the farm and in the country is one of the best places to raise a child. Teresa also grew up living in the country. We are very fortunate to live in a community that excels in education. Our schools have been recognized for their outstanding efforts in academics, scholastics, and athletics. In our community there are many activities for the children to participate in. We feel a balance between school/community activities, along with the life skills learned living on a farm will enhance the children we raise. \n \nBrandon is doing what he loves best, and has always wanted to do since he was a child, be part of the family farm. Our farm consists of raising cattle and growing crops. Brandon also operates his own liquid and dry feed cattle business. I can''t forget to mention that we also have two dogs, numerous cats, and yes, even chickens. \nThere''s no doubt that we both love children. Teresa is lucky enough to spend majority of her day with kids. Being an elementary teacher the past 14 years, has always been a dream and goal of hers since she was in the 1st grade. She is currently teaching 5th and 6th Grade Science. She wouldn''t trade teaching for anything. \n\nA value that we were brought up with is our faith in God. We are not ones to go out and preach to others, but we are a strong believer in God and his works. It is our plan for raise our children within the Faith of the Catholic Church. \n\nA question has been asked of us numerous times. "How many children do you have?" Often times we answer 120, being the students at school. I will be the first to tell you that I love the children I work with everyday, and we enjoy being around other children, but we anxiously await for the day we can tell others that we have a child of our own. We realize and understand that God has a plan for us be blessed with a family. It may not be the exact plan we had in mind, but we believe that somewhere out there is a child that would become part of our family and be loved. \nAs we close this letter, let us leave you with this:"Children are a Blessing." Whether or not you choose use as parents for your child, please let us know that our thoughts and prayers are with you. We wish you peace with your decision and hope that you will be comforted with the knowledge that your child will be deeply loved and cared for and will be raised to know of the loving sacrifice you made for them. \nGod bless you, as you are making this important decision.\n\nWith Best Wishes, \n\n\nBrandon & Teresa\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birthparent Letter', 3352, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1345520922, 0),
