(964, 'Hi, My name is George. I was born and raised on Long Island,  my parents live about ten minutes from us. I am a twin, my brother lives in Fl and is a sheriffs deputy. I have an older sister ,she is married , is an accountant and lives close by. My family owns 2 restaurants, which I worked in for many years while growing up. I now work full time in the automobile industry and Kelly and I also own our own business. \nI guess you could say I grew up in your average middle class working family, but at the same time I feel it was so much more. My mom  was always right "there" for us for our every single need or issue or proud moment. Actually she still is , to this very day. Although we are all grown and have our own lives and our own families,if you just "mention " something you might need or pan on getting or if there is something that needs to be done. Well it seems it magically appears or gets done. She truly cares about our happiness and will do anything for any of us at the drop of a hat. My dad, well he is the quieter kind but he has instilled in all of us a hard work ethic and in my brother and I that it is our responsibility to provide, take care of and protect our families. He has taught us you do what you need to do to provide for you family. He has worked many a 15-16 hour day in his time to ensure we had it all plus more. He had us helping out in restaurants from a young age teaching us that if you want something , you earn it. I am of the same values. Kelly and Zackary are my family , I cherish them both and can''t imagine my life without them. I would do  anything for either one of them. Working full time of course provides a regular salary and benefits but I was determined I wanted more security for our family. I started our business with this in mind and while it can be long hours and hard work at times,knowing my family is taken care of  is all the motivation I need.\nMy parents, my brother and my sister are all thrilled we have chosen to adopt. They know we have longed for another child for several years and the decision to adopt a precious one feel right to both Kelly and I. We adore our son and how he is turning into a great young man.  We would feel honored to be entrusted by someone to raise their child. \nI know Kelly has explained how our relationship grew. It felt natural and meant to be right from the beginning. Zackary from the very start has been a joy in my life. He was a happy, well balanced smart and obviously much loved child when I met him. Kelly would just glow with love and pride for him , I couldn''t help but want to be part of that family instantly. \nNow we would love to add another to this family. We have the all in this world to give to a child and we can''t wait to start our life with them.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT GEORGE', 3624, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1345698019, 0),
(965, 'Hello,\n\nOur names are Greg and Theresa and we hope that through sharing our life story you are able to gain insight into who we are as both individuals and as a couple.\n\nOur story began in the fall of 2006 when we found each other through a Catholic website. Only one problem. There were 200 miles between us! It did make dating a challenge, but we didn’t let it stop us. Many weekends were spent traveling. Two years later we married in Milwaukee.\n\nOur neighborhood is quiet and we have great neighbors; many with children.  Time is spent in our garden taking care of flowers and a variety of vegetables.  There are large, open parks nearby that we enjoy.  Plus, we take advantage of the local bike trails.\n\nWe have enjoyed our years together and are looking forward to starting our own family and sharing our love with a child. Being able to provide a strong education in combination with Christian values is important to us.  Also, both of us grew up in households with a stay-at-home parent and we would like to do the same.\n\nOur families are very supportive of our decision to adopt.  Both sets of grandparents look forward to having another grandchild to spoil.  The holidays and many weekends are spent at the lake house with Theresa’s parents or in Michigan with Greg’s parents and sister’s family.\n\nWe are open to discussing the extent of openness in the adoption plan.  We will love this child unconditionally, but also believe that the child should know your love, too.\n\nThank you for reading our letter.\n\nGreg and Theresa\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'BIRTH PARENT LETTER', 2419, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1379384452, 0),
(966, '<p><strong>I am Madison and I have been looking forward to being a big sister for a very long time. I love singing, acting, swimming, playing with my friends, playing on the Wii, going on vacations, watching movies, and playing dress up! </strong></p>\n<p><strong>I hope that you will pick us to be the family for your baby because I am so excited to be a big sister and this will be great!<br /></strong></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'MADISON, THE FUTURE BIG SISTER!', 3132, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1345703891, 0),
(967, 'I love being a stay at home mom.  But I am not lazy by any means!  \n\nI enjoy helping out at the kids'' schools.  I like being involved there, getting to know the teachers, and getting to know the kids'' classmates.  I have helped a lot in the library and last year I substitute taught.  \n\nAt home, I am always cooking and organizing. Freezer cooking is my area of expertise and I like teaching other folks how to freezer cook.  \n\nI like to read for pleasure.  And being a former teacher, I love children''s books.  I love love love reading with my kids.  \n\nI am also a big bargain hunter.  I enjoy yard sale-ing and hitting thrift stores to find hidden treasures.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Hobbies &amp; Interests of Joy', 3152, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1345731549, 0),
(968, 'Chad enjoys working in the yard, working on technology, and hiking...................', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Hobbies &amp; Interests of Chad', 3152, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1345731647, 0),
(969, 'Both George and I felt it was important that birth moms know about the big brother,because he is going to have a very active and important role in this babies life. First let me say, he has known for many years we were trying to welcome a new addition into the family and has always been very positive about it, but we never brought into the forefront of any real discussions with him. So when we decided we really wanted to try to actively look for a baby to welcome into our family, we of course sat down to talk together as a family. Zack is simply overjoyed at prospect of being a big brother. He is an intellegent ,caring ,thoughtful, generous young man. He is an honor student , works wit our local handicapped ice hockey team for kids and volunteers with many activities at his catholic high school.he has also worked as an afterschool tutor for younger kids.  He spends time teaching kids mainly with Down''s syndrome how to skate and play hockey. I always sit and watch , and I can never tell who has the biggest smile. Him or the youngster he is helping. Now in the last couple of weeks when I am either working on this site or writing ads or on the phone with agencies or doing any kind of task involved with the adoption process, well I find him casually looking over my shoulder to see how its going. He is also helping us make our family album for our birthmom. I wish I could explain his excitement for this in words more accurately, but I can say that whenever I mention anything to do with a little one coming to us, well he gets this beaming smile across his face. LOL. He will be the lil ones Godfather and he cannot wait for that added role and responsibility in his life! Please if you do contact us do not hesitate to ask anything you wish about him and his upbringing. I firmly believe he is the best reference we could ever have as he has blossomed into a great young man.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Zack', 3624, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1345751586, 0),
(970, '<p><span style="font-family:georgia, palatino;font-size:medium;">As parents, we will provide a safe, fun, loving and nurturing home.  We will be consistent, patient and set clear expectations for behavior and above all, love the child unconditionally.  We plan on discussion adoption at an early age because we want him or her to feel good and comfortable above being adopted.  Traci will be a stay at home mom to care for the baby.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:georgia, palatino;font-size:small;"> <br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Parenting Style', 3389, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1345828313, 0),
