(1030, 'We are very lucky to be close to both of our families. Everyone is a great support system and just a phone call away.\n \nStan''s family all live within a mile of us.  The nieces are looking forward to babysitting, Stan''s sisters are looking forward to a baby in the family.  Grandma is looking forward to our walks to her house.\n\nChris'' parents live in Michigan on a lake.  We try to spend as many weekends as we can in the summer with them enjoying boating, tubing, etc.  In the winter we enjoy the snow and snowmobiling.  They come to our home often to celebrate holidays, birthdays or just when we need them.  Her brother lives close and she spends a lot of time with her nieces.  They are very excited to have a little cousin.\n\nWe enjoy going on vacation with both of our families.  Almost annually we have a family vacation with Christine''s family.  We also occasionally travel to Poland to visit Stan''s extended family.  He has aunts, uncles, and cousins in Poland and we have many places to stay and visit.  We are so excited to experience our families and travels with a child.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Extended Families', 3753, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1349394145, 0),
(1031, '<p>With so much family around, we''re never at a loss for a good family tradition! Our family is very active and hands-on.   Thanksgiving is spent first with Chris'' family at her Grandparents home with Grandpa still carving the turkey at 100 years old.  Then it is off to Stan''s sister''s for coffee and dessert.  A traditional Polish Christmas Eve is spent with Stan''s family and the traditional American Christmas Day is spent with Chris'' family.  A multicultural Easter is celebrated at our house with both families together and an Easter egg hunt for all.  Finally there is never a loss for celebrating everyone''s individual birthday.  From our parents to each niece and nephew, everyone gets their own party.</p>\n<p>We are very blessed with families that enjoy spending so much time together. We have definitely grown to love our family traditions, and we look forward to sharing these family traditions with a child!</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family Traditions', 3753, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1349397340, 0),
(1032, '*Every Friday night as a family we go out to eat, get ice cream, and either watch a movie or play a board game together.  Makenzie also "sleeps over" with us-she sleeps on the couch in our sitting room.\n\n\n\n\n*Each morning Sam takes Makenzie to school.  Each afternoon Jennifer picks her up from school.\n\n\n\n\n*Each evening we gather together as a family and say our prayers.  After prayers Sam and Jennifer alternate nights laying with Makenzie for a few minutes of just talking.\n\n\n\n\n*Birthdays are big in our family!  Everyone has a birthday party every year.  For Makenzie, there is a birthday fairy that comes each year.  She decorates her door and leaves her a gift on her dresser.\n\n\n\n\n*Every Easter we have an Easter Egg Hunt with both Jennifer''s family and Sam''s family.  After church on Easter Sunday we go to Sam''s mom''s house to have lunch with his sister''s family, his mom, and his Granny.\n\n\n\n\n*Every Thanksgiving we get together with each side of our families.  On Jennifer''s side there are usually at least 60 people there-most of which are children!  \n\n\n\n\n*Every Christmas Eve Jennifer''s parents spend the night to watch Makenzie open gifts Christmas morning.  Later in the afternoon we go to Sam''s mom''s to have Christmas with his side of the family.  \n\n\n\n\n*The day after Thanksgiving our elf, Twinkle, comes to our house and creates mischief until Christmas.  This is a new tradition that was just started last year, but it is one that is so exciting and will go on for a very long time.\n\n\n\n\n*We go on at least one vacation a year-this year we''ve actually been on 3.  Some of those vacations are spent with our extended family.\n\n\n\n\n*We attend church each Sunday and Wednesday.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family Traditions', 3880, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1349665646, 0),
