(1034, 'Hannah is a happy, energetic, strong, and motivated little girl. Her first love is animals and her best friend is our chocolate lab, Abby. Hannah enjoys giving Abby commands for retrieving. She also enjoys dance and tap class, horse riding lessons, music, fishing, cooking, and learning new things. Hannah is curious about the world, how things work and is always asking questions. During the week she attends daycare. Hannah is a very social person and likes the time she has with her friends. We encourage Hannah by giving her more independence and responsibility as she grows and matures. Hannah is very accepting of change and looks at things as glass half full. Hannah is looking forward to being a big sister.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT HANNAH', 2438, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1349698284, 0),
(1035, 'Our religion has always been the focus of our marriage and family life. We both grew up in strong religious families. John belongs to a Lutheran Church and I belong to a Catholic Church. We are both strong in faith and committed to the faith we were raised. We each attended parochial school from kindergarten thru 8th grade and were married in the Catholic Church.\n\n\n\nHannah goes to Church with us on Sundays and Holidays. Hannah will attend a parochial school starting in the fall of 2013 until at least 8th grade. She enjoys attending and participating at Church.\n\n\n\nGod is a part of our daily life. We say prayers thru out the day, listen to religious music, and have conversations that keep God our focus. During Advent and Lent we do extra activities at home to bring us closer to God.\n\n\n\nWe help with the cookie walk and parish festival during the year and try to attend church activities as we can.\n\n\n\nDuring the year we also involve Hannah in activities that promote the beliefs taught to us from the Bible. We adopt a family at Christmas and donate to the food pantry, St Vincent De Paul, Human Society, school supply drive, and others. As she gets older we will involve her in more activities and have her volunteer at Church.\n\n\n\nWe are a family that believes the best guide for our life is God.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR RELIGION', 2438, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1349670189, 0),
(1036, 'Fun Facts:\n\nLoves quads, tractors, and trucks and the bigger the better.\n\nHas 3 battery operated quads courtesy of his grandma. He has parking spaces in the garage. He washes them and prays for them.\n\nHis biggest goal in life is to be 16, so he can get his driver''s license.\n\nHe''s building a river in our backyard that he''s been working on for two years. Our neighbor has a beautiful one and he wants one just like it.\n\nHe''s loves money and will patiently save it for the things he wants to buy.\n\nHe''s incredibly smart- at least that''s what his doctor keeps telling us.\n\nHe''s very social, determined, and a natural leader. He also has a very infectious personality.\n\nHis favorite colors are blue and green.\n\nHe''s very opinionated about his hair and the clothes he wears.\n\nDaddy is his best bud and he tries to emulate him in everything he does.\n\nHe''s fiercely competitive. HATES to lose and won''t give up until he wins.\n\nHe''s a great swimmer and has been asked to join swim team this year.\n\nHe also loves baseball and basketball. He''s currently playing baseball.\n\nHe sleeps with his monkey, his mommy blankie and his birthmom blankie.\n\nWants to be a big brother more than anything else in the world!\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Carter', 3643, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1349728622, 0),
