(1040, 'I shared this true and personal story, today, on my Facebook page.  It seems appropriate to share here, as well.\n\n<3 Beth\n\nHave you ever had a moment that doesn''t seem like a big deal in the moment, but when you think about it later, perhaps the moment is bigger than you could fathom? Today, I had one of THOSE moments. While shopping, I stopped in Barnes and Noble to look for a specific book. I was met at the customer service desk by a sweet woman, probably in her 50''s. I asked her to direct me to a specific book \nabout adoption. As we walked to the shelf, she said, "I don''t mean to be too personal, but are you adopting?" I answered with the blanket statement, "Maybe someday. We are home study approved, but you never know." As we approached the shelf, she said, " I am adopted. And I led a great life. I''m lucky to have the mom and dad that I do. And I see the hope in your eyes that I would imagine my own mom had so many years ago. It''s neat to see." I really didn''t have a response, so I smiled and thanked her. But, now, as I sit here, I can''t put into words how that could have been a powerful moment for that stranger and I''m kinda glad that I was part of her day. And that''s all...\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'A Moment That Meant A Lot...', 2395, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1350252540, 0),
