(1073, '      I love to travel. I am a firm believer that “travel is the only thing you buy, that makes you richer”. Learning about the history, architecture, different cultures, and regional food is a lot of fun and I hope to continue seeing other places in the future.\n\n      When we are home I love to work on different projects. I am very interested in interior design and I love to watch HGTV. We bought our home over 5 years ago and since then it is an ongoing project. Tom sometimes jokes that I repaint a room before the old color has a chance to dry. As much as he exaggerates, I do like to change things around. When we are finishing one project there is usually another one on my mind. I think that scares Tom a little bit, or maybe he just used to it by now. \n\n      My newest hobby, which I discovered about three years ago, is gardening. When we bought our house the front and back yard looked like a disaster. Now, instead of overgrown weeds and bushes, we can enjoy flowers, evergreens and beautiful trees. This year I even tried to grow some herbs, fruits and veggies and that gave me a lot of satisfaction (and lots of cucumbers). I love to spend time outside and really enjoy working in our garden. Whenever weather is nice we eat outside. Lola also likes playing outside; although she is the only retriever I know who does not want to retrieve anything!\n\n      I also like to bake. That is something I did with my Mom since I was little. She always let me “help” her but at the same time I learned a lot too. This is one of my hobbies which I think Tom enjoys the most! \n\n      I cannot imagine my life without different forms of art.  There is nothing better to relax then reading a good book. There are some books which will stay with me forever. They can inspire, make you think, or cry, or just carry you someplace else after a long day. Music has the same power for me. Depending on the mood, I listen to everything from classical music through country, pop, rock and hip-hop. I love to watch ballet or to see exhibits and living close to big city makes it all much easier.  \n\n      As much as I like to read I hate to exercise! There are however some activities I do enjoy like yoga, biking, snowboarding, and talking long walks with Lola. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Interests and Hobbies of Agnes', 3733, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1351823492, 0),
(1074, 'We were both born and raised in small towns in southeast part of Poland. Agnes’s parents still live in the same house where she and her two older sisters grew up in. Tom’s parents moved to the US with him and his younger sister almost 20 years ago. His father and his sister live in Chicago with her family. Tom’s Mom has passed away suddenly a few years ago and she is greatly missed. All our siblings have children. While the youngest one is just 19 months, the oldest one turned 19 this year and went to college. We are very blessed to have people in our lives who showed us what unconditional love means, and who have always been there for us. We will be forever grateful for that and we hope to be as good parents for our children as our parents were for us. Our families are very important to us and we try to spend as much time with them as we can. All the members of our families are very excited that we are adopting and cannot wait to know and love this very special baby.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Families', 3733, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1351823710, 0),
