(1116, 'My name is Brad. My wife''s name is Amanda.\nWe met over twelve years ago while working late on projects in college. \nAmanda says that she liked my creative flair, and that I couldn’t believe there was life outside of studying.\n \nI liked her daring, drive, and intelligence. Oh, did I mention that she is absolutely gorgeous? I also figured that I didn''t have a shot with her.\n \nSince we are being, ''all cards on the table'' honest here, I''ll tell you that Amanda can be a bit impatient at times. Lucky for us, this was one of those times. She walked into the class I was supervising and asked, "So…when are you going to ask me out?" It is exceedingly difficult to supervise a class of Freshmen when a gorgeous girl walks into the class, and calls you out. So, here I am, put up or shut up time. I put up, and took her on our first date,,,To meet my entire family.\n\nDid I mention that Amanda can be extremely patient, as well? Again, lucky for us, this was one of those times. I don''t know what I was thinking, but I subjected her to my mom, dad, brother, sister, their spouses, my aunts, uncles, cousins, and THEIR spouses. Don''t get me wrong, my family is great, but that''s a lot for anyone to take. We also narrowly avoided getting sucked up by a tornado on the way home. First date, no kidding, and she stayed. I met Amanda''s family a month, or so, later. Her dad just wanted to be sure that my intentions were honorable. Something about owning a lot of land, a front loader, and no one missing me...but that is neither here nor there. A couple of years later, we were married in Amanda’s hometown. It must be providence.\nFast forward 10+ years. We have found a great city in which to live, and work. We created successful and truly rewarding careers in product design (more on this in another section). We adopted three wonderful cats, bought and remodeled our first home, and traveled all over the world. We also bought our next house, enjoy golfing, picked up fishing, and archery (more on that later, too).\n \n\nIt is safe to say that we have happy and fulfilling lives, but we have always known that something is missing. We wanted to share all of it with kids. We tried to do just that for years, but one miscarriage led to another and another and, well, you get the picture. The specialists were called in, tears were shed, deep seeded beliefs were questioned, and something was made very clear. We still want a family, but it isn''t going to happen that way,\n \nWe are both excited to welcome an adopted child into our home to love, cherish, teach, and maybe spoil a bit. This decision must be very difficult for you, but we have so much love that we want to share. Please know that you will make a family like us so happy, and that you will be giving your child a wonderful safe home.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'The Story of Us', 3769, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1352511443, 0),
