(1253, 'Born on March 10, 2008, Nate was a healthy baby. We are very grateful that he has also enjoyed a happy, healthy first four+ years of life. This is a very loving and lively boy, who laughs a lot and makes others laugh—saying and doing the funniest things each day. His imagination has been growing by leaps and bounds lately, so you never know when he might suddenly board a spaceship heading to a far-off planet … and take you with him!\n\n\nInterests: Nate has frequent play dates with his school pals and many of our friends’ children—he gets along well with other kids and has some super-fun friends. Aside from lots of physical activity, Nate enjoys playing games and building things (e.g., with legos, magnetic blocks), drawing (lots of space-related stuff), and books. He’s got lots of interests but seems especially drawn to things like the ocean, bugs, cars, big buildings, electricity, weather, outer space, etc. He also loves riding in planes, trains, and boats too.\n\n\nOutside the home: Nate is enrolled in a wonderful preschool, where he’s been going since he was 2 years old. The kids there get a lot of individualized attention and it shows—they''ve formed this beautiful tight-knit little group that seems not to exclude anyone. For more than a year, Nate’s been doing gymnastics (which he totally loves) every Monday. He’ll have swim lessons again this spring (indoor, at the community center) and summer (at our neighborhood pool), and we plan also try Tae Kwon Do, soccer, or T-ball. Last spring, he started going to a speech therapist for some minor pronunciation issues. He’s making good progress and will soon be going less frequently. He certainly loves talking and is a very expressive child, sharing his thoughts and feelings proudly.\n\n\nAs a future big brother: It has always been so gratifying and touching to see how gentle Nate is with babies and young children; he seems to instinctively “adjust” to their size and abilities. We are super excited to see him and his younger brother or sister together—having fun, learning, and growing together. We believe they will be one of each others'' greatest joys and assets in life.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Nate', 5253, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1363219728, 0),
