(1153, '<p>One of the things that excited us most about the move is that we would be very close to my family when our adoption occurred.   New York isn’t that far, but how nice that grandma and grandpa and aunts and uncles are just an hour away in Thurmont, MD – just outside of Frederick.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Holidays with my family are easy.  Neither Joe nor I are particularly religious, but we each grew up with strong values about family and commitment and service.  We celebrate Easter and Christmas with family and friends.  Every year, my grandmother hosts a Christmas Eve open house.  The extended family gathers at her house, and she always has a great spread.  We eat, visit and exchange gifts well into the evening.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Joe’s family lives in Reno, Nevada and we sometimes go west, or his family visits us here in Maryland.  We’re excited to take our child out west to experience the other side of the family and enjoy all the west has to offer.  Joe was captain of the ski team in high school, so I’m sure our little one will be introduced to winter sports on those great western slopes at a young age. Both sides of our family, and our friends, are so excited and supportive of us adopting, we need to keep helping them be patient!   ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'FAMILY', 4804, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1353966843, 0),
