(1214, '<h1><span style="color:#ff0000;">Birth Mother</span></h1>\n<p>Learning of an unplanned pregnancy can leave you feeling lost, alone and scared. You have many decisions to make, and we are committed to helping you through this difficult time.</p>\n<p>If you choose to work with Heart to Home Adoption Agency, LLC we have a variety of services that can give you support. Some of the Birth Mother Services we can offer you are:</p>\n<ul><li>Toll free Birthmother line 24-hours a day 7 days a week</li>\n<li>Confidentiality</li>\n<li>Support during birth of your baby</li>\n<li>Counseling</li>\n<li>Caring, supportive and dedicated staff</li>\n<li>Legal assistance</li>\n<li>Direct placement to new adoptive parents - NEVER any foster care</li>\n<li>The opportunity to choose a relationship with your baby''s adoptive family</li>\n<li>The opportunity to receive pictures and letters from your adoptive family</li>\n</ul><p><span>Birthparents'' Placement Process</span></p>\n<p>We will be here to walk you through these simple steps:</p>\n<ol><li>Contact us at 859.489.3055</li>\n<li>Complete and return all forms in the envelope provided as well as proof of pregnancy from your doctor or local clinic.</li>\n<li>Expect a call from a caring member of our staff.</li>\n<li>Discuss your adoption plan.</li>\n<li>Begin making a delivery and placement plan with your counselor, which includes choosing an adoptive family.</li>\n<li>Your birth mother coordinator will be with you through the labor and delivery of your baby.</li>\n<li>About three days after the baby is born, you will sign documents consenting to the adoption. At this critical time, you will have support, love and understanding.</li>\n<li>Ongoing counseling for you.</li>\n</ol><p> </p>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Phone: 859.489.3055</p>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p><a href="mailto:hearttohomeadopt@gmail.com">hearttohomeadopt@gmail.com</a></p>\n</div>\n<p> </p>\n</div>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Unplanned Pregnancy ', 5122, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1358865384, 0),
(1211, 'We have absolutely loved being married for the past few years!  We know it is because we are best friends.  We make each other laugh and still have fun together every day!   We are just your average, easy-going couple.  We are very out-going and have an amazing group of friends.  We get together with them for monthly game/dinner nights and plan vacations to different places every year.  We also have the most supportive, fun-loving family.  It seems that we are always celebrating someone''s birthday, graduation or other special event!\n\nWhen it is just the two of us, a typical evening consists of us taking our dogs, Annette and Charlie, for a walk, making dinner together or walking into Carytown for a bite to eat.  We make time to chat and relax every night. We curl up on the couch and Andrew turns on some football while Emily glances up from whatever book she is into at the moment.  When Emily has girls night or has found the motivation to get to the gym,  Andrew may be doing some yard work or playing on his indoor soccer team.\n\nLife is good, but we know that when a little one joins our family, it will be complete. :)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 5068, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358637186, 0),
(1200, 'Let me tell you about the life we can provide for your child/ children (if twins, triplets or siblings)\n\n\nIt is a life of a lot of laughing, lots of music, lots of hugs and an enormous amount of people\n\n\nIt is a life of with a LOT of reading and education\n\n\nIt is a life with the baby having its own bedroom, bathroom, and closet.\n\n\nIt is a life with grandparents. . .three VERY hands on grandparents who like to sing and read books and walk along the beach collecting shells. . .\n\nIt is a life where going to college is expected and their adoptive parents will pay for whatever school they want to go to \n\nIt is a life where they will work summer jobs to make spending money, but they can participate in whatever extracurriculars for school they would like. . .(Andy''s set on Running and Tae Kwon Do, I would love Dance and Piano) but they get to choose what they want to do. . . \n\nIt is a life of getting up late on the weekend and making pancakes, watching Monday night football with nachos, and movies with popcorn made in the air popper and not in the microwave (it tastes so much better). . .\n\nIt is a life of "let''s go" with friends to go play with and adventures to have. . .\n\nIt will be a life of travel. . .having your own little monogrammed suitcase to travel with. . .not just to visit family. . but to go to see Italy, Greece, Ireland. . .to walk the cobbled streets of London and grow up knowing that you are a part of a bigger world. . .\n\nIt will be a life where the baby will be the focus. . .but not spoiled. . . challenged. . but not pushed. . .given opportunitites. . .and allowed to be anything he or she want to be in this world. . .\n\nMost of all. . .over everything. . .the baby will be loved. . and held. . .and told "I love you" everyday. \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'The Life We Dream of Providing for The Baby', 2971, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1357704738, 0),
