', 'The Life the Baby Would Have as a Member of Our Family', 2971, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1358911242, 0),
(1203, 'On Children\n Kahlil Gibran\n\nYour children are not your children.\nThey are the sons and daughters of Life''s longing for itself.\nThey come through you but not from you,\nAnd though they are with you yet they belong not to you.\n\nYou may give them your love but not your thoughts, \nFor they have their own thoughts.\nYou may house their bodies but not their souls,\nFor their souls dwell in the house of tomorrow, \nwhich you cannot visit, not even in your dreams.\nYou may strive to be like them, \nbut seek not to make them like you.\nFor life goes not backward nor tarries with yesterday.\n\nYou are the bows from which your children\nas living arrows are sent forth.\nThe archer sees the mark upon the path of the infinite, \nand He bends you with His might \nthat His arrows may go swift and far.\nLet your bending in the archer''s hand be for gladness;\nFor even as He loves the arrow that flies, \nso He loves also the bow that is stable.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'On Children', 834, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358040628, 0),
(1204, 'How are you going to spend this precious life that you have been issued? Will you spend it trying to look good and creating the illusion that you have power over circumstances, or will you surrender to find out the truth about the discovery of  life and its lessons.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'This precious life', 834, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358045077, 0),
(1205, 'Brian and I met in March of 2002.  At the time Brian was working at Detroit Metropolitan Airport on Active Duty with the Michigan Army National Guard and I worked at Einstein Bagels.  We met through a friend I had worked with and we both knew it was love at first sight.  From that moment on we were inseparable.\n\nBrian proposed in November of 2003 before he was deployed to Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.  Upon returning from Cuba we got married six months later, in May of 2005.\n\nWe have been married for over 7 years and look forward to 70 more years together.  \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'How We Met', 5066, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358163054, 0),
(1206, 'Kristin was baptized into the Catholic faith at one day old before her first open heart surgery.  As a result, religion has always played an important part in her life.  I was not Catholic when I met Kristin, but after meeting her and going with her to church I, too, became Catholic.\n\n\nNeither me nor my sisters were baptized into any religion and after seeing how the Catholic faith has helped Kristin and I throughout our life my sister and her husband along with five of their kids also became Catholic.  We are proud to say that we are the godparents of 5 children.\n\n\nBrian and I believe that a good marriage is built on love and trust.  We both feel that through our 7 years of marriage each day brings new challenges and the saying of what does not kill you only makes you stronger is one of our favorite quotes to live by.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR FAITH', 5066, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358163144, 0),
(1247, 'We live in a small suburb of Kansas City.  Our family-filled neighborhood is full of trees and safe streets for kids to ride bikes. Our neighborhood is also near many different nature trails and playgrounds.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 5278, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1363131845, 0),
(1248, '     We were married in August of 2002.  We were married in the Catholic church and the church still plays an important part in our lives. We are a honest, hard working and compassionate couple. We have strong family values that have been passed down to us from our parents.  We enjoy each other’s company. We love to goof off and have a good time. We have great respect for each other and our marriage.  \n     \n     We also enjoy spending time with our friends and family.  We are blessed that our family lives so close together.  We also have best friends, who we consider family, that we are lucky enough to spend lots of time with. \n\n     We love to travel.  Jim is lucky enough to have a month of vacation each year and Jen is off each summer.  We try and take at least two vacations a year.  We spend our summer vacation at our families lake house in Minnesota. We love going to Florida to spend a relaxing week at the beach.  We also travel with our friends and family to enjoy various lakes in the midwest.\n\n     Our family has many traditions.  Christmas, Thanksgiving, Fourth of July, birthday’s and camping trips are the many things we do each year. These are important times for us because we are making many happy memories!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family and Traditions', 5278, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1363132041, 0),
(1209, 'We are so happy that you are reading our profile. We have wanted a baby for so long and are so looking forward to sharing our lives.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Excited!', 3313, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358426261, 0),
(1210, 'In the summer to get away, we go to a family house in Michigan on a small lake where we have a pontoon boat and some jet skis. Jim and I have fun looking for frogs as well. We have bon-fires and so-mores, yum! Its a lot of fun.\n\n\nWe also visit my sister who lives on a farm in Ky. which is a lot of fun too. She has chickens, which my nephew is in charge of. We love to escape to the hills of Ky. where there is lots of good music and beautiful sights outside.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'summertime', 3313, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1358427345, 0),
