(1223, 'At age 22, Tammy moved to Garden City, KS, to take a job teaching middle school English.  Shortly after moving, she met Nathan while proofreading his papers for a business class he was taking at the local junior college.  He took her out to dinner to say thank you for her help.  It ended up being a 5 hour dinner.  The courtship was a short one; it was about 5 months.  They got married in January of 2005.  They found out that Tammy was pregnant in late April of 2005.  Clara was born at 38 weeks on December 30, 2005, after a very challenging pregnancy.  After a very difficult and scary stay in the Newborn ICU, Clara was allowed to go home in mid January 2006.  Nathan and Tammy went on to have two more pregnancies that both ended in miscarriages.  It was not easy or according to several doctors, safe for Tammy to get pregnant and carry a baby to term.  They decided on open adoption through Catholic Social Services.  After almost 6 months of working on the process and having only one meeting left to complete the homestudy, Tammy became pregnant unexpectedly (it was never an issue to get pregnant, just to keep the baby and not cause problems with Tammy’s health).  They inactivated the adoption.  After almost 35 weeks of a very hard and complicated pregnancy, Mark was born on August 6, 2009.  He was allowed to come home after 2 ½ weeks in the Newborn ICU.  He came home on oxygen due to his prematurity and getting pneumonia in the hospital a few days after birth.  Today, both children are healthy.  Due to the risk to any future biological children and Tammy''s health if she got pregnant again, Nathan and Tammy made the permanent decision through surgery not to get pregnant again.  Nathan and Tammy both wanted to complete the open adoption process they had started.  In late 2012, they felt the time was right.  They hope to have a little boy or girl to add to their family as well as create a relationship with any birth parent that would like to.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 5187, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1359780533, 0),
(1224, 'Clara is our 7 year old daughter.  She was born on December 30th, 2005, after a very complicated pregnancy and scary birth.  Today, Clara is healthy although she does have PDD-NOS (type of autism) but is high functioning.  She is currently in first grade at a local Catholic elementary school.  With the help of an IEP, she is successful in school.  Clara is a very sweet child that likes to please others.  Clara''s favorite things include special time with just mommy or daddy, playing baby dolls (she also LOVES real babies), and using her Ipad for both learning and games.\n\nMark is our 3 1/2 year old son.  He was born on August 6, 2009.  Again, the pregnancy was complicated.  He was born at 35 weeks for his safety as Tammy''s body was attacking him.  Today, Mark is healthy and normal functioning.  He loves to go to a home preschool and make projects.  Mark will go to the Catholic school Clara is in next year for a more formal preschool program.  His personality is very loving, but also very ornery.  The saying "he''s all boy" definitely applies to Mark.  Mark''s favorite things include "wrestling" with daddy, playing with big sister (or driving her crazy not sure which), and playing with anything related to water.\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'The Kids (Clara and Mark)', 5187, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1359822925, 0),
(1225, 'We have one dog, Buddy.  He is a purebred collie that Nathan and Tammy rescued from the shelter during Tammy''s pregnancy with Clara.  Buddy is about 11 years old now, but he''s still very involved with the kids.  He''s especially close to Clara.  When in utero, Clara used to kick after Buddy would bump his nose into Tammy''s stomach just hard enough to make Clara kick.  It never hurt Tammy or Clara, but became a comfort to Tammy as Clara didn''t move much, making Tammy nervous that Clara was ok.  Buddy thinks of himself as a member of the family as does Nathan, Tammy, and the kids.  If it were up to him, he''d have a spot at the dinner table (notice I said if it were up to him).  He''s very watchful over both children and is quick to tattle to Tammy or Nathan if the kids are fighting/playing too rough.  Buddy is extremely important to the whole family.  When Nathan and Tammy moved the family 23 miles into a school district that would provide better services for Clara, it was never a question that they would only rent from a landlord that allowed Buddy (as at that time, their house hadn''t sold in the other school district).  Buddy is currently looking forward to a baby for one main reason...the food droppings of course.   ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family Dog (Buddy)', 5187, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1359823605, 0),
(1226, 'Estoy agradecida por la oportunidad de compartir un poco de mi vida contigo. Admiro tu fuerza y valor por pensar en adopción abierta.  Me daría mucho honor de ser parte de la vida de tu niño y anticipo aprender más de tus esperanzas y deseos del futuro. Daría la bienvenida a la oportunidad de compartir este viaje increíble contigo. Estoy aquí para ofrecerte alivio y apoyo en los meses y años que vienen. Te espero lo mejor!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Hablo Español!', 5019, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1359844170, 0),
