(1441, 'We began dating in October of 2010 and were married in June of 2012.  While we have been married for only a short amount of time, it is as if we have known each other all of our lives. Before we were married we knew that Shawn was unable to have children and that we wanted to expand our family. It was during this time that we first began to explore adoption. While we are unable to have children of our own we have a strong desire to parent. To us adoption seems the natural way to expand our family.   We admire your courage and strength and the love that you have for your child we thank you for taking the time to read about us.  We are open to having an on-going relationship with you as we feel that openness helps to provide a loving and stable environment for all. \n\n\n\n     We enjoy going to outdoor concerts, camping, being adventurous and spontaneous during traveling and we love to spend time with our family and friends. We believe that family is the most important thing in life.  In Shawn''s free time you will often find her playing volleyball, reading a good book or practicing yoga. During John''s free time, he is found on the soccer field.  After years of playing, he continues his passion for the sport by coaching for a competitive soccer club. Together John and Shawn like to hitch-up their pop-up camper and spend the weekends enjoying the outdoors. \n\n\n     We have a nine year old English Bull dog named Harley. Harley is loved by all who meet her. She is great with our nieces and nephews and they love to take her on walks. Harley''s favorite pass time is sleeping.\n\n\n     We are looking forward to starting our family. We admire your courage and strength as you make this difficult decision. We want to assure you that your child will be the center of our world. We are ready to welcome your child into our home with open arms. We have a passion for becoming parents and to providing a loving and supportive environment for your child. We will provide your child with unconditional love, a loving extended family, educational options and we will provide guidance and support throughout every opportunity presented to your child. We would like to thank you for considering us as you travel through this difficult journey and for helping us to make our dream of becoming parents come true. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About US', 4536, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1374778057, 0),
