(1255, 'We''ve got more of these on our website and in our profile book, but we were really touched by this one, from the director of our son''s preschool. I think it''s because it comes from someone outside our closest circle of family and friends and yet captures exactly what it is that we strive for ...\n\n\n\n"It is a pleasure to write about the Tom and Becky''s character and parenting style. I have known them for several years, as they have brought their son to our preschool. The love they feel for their son is inspiring. They are always there to support and encourage him and it is evident through the compassionate words they use, their flexibility, their physical affection, their joyful attitude, and the way they adapt, collaborate and communicate with his teachers. What also strikes me as particularly impressive, though, is that they share this love with the other children in the preschool. They give a lot of themselves to encourage the other children, involve themselves in school activities, support other families that may be struggling, extending their friendship, and make all children and families feel included in their emotional generosity. Tom, Becky & Nate are a wonderful part of our [preschool] family and the teachers and I are thrilled to know them. \n\n~ Dawn, Owner/Director [at Nate''s Preschool]\n \n \n \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Testimonials', 5253, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1363289957, 0),
