(1266, 'The Internet is amazing. If not for it, Tom and I would not be together. Nate would not be here! We owe so much of our happiness today to this technology, but it also has its limitations.\n\nIt''s hard to get across in words and pictures who we are. Even in person, it takes a good amount time to REALLY get to know people. (I am a firm believer in this.) You need to see how they are in different situations: not only under normal circumstances, when things are going well, but also when things are hard. Over time, you may see all sorts of things about people that they''d never think to tell you in a forum such as this--things you like, things you don''t like, things you''re not sure about. \n\nI, Becky, am writing this section in an attempt to reveal a little bit more about who we are, what we''re like, and how we''ve come to where we are now. My goal is to be as open and honest as possible. I''ll add to it as I think of things...\n\n ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Inside Scoop on Us: A List of Random Facts and Observations :)', 5253, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1364079721, 0),
