(1271, '<p style="text-align:justify">After we remodeled our condo, we decided to scale up our domestic projects. So we bought a house. 3 bedrooms, 2 Baths, open floor plan, with a playroom perfect basement, looking onto a fenced in backyard, and plenty of room to keep building. Filled with the thunder of kitty paws, the smell of Amanda''s baking, and Brad''s building...It is missing a baby''s laughing. (Oh, ya, and Norman, the squirrel, lives in the tree out back. The kitties REALLY like Norman.)\n</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our House', 5413, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1364882879, 0),
(1297, 'Throughout this webpage, you will learn a little about me – about my family, my friends, my hobbies, and my passions! One of the most important things to know about me is that I have spent countless hours praying and preparing for this moment.\n \nI have always dreamed of being a mother, and adoption has always been a consideration. I believe that families are created in different ways, and for many, adoption is a great option. I am familiar and comfortable with adoption because my life has already been blessed immeasurably by several adopted children. These children have brought so much love, laughter, and joy into my life; I honestly cannot imagine a life without them. After much reflection and prayer, I am ready to begin my own journey into motherhood. Even though I am currently single and will have sole responsibility for this child, in no way would I be raising this child alone. My entire family and network of friends are just as excited to welcome this little one into our world.\n \nI am a professional woman, who actually enjoys working and has been blessed with career success. Because I intend to keep working, I have sought the advice and counsel of other professional women who are currently raising kids (or already have done so). With the help of these women, I am developing a list of resources and strategies that I can use, when the time comes. But more importantly, I already have a support system of women who are doing the same thing – juggling work and family – and doing it all quite successfully.\n \nIn addition to working and spending quality time with my family, I have several hobbies that you’ll learn more about as you read. All in all, I think people will say that I am full of love, lots of fun, and overflowing with energy and enthusiasm for life and living! \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Me', 5498, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1365622456, 0),
(1307, 'April 26 - So if we met you at a party tonight, and we didn''t know each others'' situations, I''m wondering: what details from our lives would probably come out? Something like this, maybe...\n\nBecky just started training for Baltimore''s 2013 marathon - Tom practices "old time" traditional guitar tunes every chance he gets but sometimes he throws in something from left field (currently, for example: the theme from Napolean Dynamite) - Nate draws many, many pictures per day and maybe 90% of them are very intricate spaceships (he seems to have a photographic memory for certain things) - Becky''s phasing-in to our household/lives foods, products and practices that are green/organic/non-toxic and phasing out what''s not (this is a growing interest of hers) - Tom is reading the biographies of Thomas Jefferson and Walt Whitman **simultaneously** (makes for great conversation!) - Nate won Party-Junior Monopoly tonight ... and he won''t let us forget it - Becky is going to be a stay-at-home-mom/freelance writer & editor starting in June 2013 - We''re going to Castine, Maine for our family vacation this year, sharing a place with some family friends -- can''t wait! - Becky has begun working on a young adult novel - Secretly, Tom actually likes mowing the lawn (it''s relaxing) - Nate just started soccer (so far, so good) - We are going to a housewarming picnic on Sunday -- can''t wait to see how happy and proud our friends are of their new place, which is a loooong time coming... \n\nSee, I think you can learn about a person through small talk. Wonder what we''d learn about you? Would love to have that talk -- small talk, deep conversation, or whatever. Hope we can begin soon! \n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'SMALL TALK, LATE APRIL....', 5253, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1367149154, 0),
(1291, 'Goran is a wonderful teacher and a lvoing husband.  He is my"rock" and has such a calming spirit and a quiet strength about him.  My family quickly took to his charming personality and our nephews love to play hide-and-seek with their Uncle Goran.  He enjoys playing basketball and reading in the evening.  I can''t wait to see Goran teach the newest addition to our family how to make a basket.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Goran by Lori', 1538, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1365265816, 0),
(1292, 'We are so blessed to have great family ties with similar values and support.  We both feel our parents were our role models and inspiration in life.  We are close to both sides and look forward to spending time together as a whole family.  We love to get together and spend our time fishing, swimming, camping, grilling,watching movies together and going for walks.\nWe thank you for the time you''ve taken to get to know us through this website.  We hope you know how loving and courageous you are in giving your child this selfless gift.  Please take comfort in believing that there is a safe, loving, and permanent home waiting for your child.  We know that adoption is a lifelong journey for all of us, and we will approach it with compassion, honesty, and commitment.\nWe all want what is best for your child and we will respect your wishes when it comes to establishing a level of openness and contact that makes you comfortable.\nWith loving support and respect,\nLori and Goran', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family', 1538, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1365266196, 0),
