(1277, '<p>Let me tell you a little about my Adam. I''m sure you have heard many girls say that they have the best husband in the world... I am convinced that I do! Adam treats me like a princess and he is always such a gentleman. He has such a caring personality and he always puts other''s needs before his own. He is very quiet until you get to know him, but he is a really funny guy once he opens up. He loves to joke around and have fun. People love him and are drawn to him. All of our friends and family respect him and really look up to him. Adam works at a large local hospital and he has a wonderful work schedule. He works three twelve hour shifts, Monday through Wednesday, which will allow him to spend more time with our baby. <br /><br /><br />Adam also has an adventurous side. Every time we go out to eat, he always orders the most peculiar thing on the menu, so that is the running joke when we go out to eat with friends and family. The question of the night is, "What will Adam order?" Some of the things that he enjoys is college football, fishing, and grilling. He loves being outdoors during the summer time and spending the day at the lake. I hope that I have assisted you in getting to know Adam a little better. I could not ask for a better husband, and I know he will be a wonderful father too. Your child will be so blessed to be able to have a father like Adam. I cannot wait to see our dream of becoming parents come true!</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Adam', 5291, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1364908587, 0),
(1278, '<p>We met at a youth church camp while we were both in high school. We attended different high schools, but that did not stop Adam from driving down every single weekend to visit. We were both very busy playing sports, but some how we still made time to talk on the phone every night and mail letters during the week. We dated for six years and then we got married after college graduation. <br /><br />We really have an awesome relationship. We are truely best friends. Our personalities are completely opposite, but I think that is why we get along so well. Adam is more laid back and shy until you get to know him, while Sabrina is very outgoing and never meets a stranger. We are surrounded by many close friends and both of our families live near. We have been so blessed with a wonderful family. Our parents and family are beyond supportive of us adopting. They are all so excited and have already started buying baby things for us.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We both share a passion for helping others and we both work at large local hospitals. We both participate in household chores and we work as a team in everything we do. We both love to cut up and have fun, so there is always laughter in our household. For fun, our favorite place to go is the beach. We just love the peaceful sound of the waves hitting the shore. We also love spending time at the lake and grilling out with family and friends during the summer. In the fall and winter seasons, we love to go to the mountains in Tennessee. The mountains are absolutely breathtaking when the leaves have changed colors for fall. We also love the snow in the mountains during the winter.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>We already have a nursery that is completely ready to welcome a baby into our family. We could not be more excited and anxious to meet our precious baby. It will definately be a dream come true and a long awaited answered prayer when we recieve that phone call! </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Getting To Know Us', 5291, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1364908348, 0),
(1279, '<p>My name is Brad. My wife''s name is Amanda.We met over twelve years ago while working late on projects in college. Amanda says that she liked my creative flair, and that I couldn''t believe there was life outside of studying. I liked her daring, drive, and intelligence. Oh, did I mention that she is absolutely gorgeous? I also figured that I didn''t have a shot with her.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Since we are being, ''all cards on the table'' honest here, I''ll tell you that Amanda can be a bit impatient at times. Lucky for us, this was one of those times. She walked into the class I was supervising and asked, "So…when are you going to ask me out?" It is exceedingly difficult to supervise a class of Freshmen when a gorgeous girl walks into the class, and calls you out. So, here I am, put up or shut up time. I put up, and took her on our first date,,,To meet my entire family.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Did I mention that Amanda can be extremely patient, as well? Again, lucky for us, this was one of those times. I don''t know what I was thinking, but I subjected her to my mom, dad, brother, sister, their spouses, my aunts, uncles, cousins, and THEIR spouses. Don''t get me wrong, my family is great, but that''s a lot for anyone to take. We also narrowly avoided getting sucked up by a tornado on the way home. First date, no kidding, and she stayed. I met Amanda''s family a month, or so, later. Her dad just wanted to be sure that my intentions were honorable. Something about owning a lot of land, a front loader, and no one missing me...but that is neither here nor there. A couple of years later, we were married in Amanda’s hometown. It must be providence.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Fast forward 10+ years. We have found a great city in which to live, and work. We created successful and truly rewarding careers in product design (more on this in another section). We adopted three wonderful cats, bought and remodeled our first home, and traveled all over the world. We also bought our next house, enjoy golfing, picked up fishing, and archery (more on that later, too).</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>It is safe to say that we have happy and fulfilling lives, but we have always known that something is missing. We wanted to share all of it with kids. We tried to do just that for years, but one miscarriage led to another and another and, well, you get the picture. The specialists were called in, tears were shed, deep seeded beliefs were questioned, and something was made very clear. We still want a family, but it isn''t going to happen that way. We are both excited to welcome an adopted child into our home to love, cherish, teach, and maybe spoil a bit. This decision must be very difficult for you, but we have so much love that we want to share. Please know that you will make a family like us so happy, and that you will be giving your child a wonderful safe home.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'The Story Of Us', 5413, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1364905231, 0),
(1308, '<p><span style="background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;color:#0000ff;font-size:large;">We''ve created a profile on Adoptimist!  It''s full of pictures </span><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;color:#0000ff;font-size:large;">a</span><span style="color:#0000ff;font-size:large;"><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;">nd adoption journal entries.  Come and visit to learn more about us!        </span></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="background-color:#ffffff;"><span style="color:#0000ff;font-size:large;"><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;">Click on the link below  </span></span><strong style="font-size:10px;"><span style="color:#0000ff;font-size:xx-large;"><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;">↓</span></span></strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:center;"><strong style="text-align:left;font-size:medium;"><span style="font-family:verdana, geneva;color:#ff6600;"><a href="https://www.adoptimist.com/adoption-parent-profile/2619">https://www.adoptimist.com/adoption-parent-profile/2619</a></span></strong><img style="color:#0000ff;font-family:verdana, geneva;font-size:large;vertical-align:baseline;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/Sampsawender/20130502_183717.jpg" alt="kristin and becca adopt" width="80" height="60" /></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'CHECK OUT OUR FULL PROFILE ON ADOPTIMIST', 2837, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1368041702, 0),
