(1324, '<p>Our journey together started in 2002, when we were introduced by amutual friend. Three years later, a move to Sacramento, the purchase of a house and a lot of wedding planning, we were married. Despite the rain on our outdoor wedding, it was an amazing start to our beautiful life together. We are an easy going, loving couple and truly each other’s best friends. We always have fun together and frequently find ourselves laughing or just being silly, by making crazy faces at each other or singing made up songs.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Journey', 5748, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1368571493, 0),
(1325, 'We live in a close knit, well establish neighborhood in Sacramento. We know all our neighbors and it is rare that we can go outside without\nsaying “Hi” to someone. Walking our dog Rocky usually turns into\nsocial time as the neighborhood children play with him; he loves the\nattention and is very gentle. Our neighborhood is very family oriented and we can’t wait for our child to be part of the annual 4th of July Block Party. We live within walking distance to many great parks and highly recommended schools. The American River is close by and comes in handy for a refreshing swim on those warm summer days. We have\nenjoyed updating our house and we love the home we have created. We are excited to share our lives and love with a new baby.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 5748, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1368571570, 0),
(1326, 'In our free time we love to travel and sightsee, whether it is out of state, another country or a day/weekend getaway. Our abroad travels tend to take us to the Caribbean, as we love the ocean, outdoor\nactivities and the care-free atmosphere. We look forward to exposing our child to different cultures and experiences both through our travels and in our local community. One of the things we love so much about Sacramento is its cultural diversity.\nIn the summer we enjoy camping trips with close friends and can’t wait to watch our child enjoy their first toasted marshmallow. We frequently attend San Francisco Giants baseball games and often spend\nweekends in the city so we can see a musical or play as well. Winter tends to take us to the Sierra\nMountains where we can play in the snow, go sledding or skiing. We are looking forward to making our first snowman as a family. We also find a peacefulness cuddling on the couch, watching a movie with a bowl of popcorn-made on the stovetop, of course!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Interests', 5748, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1368571652, 0),
(1327, 'Our families and all our friends are almost as eager as we are about our plans for adoption. Their love and support is something we cherish and know we are blessed to have. We talk/Skype frequently with Frank’s family in Rhode Island and see them as often as we can. Bridget’s parents and brother are a short walk from our house. Bridget’s parents are anxiously awaiting their first grandchild and can’t wait to start the spoiling. Bridget’s mom, Beth, is retired and has been very patiently awaiting this arrival, by sewing blankets and bibs for her first grandbaby. Grandma Beth will be our main source of day care during the\ncouple days a week that we will need childcare.\nWe are surrounded by a large, close group of friends, some of which we have known since childhood. Many of them have young children and we are honored to be the godparents of two beautiful girls. We get together with friends and family often and love hosting gatherings at our home, whether it’s for the\nholidays, to BBQ or have a friendly game of Wii bowling.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family &amp; Friends', 5748, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1368571721, 0),
(1328, 'We feel it is so important for our child to know where their life story began and they will always know how much you love them and how special you are to us. We truly believe a child can never have too many people in their lives that love and support them and we will do everything we can to\nfoster a loving, healthy relationship with you. We will take great pride and honor in providing a home that they can flourish in, surrounded with love, guidance and encouragement. We hope that by learning more about us and knowing our commitment to raise a well rounded, confident child will give you peace of mind. We look forward to getting to know you and\nsharing this journey with you.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Promise To You', 5748, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1368571821, 0),
(1329, '<p><span style="font-family:''arial black'', ''avant garde'';">All About Love Adoptions</span> 64 E. Uwchlan Avenue #248 Exton, PA 19341 •  </p>\n<p>E-Mail: <a href="mailto:info@AHSAstaff.com">info@AHSAstaff.com</a> Business: 610.429.1001 Fax: 800.871.3196</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Adoption Agency', 5699, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1370830494, 0),
(1330, '<p><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LoriandSam/615276_10151048469287720_1870443332_o-1.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="300" /></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">Lori is a truly remarkable, and very unique woman. This was obvious to me within five minutes of meeting her although it took two or three days before I realized she was exactly what I needed for the rest of my life!She has an ability to read situations and people and provide whatever is needed at that time, whether it is a joke and a smile to lighten the mood, a sympathetic ear to hear the problem or a display of energy and motivation to get the issue tackled.As a full scholarship college athlete in soccer she showed boundless energy and a competitive, determined spirit. As a Mother, she demonstrates the same traits and our four year old loves the fact her Mom can be as fun and silly as any of her friends.Lori''s role as an early childhood educator sees her both as a classroom teacher and as a special instructor, helping young children and their families where they may need some extra help with the child''s development.Lori has really found her path in life and our daughter and I are the luckiest people in the world that this path includes us! Having been adopted at birth into a wonderful, loving family and also enjoying a positive relationship with her birth mother, Lori has provided me with a great insight into how adoption can work. I am so grateful I have Lori in my life to give me the support and balance I need as well as being the greatest Mom to our child. I just can''t wait to share the experience of growing our family through adoption with her.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Lori, By Sam', 5699, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1377223742, 0),
(1331, '<p>                                                             <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/LoriandSam/wedding_photo_black_and_white.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="287" />                                                    </p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">When I first agreed to meet  Sam, I thought I was going out for a fun date with a guy who had a  "cool" British accent.  Little did I know I was going to meet the man of my dreams.The moment I met Sam, I knew that it was not just his accent that caught my interest, but his intelligence, wit, charm and there was never any of those awkward moments of silence.  Twelve years later he still has that same wit, sense of humor, and charismatic personality, not only with me but his daughter, the children he coaches and those who come into contact with him.  As a Distribution Manager, Sam motivates and organizes many different people each day and he is also the Director of Coaching for a local soccer club.  This is his passion after his family of course, and he devotes his time leading and nurturing the children who play for him as well as the other coaches within the club. His influence on these children expands off the field where he demonstrates quite how much he cares for these kids and makes him stand out as a coach. Perhaps the traits that make Sam such a fantastic father and husband is his determination and passion. When he decides on something being right way to go, he will not stop until he has traveled that path. This means his family enjoys everything they could wish for from their father and then some!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Sam, By Lori', 5699, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1373833837, 0),
(1332, 'In 2002, against both of our better judgment, we agreed to meet on a blind date, encouraged by the middle school students and their parents who Lori was teaching at the time and Sam was coaching.  By the next day we were in a serious relationship and within two weeks we were planning a trip back to England for Christmas to meet Sam''s family.  Sam had forewarned them he was bringing home the girl he was going to marry.  Although Lori agreed within a few short months that an engagement was imminent, she made Sam swear he would not ask her until at least a year of dating.\n After nine or ten months, Lori started to complain about a lack of a ring!  Sam ( a British Citizen) had to renew his work visa, given his plan to return back to the UK had changed so dramatically!  After a Jewish based ceremony at the Philadelphia Cricket Club in August of 2004 we enjoyed a honeymoon in Jamaica, followed by a trip to England to repeat our vows at a Christian based service in front of our UK family and friends, plus a few travelers from the USA.\nWhile the instant attraction from that first date has not dwindled in the slightest, it has given way to a deeper understanding that without each other, neither of us are complete.\n\nHaving spent a large part of our professional lives working with children, we were both ready to start growing our family shortly after we were married and presumed the process would be straight forward and immediate.  However, after several months of trying to conceive without success, we sought fertility treatment.  After a great deal of expense physically, financially and most noticeably of all, emotionally, we took a break from treatment having been told we were in the 1% of infertile couples that are classified as "unexplained."  During that break from treatment we conceived naturally and have since devoted our lives to the miracle that is now our four-year-old daughter.  A few years ago we started to try to conceive a sibling for Ellarose but ran into the same issues we faced the first time around.  This time we only endured about 9 months of treatment, assessments and surgeries in an attempt to have another child.  Although we do not feel quite the same grief and devastation we felt the first time, the three of us still feel our family is not yet complete.  \nAfter many discussions as to the appropriateness of adoption for our family, aided by Lori''s unique understanding of the subject, having been adopted herself and having a special, unique relationship with her birthmother, we are in complete agreement that not only is it something we feel is right for us, we feel it is the very reason why we have the "unexplained infertility" issue in the first place.   We truly believe we are well prepared and destined to become adoptive parents to a child and we are able to offer them a comfortable and loving home and more importantly, a close and loving family.  That "unexplained" part of our diagnosis is no longer a mystery to us; it is easily explained, as it has led us down this path.\n\nWe love to take family trips as often as possible, visiting friends and family in Toronto and of course England, where Ellarose gets excited to see her cousins and Grandparents and the rest of the very tight extended family.\nIn the fall and winter we take trips to the mountains to snow tube and ski and we love to take trips to Disney World. In the spring and summer we like to go to the beach with our friends and family, although most of the time is spent doing anything but lying in the sun! \nFor all those days we can’t spend on vacation, we are fortunate enough to live in a beautiful home that has a huge yard, surrounded by trees, which becomes the perfect setting to play, have cookouts, explore and relax. During the winter, we have plenty of space indoors to play or to unwind watching a movie together.\nOur whole family is very active. Lori and Sam still play soccer regularly and Sam does a lot of coaching.\nEllarose loves to play outside or go to her swim, dance or soccer lessons. However, her Grandma was thrilled last year when she to appeared on stage next to her in a musical!\nThank you for your the time you have taken to read this brief account of how we have started to become a family. We have so much love to give another child and the three of us can''t wait for our family to grow again.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'A Little More About Us', 5699, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1368668315, 0);
