(1346, '<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;">We have three family dogs named Shia, Bella and Yama.  </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;">Shia is a Black German Shepard who we adopted from the local animal shelter 2 years ago. She is active and loves to play ball outside, swim in her pool, loves the lake, playing in the water at the lake and enjoys playing in the snow! She is watchful of her little sisters and likes to play tug of war with Bella whenever she can get Bella to play. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;">Bella is a black chihuahua mix who we adopted from the animal shelter 4 years ago. She is playful, likes to play ball, loves to cuddle and snuggle and be loved.  Bella enjoys playing with her sisters and being outdoors until it gets cold.  </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;">Yama is a small chihuahua who Kerri got 6 years ago. Yama would sleep all day if we let her. Yama can be cold even in the warm weather. She enjoys laying in the sun in the Summer and would rather not go outside in the Winter and would like to stay bundled up. Yama loves to snuggle and be wrapped up in a blanket. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;">All 3 will be very accepting of a child in the home and they can''t wait for a new addition to the family!!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Shia Bella and Yama (Family Dogs)', 4942, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1381967496, 0),
