(1480, '\n<p>I had a happy childhood and want to provide the same type of environment for our children.  I grew up the oldest of three - I have a younger brother and sister with whom I am still very close. My parents were our biggest fans and provided all of the love, security, and encouragement a child could want.<p>\n<BR />\n<p>Jon and I met through a mutual friend in college.   I was attracted to Jon’s witty sense of humor, his loyalty, his work ethic, and his love for Jesus.  I knew he was the one I wanted to spend the rest of my life with and raise children with.  We’ve been happily married for 16 years.</p>\n<BR/ >\n<p>We were blessed 5 years ago when we adopted our son, Sam.  He is the love of my life – like my heart walking around outside of my body :) . He just started Kindergarten and loves it!</p>\n<BR />\n<p>I am an accountant and have been with the same accounting firm for more than 15 years.  I work part time so I can be home with Sam after school.  I love to travel and we try to take a trip each year.  I also enjoy reading (when I can find the time), piddling in the yard, and decorating our home, especially for the holidays!</p>\n<BR/ >\n<p>Sam was an answer to many prayers.  And, as much as we have enjoyed every minute, I have always felt our family was somehow incomplete.  I think it is so important for Sam to have a brother or sister to love and grow up with and for that little brother or sister to have a big brother!  So, we are very excited to start our adoption journey again.   </p>\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Debbie', 1663, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1382495696, 0),
(1350, 'Dear Birthmother, \n\nWe are Jai and Leah. Words can’t express our gratitude for considering us as adoptive parents to your child. We think of you daily and pray for you to find peace as you consider your options and make this difficult decision. If you choose us to be your child’s adoptive family, he or she, will be loved and cherished by all off the people in our lives. We offer a commitment to your child’s education and to their development as a happy, healthy individual. \n\nThree years ago we discovered we are unable to conceive children. Determined to be parents, we began our adoption journey. We read books and took classes to find out as much as we could about adopting a child. We met with a panel of birth mothers in Texas. Each woman bravely shared her story about why she chose adoption. Perhaps the greatest insight we obtained was the decision to pursue an open adoption. We listened to biological and adoptive parents share creative ways they stay in touch and how beneficial this connection has been for the child. In June of 2011, we got the phone call our son was born! During the next few days, we met with his birthmother, birthfather, and birth grandmother! We listened to them share their hopes and dreams. We brought him home when he was 6 days old. It’s been the greatest two years of our lives! \n\nOur open adoption looks slightly different with each member of his biological family. We send email updates and pictures every few months. We have dinner together a few times a year. Sullivan has a picture of his birth family in his nursery. There is another photo proudly displayed in our living room. The teddy bear she sent has a special place in his crib. Sullivan will always know the story of how he came to us. We are proud of his biological parents for their courage and wisdom. We believe there can never be too many people who love him. \n\nJai and I are ready to adopt a sibling, or siblings, for Sullivan. Ideally, we are looking for birthparents who would consider an open or semi-open adoption. We are willing to work out a situation you feel comfortable with. Please know we will always send photographs and share milestone stories with you! \n\nIf you have questions we can answer, please be in touch! Good luck with your decision. Remember, trust your gut! I believe every child finds the family they are destined to be with. Thank you for your amazing courage! \n\nWarmly, \nJai, Leah and Sullivan\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Dear Birthmother', 5784, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1369419711, 0),
