iblings, for Sullivan. Ideally, we are looking for birthparents who would consider an open or semi-open adoption. We are willing to work out a situation you feel comfortable with. Please know we will always send photographs and share milestone stories with you! <br />If you have questions we can answer, please be in touch! Good luck with your decision. Remember, trust your gut! I believe every child finds the family they are destined to be with. Thank you for your amazing courage! </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><br />Warmly, Jai, Leah and Sullivan</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Dear Birth Mother:', 5784, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1369421116, 0),
(1352, 'I live in a spacious and welcoming 4-bedroom home in a very family-oriented community. My neighborhood has countless child-friendly features just a short walk from my front door. There are playgrounds, pools, basketball courts, soccer fields, nature trails, duck ponds, and a community center within a 3 minute walk. The public and private schools in the area are also excellent. It’s a fantastic community for raising children.\n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'My home', 5686, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1375381323, 0),
(1353, '  I (Melanie) grew up with a large extended family.  My cousins were my best friends, and most of them lived in the same town.  My parents and grandparents, aunts and uncles, and cousins have really played a large roll in my life.  Some of the best memories of childhood that I have are of family gatherings on holidays and birthdays. Even more importantly, I learned from my family the art of "being there" for one another in times of need. \n\n   Our immediate family consists of Joe, our son Michael, and me.  Michael is the light of my life!  I call him my "angel boy".  He is a sweet little boy - sensitive and curious, and feisty too! He has endured so much medically with surgeries, but he has always been so strong and such a fighter!\n\n   Michael is very affectionate with us and his grandparents and teachers.  He attends the local elementary school which is across the street from our home.  He loves animals and visiting  a local farm.  He enjoys all types of music and hums along with our church choir. \n\n   I believe Michael will be a blessing to a sibling.  His future brother or sister could learn so much from him.  They will learn compassion and tolerance of differences and disabilities in people.  They will learn, just as we are learning, that every person is sacred and has a special role to play in this world.  \n\n   I also believe Michael will learn so much from having a sibling.  He will have someone to share his life with, to play with and grow up with.  He will likely be inspired to try new things as he sees his sister or brother reaching their own milestones.  He will learn to share his toys and our attention!  (Right now he is the prince of the house:))\n\n   Michael has grandparents and uncles and aunts and cousins who love him, and any child we are blessed with will be surrounded by many people who love and care for them.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'OUR FAMILY', 5772, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1376591534, 0),
(1455, '<p><strong>From Christine<span style="color:#0000ff;"> (and Todd)</span></strong></p>\n<p>We got started late in comparison to many.  We were both thirty seven  years old when we met.  I truly started to wonder if I was ever  going to find the right guy.  We met at a church New Year''s Eve young  adult party.  Not what I would''ve expected.  <span style="color:#0000ff;">(Todd: I knew she was coming to the party and was on a mission to talk to her.)</span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#0000ff;"><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;">I didn''t  quite understand who Todd was when we first started talking ''cause he is  unlike any other guy I''d ever met. He''s really laid back, quiet, with a  funny sense of humor.  But when the music started playing and we  started dancing (Todd is a great dancer, he''s got soul), I knew I had to  get to know him better, that there was more to him than meets the eye. <span style="color:#0000ff;">(Todd: I had to fight off a few dudes, but it was my moment.  She''s a great dancer, herself!)</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;"><span style="color:#0000ff;"><br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;">I truly  believe God helped me find my soul mate; thankfully, because I don''t  think I could''ve picked the right man otherwise.  We fell in love  quickly and knew we wanted to marry five months into dating.  Todd is my  best friend, my charming, loving, generous husband, my partner in life  and in business, a man in whom I wish every child could have as a  father.  He inspires and supports me, he''s constantly making me laugh,  he loves me with complete abandonment, and we look forward to loving  your child with this same fierce commitment, love, support and  abandonment.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;"><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#0000ff;">(Todd:  Christine is the girl I''ve waited for my whole life, my dream girl.  I  only wish I could''ve met her 20 years earlier, but God had His plan and  I''m so thankful for the gift she is.  She is beautiful and passionate  about life.  She has a fierce heart, a vulnerable heart.  She''s my best  friend.  We balance each other and we pursue each other still. Through  this process, I constantly envision her as the mother of our child, and  how she will nurture, protect and deeply love the child God has for us.)</span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#0000ff;"><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;">I''ve never  been more happy than I am during these first several years being married  to Todd.  We are ready for this next chapter in our lives, to start a  family and have read books as well as gone through special adoption  counseling/training.  It''s been important and grounding for us as we  prepare to be parents and has taught us a great deal about the  importance of an open or semi-open adoption whenever possible.  We are  much more confident now in the ways we can support our child to build a strong sense of  indentity.  We are committed to you to  always cherish and love your child unconditionally, and our families cannot  wait to welcome, celebrate and spoil them.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;"><br /></span></p>\n<p>If you choose us to  parent your child , he or she will grow up in a stable, loving,  creative, financially secure, God-fearing and God-loving home.  We both  plan on taking very active roles as parents, and have been blessed with  careers/businesses in which we work from home.  We look forward to  reading to him/her, travelling, teaching them to swim, to explore and  learn about other cultures, to play sports, to experience the arts,  provide them with the best education possible, attend a fun, embracing,  culturally diverse church, and they will be surrounded by family,  friends and neighbors committed to the same.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Thank you for considering us as your child''s  future family.  We pray that you find peace and have confidence in the  choice you make for your child.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 6118, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1376927536, 0),
(1354, '<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">     We were married in August of 2002.  We were married in the Catholic church and the church still plays an important part in our lives. We are a honest, hard working and compassionate couple. We have strong family values that have been passed down to us from our parents.  We enjoy each other’s company. We love to goof off and have a good time. We have great respect for each other and our ma</span><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">r</span><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">riage. </span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">           <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/jimjen/BJs_Wedding_088.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="375" />     </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;"><span> </span>We also enjoy spending time with our friends and family.  We are blessed that our family lives so close together.  We also have best friends, who we consider family, that we are lucky enough to spend lots of time with.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">          <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/jimjen/IMG_0114.JPG" alt="" width="500" height="375" /><br /></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>     <span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">We love to travel.  Jim is lucky enough to have a month of vacation each year and Jen is off each summer.  We try and take at least two vacations a year.  We spend our summer vacation at our families lake house in Minnesota. We love going to Florida to spend a relaxing week at the beach.  We also travel with our friends and family to enjoy various lakes in the midwest.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;"><img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/jimjen/IMG_0356.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="300" /><br /></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">     Our family has many traditions.  Christmas, Thanksgiving, Fourth of July, birthday’s and camping trips are the many things we do each year. These are important times for us because we are making many happy memories!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">                          <img src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/jimjen/Mothers_Day-Memorial_Day_-_Junction_city_059.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="300" /><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family and Traditions', 5278, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1369782220, 0),
