(1369, '<h3>Our Story</h3>\n<p>We met through mutual friends. Josh''s friend from childhood married Katie''s friend from high school. They set us up on a blind date. Immediately we realized it was meant to be.<br /><br />From the time we began dating, more than 6 years ago, we knew we wanted to have kids together. Katie was born with a hip condition which would make it difficult for her to carry a child, so adoption was always something discussed as part of building our family. For the past 2 years we have undergone intense fertility treatments and the whole pregnancy thing is just not working for us. Because adoption was always something we wanted to do we decided what better time than now. We truly feel that a Higher Power is pulling us in this direction to adopt. <br /><br />We were both raised in families with A LOT of love and we feel grateful to share that love with a child. Josh has one younger sister and Katie has two older brothers. Both of our siblings and parents are eagerly awaiting a possible first niece/nephew, grandchild to dote on. </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 5814, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1370372769, 0);
