(1375, 'We have been married for 11 years, and started dating our junior year in high school.  We''ve been inseparable ever since.  In 1998 we both attended the same college.  Steve received a Masters degree and Sheila double majored and received a Bachelors degree.  While in college, we got very involved in our campus church and really came to realize the importance of God in our lives and in all the decisions we make.  When we married, it was because we deeply loved each other, wanted the best for each other, and felt God was calling us to be married.  It was His will for us to create a new family centered on life and love.  We have always wanted a big family since we were engaged.  Our parents all came from larger families (4, 5, and 6 kids) while we both only had one other sister.  Growing up surrounded by many aunts, uncles, and cousins showed us how much fun growing up in a large family could be.  We knew having lots of children was a great way to have a joy filled home.\n	After our third son was born, the doctors told us we couldn''t have any more children.  What a shock that was!  Even while we were still in the hospital, we started discussing adoption.  After some time and prayer, we came to see that God was calling us to make our family bigger through adoption.  We know how awesome God''s plans are and how they are always so much better than our own plans.  We can''t wait to meet the children He has in mind for our family.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 3293, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1370834189, 0),
(1376, '<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"><span style="font-size:medium;font-family:''times new roman'', times;">We have been married for 12 years, and started dating our junior year in high school.  We''ve been inseparable ever since.  In 1998 we both attended the same college.  Steve received a Masters degree and Sheila double majored and received a Bachelors degree.  While in college, we got very involved in our campus church and really came to realize the importance of God in our lives and in all the decisions we make.  </span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"> </p>\n<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"><span style="font-size:medium;font-family:''times new roman'', times;">We have always wanted a big family since we were engaged.  Our parents all came from larger families (4, 5, and 6 kids) while we both only had one other sister.  Growing up surrounded by many aunts, uncles, and cousins showed us how much fun growing up in a large family could be.  We knew having lots of children was a great way to have a joy filled home.  After our third son was born, the doctors told us we couldn''t have any more children.  What a shock that was!  Even while we were still in the hospital, we started discussing adoption.  After some time and lots of prayer, we came to see that God was calling us to make our family bigger through adoption.  We know how awesome God''s plans are and how they are always so much better than our own plans.  We can''t wait to meet the children He has in mind for our family.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story', 3293, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1370965373, 0),
