(1377, '<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"><span style="font-size:medium;font-family:''times new roman'', times;">We have three boys, David age 9, Joshua age 7, and Nathan age 5.  The boys love playing together, especially with Legos.  David enjoys reading to his brothers after we put them to bed.  His favorite subject is science.  Joshua enjoys watching movies together as a family (especially Star Wars The Clone Wars).  Nathan is a huge fan of Thomas the Tank Engine, and just loves anything with wheels.  All the boys love playing with our friend''s babies when they come over.  They talk about when we will have a new baby all the time, and it is hard asking them to be patient.  </span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"> </p>\n<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"><span style="font-size:medium;font-family:''times new roman'', times;">We have been blessed with very large extended families.  Steve''s parents, sister, five sets of aunts and uncles, and eight cousins all live nearby.  Sheila has her parents, one grandma, eight sets of aunts and uncles, and 19 cousins all within 20 minutes of our house!  We see everyone about once a month, but even more often in the summer, because of all the family parties for birthdays, graduations, and holidays.  We see Nana and Papa (Sheila''s parents) at least once a week, going out for dinner or playing at their house.  The boys'' favorite place to go is Nana and Papa''s house where they can play in the park with Nana, help Papa in the garden, and stay up late watching the fire in the backyard on warm summer nights.  Baba and Gigi (Steve''s parents) come to visit every other week.  The boys love playing chess and other board games and watching movies with Baba and Gigi.  They think their grandparents are the best!</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 3293, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1370965409, 0),
(1378, '<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"><span style="font-size:medium;font-family:''times new roman'', times;">We have our own house in a beautiful suburban neighborhood.  Our street is off the main roads so traffic is very light.  Our backyard is spacious and has a fort and swing set that the kids love playing on.  There are 4 parks within a few blocks of us, and many more nearby that we enjoy visiting.  We also live within walking distance of the church we attend.  There is a large forest preserve less than a mile from our house filled with deer and other animals.  The kids love looking for wildlife and pointing it out when we are biking or driving through the forest.  </span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"> </p>\n<p style="margin-bottom:0in;"><span style="font-size:medium;font-family:''times new roman'', times;">We have a whole unoccupied bedroom waiting for the new baby.  Also, because we already have three children, our house is stocked with all the things your baby will need.  We have a crib, car seats, stroller, clothes, bottles, and toys.  Because Steve has a great job as an engineer, Sheila has never had to work outside the home.  Her full time job is caring for the children.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 3293, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1370965441, 0),
(1383, 'I live in a beautiful small town with excellent schools, a diverse population, and many family-oriented community activities, such as: weekly events at the local farmer''s market, outdoor children''s movies, a children''s museum, weekly family-friendly outdoor concerts, several major street festivals, holiday parades, and many sporting events and activities. A real estate site, www.homes.com, ranked this town #1 on its "Top 10 Cities to Raise a Family" listing.  Bloomberg''s Businessweek ranked it as the "Best Place in the U.S. to Raise Kids." Educational and economic information, crime rates, amenities, air quality, and diversity were factors considered in the nationwide ranking.\n\n \n\nMy home is a lovingly restored, 4-bedroom, 1888 farmhouse on a picturesque small horse farm, just three miles from the university campus.  I live here with my two fluffy cats, Squishy and CiCi, and my Bichon Frise, Buffy.  They are all very friendly and enjoy the company of children.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'My Home', 5836, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1370896901, 0),
(1381, '<p><span style="font-size:medium;font-family:''times new roman'', times;">Steve is one of the happiest people I know.  He is always smiling, always quick to laugh.  He loves having fun, watching anything that is funny and playing games.  He especially loves playing games with our kids.  Every night after dinner, Steve sits down with the boys.  They each get to pick out something they want to do with Dad, be it play a specific game, watch something on TV or have a tickle fight.  Steve is the best Dad I know, spending most of his free time playing with the kids.  Steve is also an extremely smart guy.  He has a large and in-depth knowledge on matters of science and technology and he loves to share this knowledge by teaching and helping others.  He also has a strong and deep love for God which he shares through his involvement at church, especially in the choir and on the parish council.  </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Stephan (by Sheila)', 3293, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1370965346, 0),
(1382, '<p><span style="font-size:medium;font-family:''times new roman'', times;">Sheila is one of the most compassionate people you could meet.  She is definitely on the shy side, but when she sees anyone suffering or in need, she cannot help but intervene and try to make things better.  This makes her a totally awesome Mom!  She is always thinking about others first, and that means that me and the kids are her top priority.  She loves being a stay-at-home mom because she gets to spend so much time with the kids, teaching them things and sharing her interests with them.  She especially enjoys sharing her love of reading and music with the kids.  We have a large collection of children''s books and movies that Sheila and the boys have fun experiencing.  Sheila''s compassionate nature has also led her to serve outside the home.  She is very active in our church, leading a children''s choir, as well as being on the parish council and involved in other ministries.</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Sheila (by Stephan)', 3293, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1370965320, 0),
