(1392, '       We both work full time, but our plan for childcare is to avoid daycare centers.  Eli plans to take a 3-month maternity leave and then hopes to return to work on a part-time basis.  We hope to offset our days off such that either of us is home with our child nearly every day of the week.  Eli’s boss is very supportive of our plans to adopt and will be flexible with her schedule.  For any days that we both may need to work, Conrad’s sister, Katrina, lives in town as a stay-at-home mom and has offered her assistance.  We spend a lot of time with Katrina and her family; it is a weekly tradition for us to gather together for brunch after Mass on Sunday mornings.  \n       We like to have a Bar-B-Q, or we''ll take a trip to the zoo, or go for a hike.  One day, we went hiking on a trail near Katrina’s home that leads to a small reservoir where our dogs are welcome to swim.  The only thing that Jackson enjoys more than chasing squirrels is swimming.  As you can see, our families have some good times together and we look forward to our children playing together and developing close friendships.\n       Occasionally, we have the opportunity to get out of town.  As a veterinarian, Eli sometimes is able to travel to continuing education conferences and we will take the opportunity to turn these trips into little vacations.  By far, our favorite place to go when we get out of town, is to take a long weekend and drive into the mountains where Eli’s family has an old cabin on some property along the Colorado River.  The cabin has been in Eli’s family for many years, her grandfather bought it when her mom was a young child and, as a result, she has many happy memories of going there when she was younger.  The mountain air is so fresh and clean and at night, the sky is so clear that you can see thousands more stars than you can see in town; it’s so relaxing and refreshing to spend the weekend away from the business of town.  We look forward to being able to take our kids there some day.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'A little more about us and the things we like to do...', 5853, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1371913889, 0),
(1396, 'Feel free to contact us through this site or our email at:\nbryananddebadopt@gmail.com\n\nFeel free to call us at : 1-888-369-6632', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact Us', 5879, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1372797969, 0),
(1397, 'We met about four years ago at a birthday party and have been happily married for the last two years and know we want to grow old together.  Our relationship is built on laughter, trust, communication, and the desire to raise a family.  Both of us are ready and eager to become parents! We would love to enrich and share our lives with a child.  We are firm believers in providing opportunities for our child to explore the world and develop any interests and talents they choose.  We feel so lucky to be surrounded by caring friends and family who are nothing short of amazing in their support of our decision to adopt.\n\n\nOur Path To Becoming Parents\nEven before we got married we discussed the desire to have children in our lives. Bryan was adopted himself and we always knew that we would look into bringing a child into our home that way as well.  The dream has always been the same, to share our lives with a baby, and help raise him/her in a loving home with two parents that will treasure every single minute with them!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'How We Met', 5879, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1372009729, 0),
(1394, 'Jackson, our 5-year-old lab-mix, loves to chase the squirrels that are constantly bickering at him from the tree-tops in the yard; we think that they chatter at him as a form of bragging, knowing that they are safe on their perch and it drives him crazy.  Jackson is really good with children, our little 3-year-old nephew can crawl all over him or take toys right out of his mouth, and he has never uttered a single complaint.  We adopted Jackson from a rescue 3 years ago and we picked him because of his happy, tolerant nature.\n\n       Orion is the older of the 2 cats, he is 12 years old and his favorite thing to do is to snuggle.  He will beg for Eli to curl up on the couch to read a book, just so that he can lie in her lap and purr.  As a result of his lackadaisical and somewhat timid nature, he is not a big fan of the rambunctious dog, nor of the younger cat, Briggs.  Briggs is 4 years old and he is constantly pouncing on Orion in hopes of getting him to play, but Orion is never interested.  Above everything else, Briggs loves to eat and his favorite treat is green beans.  Whenever we put a pot of green beans on the stove to boil, Briggs comes running and starts begging at us until they are done.  Eli has taught him to sit up like a dog before he gets his treat.  Neither of the cats have had very much exposure to children; they tend to get out of the way when our nieces and nephews are around the house.  We do not, however, have any fear of a child’s safety around our cats.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About our pets', 5853, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1371913670, 0),
