(1401, '<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">Growing up in Goodland, KS was a wonderful experience as a child. <span> </span>Goodland is a small town in western Kansas with a population of about four thousand people.<span>  </span><span> </span>I was the youngest child in my family, and I have an older sister and brother.<span>  </span>My father, Dale, worked as an appliance repair technician, and later he owned his own repair business.<span>  </span>My mother, Linda, worked several jobs as an administrative assistant for the schools, and later she became and still works as the Sherman County Clerk.<span>  </span>I have one sister, Shawna, who is six years older, and one brother, Jeremy, who is two years older.<span>  </span>As a child, living in a small town provided a safe environment to grow and learn.<span>  </span>I had great teachers who fostered my interests in science and math.<span>  </span>I have many friendships that started in grade school and continue to this day.<span>  </span>In high school I was active in many academic groups, and I also was a long distance runner in cross country and track.<span>  </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">My family, growing up, was loving, supportive, and had a strong sense of togetherness.<span>  </span>My dad exemplified what it means to work hard every day.<span>  </span>He instilled in us kids a strong work ethic and a commitment to family.<span>  </span>My mother instilled a great many qualities, one of these being to never give up and never stop trying.<span>  </span>She was always very supportive of my activities, whether it was academic, sports, or choir.<span>  </span>I also grew up close to both of my grandmothers, and enjoyed spending time with both of them.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">Our family is still very close, and even though we are spread out over Kansas and Colorado, and don’t get together as often as I would like, we have a great time when we do.<span>  </span>My family plans a vacation every year, and in the past few years we’ve been to Mexico, the Rockies, Branson, and several lakes in Kansas.<span>  </span>We always have a lot of laughs when we get together.<span>  </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">On my side of the family, my sister and her husband, Tony, have three wonderful girls, Mackenzie, Emily, and Addison. <span> </span>My brother and his wife, Katie, have two boys, Reid and Nate, and one girl, Bree.<span>  </span>They are all very sweet, caring, and fun kids.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">Michelle and I were introduced by a mutual friend in 2003, and we right away hit it off.<span>  </span>We shared common interests growing up, in music, and in humor. I found her to be very pretty with beautiful blue eyes and a great laugh. I was also drawn to her intelligence and her fun personality.<span>  </span>We continued to date several years before being engaged in September, 2005, and being married on April 29<sup>th</sup>, 2006. <span> </span>I value Michelle as a caregiver, and her unconditional love and support. <span> </span>She is thoughtful and considerate of others. It’s these qualities that will make her a great mother.<span>  </span>We share a love of camping, boating, and I’ve even gotten her to enjoy fishing, even when she has to bait her own hook!</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">Although we do not have children, we do love our dog as if she was one.<span>  </span>Our dog Mia has been a part of our family for almost 10 years, and she is a very kind and loveable golden retriever.<span>  </span>She loves more than anything to spend time outside with us, and can seemingly play fetch for hours.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">I would describe my personality as a reserved, rational, independent, and adventurous spirit.<span>  </span>I easily make friends and am very loyal, trusting, and generous to those close to me.<span>  </span>I am somewhat of an introvert, and enjoy time alone to think and make decisions.<span>  </span>I believe this helps me be a good listener and a patient teacher.<span>  </span>I have always had a drive to figure out how things work, and I enjoy working on projects that require logical analysis.<span>  </span>I believe people should be treated with fairness and equity.<span>  </span>I am an action oriented person. I like to be up doing things.<span>  </span>I also enjoy adventurous activities like boating and wakeboarding.<span>  </span>I like the opportunity to work in my garage, where I have developed a hobby of woodworking and carpentry.<span>  </span>Over the years, I have accumulated enough tools to complete a variety of different projects.<span>  </span>Overall, I am an optimistic, cheerful, trusting individual.<span>  </span>I believe that I possess good qualities to teach and instill strong values as a parent.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">Spiritually, I am of a Catholic Christian background.<span>  </span>However, I was taught to be accepting and sympathetic to those of other faiths and spiritual backgrounds.<span>  </span>My faith has given me a strong commitment to helping others, and treating others as I would like to be treated.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">Upon graduating pharmacy school in 2002, I have worked as a pharmacist in Manhattan, KS. <span> </span>I have worked as a hospital pharmacist the last 9 years.<span>  </span>I find my work very fulfilling.<span>  </span>Every day I make an impact by helping patients, nurses, and physicians.<span>  </span>In my job, I review medication orders from physicians, and ensure the safe and effective delivery of these medications to our patients.<span>  </span>I also answer drug related questions from patients and other health care professionals. The part of my job that I enjoy the most is programming our pharmacy system software to prevent drug related errors from reaching our patients.<span>  </span>Another satisfying aspect of my job is the camaraderie that exists in the pharmacy.<span>  </span>We are a tight knitted crew that work really well together, and also have fun outside of work.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">Infertility, unfortunately, has been a dark cloud over our marriage the last 5 years.<span>  </span>Our doctors have told us that we have what is called unexplained infertility, although there could be some issues with the quality of Michelle’s eggs.<span>  </span>Regardless, it has been a challenge, and a process of grieving the fact we cannot conceive our own child.<span>  </span>We still yearn to be parents, because we feel that there is lot of love for us to give a child, even if it is not our own biological child.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:.5in;">If we are blessed to become adoptive parents, I feel that I could provide a loving and safe environment for the child.<span>  </span>I will be a good listener, and be a patient father.<span>  </span>Michelle and I also have decided that in order for the child to grow up healthy, that we would maintain any level of openness necessary for that to happen.<span>  </span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal">Thanks for reading and God Bless!</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT WES', 5705, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1376447692, 0),
