(1406, 'Dear Birth Parent(s)\nWe are Whitney and Tyler and we are honored that you have considered us to be adoptive parents! After two years of the pain and heartbreak of infertility, we have turned to adoption, and this seems to be the path we should have take all along. Adoption has been and exciting and very positive situation for us so far. We hope to find a birthmom or family that we can remain close friends with over the years and watch their child grow together. \n\n We want you to know that we understand what a monumental decision it is that you are making. We promise to give your child the best life that we can. \nWe have a large family with lots of nieces, nephews and cousins to play with! We both have excellent jobs, Tyler being a distributing representative, and Whitney a first grade teacher. We are both college graduates, and Whitney is working on completing her master''s degree. We will be able to provide a good education, family vacations, and lots of love and laughter. We live in a cozy home with two dogs who are basically giant babies! We have two grandmas and one grandpa anxiously awaiting a little one to spoil. We are young and energetic, and we want to be the type of parents who are active and involved with our children. We want to spend evenings on our deck, chasing fireflies, riding bikes to the park and blowing bubbles. We enjoy the simple things! We are smart with our money and choose to save more than spend. We would rather live in a modest house and spend our money on outings and experiences with our family.  \n	We are both Christians and have been raised in Christian homes. We want our child to have a good moral compass and as sense of right and wrong. We don''t plan to force religion on any child, but we want to expose them to our faith and make sure they are familiar with the Bible so they may make informed decisions about their faith when the time comes. Being raised in the church helped us so much as far as being on the right path and making smart decisions, so we want this for our child as much as possible.\n	We hope this letter has given you a glimpse into our lives as potential parents. We hope that you feel a connection with us that gives you a sense of comfort to move forward with an adoption plan. We want you to know that we are open to contact should you so desire. We would be more than happy to visit, send pictures, letters or emails to keep you updated on this precious little one. We will always admire the brave decision you made and speak of you with the utmost respect to your baby. Adoption could only be described as the selfless act of love on a birthmother''s part. \n				\nThank you for considering us! God bless you in your journey!\n													Whitney and Tyler\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birth Parent Letter ', 5157, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1384658961, 0),
(1418, '<p><span style="font-size:small;">Hello!</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;">We are a couple with lots of love to give and we are looking forward to becoming parents! We have great respect for you as you consider an adoption plan for your child. We hope that what we share on this page and the <span style="text-decoration:underline;"><a title="A little bit about us..." href="http://www.parentfinder.com/PDFTemplates/user/5875_1165_2013-07-08.pdf" target="_blank">eBook</a></span> will give you confidence that if chosen, we would raise your child in a loving environment filled with opportunity.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;">We have been married since 2001 and are very much in love. Our home is in Florida, close to the beach. We enjoy an active lifestyle: golfing, tennis, scuba diving, and yoga.  We also like to spend time with family and friends, all of whom are very excited to welcome a little one with open arms.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;">Growing up we both had loving parents that taught us many of the important life lessons that we will share with a child: value of education, respecting differences, and the love of family. It is our desire to raise the child knowing that he or she has been adopted. Should you choose us, we’d like to get to know you so that we can share what we learn with the child growing up.</span> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;">Please contact <span style="text-decoration:underline;"><a title="The agency we are working with..." href="http://www.parentfinder.com/hausmannhickman" target="_blank">our agency</a></span> if you would like to know more about us. </span><span style="font-size:small;">Thank you for your thoughtful consideration!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:small;">Ron &amp; Andie</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our letter to you...', 5875, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1373926896, 0),
