(1428, '<p><strong>Cadence and Dallys: The Apples of Our Eyes</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span> </span>As the mother and father of Cadence and Dallys, we can only express how incredibly beautiful and wonderful they are to have in our lives. Our world revolves around them completely and we do everything we can as parents to ensure that they have the opportunities to learn and excel in all areas of life.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span> </span>Cadence Nevaeh Pearson was born on September 5th, 2005. She has beautiful long blonde ringlets and mesmerizing blue eyes. She has a very mellow temperament and loves to help daddy around the house with chores and fixing things. She is an incredible older sister to Dallys and is definitely a mother hen; caring for her sister and looking out for her as much as she can. She seems to be very understanding of the adoption process and looks forward with excitement to being a big sister to another little one.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span> </span>Dallys Shelby JayLee Pearson was born October 12th, 2009. She resembles her sister, but her hair is more loosely waved than curled. She is the baby of the family right now and can be a little high maintenance as a toddler, but is a very sweet, loving, and unique child. She is a little grease monkey and loves to help her daddy work on the Mustang. Although Dallys is too young to fully understand what the adoption process is, she has a very good understanding that soon there will be another baby in the house and looks forward to the day when she gets to be a big sister too.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Cady and Dallys', 5956, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1392248876, 0),
(1429, '<p>            Tylor and I met through a mutual friend in the fall of 2003. We remained acquaintances for about a year and started dating each other in November of 2004. Shortly thereafter, we learned we were pregnant with our first daughter. In March of 2005 Tylor asked me to marry him and I said YES! Ultimately we chose to wait to get married until we had known each other longer and knew each other a little better. We were adamant about not getting married simply because we were having a child together, but because we loved each other and wanted to be together. As we went through the pregnancy, Tylor was constantly by my side; attending every doctor’s visit and helping me in any way he could. He was truly amazing and incredibly supportive throughout my difficult pregnancy with our oldest daughter Cadence, whom we now lovingly call Cady. She was born on September 5<sup>th</sup>, 2005. We chose to be married on March 17th, 2007, St. Patrick''s Day, a humorous gesture relating to my Irish heritage. We decided on a small wedding with just close family and friends. We were wed on a gorgeous spring day in Sedgwick County Park and Cady was our flower girl.</p>\n<p>            Since, then, we have welcomed another beautiful daughter to our family. Dallys was born October 12<sup>th</sup>, 2009 following another very rough pregnancy which, unfortunately, has left me unable to have more children of our own. Our daughters bring tremendous joy and purpose to our lives. We always knew we wanted to have a family and being parents is the most rewarding and important job we’ll ever have. However, Tylor and I truly believe that our family is not yet complete. There isn''t a day that goes by in which we don''t thank God for the wonderful blessings he has given us in Cady and Dallys, but we do feel as though there is a piece of the puzzle missing. We feel that bringing a little boy into our home would complete our family and giving our daughters a baby brother would be a delight beyond words. Adoption has always been in our hearts even before our inability to conceive and we are truly are grateful to have this option. We pray only that we may be blessed with the opportunity of loving another child through it. Together, we share a very special history and our commitment to each other runs deep. We have learned that we can handle anything life throws at us as long as we keep a positive attitude and keep in mind that God is always on our side.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Lives Together ', 5956, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1392248709, 0),
(1504, 'Feel free to call or text us anytime at 917-720-CARE (2273), or email us at LovingCaringCouple@gmail.com. We''d love to hear from you!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact Us', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1392762621, 0),
(1505, '<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We are a warm, friendly and happily married young couple. We are fun-loving and playful and we love kids! We dream of building a beautiful family and providing a loving and nurturing environment to raise a child. We are excited to spend lots of quality time with a child, reading books, playing games or simply having fun!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">Tova is 27 years old and a child at heart. She is warm and bubbly, and is always happy and laughing. Tova loves history, and even works part-time in a museum. Tova is amazing with children - every child instantly adores her - and she will make an unbelievable mother. David is 29 years old and works as an actuary. David is a huge sports fan, loves to sing and has been playing golf since he was 10. David has a warm heart with lots of love to give to a child.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We promise to provide a safe and warm home to raise a child. We promise to provide a solid education and a financially secure environment. A child in our home will have every opportunity for a bright and beautiful future.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We are extremely close with our loving families who will make any child feel loved and accepted. Our community is very warm and friendly, filled with young families and lots of children. Near our home there are a number of great schools and playgrounds, and the sounds of playful children can always be heard nearby!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"> We want to thank you for considering us as adoptive parents. We have the utmost respect for your courageous choice to place your baby through adoption. </span><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">By taking the time to choose the right family for your child, you are showing a tremendous amount of selfless care and concern for your unborn baby.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We would love to speak with you, meet with you, or do whatever it takes to make you comfortable. Feel free to call or text us anytime at 917-720-CARE (2273), or email us at <span style="text-decoration:underline;"><a href="mailto:LovingCaringCouple@gmail.com">LovingCaringCouple@gmail.com</a></span><a href="mailto:LovingCaringCouple@gmail.com">.</a> We''d love to hear from you!</span></p>\n<p><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">With love and warmth!</span></p>\n<p><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">Tova &amp; David</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'To A Special Friend', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1407636897, 0),
(1430, '<p>Thank you for taking the time to get to know our family. Despite never being able to fully appreciate the pressure of this decision, we do have enormous respect for you taking it on. Both Lori and her brother were adopted at birth. Having witnessed and experienced the wonderful family they have, their upbringing and the opportunities in life they have been afforded, the very notion of adoption, although far from easy on any party, can be the greatest gift anyone could give. </p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Birthmother Letter', 5699, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1374804120, 0),
