(1452, 'We have a delightful, caring and intelligent adult daughter, Jussi, who has brought us great joy.  She is a 23 year old college student majoring in physical therapy and specializing in children''s therapy.  Jussi is a talented swimmer.  She coaches a team of 150 children between the ages of 4 and 18 and also works as a nanny for toddler twin boys while she is in college.  She loves children and started wishing for a baby brother or sister when she was very young.  She is still waiting for that dream to come true.  \n\nJussi had a wonderful childhood.  Summer days were spent riding bikes, jumping ropes and swimming in pools.  Fond winter memories are of sled riding, making snowmen and drinking hot chocolate on snowy days.  Jus was given the choice of pursuing any sport or activity that interested her.  When Jus was interested in softball, Christine pitched the ball endlessly in the backyard.  When it was lacrosse, two sticks were bought so we could throw the ball back and fourth.  Girl Scouts, swim team, saxophone lessons, dance classes and gymnastics were some of the choices that were pursued.   \n\nWe loved watching Jus learn how to crawl and speak her first word.  Time was dedicated to raising a strong, confident and healthy daughter.  We found the greatest joy in watching our daughter become an adult.  Jon came into parenting when Jussi was a teenager.  He took on the challenge with his whole heart and became a wonderful father.  The three of us are ready for a baby to join our happy lives.  Jussi will be the best big sister.  She has a ton of hugs to give.  She is filled with cuddles, love and talent to share with the baby brother or sister she has dreamed of for so many years.   \n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Daughter', 6012, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1382813462, 0),
