(1464, 'Our friends all share in our joy and excitement at becoming parents. All of them have young children, so playmates will never be in short supply!\n\n\n\n\nBoth sets of parents live close by as well. We see them often and enjoy the time we spend together. Family means everything to us! Our parents can''t wait to be grandparents.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Friends and Family', 4663, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1377747811, 0),
(1465, 'Dear Birthmother,\n\n\nIt must be an extremely emotional and trying time as you are making this decision and we would like to sincerely thank you for the selfless decision that you have made.  We are also extremely excited that you have chosen to take a little time to learn more about ourselves and we are looking forward to learning more about you, as well, if that is what you desire.  Please know that the love and care that we will give her is the same love and care as the decision that you have made.  We hope that this gives you comfort in knowing that you have made the right decision.  \n\n\n\nWe have always talked about adopting, and we are extremely enthusiastic in knowing that our dreams will be coming true.  We hope that you decide that we are the adoptive parents for your baby, and should you decide this, we will let her know how much she is and was loved.  We are humbled by your decision and words cannot express how much we admire you and how thankful we are for considering our family as the family for your child.  May the blessing of your decision be shown in the thankfulness that we have to you.\n\n\nOur names are Kim and Jim and we have been married for over 15 years. We have known each other since we were both 11 years old as we both grew up in neighboring towns in Central New York.  Our time together as children, leading up to our engagement was wonderful.  We were the best of friends and our families were close then.  We knew that we were meant to be together and our love and respect for each other grew each and every day.  In 1995, shortly after Jim entered the Navy, we got married.  We are not only husband and wife, we are best friends.  We have three boys; James (16), Tanner (12) and Bryce (9) and they are extremely excited about having a baby sister.  They will love her just as much as we will.\n\n\nWe raise our boys to believe in their religion, treat everybody with respect, to always do their best, and to work hard toward accomplishing their dreams.  They are wonderful boys that are so caring and always have smiles on their faces.  They are all doing well academically and are very athletic.  When asked to do something, like chores, they do so without hesitation.  We will raise our daughter the same way and give her the resources that she needs to accomplish all the dreams that she has, as well.\n\n\nJim attended Brockport College and Kim attended Herkimer County Community College.  Jim has been in the Navy for over 18 years and Kim is a stay at home mother.  Jim enjoys playing golf, is active in the boys’ schools and sports, and volunteering in the local community.  Kim also enjoys sports, where she was a bowler in college, is active in the boys’ schools and sports, and enjoys reading.  We both enjoy spending time with family and friends.  We love to spend quality time together as a family.  We enjoy things such as family movie nights, going camping, playing in the yard and park with the boys, and roasting marshmallows during a summer night. We also love to travel, whether it is to a museum, a sporting event, trips to see family, or to Disney World we enjoy that time together.  \n\n \nWhile Jim has been in the Navy, we have lived all over the East Coast, as well as London, England.  We have now settled into our “forever home,” as Jim will be retiring from the Navy in 2016.  Our home is a 5 bedroom, 3 baths; split foyer home in Maryland with one acre of land, spacious front and side yards and a large fenced in back yard.  It also has an in-ground pool.  Our neighborhood has a community park with sports fields and is three blocks away from a river with a dock.  The elementary, middle, and high schools are all within a three mile range.  We live in a wonderful, quite neighborhood where kids, of all ages, play together and all the neighbors treat each other like family.  We have two dogs; a chow named Valley and a Llapsa named Chloe.  We also have a cat named C.C.  All our pets are well mannered and absolutely love children.\n\n\nWe are both very close to our families.  Jim’s mother and husband live in Central New York, as does Kim’s mother and father, as well as her sisters – one which was adopted.  Jim’s father lives in North Carolina and his brother lives in Texas with his family.  We spend as much time as possible with both sides of our family, spending time together during the summer and holidays.  We have 10 nieces and nephews between our families, ranging from age 7 – 19 that, along with our families, are looking forward to and awaiting the arrival of a new baby girl into our lives.  \n\n\nEven before getting married, we discussed adopting, and continue to talk about it ever since.  When Kim was advised by her doctor not to have any more children biologically, we knew that was a sign from God that the time is now for our dream of adopting to come true.  We are most grateful that our blessings have been answered because of the loving and caring decision you have made.  Our thoughts and prayers are with you.\n\n\nKindly and Warmly,\n\nJim and Kim Legg\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'BIRTHMOTHER LETTER', 5833, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1377895267, 0),
