(1478, '<p style="text-align:left;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;">If we are chosen to be parents, we will provide a loving and caring environment where we will support, teach, guide, respect and be involved in their life, whether that be watching activities or hobbies or spending time during dinner or homework.  We will want them to know that we support them no matter what and that they have the ability to achieve anything they set their minds to.  We look forward to raising our children in a home which has love, respect and family unity. We want our children to have the same opportunities in life that our parents gave to us. We were taught to love, be respectful, were given guidance and motivation to do the right things in life. These traits are values that we want to pass onto our child.  </span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:left;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"> </span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:left;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"> </span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:left;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span>We promise to love, encourage, support and motivate your child to become whomever he or she would like to be, we want to provide a safe, loving and secure home.  Whether it is doing homework, enjoying dinner together every night or rooting him or her on in their chosen hobby, if we are chosen we will be there with lots of love and a lifetime of  support.  </span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:left;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span> </span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:left;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span> </span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="text-align:left;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''book antiqua'', palatino;font-size:small;"><span>We want them to know of the adoption from day one and know that your decision was one made of LOVE!!  </span></span>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      </span></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Parenting', 4942, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1381977093, 0),
(1479, 'We adopted our son Bodie who is now 2 years old.  We were able to attend every Doctors appointment and be in the delivery room when he was born.  He is such a fun loving little boy and we are extremly blessed to be his parents.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Bodie', 1628, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1400698207, 0),
(1481, 'Forest and I are pretty adventurous people.  We love to travel and hike.  We prefer to travel by car (ROAD TRIP!!). The thought of flying anywhere is quite boring to us because we can''t stop and see things along the way.  Your child will travel with us and experience a lot of fun outside!  \nForest and I attend a large christian non denominational church regularly.  Your child will attend church weekly with us and learn about the love of Jesus. \n We LOVE holidays!  One big thing missing from our house, is a child to enjoy the holidays with.  Kids make the holidays so much more fun! Your child will have no shortage of attention anytime, especially around the holidays as we are always with family during this time, having fun celebrating.\nEducation...this is very important to Forest and I.  We both have a 4 year degree and various certifications under our belts.  We firmly believe it has opened many doors for us career wise.  Your child will be educated from very early on.  I (Geniece) LOVE to read and your child will be read to from day one and exposed to other learning opportunities. Higher education will be made a priority for your child!\nMost important?  Your child will be LOVED!  We have a lot of love to share.  We aren''t rich and we don''t live in a mansion, but we have fun and love each other. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'What will life be like for your child...', 6368, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1388633303, 0),
