(1485, 'Although we are from the New York area we are willing to travel to many other states to adopt.  We are available for last minute placements, as well. We already have a crib, bassinet, car seat/baby carrier, clothing and many other baby items.  We are all set whether it''s a boy or girl. Please feel free to call our toll free number at 1-877-959-8265 or you can e-mail us at Wantingtoadoptababy@yahoo.com.   ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'WE ARE WILLING TO TRAVEL TO MANY OTHER STATES TO ADOPT AND ARE AVAILABLE FOR LAST MINUTE  PLACEMENTS', 5718, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1405620726, 0),
(1486, '"I can honestly say that my parents are the best I have ever met. Teaching respect, virtue, responsibility, and self-discipline from a young age, they prepare their children to be successful and productive adults. I am currently double-majoring in computer and software engineering at the University of Wisconsin and am academically far ahead of my peers. I do not say this to brag, however; I owe my success to my parents, who not only taught me all the values mentioned above and more, not only provided me a quality homeschool education, not only provided for all my needs and aid me in my studies however possible, but also have graciously allowed me to continue living at home while I make my way through school. The value of the stable home environment and the love that we have for each other here is simply beyond my ability to describe. Truly, our family has much to offer to a child, everything that ''money can''t buy''."     - Oldest son \n\n\n"I couldn’t have asked to grow up in a better home than this one. Whatever we do, we do it together. When we started our farm, we were realizing our dream to have a place where we could work together and look out for each other. Each one of us has something on the farm that we enjoy, such as chickens, cows, or sheep. We have opportunities to pursue our individual dreams, yet our main purpose here is to take care of one another. Our farm is the ideal place to learn, to develop character, and to grow physically, mentally, and spiritually. I believe that everything I enjoy in my life, including the hope I have for my future, I owe to the wonderful influence that my family has had on me."     - Second oldest son \n\n\n"I feel greatly blessed to have been raised in this family. We share a love that I believe is rare in other families. Everything we do is done together. Our work as well as fun is participated by everyone. My parents raise us in a unique way. Because of homeschooling, I have learned to challenge my mind, think clearly, and also teach my younger brothers and sisters. Living on a farm has taught me the value of hard work and to appreciate the organic foods we are able to enjoy. At the same time, Mom and Dad encourage me to pursue my interests in medicine and my desire to be a midwife. Still, one of my favorite things to be is a big sister. After all, my best friends are my parents and siblings."     - Oldest daughter ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Some Words from our Oldest', 6456, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1385527070, 0),
