 Everything we do is done together. Our work as well as fun is participated by everyone. My parents raise us in a unique way. Because of homeschooling, I have learned to challenge my mind, think clearly, and also teach my younger brothers and sisters. Living on a farm has taught me the value of hard work and to appreciate the organic foods we are able to enjoy. At the same time, Mom and Dad encourage me to pursue my interests in medicine and my desire to be a midwife. Still, one of my favorite things to be is a big sister. After all, my best friends are my parents and siblings."     - <i>Oldest daughter </i>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Some Words from our Oldest', 6456, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1385527592, 0),
(1488, 'Although we disagree on when our first date was, we agree that we started dating in 2005.  Derek proposed in June 2006, and we were married in December 2006, in Santa Fe, New Mexico (where we were living for one year for Derek''s job).  Our wedding was very small, but we had a fabulous time celebrating with our family and close friends.  Before the wedding, Holly made a wish that we would have a white wedding.  She got her wish, as Mother Nature delivered in the form of 36 inches of snow!\n\n\nWe moved back to Kansas City in 2007 and started working at law firms.  The next year we decided to start a family.  After several years of not being able to conceive, we transitioned to adoption.  In October 2011, we got a phone call from a social worker about a young couple that was expecting a baby in January 2012.  This couple had seen our profile and was considering us as potential adoptive parents.  We were extremely excited.  We met with the couple the next week and, a few days later, learned that they had selected us as adoptive parents.  The social worker called us on Holly''s birthday with the news.  Over the next few months, we spent time with the young couple and got to know them and their families.  Then, in January 2012, we all headed to the hospital and Kolbe Sage was born.  He was immediately loved by everyone present.  His adoption was finalized in March 2012.  And we continue to see his birthparents on a regular basis. We are hopeful that another couple will give us the opportunity to experience the same joy with the birth and adoption of a second child.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family Story...', 1531, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1385925230, 0),
(1489, 'We joyfully welcomed Kolbe Sage into our family in January 2012.  He has been a tremendous blessing, and we are grateful every day that his birthparents entrusted him to our care.  In honor of his birthparents, Kolbe is named after St. Maximillian Kolbe, a martyr for charity.  Since his birth, we have watched Kolbe grow from a tiny infant into an active, talkative, and imaginative little guy.\n\nIn the past two years, we have celebrated his birth with our family and friends.  We have taken him on two trips to Colorado, and to several baseball games (Royals, T-Bones, and even the All Star game).  We have helped him learn how to roll over, sit up, crawl, walk, and now run.  We have played with him, read him books, given him baths, taken him on walks, taught him how to eat solid foods, and introduced him to ice cream.  We have learned that he loves choo-choos, the movie Cars, airplanes, being outside, water, all kinds of animals, chocolate milk, and our boxer dog Gracie.  He is our joy, and we are so proud to call him our son.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Kolbe Sage...', 1531, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1385754752, 0),
(1490, 'We live in a suburb of Kansas City in a four-bedroom colonial house that was built in 1989.  Our home is on a corner lot in a quiet neighborhood with lots of young families with children.  We also have a large, fenced backyard that is perfect for children.  The elementary school is in our neighborhood and is the same elementary school that Holly attended.  We also live close to the city pool, a public library, a local museum, several parks, an extensive walking trail, and our parish church.\n\nOur home is close to Holly''s family.  Her parents live a few blocks away, as does Holly''s brother Josh and his family.  Her brother Noah and his boxer dog Paisley live a few blocks to the west.  And her sister Kim and her family live within ten minutes.  We also live close to Holly''s paternal grandmother.  Because we live so close, we get to see our family (and Kolbe gets to see his cousins) several times a month for dinner, trips for ice cream, or playdates.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 1531, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1385755154, 0);
