(1491, 'Kolbe has been a blessing.  And an unexpected benefit has been the relationship we have developed with his birthparents.  Both of Kolbe''s birthparents are involved in Kolbe''s life, and we hope he has a continuing relationship with them throughout his life.\n\n\nWe would love to have more children and develop a similar bond with a second child''s birthparents.  We look forward to watching another small person develop from an infant, into a child, and ultimately into a healthy, educated, and independent adult.\n\n\nIn addition, we are both extremely close to our siblings.  Our siblings played a key role in shaping our personalities.  For example, we both had to learn to share.  But we also both had the comfort of knowing that there was another kid who would always be on our side and watching out for us.  We know Kolbe will be a tremendous big brother, and we are eager for another child to complete our family.\n\n\nIf, after reading this profile, you think we might be a good family for you and your child, please contact us through Catholic Charities.  We are willing to answer any questions.  In addition, several family members and friends have participated in our adoption search by writing letters describing us.  We are happy to share these letters with you so that you can better understand us.  If you would prefer a closed adoption, we are also open to that arrangement as well.  Again, thank you for considering our family.  We are truly honored.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Why We Are Pursuing Adoption...', 1531, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1385925066, 0),
(1492, 'Andrew & Annie', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Pictures', 6447, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1388362753, 0),
(1493, 'http://wantingtoadoptababy.wix.com/adopt', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Please visit our website for our profile', 5718, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1388363667, 0),
(1494, 'You can call me Jay, all my friends do! I was raised Catholic. You''d might think that''d be traumatic for a young gay boy, but I had a clergy who spoke more of God''s love and forgiveness than of his wrath and vengeance. As a parent I will strive to be like these people who may not of approved of what I was telling them, but they did not condemn it either. Love should be unconditional.  \n\nFrom the moment I knew how to read, and for as long as I can remember, I was a fan of Superman. It was always cooler to like Batman or Spider-Man or the Wolverine, but Superman was my guy. He''s the one that stood for hope and caring. Superman saves people. More than anything else I believe this has had the greatest effect on my world view. It means that I believe that good people will always win out in the end! Even if it takes a very long time, and there is a struggle to get there!\n\nFew things that are worth having come easily or without sacrifice. For a long time I resisted the idea of adoption. I didn''t feel like there was enough acceptance in the world for two men to adopt a child. With the recent repeal of Don''t Ask Don''t Tell and of the  Defense of Marriage Act, as well as the several states that have legalized same-sex marriage, I was made hopeful.  It means that love and kindness trump hatred and brutality.\n\nNow I believe that in the very near future people will be wondering why gay marriage was ever controversial in the first place.\n\nLearn more about Chris and Jay at<a href="http://jayandchristopher.com"> jayandchristopher.com</a>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Jay', 6248, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1388457016, 0),
(1495, 'The plan is for Julie to stay at home and be a full-time mom. We think it''s really important for children to get a good foundation in the home. We''d both like to be very active in our children''s activities and we''d like for our children to be very involved in the church and community. We hope to help them discover their interests and talents and then give them plenty of opportunities and encouragement to pursue them. \nWe want our home to be a place where love is abundant, but discipline is important as well. We really think that the two go hand-in-hand. We really like the calm, but firm approach to discipline. We''ve seen it used so effectively in others'' parenting styles. \nWe both firmly believe in the value of education and want to provide every opportunity possible for our kids to pursue their goals. We both went to private, Christian schools for most of our schooling and would like our children to have the same experience. We''ve already started a college savings fund and will also likely use some military benefits to help fund their college education as well.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Parenting Style', 6496, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1389401117, 0),
(1496, 'We both grew up in Christian homes and accepted Christ into our lives at young ages. Our faith in God has brought us through many ups and downs in life, and to the place we are today, ready and hopeful to adopt. We plan on raising our children to know and love Jesus, to serve Him by serving others, and to realize that God has great and wonderful plans for their lives. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Faith ', 6496, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1389401183, 0),
