(1499, 'Steve is 39 and in the military where he trains people.  He is very active and loves to run, bike, hike, and camp.  If he isn‘t on the move he is probably reading; our whole family loves books.  He enjoys his work but his family is his top priority.  He plays lots of chase and hide and go seek with the children and makes up funny stories at bedtime every night.  He loves to make the children laugh.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'MEET STEVE', 6539, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1391575164, 0),
(1500, 'Tracy is 38 and loves being a homemaker.  She loves to teach the children, read, make quilts and little girl clothes, garden, make cupcakes, and talk with her friends.  She taught elementary school before she was a mommy but stopped to be home with the children.  She loves being able to help our children discover the amazing world God has made.  She also loves spending lots of time talking with each child and hearing what is on their mind.  She isn’t a storyteller like Steve but reads to each child every day and sings them each their special song at night.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'MEET TRACY', 6539, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1391575266, 0),
(1501, 'We met at a church event and were married the next year. We were Christians before we were married and our faith is important to us.  We both love the mountains and the beach.  We love to spend time together talking and being outside.  Our home is a little bit outside of town in a peaceful neighborhood.  We have a big backyard that backs the woods where we spend a lot of time.  Sometimes we see bunnies and deer.  Our extended families don’t live nearby but we keep in touch and visit.  Our parents and family all adore our children and are excited about us adopting again.  We have a lot of good friends through church and our children’s activities.\n\nOur home is a lively place where there is a lot of laughter.  We try to maintain a routine to help the children know what to expect each day.  We try to laugh together and make things as fun as they can be.   \n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'ABOUT US', 6539, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1394220907, 0),
(1527, '\nMolly.  Her name means "Wished for Child."  She was not only wished for, but prayed for by so many people.  Her adoption was one of the most emotional, amazing, wonderful, times in our lives. We still keep in contact with her very special first family and they delight in seeing Molly grow into a young lady.  Molly is truly our little ray of sunshine :)  Ever since she was born, Molly has captivated people with her big blue eyes and her dimpled smile.  She loves interacting with people and makes friends very easily.  Molly loves to be on-the-go and exploring on new adventures.  Molly really enjoys dancing and hip hop, and has also started basketball, soccer and cheerleading.  We cannot forget her love for the Disney princesses and anything that is pink.  Molly is in kindergarten and she loves the friends she''s made, the teachers and just the pure joy of learning.  She is a learner by nature and is very inquisitive and curious.   She has just started reading and is very proud of herself - as we are of her!  Molly is one of the most thoughtful and polite little girls and loves to help out around the house.  Molly also enjoys playing with her cousins and all of her friends from school and in our neighborhood.  Molly is so excited to become a big sister.  She cannot wait to help feed and change the baby and to teach them all of the things that she has already learned, because she is a "big girl."  She cannot wait to share all of her toys with the new baby and take the baby for walks outside.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Molly', 5159, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1394300623, 0),
(1502, 'A copy of our Adoption Book can be viewed at the following sit:\n\nhttps://dallasandderekwoody.shutterfly.com/28', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Adoption Book', 6542, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1391878495, 0),
(1503, '<p><span style="color:#339966;"><strong><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><span style="color:#ff00cc;">Please </span><span style="text-decoration:underline;"><strong><a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/PDFTemplates/user/6491_1264_2014-07-20.pdf">click here</a></strong></span> <span style="color:#ff00cc;">to download our PDF Adoption Profile book, or click on the "<em>Print Profile"</em> button at the top of the page.</span></span></strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">The PDF contains a lot more information about who we are, how much unconditional love we have to offer your child, and the wonderful family and community that we are a part of.</span></p>', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Profile Book (PDF)', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1408119650, 1),
(1593, '<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong>We are extremely close with our families. Literally!</strong> </span><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- Both our families live around 30 minutes from our home </span><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- Tova texts her brothers constantly, and they and speak almost every day! </span><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- David works at the same company as his brother </span><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- David’s sister sends her kids to the playgroup where Tova helps out in her free time </span><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- We each have 13 first cousins, and we stay in touch with all of them! </span><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We are constantly crossing paths and we see each other all the time! We make sure to set aside time for spending with family, and we have tons of large get-togethers to celebrate holidays, birthdays, graduations, or just about any excuse to see each other. </span><br /><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">Tova comes from a very musical family – her father and uncle play the violin, the piano, and can also sing. At some family gatherings, they play a duet for everyone to enjoy. David''s family is very sports oriented - growing up, David remembers playing baseball, basketball, football and going golfing with his father and brother. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1405364758, 0),
(1506, '<p><strong><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">Please call or text us: <span style="color:#0000ff;">917-720-CARE (2273)</span>,</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">Or email us: <span style="text-decoration:underline;"><a href="LovingCaringCouple@gmail.com">LovingCaringCouple@gmail.com</a></span>.</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We''d love to hear from you! </span></strong></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact Us', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1405363471, 0),
(1507, '<ul><li><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We promise to provide a safe and warm home to raise a child. </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We promise to provide a solid and well-rounded education along with a financially secure environment. </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We promise that the child will know that you love him or her very much and that you want the best possible future for him or her. </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We would love to share pictures and letters with you. </span></li>\n<li><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">A child in our home will have every opportunity for a bright and beautiful future. </span></li>\n</ul>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Adoption Pledge', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1405369981, 0),
(1508, '<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/lovingcaringcouple/Our_Backyard.JPG" alt="Our Backyard" width="164" height="219" />Our home is always open to friends and family. We love having our friends and their children as guests in our home, and they''re always commenting that our home is warm, welcoming, and homey. Behind our home is a large shared yard with plenty of room for kids to run around and have fun.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br />We are part of a warm, youthful and very friendly community, filled with young families with lots of little children. There are four playgrounds near our home, and the laughter of playful children can always be heard nearby. Near our home there are a number of great schools and we plan to emphasize having a good education. <br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Home', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1405364178, 0),
(1509, '<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><img style="float:right;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/lovingcaringcouple/Wrigley_Field_5.JPG" alt="Us" width="219" height="146" /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We are a warm, friendly and happily married young couple. We are fun-loving and playful, and we love to joke around, especially with each other. We are extremely open and trusting with each other, and we are each others best friend!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We dream of building a beautiful family and providing a safe, stable and nurturing environment to raise a child. We are excited to spend lots of quality time with a child, reading books, playing games or simply having fun! </span></p>\n<p><br /><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><strong>Our Favorite Things To Do:</strong> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- Relaxing in parks or botanical gardens </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- Hiking </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- Touring historic sites </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">- Spending time with children. Our friends'' children adore us! </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><br /></span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1405364341, 0),
(1592, 'We are extremely close with our families. Literally! \n\n- Both our families live around 30 minutes from our home \n- Tova texts her brothers constantly, and they and speak almost every day! \n- David works at the same company as his brother \n- David’s sister sends her kids to the playgroup where Tova helps out in her free time \n- We each have 13 first cousins, and we stay in touch with all of them! \n\nWe are constantly crossing paths and we see each other all the time! We make sure to set aside time for spending with family, and we have tons of large get-togethers to celebrate holidays, birthdays, graduations, or just about any excuse to see each other. \n\nTova comes from a very musical family – her father and uncle play the violin, the piano, and can also sing. At some family gatherings, they play a duet for everyone to enjoy. David''s family is very sports oriented - growing up, David remembers playing baseball, basketball, football and going golfing with his father and brother. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Family', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1405364330, 0),
(1510, '<object width="500" height="300"><param name="movie" value="http://v.veopod.com/vp1.swf?config=http://v.veopod.com/style%3Fv%3Dplaylist-24107"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://v.veopod.com/vp1.swf?config=http://v.veopod.com/style%3Fv%3Dplaylist-24107" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="500" height="300"></embed></object>\n<BR>\nThis playlist is a collection of songs that spans our journey from marriage, infertility struggles and acceptance, deciding to adopt, and looking forward to loving fully our new child along with the birth family.\n<BR><BR><B>\n"Make You Feel My Love"</B> - This song will forever represent the love between me and Wesley and has been featured in many key moments of our life. While dating, Wes often played this song for me (the Garth Brooks version as he is a big Garth fan!) and the sung this song to me as part of his proposal. It was an easy selection to pick this as our first dance at our Wedding.\n<BR><BR><B>\n"I''ll Follow You"</B> - Once we were settled as a couple, we tried to have our own child, but were soon confronted with infertility issues. I found out that I was allergic to Progesterone, a hormone needed to support a baby while developing in the womb. Although this diagnosis was difficult for me to learn of, Wes was by my side the entire time, guiding me through the deep and keeping me close to him.\n<BR><BR><B>\n"Counting Stars"</B> - As a couple we explored ways to conceive a child biologically and quickly found we would be putting my life and the child''s at risk. Surrogacy was an expensive option and we were uncomfortable with some of the ethical choices that might come with treatments.\n<BR><BR><B>\n"Let Her Go"</B> - This song touches my heart. It''s my melody of letting go of my biological child. Sometimes we don''t know how much we love, want, or will miss something until it was taken away from us. Especially when its gone suddenly, without warning, and we have no control over it.\n<BR><BR><B>\n"Compass"</B> - After exploring our biological options to have a child, my husband and I became excited about the idea of adopting. The more we listened to our hearts we knew it was the path we were suppose to take.\n<BR><BR><B>\n"Love Alone is Worth the Fight"</B> - As we have worked through our infertility and the application for adoption, we know its all worth it, because one day we will be able to share our love with you, the birth parents, and an extraordinary child.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Gwen&#039;s Adoption Playlist', 6570, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1394320355, 0),
