(1529, '<b>Phone:</b> 1-877-275-7532 (toll-free)<br/>\n<b>Email:</b> julie.ernest.adopt@gmail.com<br />\n<b>Blog:</b> <a href="http://www.parentfinder.com/blogs/posts/jmorahan">Our Blog</a><br/>\n\n<br/>\n\n<b>Our Agency:</b> Lutheran Family Services<br />\n<b>Phone:</b> 303-217-5850 (Emily Frank)', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact Us', 6566, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1397744968, 0),
(1530, '<p><span style="font-size: small;">Although we haven’t met, we have a tremendous amount of love and respect for you and the difficult decision you have to make about your child’s future. We can''t imagine everything you are going through, but we did see firsthand how difficult this decision was for our daughter’s birth mom to make when we went through the journey with her (and we still stay in touch to this day!). We praise God for all parents who chose life and pray that He will give you comfort and support no matter what you decide.</span></p>\n\n<br />\n\n\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Thank YOU for taking the time to learn about us and consider us to be your child''s forever family. We want you to know that if you choose us to be your child''s parents, we will love him or her unconditionally with all of our hearts. Though we are far from perfect, we will strive to be the best parents we can be, providing your child with a loving, stable home and plenty of educational opportunities. If you are interested in staying in contact (pictures, letters, email, or even regular visits!) after the adoption is completed, we are more than happy to do so.\n</span></p>\n\n<br />\n\n<p><span style="font-size: small;">Please feel free to contact us by phone or email if you are interested in getting to know us better to see if we might be the right match for you. We promise not to pressure you and to make sure that we can meet the needs of both you and your child.</span></p>\n\n<br />\nWarm regards,\n\n<br/>\n\n<p style="font-family:''Brush Script MT'', cursive;font-size:24px">Julie, Ernest, & Hayley</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Welcome', 6566, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1395377725, 0),
(1534, 'Hi! I want to share with you two types of info: characteristics of myself and a biography of me. Sound exciting enough yet?? Let’s get started!!\n<BR><BR><BR>\n<p style="font-weight:bold;">\nGwen’s Characteristics</p>\n<BR>\nSharing some of my strongest character traits is important to me, because I figure a child in my home will certainly be exposed to these things! So this section is dedicated to my morals, interest, and values - in no particular order.\n<BR><BR>\nI LOVE animals! We have a dog, Pete (Corgi mix), and he is about to get a little sister (Blue Heeler). We would have more pets, but Wes keeps me in check. I think growing up on a farm sparked my love and compassion for animals from a young age. My family taught me to respect and care for all living creatures and I hold this value close to my heart for all creatures big and small.  \n<BR><BR>\nEmpathy for others is important. This helps to build a kind and caring world. If we can place ourselves in others’ shoes , I believe it’s the first step to caring for others. All of these things are important characteristics I hope to instill in a child: care for others, compassion, and empathy. Somehow my mother, with the help of my extended family, raised me with a strong value for these things. I pray I can pass these onto a child as well.\n<BR><BR>\nLiving an active life within the Church has built my spirituality and given me peace. We will as families (both immediate and extended)  enjoy spiritual activities together. My faith has given me strength, peace, and hope in the most difficult times in my life.\n<BR><BR>\nFootball!! I am a HUGE football fan. The best time of the year is NFL season and I go a little nuts following the New England Patriots. We recently had a new Professional Indoor Football team move to Dodge City, so now I also have the Law to root for too!\n<BR><BR>\nI strongly value education. I want to teach strong critical thinking skills to our little one so they can think for themselves and form their own educated opinions. Since I went to school for science, I imagine I will pass some of that on to a little one, but I think I will incorporate general  learning activities into daily living.\n<BR><BR><BR><p style="font-weight:bold;">\nGwen’s Biography</p>\n<BR>\nI was raised on a farm by an extremely loving, unbelievably hardworking, single mother. I have one older brother who I look up to a love very much. He gives me great advice, is full of wisdom, and one of the hardest working people I know. I grew up in northeast Kansas outside of a very small town (think less than 400 people). I went to school for biological psychology and spent two years in graduate school studying neuroscience.\n<BR><BR>\nI met my husband, Wes, while in college. Two years after meeting, we married in my hometown (with a blue bouquet!) and started our happy ever after. We moved to the east coast so I could attend graduate school in Bethesda, Maryland. After two years we moved to Key West, Florida were Wes began his career within the National Weather Service. We both missed the Kansas life and our families, so we were thrilled when he was offered a position in Dodge City. We moved here in 2011 and have been happy in our home ever since.\n<BR><BR>\nI have a close extended family. We will usually get together for holidays and anniversaries and I always look forward to my grandmas cooking! As I mentioned in the beginning, my immediate family includes my mom and brother. My parents separated and then divorced with I was in junior high. It was odd for me to marry Wes, because I couldn’t imagine forever. But I have been shocked at how much our love has grown for each other every year. Now I can’t imagine anything except forever.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Gwen', 6570, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1395445700, 0),
(1531, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/2037-ShanAndMitch/2037-ShanAndMitch.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Shannon and Mitch''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 2037, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1394475978, 1),
