(1547, 'Kim is eager to be a Mama and Chris is looking forward to being a Daddy. We have been planning for a little one to come into our lives for the past seven years.  We long for the day when we can teach a son or daughter about history, nature, technology, reading, music, and how to ride a bicycle.  Chris is eagerly awaiting the days when he can play with cars and trains, Legos, Battleship and other games.  Kim looks forward to curling up on the couch with a cozy blanket on a rainy or snowy day and reading about myths, dragons, dinosaurs and animals.  \n\nChris anticipates teaching a little one about his favorite subjects in school - math and science.  He looks forward to making pizza with our little one, or baking cookies together.  Kim is awaiting the day when she can teach this little one about American history through the American Girl stories.  There will be teddy bear picnics, tea parties fit for a princess, and dress up days with high heels and tiaras.  We plan to have a study/playroom for this little one.  There will be a desk, computer, and various reference books to assist with study needs.  This room will also serve as a place to keep toys and play with them.\n\nWhile we are unable to have a biological child, we will bond with this little one from the first days.  We will immerse him or her in music, language, and reading.   Mozart’s music and other classical music is soothing and enriching for babies.  We will play classical music and move his/her hands to the music.  When it is naptime, we will play soothing music to encourage a peaceful nap.  As a Librarian, Kim loves reading with children.  We will read children’s books all the time to build this little one’s imagination.  We will talk continuously with him/her to encourage speaking.  \n\nKim grew up in a home with her parents and extended family including her grandmother, aunt, and cousin, Adrienne.  It was a wonderful way to grow up, being surrounded by love and guidance from different family members.  Kim and Chris live in a two family home with Kim’s Mom.  This little one will grow up in a home with an extra role model to love, support, and guide him/her through life.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Kimberly and Christopher as New Parents', 6655, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1398010632, 0),
(1548, 'Chris and Kim have very different families.  Chris has a very small family consisting of his parents, brother Tim, uncle/aunt/cousin in Connecticut, and an uncle and aunt in California.  He also has a step grandmother in New Jersey and they recently celebrated her 100th birthday.  Kim has a large family consisting of her Mom (sadly her Dad passed away five years ago), brother and his fiancée, and numerous aunts, uncles, and cousins.\n\nHolidays are shared between our families.  Kim and Chris host Mother’s Day and Father’s Day to spend those holidays with both families.  On Mother’s Day, Kim prepares a special dinner and even tries to bake.  The dinner is always fabulous.  The dessert?  Not so much.  Kim loves the spring and brings the season into the celebration.  The table is set with floral table linens and dinnerware, and a spring menu is served.  When we have a little one to share in the celebration, the grandmothers will receive a special gift from him/her.  On Father’s Day, Chris, his Dad, and his brother Tim barbecue a typical hamburgers and hot dogs meal with all of the fixings – ketchup, mustard, relish, onions, beans, and chili.  They enjoy the bonding and time together.\n\nOn St. Patrick’s Day, Kim’s Mom makes the traditional Irish dinner of corned beef and cabbage, and we watch the parade.  Christmas Eve is at Chris’ parents’ home and Christmas Day is at Kim’s Mom’s home.  Kim’s brother David and his fiancée Erin drive down from the Albany area late on Christmas Eve and arrive around 2:30 am on Christmas morning.  They bring their two 75 pound dogs and awaken the entire house when they come charging in.  Kim’s favorite thing to do on New Year’s Day is to watch the Rose Parade.  She looks forward to enjoying the Rose Parade with a little one to marvel at the beautiful floats made solely from plant materials.\n\nThe family events of 2013 were the Christening of Kim’s cousin Lisa and Ed’s baby, Abby, (their fourth child and first daughter) and the Communion of Kim’s cousin Nick and Susan’s daughter, Kaylee.  At Abby’s Christening, there were approximately 25 children under the age of 6.  The children all sat at one table and had placed their orders in advance.  The waiter asked, “Who ordered chicken nuggets?  Who ordered spaghetti and meatballs?”  Each child raised his or her hand for each item.  The highlight was getting to hold Abby for a few minutes.  While Kim held her, she was looking all around and smiling. \n\nAt Kaylee’s Communion, there were about 20 children ranging in age from 6 months to 9 years old.  The children danced and played games with the DJ’s guidance.  Kaylee was the clear winner at hula hooping.  She could even hula-hoop while drinking her soda!  It was beyond entertaining to watch the children and we look forward to the day when our little one will be able to dance and hula-hoop with us.\n\nIn 2014, the family event of the year will be the Christening for our little one.  We can see it all now.  The Pastor will baptize the baby, and introduce him/her to the congregation.  A celebration at our home will follow the service.  The grandparents, siblings, aunts, uncles, cousins, and friends will all be invited.  There will be about 15 children under the age of 10 to join in the festivities.  We will have finger foods (like chicken nuggets and hot dogs) and mac and cheese for the children.  We will supply many toys (such as Lego Duplo blocks, dolls, stuffed animals, cars, and trains, as well as outdoor toys like tee ball and Frisbees) to enjoy a fun day with the children.\n\nWe look forward to planning birthday parties for our little one.  We would like to have a princess theme, or a tea party, or dinosaurs, or Disney, or Candy Land.  There will be a kids’ party and a family party.  Weddings are a much-anticipated event in Kim’s family.  Her brother and his fiancée will be getting married in October 2015 and the family is already making their own plans for the big event.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Celebrations and Holidays with Our Families', 6655, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1398010854, 0),
(1549, 'We would be delighted if you would contact Kim at 1-877-439-4277.  Kim and Chris look forward to getting to know you better.  If you have any questions about us or the legal process, please feel free to contact our attorney, Suzanne Nichols at \n1-800-255-1415.  \n\nThank you again for considering us as adoptive parents to your baby.  \n\nLove, Kim and Chris\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Contact Us', 6655, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1398011451, 0),
