(1559, '<div style="float:left;">\n<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;">We  would like to thank you for reviewing and reading our profile. We are  grateful that you are taking the time to get to know us a little through our page. We know you have a big decision to make in choosing  adoptive parents and we have already started praying for you and your  family. We would love the opportunity to parent a son and provide a safe, loving environment for him to grow up in. We will be supportive parents that nurtures and grows his interest and strengths and as well will parent with patience and love.</span> <span style="font-size:small;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;">Adoption  was a calling placed on our hearts even in the early years of our  relationship as James was adopted when he was 3 months old. We will be  able to offer a unique experience to a child growing up in our home with  James being adopted himself. We are very excited to become first time  parents and start our adoption journey! </span><span style="font-size:small;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;"> </span></p>\n<br /><p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;color:#00bfff;background-color:#ffffff;"><br /></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><br /><br /><br /></p>\n</div>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'To Someone Special:', 6409, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1401991362, 0),
(1560, 'Ellie is a beautiful, stubborn, and intelligent three year old girl.  She loves pink, sparkles, princesses, dirt, Johnny Cash, animals and steak.  She is kind and tender hearted and can easily get her feelings hurt.  She will push any limits and boundaries you set and then climb up into your lap for a "mooch" (smooch) and a hug.  She loves to be outside and ride her scooter.  She loves to sing and dance.  Never did we think we would spend our Saturday nights playing ring around the rosy and singing every song from Frozen.  She loves to make up silly songs and dances and we constantly hear "Watch me do this!" or "Let me do that!".  One of her favorite things is to crack eggs.  She is quite good at it, especially for a three year old!  She is quite a traveler.  At last count she had nine states and Canada!  She likes to fly on airplanes and is a real trooper on long car rides.  She can unlock an iPhone or iPad quicker than anyone.  All she wants to do is scroll through your photos and videos and see if you have any good games she can play.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Ellie', 6578, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1400766608, 0),
(1561, 'Toby is our one year old Golden Retriever.  He is about 90 pounds and is all puppy!  He is the son of our first Golden, Zeke, who we suddenly lost to cancer before Toby was born.  Toby and Ellie are more like siblings.  They fight and he seems to know how to push her buttons but at the same time, he will play fetch as long as you are willing to play and she loves that he will bring the ball right back to her.  ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Toby', 6578, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1400688990, 0),
(1562, '<p><span style="background-color:#ffffff;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:medium;">We met in church when I was 13 and James was 15. We started a relationship 2 years later and have been together ever since. Growing up together from a young age gave us time to nurture a close friendship which only grew as we got older. When we decided to marry in March of 2004 we could honestly say we were marrying our best friend, and after 15 years there is no one else in the world we would rather be with than each other</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'How we met', 6409, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1400723568, 0),
(1564, '<p><span style="color:#800000;font-size:large;">Please view our profile on Fire Fox and not Internet Explorer it appears Internet explorer is having an issue displaying our full profile. I have sent a helpdesk message about this to parent finder. Thank you</span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'View our profile on Fire Fox ', 6409, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1401044620, 0),
(1565, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/6702-grohfamily/6702-grohfamily.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Amanda and Ed''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 6702, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1401211102, 1),
(1566, '<p><span style="font-size:small;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;"> </span><strong><span style="font-size:small;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;">Parenting Goals and Dreams:</span></strong></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">*James:  As we are looking to be matched with a son I am going to continue to  live my life to be a good example to him and help guide him to be a  loving husband, provider, a man of his word, loyal to friends and  family, treat others with respect, work hard, and most of all to love  God.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color:#000000;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">*Angela:  I have always known I wanted to be a mother and will care for him with  lots of love and thankfulness that I have been given such a precious  gift. </span><span style="color:#000000;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We will be supportive parents that nurtures and grows his interest and strengths and as well will parent with patience and love.</span> You will forever have a special place in my heart for the blessing  you will be giving us of parenthood and a son. </span></p>\n<p><strong><span style="color:#000000;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">Adoption Openness:</span></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span style="color:#000000;font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;"> </span></strong><span style="font-family:''comic sans ms'', sans-serif;font-size:small;">We would love to maintain contact with you even after the adoption has been finalized if this is your wishes as well.  We want you to be comfortable in the choices you are making and we are open to providing you with written letters, sending pictures, and/or having an account online to provide you updates. We want to maintain a level of contact that you are comfortable with so we can support you in this adoption journey.  If there is another way you would like to stay in contact we are open to hearing your thoughts and ideas. We as well can accommodate a closed adoption if this is <span style="text-decoration:underline;">your </span>desire to maintain<span style="text-decoration:underline;"> your</span> privacy. </span></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Parenting Dreams and Adoption Openness  ', 6409, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1402023877, 0),
(1568, 'Melissa works for an international conservation organization that helps farmers and foresters who live in tropical countries take good care of their land and make enough money to support their families. She has always been passionate about animals, nature, and going on adventures, which led her to this career. Her job is family-friendly with great benefits. She''s fluent in Spanish and travels to Latin America every year. Co-workers bring their families on trips, and we can''t wait to bring a child with us! Melissa works entirely from home, and has a very flexible work schedule.\n\n\nJason owns two successful restaurants; his partners are a married couple with two children. They are respected places with wonderful staff who are like family. It''s a lot of work, but a lot of fun! Jason has managers and only works 2-3 nights per week, and is home during the day.\n\n\nMelissa had a very traditional childhood - a successful father, stay-at-home mom, and her parents are still happily married. Jason''s childhood was more interesting - at times his family was poor, his parents divorced, they moved a lot, and he became a teenage father. Despite these challenges, he is a successful and happy husband, businessman and father. We have a mix of very valuable life experiences that gives us a deep understanding and compassion for people''s unique experiences, which we believe will help us be great parents with a strong, happy family of our own.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'What Makes Us Unique', 4702, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1402608838, 0),
(1569, 'Becoming parents will be the most meaningful and important part of our lives. We spend a lot of time with our family, which is very important to us and we can''t wait to have a child of our own! We love to play games, read books, snuggle, and be silly with our nieces, nephews, and our friend''s kids.\n\nJason has a 21-year-old son, and watching him grow up and become a smart, funny, responsible person has been the most amazing and rewarding experience. Showing something new to a child and watching the wonder and excitement come over their faces is just incredible. We will have so much fun taking a child to the zoo, museums, and parks and will encourage him or her to learn to do things like swimming, art, music, sports, dance lessons - whatever they show interest in!\n\nWe love to travel all over the world and are really looking forward to bringing a little one along on our adventures. We''ll teach the child to speak Spanish as their second language, so they can get the most out of the time we''ll spend with our family in Ecuador. Building a strong moral foundation and understanding the importance of being a good person and helping others is also something we strongly believe in and will instill in a child.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'What It Means to Be Parents', 4702, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1402610389, 0),
(1570, 'For more information, please contact our agency. Adoptions Together has much more to share with prospective birth parents about our family. Thank you.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'MORE INFORMATION', 6748, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1402629109, 0),
(1571, 'I (Melissa) have always had a heart for adoption. I remember being 6 or 7 and wanting my parents to adopt - knowing that adoption was something God had in store for me. As a teenager, God continued to fuel my passion for the adoption process and during high school I spent much of my time doing fundraisers for adoption agencies while dreaming of the day that I would get to walk out my own adoption journey.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When Andrew and I first started talking about marriage, the topic of adoption was discussed time and time again. I can’t explain how joyful I was to hear him say that he would love to adopt a baby one day and that he, too, felt like that was something that God had in store for us. We both see adoption as a beautiful picture of the Gospel and are honored to get to help paint that picture.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In 2013, Andrew and I were told that it was highly unlikely that we would ever have biological children. We took this news as God’s clear voice telling us that He wanted us to begin our adoption journey now. The timeline wasn’t what we expected, but we are overjoyed that He has chosen to bless us in this way.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We are excited about sharing pictures, and letters with you, if you were to decide that we are the right couple for your baby, and are praying daily for the the child that will join our family. We know we aren’t perfect, but can promise you that we will do our best to raise all the children we are blessed with in a home full of love, laughter, and God’s Word.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Why Adoption', 6696, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403023150, 0),
(1572, 'Andrew and Melissa were both homeschooled and met in a debate competition in high school &ndash; from two different states but both with a love of speech/debate competition and working for excellence. Although Melissa won that debate round, Andrew says he won because he met the love of his life.&nbsp; Since our families lived in different states, they made lots and lots of road trips to see each other and got to know each other and each other&rsquo;s families very well. A few years later, Andrew took Melissa out to his college town, they talked about their future together and in front of a big, beautiful, outdoor Christmas tree, Andrew got down on one knee and asked her to marry him. She couldn&rsquo;t have said yes fast enough!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Their wedding was an incredible experience! The first nine months of married life involved Andrew finishing college and then Melissa and Andrew making their first big move. Andrew got a great job but we were all aware that this first move would be temporary. Their next move a year later brought them to where they are now, almost right between both sets of in-laws! Andrew got a great promotion and we all knew this move would be a little bit more permanent. This was the year they bought their first house and began this wonderful journey into adoption!</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Story, as told by our Moms', 6696, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403023201, 0),
(1573, '<p>~ College Degree in Marketing</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Oldest of four kids</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Occupation: Purchasing Manager</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Has also been: An ordained minister, Radio DJ, and coach</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Some of my favorite things: My beautiful wife, sports and&nbsp; coaching, teaching the Bible, music&nbsp; (all kinds), coffee, fitness, being outside</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ On my Bucket List: Become a dad, hike Mt. Everest, become a published author, join the Disney Vacation Club</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Andrew at a Glance', 6696, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403031761, 0),
(1574, '<p>~ College Degree in Communications</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Oldest of seven kids</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Occupation: Office Administrator</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Has also been: A speaker and Childcare Director</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Some of my favorite things: Football, ice cream, reading, Disney World, playing games, music, helping&nbsp; people, playing with kids, and Andrew, of course!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>~ Dreams: Be a stay-at-home mom and write a book</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Melissa at a Glance', 6696, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403031770, 0),
(1575, 'We were married on a beautiful August day and it could not have been more perfect! Our wedding party was made up completely of family, with the exception of Andrew&rsquo;s best friend. Both of our fathers performed the ceremony and we had a beautiful worship service to celebrate our marriage commitment. Surrounded by family and friends we entered joyfully into a promise that will last forever.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>We are so grateful that both of our parents have strong marriages and have taught us about the importance of work in a marriage. We vowed that day to be together until death do us part, and this is not a vow that we take lightly. Our marriage is something that we work on daily and has priority in both of our lives. We want the children in our home to grow up knowing what to look for in a spouse, knowing that marriage is a wonderful blessing, and looking forward to the day that they can make that same commitment to the love of their life.</p>\n<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="http://www.parentfinder.com/media/users/AndrewandMelissa/wedding9.jpg"width="289" height="186" /></p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Wedding and Marriage', 6696, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403031210, 0),
(1577, 'Jennifer loves camping, traveling, cooking, playing the piano, scrapbooking, reading, walking the dogs, and spending time with family.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Hobbies of Jennifer', 6762, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403368634, 0),
(1576, 'Isaac loves to play his instruments (trombone, baritone and saxophone), read, work on his computer, and work on his car.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Hobbies of Isaac', 6762, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403368517, 0),
(1578, 'Mark loves camping, traveling, hunting, motorcycles, model trains. cooking, reading, and spending time with his family.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Hobbies of Mark', 6762, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403368688, 0),
(1579, 'We have two boys from Mark''s first marriage, Isaac and Adam.  We love them so much, but we feel someone is yet missing from our family -- a baby God has chosen to be part of us.  We tried to get pregnant unsuccessfully and after much prayer and discernment, we feel God leading us to adoption.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Why We Want to Adopt', 6762, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403369007, 0),
(1580, 'Adam loves to play sports (baseball, basketball, and football), go camping, go boating, play video games, and model trains.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Hobbies of Adam', 6762, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1403369097, 0),
(1581, 'Text us at 424-248-5991', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'To chat with us...', 6651, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1407334036, 0),
(1582, 'We reside in a very small rural community, which offers many family activities and opportunities for families to be outside! \n\nFull police, fire, and medical services are available, as well as, restaurants and shopping centers close by. \n\nThere are many parks and a library offering an abundance of resources for children. Our home is also within a mile from the bike trail, the lake where we enjoy taking our boat out, and many trails that we can ride our quads and dirt bikes. Our community is very family-oriented and friendly. \n\nWe reside in a ranch style home just outside of town on a two acre lot. Our home is four bedrooms, two bathrooms, with a two care attached garage. The main level of our home contains the kitchen, dining room, and living room in an open floor plan, the guest bedroom, office, and a full bathroom. The kitchen/dining room opens onto our covered porch to our large fenced in backyard. The second story is where our Master Bedroom/bathroom and the fourth bedroom that is fully set up as a nursery. We also have a full basement that is partially finished. \n\nThe best part about where we live is the people that surround us. Both sides of our family live within a 15 mile radius or closer, with Sheena''s sister and cousin living right around the corner!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Home and Community', 6663, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1405040266, 0),
(1583, 'We lead an active lifestyle. When we are not working, we love spending time with each other and our families. We enjoy attending Church, family dinners on Sunday, sporting events, motocross races, and being outdoors together. \n\nWe are very active in our god children/nieces and nephews lives. We love spending time with Averil and Zack- Chuck''s sisters children, Amelia (Millie) and Griffin- Sheena''s cousins and our best friends Ali and Scott''s children, and Chuck''s cousins Emily and Reggie''s child Bentley. From playing outside to sleepovers or blanket forts to cartoons, every moment that we spend with our favorite little one''s are times that we cherish and love! We cannot wait to give them a little cousin to play with!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Family Lifestyle', 6663, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1405040038, 0),
(1584, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/6787-JennyandJohn/6787-JennyandJohn.html target= _blank>here</a> to view Jennifer  and John ''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 6787, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1404923986, 1),
(1585, 'We love traveling. Because most of John''s family is in Germany, we visit there every summer. You can see a real castle from his mom''s house, so it''s just like being in a fairytale! His aunt lives in Spain, and it''s really fun to visit her at her house right by the beach! \n\nWe''re both music lovers. We enjoy going to concerts-- Bach, Bon Jovi, Beyonce--it''s all good! John loves playing guitar, and we both like singing with friends and family or in choirs. If our child wants to play an instrument, we''ll definitely encourage that!\n\nWe''re also animal lovers! We love playing with our sweet, gentle cat, Seena (her name means "swan," and she''s got all-white fur to match). We also enjoy going to the zoo. John likes visiting the alpacas and Jenny always says hi to the polar bears. We hope our child will discover her or his own furry friend there, too.\n\nBeing outdoors is a big part of our lives. Jenny especially loves hiking, biking, and learning about flowers and plants. John enjoys swimming and soccer. We look forward to lots of time at the playground, healthy exercise and nature discovery with our son or daughter.\n\nWe''re both frequently to be found reading a good book, magazine, or blog. Jenny likes mysteries, African American and international fiction, and history-themed readings. John likes politics, history, and current events. In addition to reading on our own, we sometimes also chose a book to read aloud in chapter by chapter to each other. We like children''s literature, and have a huge trove of kid''s books that Jenny''s mom has saved for us. We can''t wait to practice reading with our child!\n\nWe don''t watch a lot of TV, but when we do, it''s usually something silly like "The Office (we can quote whole scenes from almost any episode), "Parks and Recreation," or "Saturday Night Live." We''ve also gotten hooked on "House of Cards" and "Downton Abbey." And as historians, we always enjoy a good documentary!\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Our Interests &amp; What We Do for Fun', 6787, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1404941718, 0),
(1586, 'When it comes to being an adoptive family, have great role models all around us. Two of our friends are adopted themselves and have ongoing positive contact with their birth families. Other friends adopted two daughters from China, and another couple brought their daughter home from Russia. Jenny’s relatives adopted daughters from Colombia and other family members adopted a biracial daughter through the U.S. foster care system. We can’t wait to join the ranks of these proud adoptive parents! We also think that getting to know other adopted kids in our family and circle of friends will help our child understand that being adopted is okay, that she or he belongs, and that it''s love that makes a person part of a family.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Adoption Stories in Our Family &amp; Among Our Friends', 6787, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1404934240, 0),
(1587, 'Because we are blessed with friends and family members from many different racial and ethnic backgrounds and from all over the world, raising our child to be globally aware and to value his or her own heritage is important. We hope that that being around people from many nations and cultures, and who belong to a variety of racial and ethnic groups will help our child--whatever race or ethnicity she or he belongs to--to develop a healthy and proud sense of identity. We believe this will be especially important if our child''s racial or ethnic background differs from our own. In addition to Germany (where John is from), our friends and family include people from England, China, Denmark, India, Italy, South Africa, South Korea, Spain, and Turkey. Our friends and family members also include biological and adopted children who are African American and multiracial, as well as children who were adopted from other nations. We also both teach about race and ethnicity in the United States. Jenny''s academic research as a historian is on African American families in the 1800s and early 1900s, and on multiracial African American-Native American families. John teaches about racial discrimination and civil rights movements in the twentieth-century U.S. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Diversity &amp; International Connections Among Our Family &amp; Friends', 6787, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1404927445, 0),
(1588, 'We met ten years ago in graduate school as part of a group of friends who enjoy cooking, bowling, playing Trivial Pursuit, making music, going to concerts, and even acting out Saturday Night Live sketches together. Because we were close friends first, it’s hard to know exactly when we fell in love. But the rest is easy: We got engaged on Halloween, told our parents at Thanksgiving, and planned our wedding over Christmas. Our love of family and tradition shaped our wedding. John’s godfather performed the ceremony at John’s family church in Germany, and each of our brothers sang for us. We made our vows surrounded by loved ones from around the world.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'How We Met &amp; Married', 6787, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1406342419, 0),
(1589, 'We both come from large extended families, so our child will grow up surrounded by adoring relatives! All of our relatives are absolutely thrilled about our plans to adopt and will welcome our child into the family unconditionally. We can''t introduce everyone here as fully as we would like, but here are a few quick snapshots of just a few of those who will love and nurture our child:\n\nJohn''s mom/Hopeful Future Grandma: retired elementary school teacher who looks forward to playing games, baking gingerbread, and telling German fairy tales to her grandchild\n\nJenny''s Mom/Hopeful Future Grandma: retired English-as-a-second-language teacher, volunteer GED teacher, and rescue-animal caretaker who needs a grandchild to help her decorate cookies and take care of the animals \n\nJenny''s Dad/Hopeful Future Grandpa: retired college professor, community college teacher, and choir singer who plans crazy scavenger hunts for the kids in our family and can''t wait to build lego castles with his grandchild while listening to music \n\nJenny''s brother and his wife: both music teachers who write and perform in musicals for kids, and who are expecting twin daughters soon\n\nJohn''s brother: is a guitar teacher who sings in a rock band and plays soccer in his spare time\n\nJenny''s numerous aunts, uncles, cousins, and other relatives are mostly teachers, and others have worked or volunteered as nurses, librarians, and with churches and religious organizations\n\nJohn''s numerous aunts, uncles, cousins, and other relatives live in Germany and Spain. They love soccer, Harry Potter, and going to the beach.\n\n\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Grandparents, Siblings, Cousins, Aunts &amp; Uncles', 6787, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1404934081, 0),
(1590, 'We are both college professors, so you can guess that we value education highly. Indeed, nurturing our child’s educational growth and curiosity is our priority. We live in an excellent school district. Most of our relatives are teachers, so our child will be surrounded by people who can help him or her learn! Our child can attend the college we teach at for free, but we are also saving money so our child can attend any college regardless of cost. We will do everything we can to help our child achieve his or her dreams, whatever they are!', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'Education', 6787, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1404941301, 0),
(1591, 'Here’s what we wish for to complete our loving family: \n\nOur child wakes from a nap in our colorfully painted house with a big yard and lovely flowers. He or she fell asleep listening to dad play guitar, but is now ready to play with mom’s huge stuffed animal collection, cuddle with our cat, and read from our many kid’s books. We walk with the stroller, pointing to animals and flowers we see on the way to the playground. We are glad our flexible schedule and financial stability allow us to care for our child ourselves without day care! A few years later, dad walks our child to school. They talk about the school play and review for a test. We helped with home-work last night, as always. We are so proud that our child is doing well in school and has made new friends at rehearsal. They come to an end-of-school picnic with grandma, grandpa, Jenny’s brother and his wife, and their twin daughters. Jenny’s dad leads the kids in one of his crazy scavenger hunts. Jenny’s mom decorates cookies with us. For summer vacation, we fly to see John’s family in Germany. He was born there but now lives permanently in the U.S. His mom taught elementary school and loves teaching her grandchild. We can see a real castle (now a theater) from her house; we’ll see “Hansel & Gretel” there. Soon, we’ll visit John’s nephew, who loves soccer and Harry Potter, and his aunt, who lives at the beach in Spain! We take pleasure in helping our child to learn about and be proud of his or her own racial or ethnic heritage, and we are excited that she/he can travel with us to learn about many different cultures.\n', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'A Perfect Day in Our Family', 6787, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1404934492, 0),
