(1597, '(From the words of Brent) Smart, caring and loving. A compassionate nurse, dedicated to the best possible patient care. Awesome mom. Good sense of humor. A loving and nurturing attitude toward children. Wonderful wife. Loves the outdoor. ', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Ashley', 6775, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1405808984, 0),
(1598, 'Please click <a href=http://www.parentfinder.com/profileflipbook/6491-lovingcaringcouple/6491-lovingcaringcouple.html target= _blank>here</a> to view David and Tova''s profile flip book', '1', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'E-book Profile', 6491, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1405889664, 1),
(1599, 'We first met in a college speech class; Kevin won Ashley over with his fun, clever speech about "How to Have the Best Halloween Ever".  We were both finance majors, so we had a few more classes together throughout college.  After college we started dating, fell in love, got engaged and were married at a small country church with our closest friends and family.\n\n\nWe love to be outside.  Colorado is our favorite vacation spot because it offers so many things we love such as hiking, mountain biking, fishing and whitewater rafting.  The last few years we have enjoyed training together and competing in local triathlons.  We''re excited to share our love for the outdoors with children.\n\n\nWe also love to travel.  We''ve been to New Zealand, London, Rome, Paris and Mexico.  Some of our favorite spots in the United States are New Orleans, Nashville and Colorado.  Seeing the world and meeting new people has been a lot of fun.  We look forward to traveling with our children.  \n\n\nWe don''t have any children, but we have a dog Turbo and a cat Gizmo.  Turbo loves to swim and play fetch.  Gizmo loved to nap and pester Turbo.', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 6818, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'html', 1406690833, 0),
(1600, '<p>We first met in a college speech class; Kevin won Ashley over with his fun, clever speech about "How to Have the Best Halloween Ever".  We were both finance majors, so we had a few more classes together throughout college.  After college we started dating, fell in love, got engaged and were married at a small country church with our closest friends and family.</p>\n<p><br />We love to be outside.  Colorado is our favorite vacation spot because it offers so many things we love such as hiking, mountain biking, fishing and whitewater rafting.  The last few years we have enjoyed training together and competing in local triathlons.  We''re excited to share our love for the outdoors with children.</p>\n<p><br />We also love to travel.  We''ve been to New Zealand, London, Rome, Paris and Mexico.  Some of our favorite spots in the United States are New Orleans, Nashville and Colorado.  Seeing the world and meeting new people has been a lot of fun.  We look forward to traveling with our children.  <br /><br /></p>\n<p>We don''t have any children, but we have a dog Turbo and a cat Gizmo.  Turbo loves to swim and play fetch.  Gizmo loves to nap and pester Turbo.</p>', '0', '1', '0', '0', '0', '0', 'About Us', 6818, 3, 'non,memb', 1, 0, 'text', 1406771897, 0);
